    '{"id":"01K9CKVKQT5CBS3X6ME7YKBXZW","title":"MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Strategy and Guest Management**\n\nThe team is expanding the podcast guest roster and refining episode planning to align with strategic content gaps and audience needs.\n\n- **Julia Wetta is joining the team starting next week**, replacing Tracy who left Noetic, enhancing capacity for podcast production and outreach (09:04)  \n    - Julia’s addition aims to accelerate episode development and help meet upcoming production goals.  \n    - Nancy emphasized the importance of coordinating scheduling with guests like Sam, who has upcoming PTO, to ensure timely recordings.  \n    - Rachel and Nancy plan to focus on episodes around AI integration and training, which are currently underrepresented topics.  \n    - December is targeted for recording internal episodes, leveraging quieter client periods to deepen internal content.  \n\n- **Key recent guest commitments include a verbal yes from Kristen O’Boyle, CMO of CVS Health, with a TBD recording date** (32:56)  \n    - Other confirmed recordings include Patrick rescheduled for November 18 and Kate completed recently.  \n    - This guest lineup supports building thought leadership across major industry players, enhancing Noetic’s market credibility.  \n    - Coordinating episode topics to fill gaps such as “people problems” and training will strengthen the podcast’s relevance.  \n\n- The team is considering **personalized guide materials to accompany podcast invitations**, improving engagement and encouraging deeper connections with guests (11:18)  \n    - Rachel suggested adding a custom page signed by the podcast team to make outreach less generic and more inviting.  \n    - Nancy highlighted the need to optimize this communication as a door opener, especially for guests unfamiliar with Noetic.  \n    - Colin proposed testing short introductions at the front and more detailed info at the back of guides to balance depth and readability.  \n    - This approach aims to increase guest responsiveness and potential follow-up conversations, boosting business development opportunities.  \n\n## **Lead Management and Qualification via Pipedrive**\n\nThe team is refining lead scoring and qualification workflows in Pipedrive to improve sales follow-up efficiency and data accuracy.\n\n- **LinkedIn lead gen forms are being integrated into Pipedrive with updated scoring thresholds to filter out unqualified leads** (20:46)  \n    - Nancy raised concerns about spam and low-quality leads, emphasizing the need for a points-based system to prioritize serious prospects.  \n    - Colin explained the recent connection between LinkedIn forms and Pipedrive was to provide faster visibility but lacked scoring for form submissions initially.  \n    - The team agreed to update the scoring model to incorporate LinkedIn lead gen form fills and send the revised system for Nancy’s approval.  \n    - This update will reduce administrative overhead and improve targeting by ensuring only leads meeting defined engagement levels enter the pipeline.  \n\n- **Ongoing lead data cleanup includes removing former employees like Tracy from invite lists and verifying anomalies for contacts like Dan Baum and Jacinta Dariotis** (08:55)  \n    - Nancy and Colin are collaborating to confirm lead authenticity, especially when LinkedIn profiles are missing or leads appear inactive.  \n    - The team is focused on maintaining a clean and actionable leads database to maximize sales productivity and maintain trust in the system.  \n    - Timely filtering and accurate notes on lead activity (downloads, podcast engagement) will help personalize outreach and avoid redundancy.  \n\n- The team is **rotating advertising budget toward first-year CMOs based on enrichment data showing potential for higher engagement** (18:11)  \n    - Colin identified over **2,000 first-year CMOs** enriched through Clay, aiming for an **80%+ LinkedIn match rate** to target ads effectively.  \n    - Nancy noted previous CMO Playbook ads underperformed, likely due to timing, indicating the need for more volume and better targeting.  \n    - The budget shift aims to increase qualified lead flow by focusing on recently promoted decision-makers who are more likely to seek new strategies.  \n    - This refined targeting supports higher ROI on marketing spend by engaging prospects with urgent and relevant needs.  \n\n## **Content Strategy and SEO Optimization**\n\nThe team is evolving its content approach to balance thought leadership with SEO-driven tactics to increase site traffic and user engagement.\n\n- **Current blog content focuses primarily on thought leadership but will include SEO elements to boost visibility and attract more visitors** (40:11)  \n    - Colin proposed sprinkling SEO keywords naturally into thought leadership posts to maintain quality while improving search rankings.  \n    - He offered to recommend keywords and starter copy for the insights page to increase traction, which currently lags behind the homepage and Playbooks pages.  \n    - Rachel and Nancy agreed to test this blended approach to ensure content remains valuable and discoverable.  \n    - This change is expected to drive more organic traffic, particularly to underutilized sections like insights, enhancing lead generation potential.  \n\n- **Website analytics show a dip in total visitors but an increase in engagement, with users spending nearly five minutes on site and viewing over two pages** (39:41)  \n    - Despite fewer visits week-over-week, user engagement metrics exceed industry averages by about **15%**, indicating high content relevance.  \n    - This suggests that while volume fluctuates, the audience that visits is more invested, a promising sign for deeper funnel activities.  \n    - The team plans to build on this engagement by adding targeted content and SEO improvements to attract more qualified visitors.  \n\n## **AI Program Development and Marketing Integration**\n\nNoetic is preparing a new AI-focused program to help marketers integrate AI into their workflows, positioning itself as an innovator in the space.\n\n- **An AI program aimed at helping marketers infuse AI into processes is being developed, with marketing to start before full build-out** (41:58)  \n    - Nancy plans to present this initiative at the upcoming off-site, framing it as a solution to a widespread but underserved problem.  \n    - Colin recommended launching a podcast episode on AI pain points and strategic approaches, even before the product is live, to build awareness and thought leadership.  \n    - Supporting content like blogs and LinkedIn posts will deepen the narrative, creating a holistic marketing push around Noetic’s AI philosophy.  \n    - This phased approach aims to generate interest and early leads, enabling funding or client buy-in to accelerate product development.  \n\n- **Content format will balance direct, to-the-point AI discussions with conversational training-focused episodes to appeal to different audience segments** (50:08)  \n    - Nancy plans to prepare foundational content (\"ball of clay\") for Colin’s team to shape into guides and episodes.  \n    - The training episode is expected to be more discussion-based, exploring skills marketers need amidst fast-changing landscapes.  \n    - The AI episode will focus on outlining the problem and Noetic’s approach without relying on case studies not yet available.  \n    - This diversity in format intends to engage broader audiences while building credibility in emerging marketing challenges.  \n\n## **Business Development and Client Engagement Updates**\n\nThe team is actively pursuing new enterprise clients and nurturing existing relationships to expand Noetic’s market footprint.\n\n- **Positive progress with enterprise prospects includes booked meetings with Waymo and outreach efforts to Marriott, despite some access challenges** (34:42)  \n    - Nancy mailed books to Marriott leadership and is pursuing LinkedIn direct messages after email bounces limited direct contact.  \n    - Waymo meetings are booked with Linda Chen and her supervisor, expected to occur within the next two weeks, signaling strong pipeline momentum.  \n    - Linda indicated Waymo’s aggressive expansion into **30 markets from 3**, implying a large potential contract with significant budget capacity.  \n    - This opportunity represents a fast-moving client that could substantially increase Noetic’s revenue and market presence if onboarded successfully.  \n\n- **Nancy is increasing strategic outreach to existing clients for introductions, securing five CMO leads via Marissa Jarrett, CEO of 7-Eleven** (15:40)  \n    - Leveraging existing relationships is positioned as a scalable way to expand guest and lead pools efficiently.  \n    - The team is actively interviewing for a Business Development Director to address current capacity constraints, highlighting growth ambitions.  \n    - This approach aims to systematically improve pipeline quality and volume by tapping trusted networks rather than cold outreach alone.  \n\n- **Internal episode planning and asset management improvements are underway to streamline content access and enhance team efficiency** (27:57)  \n    - Rachel requested editing access to main drive folders to better organize episode assets by guest name and improve navigation speed.  \n    - The team is cleaning up episode lists to remove non-existent recordings and planning to add internal episode recordings during December’s quieter period.  \n    - These changes reduce friction in content production workflows, enabling faster turnaround and higher-quality publishing.  \n    - Improved asset management supports scalability as the podcast and content programs expand.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast","Lead Scoring","Business Development","LinkedIn Ads","AI Program","Training"],"overview":"- **Podcast Strategy Expansion:** Julia joins to enhance podcast production; focus on AI content and internal episodes in December.  \n- **Guest Commitments:** Secured Kristen O’Boyle (CMO, CVS Health) and others to bolster thought leadership and relevance in episodes.  \n- **Lead Management Update:** Integrating LinkedIn leads into Pipedrive, revamping scoring to ensure quality prospects enter the sales pipeline.  \n- **Content Strategy Shift:** Blog content will blend thought leadership with SEO, targeting improved visibility and traffic to underutilized sections.  \n- **AI Program Development:** New AI-focused initiative to be marketed before launch; includes podcasts and content to build early interest.  \n- **Business Development Progress:** Engaging Waymo and Marriott; focusing on existing client relationships for new introductions and lead generation.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nRemove Tracy from meeting invites and add Julia Wetta as new team member (00:08)\nUpdate Pipedrive lead scoring to include LinkedIn lead gen forms and adjust filters to exclude non-qualifying leads (00:26)\nRotate more budget to first-year CMO-focused LinkedIn infographic ads and reduce less performing Playbook campaign budget (00:19)\nGrant Rachel Curtis editing access to the main podcast shared drive for better organization and renaming by guest name (00:28)\nVerify and finalize podcast asset delivery especially for Christine Calvin episode and continue managing recording scheduling (00:51)\nSend over updated quick card quotes aligning with promotional materials for Noetic (00:51)\nAdd Julia to meeting invitations replacing Tracy (00:51)\n\n**Nancy**\nProvide Colin with content input and framework for upcoming AI program and training podcast episodes (00:41)\nContinue business development outreach efforts, especially with Marriott and Waymo contacts, and inform on progress (00:34)\nMonitor and manage Pipedrive lead quality and qualification closely, ensuring filtering is effective and provide feedback on adjustments (00:26)\nCoordinate internally on planning for December internal podcast episodes focused on people-related topics and training (00:29)\n\n**Rachel Curtis**\nCoordinate with Sam for podcast guest scheduling and possible internal episode inclusion (00:29)\nReview and discuss enhanced podcast guest guides and pre-episode personal outreach for better engagement (00:10)\nFollow up internally on upcoming podcast asset status and preparations (00:51)\n"},"duration":52.540000915527344,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"id":2,"name":"nancieruder"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"nancieruder"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sa.","index":0,"end_time":230.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello, everybody.","index":1,"end_time":269.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.42,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":270.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":3,"end_time":272.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":271.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How''s it going for you guys?","index":4,"end_time":274.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s going.","index":5,"end_time":276.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feel like it should be Thanksgiving already.","index":6,"end_time":278.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Literally.","index":7,"end_time":279.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.22,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Just letting you know, I have to drop like at 3 the latest because we have to go to our on site.","index":8,"end_time":284.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.94,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So that is, I have a hard stop as well.","index":9,"end_time":287.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":284.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Although I know we sent over the agenda.","index":10,"end_time":289.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":288.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t even know.","index":11,"end_time":290.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":289.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, obviously if conversation takes us that far.","index":12,"end_time":293.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":291.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I don''t know if we''ll need the full hour.","index":13,"end_time":294.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":293.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, great.","index":14,"end_time":296.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I mean, I love spending time with you guys.","index":15,"end_time":297.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.03,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I just need to get out of here.","index":16,"end_time":299.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.63,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I totally get it.","index":17,"end_time":300.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":299.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like my part of my week.","index":18,"end_time":303.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I love your.","index":19,"end_time":304.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":303.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where are you guys doing it?","index":20,"end_time":305.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":304.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In Virginia, but it''s like an hour from me, so I just need a little time to get there.","index":21,"end_time":315.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think most people are already there, but they said that you don''t have to be there till five, so I will be there closer to five.","index":22,"end_time":322.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.55,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":23,"end_time":323.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There you go.","index":24,"end_time":324.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":323.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just how it is, you know?","index":25,"end_time":327.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":328.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":327.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s exciting stuff, though.","index":27,"end_time":329.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":328.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":28,"end_time":330.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.03,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because we.","index":29,"end_time":330.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I haven''t even met like half the team in person.","index":30,"end_time":333.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.75,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, really?","index":31,"end_time":334.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":333.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m really excited, but nervous is, you know, I have to make all these first impressions.","index":32,"end_time":340.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"There you go.","index":33,"end_time":341.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":34,"end_time":342.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.85,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m sure it''ll be great, Nancy.","index":35,"end_time":346.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":347.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":347.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re great experiences.","index":38,"end_time":348.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":347.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People don''t realize also how like, mentally taxing it can be.","index":39,"end_time":351.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":349.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, for sure.","index":40,"end_time":354.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.29,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I mean, we''re staying there overnight.","index":41,"end_time":356.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":354.97,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":357.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":43,"end_time":358.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.09,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then I come back and I have a dinner tomorrow, so I just have to change quick and head over, so it''ll be busy.","index":44,"end_time":365.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.37,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m sure you can manage, Rachel.","index":45,"end_time":369.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure you''ll crush it.","index":46,"end_time":371.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":47,"end_time":372.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.94,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That''s very kind.","index":48,"end_time":373.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I should see if Nancy.","index":49,"end_time":375.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.78,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Give me one second to see if she texted me and said.","index":50,"end_time":377.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.02,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"She said.","index":51,"end_time":377.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t see anything.","index":52,"end_time":392.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":391.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She should be here.","index":53,"end_time":394.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.79,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Give her another minute.","index":54,"end_time":397.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I do know.","index":55,"end_time":398.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Sam''s been on her invites.","index":56,"end_time":401.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":399.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And she never joins and she always, like, responds declined.","index":57,"end_time":403.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or maybe should I leave her on or.","index":58,"end_time":405.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":403.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can leave her on.","index":59,"end_time":407.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s good to have Sam on there because since we''re just a small company, like, she''ll step in when help''s needed.","index":60,"end_time":414.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.11,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But that''s a good question.","index":61,"end_time":415.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.47,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So sometimes you''ll see her, sometimes you won''t.","index":62,"end_time":417.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.47,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":63,"end_time":419.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just wanted to confirm.","index":64,"end_time":420.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I didn''t want to put a spot on her calendar.","index":65,"end_time":422.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":420.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And she''s like, every week.","index":66,"end_time":423.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got to get rid of this thing.","index":67,"end_time":424.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, don''t worry.","index":68,"end_time":426.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.2,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":69,"end_time":426.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then is Tracy still with the.","index":70,"end_time":431.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Team.","index":71,"end_time":432,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":431.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That I am not sure of.","index":72,"end_time":435.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right, I will leave it at that.","index":73,"end_time":437.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would be a Nancy question.","index":74,"end_time":439.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.48,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, there''s Nancy.","index":75,"end_time":443.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I would ask her.","index":76,"end_time":444.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.2,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":77,"end_time":445.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, you guys.","index":78,"end_time":448.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Hi, Nancy.","index":79,"end_time":449.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will turn my camera on in just a second.","index":80,"end_time":452.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I have been back to back and I just am eating really quick.","index":81,"end_time":456.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m with you, Nancy.","index":82,"end_time":458.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":457.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I. I''ve not had more than a five minute break since 9am yeah.","index":83,"end_time":463.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":458.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh my gosh.","index":84,"end_time":464.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You got to eat something.","index":85,"end_time":465.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.68,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I have oyster crackers with me just in case.","index":86,"end_time":469.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":466.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not really nutritious there, Colin.","index":87,"end_time":472.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s not.","index":88,"end_time":473.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":472.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But luckily my, my daughter''s like crawling around like the speed of lightning.","index":89,"end_time":478.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":475.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m getting my exercise.","index":90,"end_time":479.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":478.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Aw.","index":91,"end_time":480.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, she''s got a weird crawl but she''s moving.","index":92,"end_time":483.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":481.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":93,"end_time":484.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s, it''s goofy.","index":94,"end_time":485.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Love it.","index":95,"end_time":487.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.17,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We just talked about we''re going to start taking her to Frederick.","index":96,"end_time":490.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":487.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Offers free gymnastics for 6 to 12 month olds.","index":97,"end_time":493.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, wow, that''s cool.","index":98,"end_time":495.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.45,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Gymnastics at that age, it''s like rolling around.","index":99,"end_time":500.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":497.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":100,"end_time":501.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":501.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a lot more space to roll around and not bump your head than I have in my house.","index":101,"end_time":505.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":501.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, exactly right.","index":102,"end_time":507.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":505.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This enables them to like get their wiggles out and nap a little bit more deeply.","index":103,"end_time":513.289,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":508.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":104,"end_time":513.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":105,"end_time":514.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Very valuable.","index":106,"end_time":516.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Um, Nancy, right before you joined and if it''s none of my business, none.","index":107,"end_time":520.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":516.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of my business, that is totally fine.","index":108,"end_time":521.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just asking because I got like a decline notification from Sam and I get that every week.","index":109,"end_time":526.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":521.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I was asking Rachel if I should just leave her on or move.","index":110,"end_time":529.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":526.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And she said it, leave her on.","index":111,"end_time":530.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":529.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I was just asking about Tracy because I haven''t seen her in a little bit.","index":112,"end_time":533.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":530.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if she should be.","index":113,"end_time":533.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":533.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the invites or.","index":114,"end_time":534.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":533.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tracy has left Noetic so you can.","index":115,"end_time":539.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":535.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Take her off the invites.","index":116,"end_time":541.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, understood.","index":117,"end_time":541.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll update that.","index":118,"end_time":543.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":119,"end_time":545.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":544.709,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In more exciting news, happy news, Julia, who is new to Noetic, is going to join this team and I think.","index":120,"end_time":557.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You''Ll meet her probably starting next week.","index":121,"end_time":560.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":557.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we would love you to add her.","index":122,"end_time":562.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":560.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She is juliawetta consultants.","index":123,"end_time":566.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":563.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You can put the chat as well.","index":124,"end_time":569,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"She''s great.","index":125,"end_time":569.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You''re gonna love her.","index":126,"end_time":570.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.64,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":127,"end_time":571.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":570.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know you''re putting in the chat, so just wanna make sure.","index":128,"end_time":575.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":129,"end_time":576.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":575.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Julia''s not.","index":130,"end_time":577.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":576.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I always gotta make sure people aren''t doing some unique spellings.","index":131,"end_time":580.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":577.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"True.","index":132,"end_time":581.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":581.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There are a few that are pretty creative.","index":133,"end_time":583.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Also, Rachel, because I haven''t seen you since.","index":134,"end_time":589.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Wasn''t it so cool that Kate was so praising of the, of the podcast today?","index":135,"end_time":599.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":590.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes, Kate was amazing.","index":136,"end_time":601.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"She''s like, you guys are so professional and I love the guide and it felt like you really did research and it was amazing.","index":137,"end_time":608.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.3,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That''s awesome to love her episodes.","index":138,"end_time":611.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.1,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Speaking of episodes, I have one I''m going to submit soon that we had to do in teams.","index":139,"end_time":616.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.18,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Did we tell you about this?","index":140,"end_time":617.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":141,"end_time":619.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had a podcast.","index":142,"end_time":621.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Weird.","index":143,"end_time":621.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it was a weird company.","index":144,"end_time":623.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Blocked Riverside somehow, she thinks.","index":145,"end_time":626.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":624.3,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And so we just made do.","index":146,"end_time":629.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":627.42,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"With that being said, I think it will be fine because I, like, hid myself and it made three, like, equal bricks.","index":147,"end_time":639.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.02,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I think you can literally just crop them and put them on a background, but that''ll be submitted like in a box downloaded link.","index":148,"end_time":647.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I just wanted to give you the heads up in case there''s any questions with that one.","index":149,"end_time":651.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We know that assets and things might look a little bit different, but the shape of the actual, like, tiles looked really good and similar to what we have now, so.","index":150,"end_time":662.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.669,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I don''t think it''ll be anything too crazy, but just wanted you to be and.","index":151,"end_time":666.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":662.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Was that Patrick?","index":152,"end_time":667.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":666.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not.","index":153,"end_time":669.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.49,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It was.","index":154,"end_time":670.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Who do we have last week?","index":155,"end_time":672.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":671.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It was.","index":156,"end_time":672.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was Christine.","index":157,"end_time":675.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":673.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Calvin.","index":158,"end_time":677.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":676.41,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Calvin.","index":159,"end_time":677.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":677.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Calvin.","index":160,"end_time":678.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":677.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Calvin.","index":161,"end_time":679.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.729,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was saying it wrong.","index":162,"end_time":680.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s Calvin S. We had so many fun, like, kind, amazing podcast guests.","index":163,"end_time":686.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t know if this would be worthwhile, but maybe there''s something we could also add, whether it''s to the guide or send them with a little bit about us so that there''s more of an incentive to work with us after.","index":164,"end_time":697.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.13,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I always feel like that comes up organically, but we can definitely add something.","index":165,"end_time":702.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":698.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that the.","index":166,"end_time":706.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The thing that''s happening now is that, like, we''re.","index":167,"end_time":710.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''re getting now more of a mix of people who don''t know us, you know, prior.","index":168,"end_time":716.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":710.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so we''re using it as the door opener.","index":169,"end_time":718.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":716.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so I think.","index":170,"end_time":721.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":720.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think I would just say zooming out.","index":171,"end_time":725.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":723.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel, I''m really glad that you raised it.","index":172,"end_time":727.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":725.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, we need to do a more thoughtful and strategic job at how we''re leveraging those opportunities.","index":173,"end_time":734.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":727.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, at the moment, I''m more so trying to, like, mention at the top and then mention again at the back end.","index":174,"end_time":739.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":734.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, would love to get together with you one on one, see if we may be able to support you, but there may be other things we could do.","index":175,"end_time":746.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":739.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, I think you''re saying, like, even within the guide itself.","index":176,"end_time":750.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":747.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m thinking maybe even if it''s like a.","index":177,"end_time":753.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.25,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"A page at the end so they could read a little bit more about us.","index":178,"end_time":757.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.97,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And it comes from not just noetic as A whole.","index":179,"end_time":760.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But maybe from the podcast team.","index":180,"end_time":762.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.45,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like, we put our names so it''s a little bit more personal and it doesn''t feel so, like, generated.","index":181,"end_time":768.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.53,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like maybe we put.","index":182,"end_time":769.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":768.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Hi, Jeff, we''re so excited to have you on the podcast.","index":183,"end_time":773.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Here''s a little bit about us before we meet.","index":184,"end_time":776.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.86,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then sign it from us.","index":185,"end_time":778.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":777.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Just something personal to give them like a thought starter so when they talk to us, maybe they also have some questions about what we do.","index":186,"end_time":784.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":778.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I like that.","index":187,"end_time":786.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":785.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My brain immediately went a little too deep and I was like, why don''t I just do a bunch of research on each of these companies and integrate like the pain points that they are likely feeling into it and how Noetic solves them.","index":188,"end_time":796.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":787.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think that content might get a little lengthy and might feel just.","index":189,"end_time":801.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":796.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty salesy, just something organic into what we''re doing, so it doesn''t feel pushy.","index":190,"end_time":806.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s like a.","index":191,"end_time":807.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.82,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"You already kind of know us and have an idea going in so you can maybe ask some questions.","index":192,"end_time":812.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because Nancy''s been great about when she sees them saying, you know, if there''s any way we can support you.","index":193,"end_time":817.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It sounds like there''s some changes happening at your company, so maybe we can start that a little earlier.","index":194,"end_time":822.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Just like a thought.","index":195,"end_time":823.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.14,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":196,"end_time":825.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I like, I like that idea.","index":197,"end_time":829.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it just, just to tee it up a little bit more because you know that the person is going to read that guide.","index":198,"end_time":837.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":829.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the only other thing I''m.","index":199,"end_time":839.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":838.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s coming up for me is like, I wonder if, like, do you do it shorter and at the front than at the back?","index":200,"end_time":845.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":839.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I love that.","index":201,"end_time":847.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.28,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think that''s a great idea.","index":202,"end_time":848.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.32,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Honestly, I would.","index":203,"end_time":850.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":849.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My brains, like test it.","index":204,"end_time":851.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":850.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":205,"end_time":851.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":206,"end_time":852.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":852.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":207,"end_time":853.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.85,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because, like, you know, if someone, if they do read through, I mean, those frameworks are they.","index":208,"end_time":857.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":853.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do they do like, they dive deep?","index":209,"end_time":859.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":857.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, they do.","index":210,"end_time":860.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":860.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They, they read it.","index":211,"end_time":862.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":860.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And, and, and I would say half the time they come back with some very specific things.","index":212,"end_time":868.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":863.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like we''re in 135 markets, not 132.","index":213,"end_time":872.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":868.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, sometimes they come back with it''s.","index":214,"end_time":874.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":872.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s never, it''s never a ton of stuff, you know, or, you know, sustainability got added to my role last month.","index":215,"end_time":882.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":874.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Now my title is this or whatever, little things like that.","index":216,"end_time":886.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":882.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But they definitely read it.","index":217,"end_time":887.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":886.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"People, I think, really appreciate knowing where it''s all going to go.","index":218,"end_time":891.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":887.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think, I think they would read it and I think we could test it.","index":219,"end_time":896.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":893.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m fine with testing it.","index":220,"end_time":897.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":896.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I know we have, we have podcasts down the list here, but while we''re talking about it.","index":221,"end_time":901.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":897.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The other thing I wanted to tell you that I''m excited about is that I noticed that Marissa Jarrett, one of the things I''m not great at is asking existing clients and relationships that we have for like, stuff to support Noetic.","index":222,"end_time":914.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":901.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Trying to do that more and strategically.","index":223,"end_time":917.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":915.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And Marissa Jarrett, who''s the CEO of.","index":224,"end_time":922.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":918.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"7 11, like every time I was doing research on CMOs that I don''t know, she was already linked with them.","index":225,"end_time":928.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":922.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I went to her and asked her because she did the podcast and, um, if there were any CMOs that.","index":226,"end_time":934.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":929.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She thought would be good guests and would she be open to the idea.","index":227,"end_time":939.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":934.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Of introducing me to people.","index":228,"end_time":940.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":939.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And she fed me five CMOs.","index":229,"end_time":943.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":940.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":230,"end_time":945.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":944.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Um, so we''re just in the, in the throes of figuring out like, I don''t know if she wants me to just drop her name or if she''s going to do the actual intros, but.","index":231,"end_time":952.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":945.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I''m going to use that formula again.","index":232,"end_time":955.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":953.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":233,"end_time":956.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there''s anything we can provide, research, anything, please let us know.","index":234,"end_time":962.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":956.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":235,"end_time":964.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it''s.","index":236,"end_time":966.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":964.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s a volume thing.","index":237,"end_time":969.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":967.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, it''s just we are in.","index":238,"end_time":972.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":969.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The process of interviewing for a biz.","index":239,"end_time":974.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":972.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Dev director because I''m drowning.","index":240,"end_time":975.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":974.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":976.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":976.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can only imagine.","index":242,"end_time":979.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":978.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know you guys have exciting.","index":243,"end_time":982.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":980.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Time coming up in a few hours here.","index":244,"end_time":983.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, we do.","index":245,"end_time":984.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":984.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes, we do.","index":246,"end_time":985.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":247,"end_time":986.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just to recap on points, we are now in the second week of November we''ve delivered 30 points.","index":248,"end_time":990.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":986.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have 75 more in working and we sent over the Duly and Noha episodes in our Friday email.","index":249,"end_time":998.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":990.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So those are available for review.","index":250,"end_time":1000.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":251,"end_time":1003.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Looking at Playbooks.","index":252,"end_time":1005.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1003.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the infographic campaign is set up on LinkedIn.","index":253,"end_time":1007.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1005.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also went back into Clay and enriched to find more first year CMOs.","index":254,"end_time":1014.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1008.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Nancy, of course taking in the not just first year of like career CMO, but first year at this role CMO.","index":255,"end_time":1021.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1014.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have some good names in here.","index":256,"end_time":1023.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1021.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got a chief marketing and product product officer at first dibs that used to work at Etsy ebay.","index":257,"end_time":1029.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1024.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just started this role five months ago after pretty long stints at other roles.","index":258,"end_time":1036.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1030.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, probably has some things that they want to implement, but I think is definitely worth showing an ad to.","index":259,"end_time":1042.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1036.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have a bunch of people.","index":260,"end_time":1043.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1042.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like that throughout this list.","index":261,"end_time":1045.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, because they just got promoted to.","index":262,"end_time":1055.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1053.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Chief Marketing officer eight months ago.","index":263,"end_time":1057.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":264,"end_time":1058.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.9,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s good.","index":265,"end_time":1059.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1058.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I always love when people customize their URLs.","index":266,"end_time":1063.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1060.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Amusing.","index":267,"end_time":1066.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1066.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s pretty good.","index":268,"end_time":1068.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1067.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Wow.","index":269,"end_time":1069.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Now I feel like I need to do that.","index":270,"end_time":1070.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.43,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I didn''t Even mine is customized, but it''s nothing as fun as that.","index":271,"end_time":1074.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1070.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, Nancy at Noetic.","index":272,"end_time":1076.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1074.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But yeah, so we have 2,000 in this list.","index":273,"end_time":1080.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1077.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are going through matching right now in LinkedIn.","index":274,"end_time":1083.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1080.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get a match rate and hopefully it''s above 80% and we can.","index":275,"end_time":1088.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1084.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Start serving ads to those people.","index":276,"end_time":1089.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of the things when we.","index":277,"end_time":1092.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1091.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And we''ll go to metrics in a minute, but that like the, the healthcare Playbook and the CMO Playbook, I don''t think they went out at exactly the right moment, but I feel like the CMO Playbook was getting less play, less, less downloads.","index":278,"end_time":1108.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1092.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":279,"end_time":1108.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1108.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it will be interesting to see whether or not this amps that up.","index":280,"end_time":1112.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1108.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think we just need more volume in there.","index":281,"end_time":1115.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1112.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re kind of playing in a small pond, but yeah, we''ve enriched more through.","index":282,"end_time":1119.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1115.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Clay and so very excited to see how that performs.","index":283,"end_time":1122.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But to that point about, you know, not getting enough play or kind of best use of the budget leadership align leadership alignment Playbook ad is not performing the best and I think to get more out of the first year CMO campaign in healthcare, we can allocate more.","index":284,"end_time":1140.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1122.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Budget to those infographics.","index":285,"end_time":1142.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1140.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I''m good with that.","index":286,"end_time":1145.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1144.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t want to, you know, I don''t want to put it out to pasture but.","index":287,"end_time":1149.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1146.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I think just dialing up cmo.","index":288,"end_time":1153.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1150.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":289,"end_time":1153.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1153.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":290,"end_time":1155.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll make that change and then pipedrive.","index":291,"end_time":1158.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1155.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nancy, I know we were going back and forth a little bit yesterday.","index":292,"end_time":1160.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1158.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Apologies for the delay in my response.","index":293,"end_time":1163.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1160.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were all on deck.","index":294,"end_time":1165.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1163.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I forgot that it was holiday because I was working, but so, yeah, I think, I hope that the, the new filter is gonna pull the spam out.","index":295,"end_time":1179,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1166.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What I wonder about like it just some of these leads are confusing to me.","index":296,"end_time":1190.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1181,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can I just share my screen for a second?","index":297,"end_time":1194.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1192.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":298,"end_time":1194.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1194.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, There you are.","index":299,"end_time":1195.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1194.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There you are.","index":300,"end_time":1196.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1195.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":301,"end_time":1196.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m gonna just share it on mine just because I''ve got it alphabetical, which is how it works for me.","index":302,"end_time":1203.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1196.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":303,"end_time":1204.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1203.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So like Dan Baum looks like he took the brand health diagnostic, but I don''t have.","index":304,"end_time":1223.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1206.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s no LinkedIn for him.","index":305,"end_time":1224.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1223.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then I was having trouble finding him on LinkedIn, so I didn''t know if this one is real.","index":306,"end_time":1231.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1224.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Elizabeth Crocker did download the Playbook, so I think she''s.","index":307,"end_time":1239.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1234.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She''s a legit.","index":308,"end_time":1240.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1239.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is.","index":309,"end_time":1241.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1241.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is the threshold such that if they download a Playbook they qualify as a lead?","index":310,"end_time":1246.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1241.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":311,"end_time":1246.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1246.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we had switched because you were like, you had mentioned that you couldn''t see the people that were converting or filling out the forms on LinkedIn.","index":312,"end_time":1253.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1246.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we connected that directly to Pipedrive.","index":313,"end_time":1255.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1253.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":314,"end_time":1258.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1257.75,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":315,"end_time":1259.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1258.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then this person, Jacinda Dariotis, it says newsletter opt in only, which, I don''t know.","index":316,"end_time":1270.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1259.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is that enough to validate someone becoming a lead?","index":317,"end_time":1272.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1270.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I wouldn''t say.","index":318,"end_time":1274.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1273.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I need to check in on Jacinta.","index":319,"end_time":1276.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1274.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Jacinta has an Illinois, but again, no LinkedIn.","index":320,"end_time":1284.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1276.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And, and I, and, and despite having a really unusual name, you know, not Bob Smith, I. I couldn''t find her on LinkedIn, so I wasn''t sure what to do with that.","index":321,"end_time":1296.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1284.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"JD did a download.","index":322,"end_time":1300.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1296.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think I looked at him.","index":323,"end_time":1308.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1303.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it just may be a small company but, but worth.","index":324,"end_time":1314.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1311.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Worth reaching out to.","index":325,"end_time":1315.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1314.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So most of, the.","index":326,"end_time":1319.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1318.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Most of the out.","index":327,"end_time":1320.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1319.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Kim Cox was the other one.","index":328,"end_time":1324.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1323.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So this says Brand Health Diagnostic and Sibley.","index":329,"end_time":1332.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1325.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So does that mean she took a Brand Health Diagnostic?","index":330,"end_time":1334.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1332.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I don''t think we got a thing on her.","index":331,"end_time":1337.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1334.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll check into her as well.","index":332,"end_time":1339.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1338.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it was her, Jacinta and Dan.","index":333,"end_time":1343.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1339.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dan bomb.","index":334,"end_time":1346.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1345.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":335,"end_time":1347.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I do know.","index":336,"end_time":1350.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1348.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As far as the Brand Health Diagnostic, I don''t.","index":337,"end_time":1352.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1350.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know I filled it out before.","index":338,"end_time":1354.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1353.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think it asked for LinkedIn or anything like that.","index":339,"end_time":1357.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1354.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just starts out with.","index":340,"end_time":1358.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1357.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s your email address?","index":341,"end_time":1358.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1358.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s just asking for email address.","index":342,"end_time":1365.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1363.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":343,"end_time":1366.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.86,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":344,"end_time":1366.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why that wouldn''t come in.","index":345,"end_time":1367.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1366.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":346,"end_time":1369.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1367.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like this is a, this is a spam.","index":347,"end_time":1371.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1369.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":348,"end_time":1372.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But again, probably came in before you put that filter.","index":349,"end_time":1379.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1375.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":350,"end_time":1380.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s not a lead.","index":351,"end_time":1387.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1385.82,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I worry a little bit because those seem newer to me.","index":352,"end_time":1410.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1406.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I hope the filter is catching them, but I''ll.","index":353,"end_time":1414.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1410.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''ll find you.","index":354,"end_time":1415.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1414.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I know some of those.","index":355,"end_time":1416.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1416.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looked like it was like in August, so it might have been sitting like in an ether somewhere.","index":356,"end_time":1420.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1416.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":357,"end_time":1420.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1420.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then when we activated the connection.","index":358,"end_time":1422.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1420.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just synced over.","index":359,"end_time":1423.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just, I just don''t wanna.","index":360,"end_time":1425.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1423.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, I don''t want ones coming in that aren''t real because it.","index":361,"end_time":1429.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1426.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Then I''m like spending administrative time trying to figure out what is this?","index":362,"end_time":1433.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1429.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then I also want to make sure that it''s always going to my leads box.","index":363,"end_time":1441.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1433.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":364,"end_time":1442,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1441.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":365,"end_time":1442.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Had a heart attack when I went.","index":366,"end_time":1445.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1443.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"To the everyone view and I was.","index":367,"end_time":1446.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1445.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, what are these?","index":368,"end_time":1447.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1446.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So if you think that what you''ve done at this point are.","index":369,"end_time":1450.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1448.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is right.","index":370,"end_time":1452.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1451.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then I.","index":371,"end_time":1453.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1452.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then last thing is just, you know, making sure that they have hit that threshold.","index":372,"end_time":1456.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1453.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Which.","index":373,"end_time":1457.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1456.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":374,"end_time":1458.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1458.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which a newsletter signup is not.","index":375,"end_time":1459.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1458.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I do want to continue.","index":376,"end_time":1461.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1459.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if someone downloads a PDF off of the LinkedIn Legion form, do you not want them coming directly into pipedrive?","index":377,"end_time":1468.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1461.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would you rather us send you like a list of form fills on a daily basis?","index":378,"end_time":1472.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1468.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or if they, if they do, which.","index":379,"end_time":1473.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1472.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If they Download like the PDFs or infographics from the LinkedIn ads, do you want them coming directly to Pipetra?","index":380,"end_time":1480.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1474.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It all depends on that.","index":381,"end_time":1483.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1480.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Agreed.","index":382,"end_time":1484.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1483.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Threshold of points.","index":383,"end_time":1485.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1484.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":384,"end_time":1486.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1485.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, I think the idea of the points is that somebody might do, you know, one thing that is worthy of 10 points or they might do like three things that get them there.","index":385,"end_time":1501.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1486.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":386,"end_time":1502.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1501.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, so if we''re.","index":387,"end_time":1503.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1502.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I, I don''t want people who don''t meet the threshold because I think they''re not, they''re not serious enough.","index":388,"end_time":1510.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1505.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":389,"end_time":1511.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, unless you tell me that you think the threshold''s too high.","index":390,"end_time":1520.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1517.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, I don''t think the threshold''s too high.","index":391,"end_time":1522.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1521.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We connected LinkedIn to Pipedrive just to make sure that you could see form fills right away for people downloading those things.","index":392,"end_time":1533.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1523.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we did have.","index":393,"end_time":1535.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1533.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually didn''t account for LinkedIn lead gen ads in our scoring.","index":394,"end_time":1544.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1539.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had case studies and other things in here.","index":395,"end_time":1548.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1546.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Full assessment for the brand health diagnostic.","index":396,"end_time":1551.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1548.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a LinkedIn click and view.","index":397,"end_time":1553.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1552.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We didn''t have a form submission because at the time we had set it.","index":398,"end_time":1555.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1553.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Up, we weren''t running lead gen forms.","index":399,"end_time":1558.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why lead gen wasn''t in there.","index":400,"end_time":1561.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1560.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":401,"end_time":1562.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1562.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so we will update this and then send it over, make sure that we''re on the same page and then we''ll update the settings for when people get passed into Pipedrive from LinkedIn.","index":402,"end_time":1578.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1568.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":403,"end_time":1579.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1579.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, good.","index":404,"end_time":1580.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.11,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I mean, it just seemed like something.","index":405,"end_time":1581.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1580.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Changed because typically I can see in.","index":406,"end_time":1586.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.87,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"The notes in pipedrive what they''ve done.","index":407,"end_time":1588.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1586.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And if they engaged with the podcast, I''ll see an email that''s talking about the podcast.","index":408,"end_time":1596.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1589.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If they downloaded a playbook, it says so.","index":409,"end_time":1599.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1596.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s just really helpful because when I follow up with them, I don''t want to give them something redundant.","index":410,"end_time":1606.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1600.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":411,"end_time":1607.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1606.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it also can give me a sense.","index":412,"end_time":1611.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1608.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Not always, but can sometimes give me a sense of what they''re interested in.","index":413,"end_time":1614.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1611.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":414,"end_time":1616.389,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1615.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":415,"end_time":1617.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1617.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll put together the, or we''ll add the LinkedIn form fills into the lead scoring, send that over to you for approval, and then we''ll update that connection.","index":416,"end_time":1626.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1617.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":417,"end_time":1627.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1626.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then realistically, my next, like, big delve on pipedrive will likely be, well, I''ll do a bit tomorrow early and then it''ll be Friday.","index":418,"end_time":1641.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1627.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I just say that to say that like, if you are tinkering around in there and pulling some things out, this afternoon''s a good time.","index":419,"end_time":1650.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1642.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll see what I can do.","index":420,"end_time":1653.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1651.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Still back to back till 5, but 5 time it opens up tonight, I definitely, definitely can.","index":421,"end_time":1658.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1654.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":422,"end_time":1663.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we are still looking good on the podcast sheet.","index":423,"end_time":1667.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1664.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rachel, did you like what.","index":424,"end_time":1672.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1671.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What Natalie had added in here as far as documents and everything?","index":425,"end_time":1675.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1672.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, that is great.","index":426,"end_time":1679.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.79,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We''ll look at it in our internal meeting.","index":427,"end_time":1681.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1679.55,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But thank you.","index":428,"end_time":1682.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1681.95,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I.","index":429,"end_time":1683.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1682.99,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We appreciate that you''re making things even easier for us, so thank you.","index":430,"end_time":1688.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1683.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":431,"end_time":1688.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1688.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"This is so much easier.","index":432,"end_time":1689.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1688.64,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, speaking of this, I had a question about the drive.","index":433,"end_time":1694.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1690.72,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Can you please grant us or me editing access for the main page with all the folders?","index":434,"end_time":1702.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1694.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Just because I want to put, like, a folder of old episodes and then for the title names, like, I want to put the guest first so that if we''re looking at it quickly, we can navigate.","index":435,"end_time":1712.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1703.12,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So.","index":436,"end_time":1713.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1712.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So not changing anything.","index":437,"end_time":1714.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.28,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m just, like, relabeling it so it''s easier for us to find stuff.","index":438,"end_time":1718.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.4,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Just the main page.","index":439,"end_time":1721.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1720.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":440,"end_time":1722.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1721.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":441,"end_time":1723.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Also here, we did not record an internal episode after Pam Forbus and before Jenny Colopy, so we can take that one out.","index":442,"end_time":1734.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1724.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I do, per our exchange, I do have interest in doing one or two internals.","index":443,"end_time":1741.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1734.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I was thinking, Rachel, that December could be a good time to do that, just because clients tend to go a little bit quieter.","index":444,"end_time":1749.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1741.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think that would be great.","index":445,"end_time":1751.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1750.55,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I also think Sam would be great on an episode.","index":446,"end_time":1753.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1751.55,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I know she has some PTO coming up, so if we want her, we should coordinate with her soonest.","index":447,"end_time":1759.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1753.91,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that.","index":448,"end_time":1761.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1760.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think we need to just have a think about what is the focus of set episodes.","index":449,"end_time":1769.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1765.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":450,"end_time":1771.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1771.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What do we think is going to be, like, the hardest working.","index":451,"end_time":1773.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1771.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":452,"end_time":1778.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1777.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And what we need, like, what is something that we don''t really have covered.","index":453,"end_time":1781.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.32,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yet that we could see.","index":454,"end_time":1782.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1781.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"People.","index":455,"end_time":1782.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1782.64,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I feel like the people problem still.","index":456,"end_time":1785.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1783.76,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Could be a really good.","index":457,"end_time":1787.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1785.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Agreed.","index":458,"end_time":1788.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1788.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":459,"end_time":1789.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1789.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And one of the things that we''re gonna talk about at the off site tomorrow is around this AI program.","index":460,"end_time":1802.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1789.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so, like, that could be one also, I have so much content, just content ideas from going to these conferences.","index":461,"end_time":1811.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1802.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And one of the things I don''t think that we''ve done really anything on in the.","index":462,"end_time":1817.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1811.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In the podcast realm is around training.","index":463,"end_time":1821.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1817.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And there''s a lot of buzz around, like, the skills that marketers need now in the, you know, in this new atmosphere that we find ourselves in.","index":464,"end_time":1837.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1823.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so there''s at least two episodes there, I think.","index":465,"end_time":1843.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1838.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Great.","index":466,"end_time":1844.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1844.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And if we do more.","index":467,"end_time":1846.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Then we''ll have them to spread out, which is good.","index":468,"end_time":1848.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1846.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":469,"end_time":1850.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1849.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So from a.","index":470,"end_time":1851.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1850.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"From a format standpoint, Colin, like, if.","index":471,"end_time":1854.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1851.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If I gave you guys, like.","index":472,"end_time":1856.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1854.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like the ball of clay, if you will, you know, on the topic, could you work that into a guide?","index":473,"end_time":1864.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1857.27,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, we could build a framework for it.","index":474,"end_time":1866.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1865.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would just need to know ahead of time if this is one that you plan on doing on your own or plan on pulling in a guest.","index":475,"end_time":1872.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1866.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":476,"end_time":1873.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1873.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":477,"end_time":1875.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1874.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":478,"end_time":1877.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1876.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the training thing, though, I think a lot of times people get so wrapped up in planning, they forget about actual implementation process.","index":479,"end_time":1887.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1877.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, like, I feel like a cool episode could be like, so you''ve written the plan, now what?","index":480,"end_time":1891.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1887.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And really diving into, like, how it actually needs to be spread throughout the whole company into, you know, public messaging.","index":481,"end_time":1898.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1892.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How Marketing is more than just marketing.","index":482,"end_time":1899.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1898.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":483,"end_time":1900.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1899.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s pr.","index":484,"end_time":1900.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1900.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s the representation of who you are as a company.","index":485,"end_time":1903.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1901.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I feel like there''s so much that people forget, especially since we''re in planning season right now.","index":486,"end_time":1909.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1905.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So many companies are.","index":487,"end_time":1910.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1909.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That it''s not just, like.","index":488,"end_time":1912.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1911.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not that, you know, team meeting, and, like, everything''s done there.","index":489,"end_time":1919.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1914.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, it actually.","index":490,"end_time":1920.059,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1919.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So much of it happens after.","index":491,"end_time":1921.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1920.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s exactly what was occurring to me yesterday when I was at this.","index":492,"end_time":1926.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1921.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Higher ed conference, and they were saying.","index":493,"end_time":1928.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1926.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, this is the time to be planning, know for your learning and development plan, and you need to have a learning and development plan because your people have skill gaps.","index":494,"end_time":1940.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1928.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, I mean, but I think, realistically, unless.","index":495,"end_time":1949.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1944.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Unless we decided to, like, switch out the order, I think, realistically, we would not be able to go live with it until, like, January.","index":496,"end_time":1961.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1949.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":497,"end_time":1962.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1962.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":498,"end_time":1964.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1963.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":499,"end_time":1965.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1964.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s all right.","index":500,"end_time":1966.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1965.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":501,"end_time":1967.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1966.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":502,"end_time":1967.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1967.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think it''s just another one to have in a.","index":503,"end_time":1969.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1967.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the back pocket.","index":504,"end_time":1970.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1969.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we''ve gotten ahead, and that.","index":505,"end_time":1974.089,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1972.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a great place to be.","index":506,"end_time":1975.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1974.089,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":507,"end_time":1975.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1975.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":508,"end_time":1976.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1976.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Before you leave that list, I do have one exciting update, which is below Phil Cook and above Gail Lomax, we.","index":509,"end_time":1987.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1977.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Have a yes from Kristen o''.","index":510,"end_time":1991.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1987.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Boyle.","index":511,"end_time":1992.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1991.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Chris o'', Boyle, K, R, I, S.","index":512,"end_time":1995.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1993.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then O, apostrophe, capital B, O, Y, L, E. And she is the CMO of CVS Health.","index":513,"end_time":2006.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1996.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Cvs.","index":514,"end_time":2009.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2008.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cvs.","index":515,"end_time":2010.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2009.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":516,"end_time":2010.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2010.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":517,"end_time":2011.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2010.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I am all sorts of congested today.","index":518,"end_time":2014.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2011.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My brain has stopped working.","index":519,"end_time":2015.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2014.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So she''s a TBD date, but she is a verbal yes.","index":520,"end_time":2021.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2015.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So not different than Phil Cook, who I''m trying to resurrect, and Mac McGee.","index":521,"end_time":2026.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2021.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We did.","index":522,"end_time":2027.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2027.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Patrick finally rescheduled.","index":523,"end_time":2030.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2028.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":524,"end_time":2032.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2031.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So he''s a.","index":525,"end_time":2034.049,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2033.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s locked in on the 18th.","index":526,"end_time":2035.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2034.049,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s locked in on the 18th.","index":527,"end_time":2036.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2035.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And we did Kate''s today.","index":528,"end_time":2037.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2036.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Love it.","index":529,"end_time":2039.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2038.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So date wise in our Go live.","index":530,"end_time":2043.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2040.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, Rachel, one of the things I want us to talk about with getting.","index":531,"end_time":2049.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2046.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Julia in the mix is when we think we can go a little faster.","index":532,"end_time":2055.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2049.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":533,"end_time":2057.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2057.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But let''s worry about that next week.","index":534,"end_time":2061.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2059.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":535,"end_time":2064.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2061.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":536,"end_time":2065.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2064.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I love the spelling.","index":537,"end_time":2066.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2065.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So my sister spelled her name.","index":538,"end_time":2067.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2066.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I met her at the A conference.","index":539,"end_time":2073.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2071.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":540,"end_time":2075.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2074.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did.","index":541,"end_time":2076.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2075.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":542,"end_time":2078.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2078.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I gotta get a few updates.","index":543,"end_time":2079.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2078.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Marriott.","index":544,"end_time":2080.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2079.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any.","index":545,"end_time":2081.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2080.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any word back from.","index":546,"end_time":2082.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2081.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so a few updates.","index":547,"end_time":2083.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2082.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Marriott.","index":548,"end_time":2084.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2083.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I tried to hand deliver my book to that.","index":549,"end_time":2089.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2085.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Security wasn''t having it.","index":550,"end_time":2090.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2089.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Security wasn''t having it.","index":551,"end_time":2091.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2090.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I mailed it to all of them except one woman who like, got back to me as I was mailing them, who now has gone quiet.","index":552,"end_time":2101.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2091.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I cannot.","index":553,"end_time":2102.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2101.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s so frustrating.","index":554,"end_time":2103.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2102.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I can''t email the Marriott people.","index":555,"end_time":2105.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2103.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It always bounces back.","index":556,"end_time":2106.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2105.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I can only DM them in LinkedIn.","index":557,"end_time":2110.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2106.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I was just doing that this morning.","index":558,"end_time":2113.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2110.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I.","index":559,"end_time":2113.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2113.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They would have gotten the book by like last Thursday and So I was DMing this morning.","index":560,"end_time":2118.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2113.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I do think that I will eventually get at least one of them and I think it''s probably going to be Tanya Galarza.","index":561,"end_time":2125.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2118.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We worked with, like, long ago.","index":562,"end_time":2127.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2126.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Any one of them, like, has the right title.","index":563,"end_time":2131.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2129.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I just need to, like, get in somewhere so I can, like, poke around.","index":564,"end_time":2135.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2131.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Waymo.","index":565,"end_time":2136.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2136.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We are now booked.","index":566,"end_time":2139.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2137.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I met with Linda Chen and now I''m gonna meet with her boss and we are booked.","index":567,"end_time":2153.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2139.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"For.","index":568,"end_time":2155.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2154.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know, but we''re booked.","index":569,"end_time":2172.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2169.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it''s next week and if it''s not next week, it''s the week after.","index":570,"end_time":2175.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2172.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":571,"end_time":2176.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2176.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":572,"end_time":2177.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2177.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie had a funny reaction.","index":573,"end_time":2180.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2179.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s the one I had to sell.","index":574,"end_time":2181.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2180.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, Natalie had a funny reaction to.","index":575,"end_time":2185.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2182.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The Waymo lead coming in if you wanted to.","index":576,"end_time":2188.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2185.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I. I told Colin, I. I once got.","index":577,"end_time":2192.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2189.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Almost got hit by a Waymo.","index":578,"end_time":2193.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2192.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was my first time ever seeing them in Phoenix and I didn''t even know what they were.","index":579,"end_time":2200.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2194.27,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I almost got hit by one, like crossing the road and then like looked inside and there was just no one driving.","index":580,"end_time":2206.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2200.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":581,"end_time":2206.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2206.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s just so concerned.","index":582,"end_time":2208.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2206.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s very disturbing when you don''t know what you''re looking at.","index":583,"end_time":2212.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2209.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I know because I.","index":584,"end_time":2214.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2212.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"My daughter lives in Phoenix and I didn''t almost get hit by one, but I was seeing them, you know, driving all around and they sound like spaceships and they''ve got the revolving thing on the top and so you just see it and you''re like, I don''t know what I''m looking at here.","index":585,"end_time":2229.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2214.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, what is going on with that?","index":586,"end_time":2230.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2229.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then you realize there''s no driver in there.","index":587,"end_time":2232.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2230.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Which the first time you see that, it''s like, like, very disturbing.","index":588,"end_time":2234.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2232.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That said, I, I wrote in one out there.","index":589,"end_time":2240.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2234.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I was scared.","index":590,"end_time":2242.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2241.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But then once I did it, like, it was actually fine.","index":591,"end_time":2246.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2242.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s a woman that I know who.","index":592,"end_time":2248.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2246.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Lives out there who set.","index":593,"end_time":2249.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2248.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Who was like a walking advertisement for them.","index":594,"end_time":2251.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2249.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She was like, I think it''s safer than an Uber.","index":595,"end_time":2254.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2251.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, they''re so reliable.","index":596,"end_time":2256.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2255.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You don''t, you don''t tip.","index":597,"end_time":2259.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2258.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, it''s not, it''s not expected that you tip.","index":598,"end_time":2263.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2261.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And she said, I just feel safer.","index":599,"end_time":2265.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2263.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And, you know, I do it.","index":600,"end_time":2266.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2265.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I do it all the time.","index":601,"end_time":2267.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2266.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I do it to go to the airport.","index":602,"end_time":2269.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2267.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I do it if I''m, you know, going out to dinner and I don''t want to deal with parking.","index":603,"end_time":2273.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2269.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I.","index":604,"end_time":2273.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2273.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think it''s actually less expensive.","index":605,"end_time":2275.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2273.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, she was on and on about it.","index":606,"end_time":2276.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2275.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so the next day with my friends that I was out there with, we all said like, okay, let''s do it and we''ll do it together.","index":607,"end_time":2283.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2276.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I was probably the most nervous.","index":608,"end_time":2285.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2284.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But honestly, like, you''re in there for five minutes and then you''re just like, it''s fine.","index":609,"end_time":2290.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2286.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":610,"end_time":2291.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2291.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I''m sure they''re not going away or disturbing.","index":611,"end_time":2293.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2291.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":612,"end_time":2294.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2294.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you get to avoid all that.","index":613,"end_time":2296.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2294.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re growing.","index":614,"end_time":2297.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2296.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, they''re in three markets and they''re going.","index":615,"end_time":2299.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2297.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And Linda told me they''re going into 30.","index":616,"end_time":2301.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2299.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":617,"end_time":2303.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2302.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So need a ton of help.","index":618,"end_time":2304.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2303.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I do think that she has money.","index":619,"end_time":2307.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2304.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":620,"end_time":2308.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2308.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it sounds like it could be a big one.","index":621,"end_time":2310.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2308.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it could be a big one.","index":622,"end_time":2311.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2310.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s just getting on board a very fast moving train.","index":623,"end_time":2316.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2311.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":624,"end_time":2317.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2316.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":625,"end_time":2318.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2317.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I''m, I''m scratching at the door.","index":626,"end_time":2320.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2318.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":627,"end_time":2322,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2321.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Rachel, we''re continuing to go through the checklist for all the episode assets.","index":628,"end_time":2327.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2322.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know there was Mike Linton.","index":629,"end_time":2330.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2328.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You had emailed Monday and so those will be finished today.","index":630,"end_time":2334.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2330.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":631,"end_time":2336.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2335.44,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":632,"end_time":2338.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2338.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Taking a look at databox.","index":633,"end_time":2342.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2339.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re looking at a week over week measurement here.","index":634,"end_time":2345.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2342.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why visitors is pretty low.","index":635,"end_time":2347.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2345.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But did see a dip in total visitors?","index":636,"end_time":2349.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2347.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":637,"end_time":2350.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2349.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, sometimes these things just happen where people are just either on vacation or not really working as much or kind of phased out.","index":638,"end_time":2360.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2351.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we can see though is that even though visitors dropped, they were even more engaged than we''ve seen.","index":639,"end_time":2366.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2362.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The high engagement levels of higher traffic.","index":640,"end_time":2369.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2367.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, spending almost five minutes on the site looking at over two pages and balancing about 15% less than industry average.","index":641,"end_time":2380.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2369.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wow.","index":642,"end_time":2382.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2381.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good to know.","index":643,"end_time":2384.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2382.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just want to blow this up a little bit.","index":644,"end_time":2386.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2385.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the homepage, second to that, the Playbooks and the company page.","index":645,"end_time":2390.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2386.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. I''d love to see more traction on the insights page just because there''s.","index":646,"end_time":2402.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2392.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So much good stuff there.","index":647,"end_time":2404.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2402.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":648,"end_time":2405.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2405.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But.","index":649,"end_time":2410.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2410.55,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":650,"end_time":2411.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2411.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And when you guys are writing blog content, are you doing it from an.","index":651,"end_time":2414.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2411.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"SEO perspective or more of a thought leadership perspective?","index":652,"end_time":2416.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2414.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thought leadership.","index":653,"end_time":2418.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2417.75,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But we can change our approach.","index":654,"end_time":2422.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2420.77,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I wouldn''t say completely change.","index":655,"end_time":2425.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2423.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I. I actually feel like marketers in demand has a strong feeling about when people say SEO content.","index":656,"end_time":2430.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2425.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I always think or we always think content should be thought leadership with just.","index":657,"end_time":2435.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2432.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like SEO sprinkled into it.","index":658,"end_time":2437.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2435.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of like, we refer to it as.","index":659,"end_time":2440.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2437.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Worthy, but then make it SEO hard working as much as you can.","index":660,"end_time":2446.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2440.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":661,"end_time":2447.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2446.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it''s the big thing is always terminology.","index":662,"end_time":2449.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2447.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like we are in marketing every day we refer to it as xyz, a prospect.","index":663,"end_time":2454.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2449.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even if they are cmo, they may refer to it as a completely different term.","index":664,"end_time":2458,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2454.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to find the balance of like, what is the most popular term.","index":665,"end_time":2461.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2458.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To refer to these things?","index":666,"end_time":2462.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2461.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":667,"end_time":2463.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2462.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":668,"end_time":2467.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2466.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, as far as getting more traffic here, I think we need a little bit more content also before even diving into these.","index":669,"end_time":2473.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2467.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that would be another approach.","index":670,"end_time":2475.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2474,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we can do is make a recommendation for some keywords and maybe even some starter copy that we would recommend.","index":671,"end_time":2480.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2475.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Putting on this page.","index":672,"end_time":2481.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2480.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds great.","index":673,"end_time":2485.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2484.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":674,"end_time":2487.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2486.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we will work on that.","index":675,"end_time":2488.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2487.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a great idea.","index":676,"end_time":2489.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2488.4,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And that is actually everything that we.","index":677,"end_time":2494.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2493.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Had in our agenda today.","index":678,"end_time":2495.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2494.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":679,"end_time":2498.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2497.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Any.","index":680,"end_time":2498.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2498.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, good.","index":681,"end_time":2500.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2499.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we need any time on podcast assets, Rachel?","index":682,"end_time":2505.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2500.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":683,"end_time":2509.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2507.17,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Right now.","index":684,"end_time":2510.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2509.49,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think we''re in better shape.","index":685,"end_time":2512.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2510.69,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":686,"end_time":2516.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2516.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":687,"end_time":2516.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2516.41,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Is there anything else that you wanted.","index":688,"end_time":2518.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2516.85,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"To cover for them?","index":689,"end_time":2519.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2518.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, I don''t think so.","index":690,"end_time":2530.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2529.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I was just.","index":691,"end_time":2530.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2530.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So there''s chicken and egg to this, but we''re.","index":692,"end_time":2534.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2531.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Tomorrow we''re working on this, like standing up this AI sort of program where we would help marketers figure out how to infuse AI into their processes.","index":693,"end_time":2548.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2534.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s not like we haven''t built it yet because I''d like to have somebody pay us so that we can build it.","index":694,"end_time":2555.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2549.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I feel like we need to figure out how to promote it in order to then get.","index":695,"end_time":2562.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2556.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because this is just a problem that, you know, I keep running it by people when I''m talking to them and.","index":696,"end_time":2567.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2562.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And nobody doesn''t have this problem unless they''re like the biggest companies.","index":697,"end_time":2571.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2568.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So maybe like think about it with us.","index":698,"end_time":2577.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2572.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That I think it could be.","index":699,"end_time":2578.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2577.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I.","index":700,"end_time":2580.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2580.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Don''T know if it can be a podcast episode because we haven''t done it yet.","index":701,"end_time":2583.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2580.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":702,"end_time":2583.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2583.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we can''t like speak to that.","index":703,"end_time":2586.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2583.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It could be a blog.","index":704,"end_time":2588.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2587.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It could be ads.","index":705,"end_time":2591.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2589.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We had talked about last time we met Colin.","index":706,"end_time":2594.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2591.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We talked about like having ads that would show a work flow, like, you know, with the ability to tout it.","index":707,"end_time":2604.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2594.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":708,"end_time":2605.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2604.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like a micro and a macro view.","index":709,"end_time":2606.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2605.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":710,"end_time":2607.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2606.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What I would say is I don''t think we need to limit our channels though.","index":711,"end_time":2611.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2608.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even if you haven''t built it, I think the podcast episode could be around the general pain points and then like the general philosophy of how to resolve those even if you don''t have like this snow edits.","index":712,"end_time":2620.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2611.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exact approach.","index":713,"end_time":2621.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2620.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, well, I definitely have, I definitely have that.","index":714,"end_time":2624.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2621.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":715,"end_time":2624.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2624.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I, so I, I can give you that.","index":716,"end_time":2626.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2625.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then, yeah, I guess I was thinking more like, you know, you''d want to sprinkle in examples, but I think you wouldn''t necessarily have to.","index":717,"end_time":2636,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2626.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You could just sort of unpack like where we are, why is this a problem, how it would work, blah, blah, blah.","index":718,"end_time":2642.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2636,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":719,"end_time":2643.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2642.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that''s the podcast episode.","index":720,"end_time":2644.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2643.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But then if you write a blog, you can get more in depth.","index":721,"end_time":2647.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2644.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you have a little bit more filled or figured out of like your approach, allude back to that podcast.","index":722,"end_time":2651.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2647.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could have organic LinkedIn posts, like all of these things working together.","index":723,"end_time":2655.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2651.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s not just like this is on this channel that''s on that channel.","index":724,"end_time":2658.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2656.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like all these things are speaking to the noetic approach to AI and the conversations along the way.","index":725,"end_time":2663.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2658.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I like that.","index":726,"end_time":2664.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2663.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":727,"end_time":2667.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2667.36,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I think out of this meeting that we''re having tomorrow, I, I, that one is not too hard to do.","index":728,"end_time":2672.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2667.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then I think we just have to decide what the second one is.","index":729,"end_time":2675.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2672.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel, it could be, it could be brand House, as we had originally said.","index":730,"end_time":2680.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2676.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":731,"end_time":2681.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2680.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then we got short staffed and we tabled it.","index":732,"end_time":2684.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2681.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or.","index":733,"end_time":2684.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2684.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It could be about training, which I don''t think either is wrong.","index":734,"end_time":2692.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2686.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But, but just based upon like the, the buzz that I''m hearing, I think training might be harder working for now.","index":735,"end_time":2698.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2692.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree.","index":736,"end_time":2702.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2700.92,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Brain Houses, I think people kind of know they can come to us for brand work already.","index":737,"end_time":2707.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2702.84,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I feel like the others are less obvious and more needed.","index":738,"end_time":2710.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2708.22,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And you know, I would say it differently.","index":739,"end_time":2716.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2711.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think there are a ton of firms out there doing brand work, and while we''re known by some for that, there''s a lot of people working with other people to do that work.","index":740,"end_time":2725.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2716.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, if I had a dollar for Everybody who''s like, yeah, we did a rebrand.","index":741,"end_time":2728.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2726.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We worked with so and so.","index":742,"end_time":2729.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2728.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I''m like, good point.","index":743,"end_time":2732.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2729.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":744,"end_time":2732.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2732.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I think when it comes to training, particularly on these, like, soft skill trainings, I don''t know that people are doing it.","index":745,"end_time":2740.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2732.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, many.","index":746,"end_time":2742.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2741.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Anyway, there was a woman yesterday.","index":747,"end_time":2744.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2742.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, sample of one, but there was a woman yesterday.","index":748,"end_time":2746.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2744.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She''s, like, in charge of learning and development at the ama, which is the association of blah, blah, blah marketers.","index":749,"end_time":2752.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2746.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s a N, A M A and then four A''s.","index":750,"end_time":2756.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2753.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They all have A''s.","index":751,"end_time":2756.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2756.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know why.","index":752,"end_time":2757.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2756.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So they''re running the conference, and she runs learning and development for the association, and she puts up these what people would call soft skills that are, like, imperatives now.","index":753,"end_time":2769.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2757.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Things like critical thinking, collab, knowing how to collaborate, things of that nature.","index":754,"end_time":2773.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2769.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And.","index":755,"end_time":2775.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2774.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And somebody asked her like, well, how do you.","index":756,"end_time":2778.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2775.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How would you train people in those?","index":757,"end_time":2781.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2779.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And she was like.","index":758,"end_time":2784.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2783.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She talked about toastmasters and she talked about books.","index":759,"end_time":2789.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2785.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":760,"end_time":2791.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2790.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was like, so no actual training?","index":761,"end_time":2793.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2791.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wow.","index":762,"end_time":2793.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2793.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, okay, interesting.","index":763,"end_time":2798.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2794.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It seems like there''s a big gap.","index":764,"end_time":2799.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2798.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":765,"end_time":2800.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2800.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And she''s in charge of learning and development for ama.","index":766,"end_time":2803.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2800.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So is she incompetent at her job, maybe?","index":767,"end_time":2806.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2803.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or is there a desert in that space?","index":768,"end_time":2809.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2806.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, I mean, I do know.","index":769,"end_time":2811.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2809.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I know one boutique firm in Chicago that does training like that.","index":770,"end_time":2814.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2811.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m not saying it''s, like, completely an open space, but I think it''s a lot less crowded than brand.","index":771,"end_time":2820.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2814.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":772,"end_time":2821.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2821.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll review the Kate episode, but I wonder if she talked about that rollout as well.","index":773,"end_time":2826.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2821.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I would say, and this is a gross estimate, not based in any reality of statistics, but I would imagine 50% of, like, brand rollouts are just dropped on the team.","index":774,"end_time":2836.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2827.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, other than the people that were working on it and leadership, who knew, like, it''s just like, hey, guys, here''s our new colors and how we talk about our core values or, like, whatever one through nine things that we''ve done.","index":775,"end_time":2846.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2836.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, there is a new company.","index":776,"end_time":2851.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2847.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They''re not new.","index":777,"end_time":2852.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2852.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"New to me that I am getting to know that all they do is the.","index":778,"end_time":2858.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2852.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The financial and the logistical of taking a rebrand and pulling it all the way through.","index":779,"end_time":2866.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2861.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"People don''t think about.","index":780,"end_time":2868.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2867.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I literally don''t know anybody else who''s doing what they''re doing.","index":781,"end_time":2871.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2869.07,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I''m like, every client that we''ve done a rebrand for or needs that.","index":782,"end_time":2874.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2871.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And to your point, they need training so that people can understand and be compliant and all those kinds of things.","index":783,"end_time":2881.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2874.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The front end tends to get way More attention than the back end.","index":784,"end_time":2884.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2881.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":785,"end_time":2884.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2884.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do wonder if there''s a partnership possibility.","index":786,"end_time":2886.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2884.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know the company that you''re talking about, but that would be like, hey, guys.","index":787,"end_time":2891.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2886.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":788,"end_time":2893.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2891.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":789,"end_time":2893.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2893.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s what we''re talking about.","index":790,"end_time":2894.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2893.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because they told me that they oftentimes get asked for, you know, who can do the research and the brand work.","index":791,"end_time":2901.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2894.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They don''t do that part.","index":792,"end_time":2902.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2901.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":793,"end_time":2903.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2902.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then they stay in their lane.","index":794,"end_time":2905.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2903.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They stay in their lane.","index":795,"end_time":2906.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2905.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And.","index":796,"end_time":2906.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2906.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And they said that increasingly organizations don''t.","index":797,"end_time":2911.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2907.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right now in this market, people don''t want to go to the big guys like interbrand and profit.","index":798,"end_time":2916.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2911.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They.","index":799,"end_time":2916.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2916.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They don''t want to pay those fees.","index":800,"end_time":2919.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2916.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":801,"end_time":2920.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2919.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But then they get nervous with the boutiques.","index":802,"end_time":2922.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2920.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, what are they really good at?","index":803,"end_time":2923.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2922.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This is.","index":804,"end_time":2924.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2924.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This is what they were telling me.","index":805,"end_time":2925.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2924.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":806,"end_time":2926.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2925.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they tend to hound.","index":807,"end_time":2928.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2926.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":808,"end_time":2929.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2928.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s always interesting, the trust factor of a. I feel like more times than not across any industry, I have a worse experience with like, the conglomerate than the, like, mom and pop.","index":809,"end_time":2939.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2929.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, I think the people who actually take the time to get to know what I''m looking for and those types.","index":810,"end_time":2944.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2940.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of things, I get better results.","index":811,"end_time":2945.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2944.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think I''ve had that in each.","index":812,"end_time":2948.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2946.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I. I think if you really understand what the smaller company does.","index":813,"end_time":2954.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2948.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, yeah.","index":814,"end_time":2955.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2954.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Then.","index":815,"end_time":2956.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2955.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Then you''re going to have a better time because, you know, you''re talking to the people that you''re.","index":816,"end_time":2961.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2956.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, one of the biggest things that happened with the big firms is that you talk to the top brass and they are not.","index":817,"end_time":2967.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2961.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They are not your team.","index":818,"end_time":2968.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2967.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":819,"end_time":2969.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2968.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":820,"end_time":2969.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2969.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they''re not always in the day to day.","index":821,"end_time":2971.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2969.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, they.","index":822,"end_time":2972.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2971.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s different pain points all the way down the ladder.","index":823,"end_time":2974.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2972.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":824,"end_time":2974.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2974.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They''ve got 2% of their time allotted.","index":825,"end_time":2976.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2974.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":826,"end_time":2977.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2977.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just the model, you know, Model.","index":827,"end_time":2979.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2977.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s like I''m.","index":828,"end_time":2980.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2979.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They''re overseeing the work, but are they really?","index":829,"end_time":2982.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2980.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":830,"end_time":2982.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2982.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":831,"end_time":2983.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2982.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":832,"end_time":2984.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2983.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, so I will get you.","index":833,"end_time":2986.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2984.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I will get you fodder for definitely that AI one and probably also the training one.","index":834,"end_time":2996.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2988.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just want to have think about how to do each of those and I''ll get you.","index":835,"end_time":3000.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2996.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, I know you need to know, is it going to be like interview style or is it going to speak to camera?","index":836,"end_time":3005.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3000.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"My.","index":837,"end_time":3005.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3005.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"My inclination would be to do one of each.","index":838,"end_time":3007.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3005.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Mm.","index":839,"end_time":3008.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3008.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I think that the AI one is going to be a little bit more to the point and because it''s not like we can talk about our actual experience doing it.","index":840,"end_time":3019.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3010.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it''s just like, more straightforward.","index":841,"end_time":3021.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3019.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Whereas I think the training one could be more of A conversation almost like.","index":842,"end_time":3027.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3021.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":843,"end_time":3028.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3028.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s all sorts of, like, fun ideas too.","index":844,"end_time":3031.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3029.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I know you guys having a retreat, you could do like a round table type conversation.","index":845,"end_time":3036.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3031.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we''re getting to the end of the year, you can do, like, biggest hits and misses we''ve seen this year.","index":846,"end_time":3040.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3036.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s all sorts of fun things that you can do that are more of the organic play of, like, just getting Noetic out there is brand awareness.","index":847,"end_time":3048.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3041.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I know.","index":848,"end_time":3050.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3048.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We talked about doing a top hits reel, Rachel.","index":849,"end_time":3054.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3050.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes, we did.","index":850,"end_time":3056.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3054.63,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That''s a great idea.","index":851,"end_time":3057.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3056.67,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I like that we''re innovating and thinking of new things we can do because I think it''s important that we''re keeping what we''re doing fresh, thinking outside the box.","index":852,"end_time":3067.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3058.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So, yeah, we got to try things.","index":853,"end_time":3068.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3067.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Not everything will work, but something''s gonna work.","index":854,"end_time":3071.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3068.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Great.","index":855,"end_time":3072.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3071.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":856,"end_time":3074.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3073.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so I''ll add Julia to the meetings to replace Tracy.","index":857,"end_time":3078.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3074.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Keep an eye out for the Christine Calvinez episode just so we can make sure we''re all good on the assets there for the team''s recording.","index":858,"end_time":3086.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3079.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll also send over quotes like we talked about to make sure that those are aligned with the quick cards work on for whatever the next guy that we write promoting Noetic.","index":859,"end_time":3095.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3086.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And first one, maybe we do at the front.","index":860,"end_time":3097.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3095.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Second one, we do it at the end just to see how that goes.","index":861,"end_time":3101.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3097.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also checking into Dan Bomb, Jacinta and Kim Cox writing LinkedIn Legion forms into the lead, scoring and rotating the budget as we talked about.","index":862,"end_time":3113.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3101.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":863,"end_time":3114.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3113.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":864,"end_time":3115.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3115.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":865,"end_time":3116.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3116.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you all so much for joining us.","index":866,"end_time":3118.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3116.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get a snack.","index":867,"end_time":3118.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3118.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Colin, you have like 12 minutes.","index":868,"end_time":3120.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3118.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I do.","index":869,"end_time":3121.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3120.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do have 12 minutes.","index":870,"end_time":3122.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3121.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":871,"end_time":3123.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3122.64,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Breathe, eat and feel better.","index":872,"end_time":3124.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3123.12,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":873,"end_time":3125.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3124.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":874,"end_time":3127.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3126.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I hope you guys have a fantastic retreat.","index":875,"end_time":3129.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3127.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":876,"end_time":3130.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3129.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rest, refresh.","index":877,"end_time":3131.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3130.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Take it, you know, as it comes.","index":878,"end_time":3133.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3132.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys know you.","index":879,"end_time":3135.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3134.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hope you guys have a great rest of your week and great weekend and we''ll see you next week.","index":880,"end_time":3139.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3135.6,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Rachel, I''ll see you tonight.","index":881,"end_time":3140.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3139.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":882,"end_time":3141.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3140.8,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"See you in a few hours.","index":883,"end_time":3142.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3141.24,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Bye, everybody.","index":884,"end_time":3143.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3142.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":885,"end_time":3144.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3143.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"}],"dateString":"2025-11-12T19:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85039954260?pwd=7GrXTMosQASbwQapyiVncGn3aAbQCz.1","participants":["nancie@noeticconsultants.com,colin.costi