INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards',
  '## **Podcast Strategy and Guest Management**

The team is expanding the podcast guest roster and refining episode planning to align with strategic content gaps and audience needs.

- **Julia Wetta is joining the team starting next week**, replacing Tracy who left Noetic, enhancing capacity for podcast production and outreach (09:04)  
    - Julia’s addition aims to accelerate episode development and help meet upcoming production goals.  
    - Nancy emphasized the importance of coordinating scheduling with guests like Sam, who has upcoming PTO, to ensure timely recordings.  
    - Rachel and Nancy plan to focus on episodes around AI integration and training, which are currently underrepresented topics.  
    - December is targeted for recording internal episodes, leveraging quieter client periods to deepen internal content.  

- **Key recent guest commitments include a verbal yes from Kristen O’Boyle, CMO of CVS Health, with a TBD recording date** (32:56)  
    - Other confirmed recordings include Patrick rescheduled for November 18 and Kate completed recently.  
    - This guest lineup supports building thought leadership across major industry players, enhancing Noetic’s market credibility.  
    - Coordinating episode topics to fill gaps such as “people problems” and training will strengthen the podcast’s relevance.  

- The team is considering **personalized guide materials to accompany podcast invitations**, improving engagement and encouraging deeper connections with guests (11:18)  
    - Rachel suggested adding a custom page signed by the podcast team to make outreach less generic and more inviting.  
    - Nancy highlighted the need to optimize this communication as a door opener, especially for guests unfamiliar with Noetic.  
    - Colin proposed testing short introductions at the front and more detailed info at the back of guides to balance depth and readability.  
    - This approach aims to increase guest responsiveness and potential follow-up conversations, boosting business development opportunities.  

## **Lead Management and Qualification via Pipedrive**

The team is refining lead scoring and qualification workflows in Pipedrive to improve sales follow-up efficiency and data accuracy.

- **LinkedIn lead gen forms are being integrated into Pipedrive with updated scoring thresholds to filter out unqualified leads** (20:46)  
    - Nancy raised concerns about spam and low-quality leads, emphasizing the need for a points-based system to prioritize serious prospects.  
    - Colin explained the recent connection between LinkedIn forms and Pipedrive was to provide faster visibility but lacked scoring for form submissions initially.  
    - The team agreed to update the scoring model to incorporate LinkedIn lead gen form fills and send the revised system for Nancy’s approval.  
    - This update will reduce administrative overhead and improve targeting by ensuring only leads meeting defined engagement levels enter the pipeline.  

- **Ongoing lead data cleanup includes removing former employees like Tracy from invite lists and verifying anomalies for contacts like Dan Baum and Jacinta Dariotis** (08:55)  
    - Nancy and Colin are collaborating to confirm lead authenticity, especially when LinkedIn profiles are missing or leads appear inactive.  
    - The team is focused on maintaining a clean and actionable leads database to maximize sales productivity and maintain trust in the system.  
    - Timely filtering and accurate notes on lead activity (downloads, podcast engagement) will help personalize outreach and avoid redundancy.  

- The team is **rotating advertising budget toward first-year CMOs based on enrichment data showing potential for higher engagement** (18:11)  
    - Colin identified over **2,000 first-year CMOs** enriched through Clay, aiming for an **80%+ LinkedIn match rate** to target ads effectively.  
    - Nancy noted previous CMO Playbook ads underperformed, likely due to timing, indicating the need for more volume and better targeting.  
    - The budget shift aims to increase qualified lead flow by focusing on recently promoted decision-makers who are more likely to seek new strategies.  
    - This refined targeting supports higher ROI on marketing spend by engaging prospects with urgent and relevant needs.  

## **Content Strategy and SEO Optimization**

The team is evolving its content approach to balance thought leadership with SEO-driven tactics to increase site traffic and user engagement.

- **Current blog content focuses primarily on thought leadership but will include SEO elements to boost visibility and attract more visitors** (40:11)  
    - Colin proposed sprinkling SEO keywords naturally into thought leadership posts to maintain quality while improving search rankings.  
    - He offered to recommend keywords and starter copy for the insights page to increase traction, which currently lags behind the homepage and Playbooks pages.  
    - Rachel and Nancy agreed to test this blended approach to ensure content remains valuable and discoverable.  
    - This change is expected to drive more organic traffic, particularly to underutilized sections like insights, enhancing lead generation potential.  

- **Website analytics show a dip in total visitors but an increase in engagement, with users spending nearly five minutes on site and viewing over two pages** (39:41)  
    - Despite fewer visits week-over-week, user engagement metrics exceed industry averages by about **15%**, indicating high content relevance.  
    - This suggests that while volume fluctuates, the audience that visits is more invested, a promising sign for deeper funnel activities.  
    - The team plans to build on this engagement by adding targeted content and SEO improvements to attract more qualified visitors.  

## **AI Program Development and Marketing Integration**

Noetic is preparing a new AI-focused program to help marketers integrate AI into their workflows, positioning itself as an innovator in the space.

- **An AI program aimed at helping marketers infuse AI into processes is being developed, with marketing to start before full build-out** (41:58)  
    - Nancy plans to present this initiative at the upcoming off-site, framing it as a solution to a widespread but underserved problem.  
    - Colin recommended launching a podcast episode on AI pain points and strategic approaches, even before the product is live, to build awareness and thought leadership.  
    - Supporting content like blogs and LinkedIn posts will deepen the narrative, creating a holistic marketing push around Noetic’s AI philosophy.  
    - This phased approach aims to generate interest and early leads, enabling funding or client buy-in to accelerate product development.  

- **Content format will balance direct, to-the-point AI discussions with conversational training-focused episodes to appeal to different audience segments** (50:08)  
    - Nancy plans to prepare foundational content ("ball of clay") for Colin’s team to shape into guides and episodes.  
    - The training episode is expected to be more discussion-based, exploring skills marketers need amidst fast-changing landscapes.  
    - The AI episode will focus on outlining the problem and Noetic’s approach without relying on case studies not yet available.  
    - This diversity in format intends to engage broader audiences while building credibility in emerging marketing challenges.  

## **Business Development and Client Engagement Updates**

The team is actively pursuing new enterprise clients and nurturing existing relationships to expand Noetic’s market footprint.

- **Positive progress with enterprise prospects includes booked meetings with Waymo and outreach efforts to Marriott, despite some access challenges** (34:42)  
    - Nancy mailed books to Marriott leadership and is pursuing LinkedIn direct messages after email bounces limited direct contact.  
    - Waymo meetings are booked with Linda Chen and her supervisor, expected to occur within the next two weeks, signaling strong pipeline momentum.  
    - Linda indicated Waymo’s aggressive expansion into **30 markets from 3**, implying a large potential contract with significant budget capacity.  
    - This opportunity represents a fast-moving client that could substantially increase Noetic’s revenue and market presence if onboarded successfully.  

- **Nancy is increasing strategic outreach to existing clients for introductions, securing five CMO leads via Marissa Jarrett, CEO of 7-Eleven** (15:40)  
    - Leveraging existing relationships is positioned as a scalable way to expand guest and lead pools efficiently.  
    - The team is actively interviewing for a Business Development Director to address current capacity constraints, highlighting growth ambitions.  
    - This approach aims to systematically improve pipeline quality and volume by tapping trusted networks rather than cold outreach alone.  

- **Internal episode planning and asset management improvements are underway to streamline content access and enhance team efficiency** (27:57)  
    - Rachel requested editing access to main drive folders to better organize episode assets by guest name and improve navigation speed.  
    - The team is cleaning up episode lists to remove non-existent recordings and planning to add internal episode recordings during December’s quieter period.  
    - These changes reduce friction in content production workflows, enabling faster turnaround and higher-quality publishing.  
    - Improved asset management supports scalability as the podcast and content programs expand.',
  '2025-11-12 19:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Remove Tracy from meeting invites and add Julia Wetta as new team member (00:08)","completed":false},{"text":"Update Pipedrive lead scoring to include LinkedIn lead gen forms and adjust filters to exclude non-qualifying leads (00:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Rotate more budget to first-year CMO-focused LinkedIn infographic ads and reduce less performing Playbook campaign budget (00:19)","completed":false},{"text":"Grant Rachel Curtis editing access to the main podcast shared drive for better organization and renaming by guest name (00:28)","completed":false},{"text":"Verify and finalize podcast asset delivery especially for Christine Calvin episode and continue managing recording scheduling (00:51)","completed":false},{"text":"Send over updated quick card quotes aligning with promotional materials for Noetic (00:51)","completed":false},{"text":"Add Julia to meeting invitations replacing Tracy (00:51)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide Colin with content input and framework for upcoming AI program and training podcast episodes (00:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue business development outreach efforts, especially with Marriott and Waymo contacts, and inform on progress (00:34)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and manage Pipedrive lead quality and qualification closely, ensuring filtering is effective and provide feedback on adjustments (00:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate internally on planning for December internal podcast episodes focused on people-related topics and training (00:29)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Sam for podcast guest scheduling and possible internal episode inclusion (00:29)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and discuss enhanced podcast guest guides and pre-episode personal outreach for better engagement (00:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up internally on upcoming podcast asset status and preparations (00:51)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
