-- Meeting: Syncro // New North Bi-Weekly Meeting (2025-11-12 19:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '18194a27-f4fd-4f8a-b974-7e8dcaea1d46',
    '2025-11-12 19:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9ASPHK0AS47Q81N7HBA6KMX',
    'Syncro // New North Bi-Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Baylee Gunnell","Brandon Garcin","Igor Zagradjanin"}'::text[],
    1519,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86432186576?pwd=XxjYEV59FLfPJ9LkkJUeTlFTe1JCaL.1',
    '{"id":"01K9ASPHK0AS47Q81N7HBA6KMX","title":"Syncro // New North Bi-Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Guest Booking and Pipeline Management**\n\nThe guest booking pipeline is stable and well-aligned with evolving content strategy needs for early next year.\n\n- **Brandon Garcin reported having about five 15-minute intro calls and two guests scheduled for recording this Friday** (06:07)  \n    - He highlighted success reengaging lukewarm contacts from past outreach, turning some into confirmed guests.  \n    - Brandon prefers maintaining a pipeline of three to five guests to avoid overload during upcoming holidays and potential show format changes.  \n    - This measured approach supports flexibility for tweaking the podcast direction in 2024 without overcommitting resources.  \n    - The controlled pipeline size balances steady content flow with bandwidth constraints and seasonal audience availability.\n\n- **Igor Zagradjanin presented a researched list of 10 Microsoft-focused expert guests, blending media experts and technical practitioners** (06:55)  \n    - Brandon endorsed the targeted, narrower approach over prior broad outreach, seeing better topic alignment and audience fit.  \n    - Targeted campaigns are expected to yield higher engagement despite requiring more upfront research and personalization.  \n    - Brandon is open to making this Microsoft-focused pipeline a core ongoing strategy, possibly expanding beyond Microsoft later.  \n    - This shift aims to improve guest relevance and podcast resonance with strategic audience segments.\n\n## **Video Content Production and Social Clips Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to produce simple, quick-turnaround social video clips prioritizing volume and ease over high production values.\n\n- **Brandon emphasized a low-effort “point and shoot” video style for social clips, avoiding heavy creative lifts given current bandwidth limits** (10:13)  \n    - He stressed that minimal editing with bumpers, title cards, and on-screen text overlays would suffice to enhance engagement.  \n    - Brandon offered to provide a corporate font kit (Fig Tree) to maintain brand consistency with easy asset integration.  \n    - He prefers using native phone or high-quality camera recordings over platform-based capture for better video quality.  \n    - This approach supports quick content velocity and SEO benefits without taxing internal resources.\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell confirmed producing “quick and dirty” edits and will provide Brandon with an upload folder for raw footage** (16:22)  \n    - The team plans to start with one clip as a proof of concept, then expand if results meet expectations.  \n    - Clips will be formatted for both vertical portrait (YouTube Shorts/social) and blog embedding to reach distinct audiences.  \n    - Brandon advised framing shots to allow trimming for portrait without loss of quality or context.  \n    - This dual-format strategy aims to maximize SEO impact and social reach simultaneously.\n\n## **Podcast Platform and Publishing Updates**\n\nKey administrative and technical updates were addressed to ensure smooth podcast publishing continuity and improved listener experience.\n\n- **Brandon flagged Apple’s updated Terms and Conditions requiring acceptance to continue podcast publishing** (20:36)  \n    - The changes include improved chapter support allowing timed links for easier episode navigation.  \n    - Brandon will check credentials and accept the new TNCs, confirming that he originally set up the Apple listing.  \n    - This update is expected to enhance user experience without significant operational impact.  \n    - Baylee will monitor for any related issues and assist as needed.\n\n- **Baylee confirmed recent podcast recordings were added and noted two guests queued for recording this Friday** (20:16)  \n    - The client portal is being updated with new outreach and social clip assets to streamline workflows.  \n    - The team is tracking resource points and currently remains within budget constraints.  \n    - This infrastructure supports ongoing content delivery and outreach scaling.\n\n## **Meeting Automation and Workflow Improvements**\n\nThere is a need to troubleshoot and restore meeting transcription and summary automation to improve post-call productivity.\n\n- **Brandon reported that Fireflies joins his scheduled Zoom meetings via SavvyCal but does not produce meeting notes or summaries** (22:37)  \n    - He suspects a configuration issue or disconnection since setup was about a year ago.  \n    - Brandon values automated recaps due to his busy schedule and frequent back-to-back calls causing memory gaps.  \n    - Baylee agreed to investigate and possibly reset the integration, noting that starting fresh might be simpler than repairing.  \n    - Restoring this tool would reduce manual note-taking and improve meeting follow-up efficiency.\n\n## **Long-Term Content and Brand Strategy Vision**\n\nThe team is positioning content efforts to support SEO growth and audience engagement through multi-format, branded assets.\n\n- **Brandon emphasized embedding short videos in blog posts to boost SEO and complement written content** (13:14)  \n    - He noted recent Google and AI search trends favor video content alongside community signals for ranking.  \n    - The Synchro brand’s unique AI-generated visuals pose challenges but also offer strong differentiation if leveraged correctly.  \n    - Current focus is on simple, scalable content production before potentially investing in richer creative assets next year.  \n    - This phased approach balances innovation with resource realities and audience expectations.\n\n- **Brandon highlighted the challenge of maintaining high-quality brand visuals due to use of AI tools like Midjourney and Sora** (13:14)  \n    - He wants to avoid large upfront investments in image libraries until there is clearer ROI and bandwidth.  \n    - The team will continue experimenting with brand-aligned fonts and simple overlays to maintain consistency.  \n    - This cautious brand evolution supports flexibility and cost control while testing new content formats.  \n    - The strategy reflects a pragmatic balance between originality and operational feasibility.","outline":null,"keywords":["podcast guest booking","Microsoft expert outreach","social media clips","video production","Apple podcast TNC","meeting transcription"],"overview":"- **Guest Booking Pipeline:** Five intro calls done; two guests confirmed for recording. Stable pipeline aligns with content strategy for next year.  \n- **Microsoft Expert Guests:** List of 10 targeted guests chosen for relevance and better audience fit. Core strategy might expand beyond Microsoft.  \n- **Video Content Production:** Quick, low-effort video style emphasized; minimal editing to enhance engagement, with brand consistency maintained using corporate assets.  \n- **Podcast Platform Updates:** Apple’s new Terms require acceptance for publishing; improved chapter support enhances listener experience, no major operational impact expected.  \n- **Meeting Automation Troubleshooting:** Meeting notes automation not functioning; integration reset may improve efficiency, important for busy schedules.  \n- **Long-Term Content Strategy:** Focus on embedding videos in blogs to improve SEO; testing simple content first before richer investments next year.","action_items":"\n**Brandon Garcin**\nReview and accept updated Apple podcast TNCs to continue publishing (20:36)\nRecord first social media video clip using preferred phone or camera setup and upload to agreed folder (15:21)\nSend example low-effort video to team for reference (16:55)\nMonitor upcoming podcast recordings scheduled for Friday and deliver approved files (20:26)\nForward Apple email to Baylee for reference (21:42)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nProvide Brandon with upload folder/access for social media video clips (16:22)\nFinalize and deliver messaging sequence for guest outreach by the next day (10:02)\nInvestigate and resolve Fireflies transcription issue or reset integration (22:37)\nContinue development of client portal outreach module and social clip production (21:55)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nPrioritize Microsoft expert guest list outreach according to Brandon’s feedback (06:49)\nParticipate in social media clips planning and production workflow (10:17)\n"},"duration":25.31999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"id":2,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Doing Thanksgiving.","index":0,"end_time":1.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1,"end_time":2.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.24,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Starbucks is like immediately switched to their, you know, now we''ll, we''ll do a little bit.","index":2,"end_time":10.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.88,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We actually, we usually do a big friendsgiving at our house because we have no family where we live.","index":3,"end_time":17.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.44,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"They''re all back on the east coast.","index":4,"end_time":18.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.56,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But we''re not doing it this year.","index":5,"end_time":22.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":21.04,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We just have too much going on and, and not enough time or money to host a big party.","index":6,"end_time":27.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.28,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"To be very honest.","index":7,"end_time":28.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.61,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We don''t do a ton for Christmas.","index":8,"end_time":32.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.41,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''re going to be in Florida for the winter holidays this year with my in laws, which will be nice.","index":9,"end_time":38.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.13,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But no, it''s, we don''t do a ton.","index":10,"end_time":40.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.49,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s, it''s kind of fun and atypical here because you know, there''s no snow or anything like that.","index":11,"end_time":45.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.89,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So they have like shows, there''s like, like a surfing Santa meetup and there''s literally like a bunch of people like in Santa Su, like, you know, oh.","index":12,"end_time":58.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.01,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"My goodness, like ocean.","index":13,"end_time":60.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":61.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yes.","index":15,"end_time":61.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s freezing.","index":16,"end_time":62.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":17,"end_time":63.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.08,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":64.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, it''s warm enough here.","index":19,"end_time":65.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I mean it''s like probably 75 today and nice and toasty.","index":20,"end_time":69.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.64,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Man.","index":21,"end_time":71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"San Diego.","index":22,"end_time":71.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":73.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I mean it''s, you know, I, I''m, I''m, it''s like the, the constant dichotomy of like it''s, I think the best place to live depending on what you care about.","index":24,"end_time":81.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.12,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But also I''m like, can never afford anything and I''m just constantly drowning in debt and not having enough money for things.","index":25,"end_time":87.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But right about this time of year it starts to feel more worth it where it''s dropping to, you know, 20, 30, 40 degrees and all the places that I''m, I''m used to.","index":26,"end_time":96.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.12,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The other thing that they do here that''s fun is there''s a couple of like tree lighting, you know, ceremonies and festivals and stuff and they, they kind of rain down like fake snow on you.","index":27,"end_time":106.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.23,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, when you go, oh my goodness, it''s kind of cute, you get a little like, you know, a little bit of the winter wonderland.","index":28,"end_time":112.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":106.75,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But what people don''t realize the last comment that I''ll make on it because people think, oh you must miss the seasons or whatever.","index":29,"end_time":118.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.11,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like we''re, we''re three hour drive from Big Bear, which is a great, you know, super snowy mountain with a lot of good winter sports and, and you know, skiing, snowboarding, tubing, stuff like that.","index":30,"end_time":126.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, you go a couple hours in another direction, it''s pure desert and you''re kind of out in, you know, Nevada, Arizona area.","index":31,"end_time":132.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":126.79,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I mean I, I, I love living here because where I spend Most of my time is what, to me is the ideal climate.","index":32,"end_time":138.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.23,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But then if I''m like, man, I could really go for some snow right now.","index":33,"end_time":140.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.19,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You just go do it.","index":34,"end_time":141.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":140.79,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And then you get to go home and not be like, digging your car out and all the shit that I don''t miss about, you know, living in New England.","index":35,"end_time":147.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":141.83,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So to me, you get the best of all worlds.","index":36,"end_time":149.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I.","index":37,"end_time":150.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":149.87,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Some people, I guess, prefer to see, I don''t know, leaves change in their backyard or whatever it is.","index":38,"end_time":156.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":150.7,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Right.","index":39,"end_time":156.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.1,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t miss it yet, but we''ll see.","index":40,"end_time":157.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t know, Brandon, you''re.","index":41,"end_time":160.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''re making me feel less good about all the seasons changing.","index":42,"end_time":164.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''re right.","index":43,"end_time":165.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You can just drive somewhere, ask me.","index":44,"end_time":168.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"About it today that the mortgage is due, and you''ll get my.","index":45,"end_time":171.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.38,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"My other perspective on it.","index":46,"end_time":173.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.82,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Where can we move where it''s warm and not California?","index":47,"end_time":180.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that is the million dollar question, I think.","index":48,"end_time":184.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":180.69,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Anywho.","index":49,"end_time":187.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":186.53,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":50,"end_time":189.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, I want to introduce you to Igor.","index":51,"end_time":192.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m not going anywhere.","index":52,"end_time":195.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know sometimes you bring new faces.","index":53,"end_time":197.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"For a second.","index":54,"end_time":198.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.81,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But, like, I''m your account director here, so it''s always just good to pull other people to support because we got a lot of stuff going on and I want to make sure you get the best possible service.","index":55,"end_time":215.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And Igor has been helping behind the scenes for a while.","index":56,"end_time":218.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"He''s been working on your podcast.","index":57,"end_time":220.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"He''s actually been working on a lot of this Microsoft stuff.","index":58,"end_time":223.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''ll just get into that.","index":59,"end_time":226.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":60,"end_time":228.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.71,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":61,"end_time":228.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.27,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It sounds like you''re not based in the US from what I heard on my way.","index":62,"end_time":232.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.47,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And where in the world are you?","index":63,"end_time":233.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.11,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, Europe.","index":64,"end_time":234.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Nice.","index":65,"end_time":235.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Where about?","index":66,"end_time":235.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.4,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, the Balkan region.","index":67,"end_time":238.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":235.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Serbia.","index":68,"end_time":239.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.84,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":69,"end_time":240.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":239.72,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Maybe you''ve heard of it.","index":70,"end_time":241.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.08,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, never been, but I''m certainly familiar.","index":71,"end_time":244.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.04,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":72,"end_time":244.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.28,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":73,"end_time":245.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.84,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, nice to meet you too.","index":74,"end_time":246.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":245.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I see some nice guitars in the background.","index":75,"end_time":248.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Is that a Strat and telly?","index":76,"end_time":251.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It sure is.","index":77,"end_time":252.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":251.64,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":78,"end_time":253,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.52,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Well, well identified, even with the blur and the.","index":79,"end_time":255.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.08,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The acoustic in the middle is a Martin that I''ve had for, I don''t know, probably about 20 years at this point.","index":80,"end_time":261.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.8,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But when I''m not tied up doing everything we''re talking about, this is what I try to use this room for.","index":81,"end_time":266.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.4,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Nice, man.","index":82,"end_time":267.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.28,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, I also make music, like, I produce and stuff, so.","index":83,"end_time":271,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":84,"end_time":271.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":85,"end_time":272.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.68,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Swap links or something later.","index":86,"end_time":274,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.64,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":87,"end_time":275.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":274.4,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Definitely.","index":88,"end_time":276.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":275.6,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Nice to meet you, man.","index":89,"end_time":278.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.04,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Likewise.","index":90,"end_time":279.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":278.56,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, we will get into it.","index":91,"end_time":282.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll go over your guest booking updates, chat through the next steps for your social media clips, your podcasts, and the client portal.","index":92,"end_time":293.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":93,"end_time":294.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.47,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":295.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.43,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Guestbook is a pretty good.","index":95,"end_time":296.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.79,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"At least from my end.","index":96,"end_time":298.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.03,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''ve had a couple good responses.","index":97,"end_time":301.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.63,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"My favorite are people just reply on LinkedIn, like, no, like, no, thanks.","index":98,"end_time":305.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":99,"end_time":306.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.149,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I guess they assume that that will, like, close the valve, which I suppose it does because then we stop spamming them.","index":100,"end_time":313.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I just usually don''t even respond if I get spam that I''m not interested in.","index":101,"end_time":317.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.27,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But we''ve had a couple of good ones and I''ve also had two or three folks that, that I remembered sort of half booking with way back when, and then I never followed through.","index":102,"end_time":328.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.83,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And they''ve since come back and I''m recording someone, and I have someone scheduled to record this Friday that I had totally forgotten because life.","index":103,"end_time":336.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.01,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But yeah, we spent like a lot of time talking over email like a year ago and like they just then ghosted and never, you know, went forward with actually setting an appointment.","index":104,"end_time":345.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.09,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And now we have, and it was good.","index":105,"end_time":347.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.09,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And he''s going to record.","index":106,"end_time":348.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.73,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I think we''ve done a nice job of, you know, reawakening.","index":107,"end_time":353.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.97,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":108,"end_time":354.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Some of these sort of lukewarm connections that just never actually, you know, made it over the line.","index":109,"end_time":359.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":354.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So that''s good.","index":110,"end_time":360.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.67,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, good.","index":111,"end_time":361.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How are you feeling about the pipeline?","index":112,"end_time":363.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Has it been a good amount?","index":113,"end_time":365.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Not too much.","index":114,"end_time":366.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, not too much to handle.","index":115,"end_time":368.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.11,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think I''ve had maybe four or five, you know, 15 minute intros.","index":116,"end_time":373.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.91,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''ve got two people scheduled for this Friday to record and I have two others that are kind of in pipe.","index":117,"end_time":382.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I think that''s pretty good, especially because we''re still having this larger ongoing conversation about like, you know, the future of the show and what we want to do or evolve or shift heading into next year.","index":118,"end_time":394.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I don''t necessarily want to line up 10 guests in the current format if we''re going to maybe shake things up a little bit.","index":119,"end_time":400.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I think having three to five folks in the hoppers probably the.","index":120,"end_time":404.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The sweet spot for right now, which is good.","index":121,"end_time":406.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.72,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That brings us to our next thing.","index":122,"end_time":409.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I''ll.","index":123,"end_time":409.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''ll let Igor take it from here with our Microsoft audience.","index":124,"end_time":414.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":125,"end_time":416.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So basically, as you could see, the list, if I''m.","index":126,"end_time":420.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"If I''m correct, you saw the.","index":127,"end_time":422.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The list of 10 people.","index":128,"end_time":424.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yes, 10 experts.","index":129,"end_time":426.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":424.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":130,"end_time":426.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So I did some research, basically going through the conferences and events happening this year, also searched through some author articles on these topics, some YouTube podcasts, and then finally found some LinkedIn profiles of these people.","index":131,"end_time":446.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.68,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So I''m interested, like, what do you think about them?","index":132,"end_time":452.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":448.37,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Do you have any Thoughts.","index":133,"end_time":453.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.29,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And I thought everybody looked good.","index":134,"end_time":455.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.33,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t, I don''t have it up in front of me.","index":135,"end_time":458.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":456.21,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I see it''s linked here, but if I recall it felt like a good blend of kind of job titles and, and you know, descriptions and backgrounds.","index":136,"end_time":465.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.33,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":137,"end_time":466.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.87,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I liked that we had.","index":138,"end_time":469.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.87,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, I like that we have like a sort of blend of kind of some media, like author, you know, expert type folks, but also some folks that were clearly more technical, nerdy, you know, hands on keyboard with some of this stuff.","index":139,"end_time":482.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.71,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I think it''s good.","index":140,"end_time":484.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.43,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m interested to see if, you know, there''s obviously a lot more work that goes into this, so I''m curious if we can get some bites and I would potentially be interested, if this goes well, to consider this more of a moving forward approach.","index":141,"end_time":500.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":485.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Something that''s a bit narrower.","index":142,"end_time":503.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.7,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It doesn''t have to be all Microsoft all the time necessarily, but the general idea of being a little bit narrower, a little bit more targeted, a little more perhaps rifle than shotgun, which we''ve done more of the last couple of quarters, so we''ll see.","index":143,"end_time":518.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.22,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But this looks good and I think pretty well aligned with a lot of topics that are important to synchronize right now, which is great.","index":144,"end_time":523.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.18,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":145,"end_time":524.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":146,"end_time":525,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":147,"end_time":525.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Nice.","index":148,"end_time":526.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"General.","index":149,"end_time":527.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":150,"end_time":528.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":527.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, generally, yeah, these targeted campaigns are maybe take a bit more time to do the research and stuff, but in general they should like give better results because they''re personalized and yeah, people sometimes can actually see some things like mass.","index":151,"end_time":545.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Mass outreach.","index":152,"end_time":546.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":545.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":153,"end_time":548.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.96,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":549.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.04,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m as jaded as anyone because 98% of my inbox is filled with shitty versions of what we are trying to do.","index":155,"end_time":556,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.28,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I totally agree.","index":156,"end_time":557.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"With.","index":157,"end_time":561.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know you said you feel like you''re at a healthy balance right now with guest booking.","index":158,"end_time":565.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you still want to launch this?","index":159,"end_time":567.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we can.","index":160,"end_time":568.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I would sort of take this and potentially prioritize some of these folks over some of the others that are in pipeline.","index":161,"end_time":574.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.28,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"If we happen to create the problem of having so much interest that I need to do that, I''ll deal with that.","index":162,"end_time":580.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.92,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":163,"end_time":580.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.16,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And again, if we''re recording content and sort of planning to do a publishing push early next year, like we''re getting into that weird limbo anyway where I think people are going to start taking time off and being less available and we probably won''t publish as aggressively.","index":164,"end_time":596.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.16,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I think it''s all right to stack the deck a little bit and we''ll see what happens.","index":165,"end_time":602.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.36,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds great.","index":166,"end_time":603.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we are just wrapping up the final details of your messaging sequence that should be ready tomorrow.","index":167,"end_time":609.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":168,"end_time":610.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.26,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, then.","index":169,"end_time":614.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you want to chat through these clips, Igor?","index":170,"end_time":616.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":171,"end_time":618.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":617.54,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So these are.","index":172,"end_time":618.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I think you saw these two, right?","index":173,"end_time":621.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yes, I did.","index":174,"end_time":622.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.82,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Take a quick look.","index":175,"end_time":623.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":622.62,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The.","index":176,"end_time":623.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.34,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The.","index":177,"end_time":623.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.62,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The general.","index":178,"end_time":624.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.86,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Thank you for remembering that.","index":179,"end_time":626.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":624.82,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t remember anything.","index":180,"end_time":627.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.54,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I do like these.","index":181,"end_time":630.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.13,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"My questions were more so around, like, how do we bring them to life?","index":182,"end_time":635.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.33,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"What is this sort of, you know, production collaboration.","index":183,"end_time":640.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":637.21,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And maybe to back up for one second, when Bailey and I first started chatting about this, you know, I think the lowest budget version is like talking head point and shoot down the barrel, and we just do a little bit of cleanup and then we publish something.","index":184,"end_time":651.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":640.89,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That to me is like, okay, there''s very little.","index":185,"end_time":653.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.85,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"There''s still some time, but there''s very little creative work involved.","index":186,"end_time":656.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":653.77,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"This feels like it''s maybe a step or two above that, which is, hey, we''ll get some bumpers in there, we''ll get some title cards, we''ll bring some on screen text, some overlays to sort of accent some of the key point.","index":187,"end_time":665.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.89,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m cool with all that.","index":188,"end_time":667.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think the question is, you know, we haven''t done a lot of work in the Synchro brand together.","index":189,"end_time":675.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.39,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We mostly work in the Synchronized brand, which is a solid sort of small derivative of the broader Synchro brand, which is more abstract and.","index":190,"end_time":683.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.43,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And a bit more almost sort of avant garde in the sense.","index":191,"end_time":687.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":683.75,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Right.","index":192,"end_time":688.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.87,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We do a lot of crazy sort of AI generated imagery and things that are designed to look a little bit different.","index":193,"end_time":691.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.03,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t have any concerns around our ability to collaborate on that.","index":194,"end_time":695.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.17,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I just want this to be something that is kind of low hanging fruit and not something that''s going to necessarily require us to invest a lot more in order to, you know, get the value that we want to get out of it.","index":195,"end_time":708.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.97,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Because I just don''t have a ton of bandwidth and time right now to be like spinning up creative assets and, you know, doing a heavy lift of enablement in that regard.","index":196,"end_time":716.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.05,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So that was more my sort of question or what I wanted to chat through with you guys was, do we still feel like this is like low hanging fruit and easy to produce?","index":197,"end_time":725.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":716.13,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Meaning, like, can I just point and shoot in front of the camera, read the script, pass that baton over to you guys, and then it''s like, set it and forget it on my end.","index":198,"end_time":732.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.61,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And if not, then I might ask, let''s work together on it so that we can get to a point where that is the kind of, you know, partnership, at least for the first few.","index":199,"end_time":741.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.97,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":200,"end_time":742.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And Then if we want to invest more heavily and if we want to do something a little bit more creative or a little bit more, you know, visual and design, I''m definitely willing to do that.","index":201,"end_time":750.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.25,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I just don''t want to be the blocker on this.","index":202,"end_time":753.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.79,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I have way too much shit right now to be getting into a more creative exercise with you guys around it to just be very sort of candid about, you know, what''s on my plate.","index":203,"end_time":763.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.91,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"No, I think that makes a lot of sense when it, when it comes to your branding.","index":204,"end_time":768.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":764.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We haven''t done a ton of work in, in your overall brand yet.","index":205,"end_time":772.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think we could probably find like you mentioned, like our low hanging fruit.","index":206,"end_time":778.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We could either just go really simple, cut out pauses, things like that, maybe include captions for those.","index":207,"end_time":785.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I would say like the next step up from that would be to add like these, maybe a couple of these, like on screen text just.","index":208,"end_time":794.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I could certainly give you like a font kit.","index":209,"end_time":796.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":794.32,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So that''s like, you know, some of this is that that''s not a terribly large exercise.","index":210,"end_time":800.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We use Fig Tree as our primary corporate font, so I could easily provide that.","index":211,"end_time":804.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, things like that are easy, but we run into this issue all the time with vendors when it comes to imagery and motion graphics and stuff because most of what we''re doing is in mid journey and you know, Sora and some of these other tools now.","index":212,"end_time":814.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.31,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So again, it''s, it''s not, you know, it''s.","index":213,"end_time":818.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":814.23,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We''ve created that problem by doing something very sort of unique and original to Synchro.","index":214,"end_time":822.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.55,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So this is far from the first time that I''ve run into it.","index":215,"end_time":825.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.11,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I don''t want to sign us up to like render, you know, 50 images that we can use as a library.","index":216,"end_time":831.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.63,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like maybe next year we can get into that.","index":217,"end_time":833,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.12,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":218,"end_time":835.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I like, I like where we''re headed here.","index":219,"end_time":838.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":836.04,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And again, just to sort of reinforce the original driver behind this, you know, we blog a lot about these topics, we publish content and other mediums around these topics.","index":220,"end_time":848.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I like having short, crispy videos we can push out on social.","index":221,"end_time":850.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":848.12,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I like the idea of being able to embed this content within the articles, which seems to be helping a lot more with search lately.","index":222,"end_time":856.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.92,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"As Google and AI Search know re favors video alongside like Community and Reddit and some other platforms that are showing up far more heavily than they were, you know, six 12 months ago.","index":223,"end_time":866.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.56,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I think there''s some good sort of proof of concept here.","index":224,"end_time":869.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":866.58,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But let''s just make it like, you know, quick and dirty and kind of Low budget, so that it could be more about, like, volume and velocity rather than, you know, some beautiful, highly produced, you know, Hollywood version.","index":225,"end_time":881.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.7,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Right.","index":226,"end_time":881.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.22,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, you got it.","index":227,"end_time":883.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll do some quick dirty edits.","index":228,"end_time":885.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":229,"end_time":885.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":885.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And pick.","index":230,"end_time":886.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.32,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"When we do that.","index":231,"end_time":887.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.96,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":232,"end_time":888.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.8,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Let''s pick.","index":233,"end_time":888.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.24,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"If you guys have a recommendation, I can also take a look through of, like, let''s start with this one.","index":234,"end_time":894.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You know, this one we feel would be the strongest or the best.","index":235,"end_time":896.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.12,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I''ll just take, you know, five minutes out of my day at some point, maybe next week, and I''ll just crank out, you know, a recording.","index":236,"end_time":906.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.52,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"What''s the best way, now that I''m thinking about it a little bit, to sort of traffic that over to you guys?","index":237,"end_time":910.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.32,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Because this is not like.","index":238,"end_time":912.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.96,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"This is outside of like podcast request form, you know, type submission.","index":239,"end_time":916.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.32,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, should I just shoot you a drive link to a video?","index":240,"end_time":919.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.72,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, what''s.","index":241,"end_time":920.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"What''s easiest?","index":242,"end_time":921.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":920.2,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, either you can.","index":243,"end_time":923.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You could still record on Riverside.","index":244,"end_time":925.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":245,"end_time":926.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.36,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Should I do that?","index":246,"end_time":927.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.96,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Because I could get much higher quality with my native hardware than through that.","index":247,"end_time":932.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":927.64,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I just record with whatever is going to get you the best quality.","index":248,"end_time":936.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, I know you have some fancy camera stuff.","index":249,"end_time":938.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is the best camera I have.","index":250,"end_time":940.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.96,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":251,"end_time":940.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":940.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Honestly, I mean, I''ve got my external, I''ve got Riverside, but I''ve done it for some, you know, personal projects and like, shooting cinematic in 4K on this looks better than anything attached to my computer.","index":252,"end_time":951.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.92,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I can just do that.","index":253,"end_time":952.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":951.44,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":254,"end_time":953.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, Riverside, if that''s easiest.","index":255,"end_time":955.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or if you want to record just right on your phone, set it up on a wall or something.","index":256,"end_time":959.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And you don''t mind, you don''t have a problem with, you know, chunky file size.","index":257,"end_time":963.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":959.24,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Right?","index":258,"end_time":963.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.24,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Because that''ll be, you know, if I do five minutes at 4K, we''ll be looking at, you know, several gigs worth.","index":259,"end_time":968.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.44,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I like the, the, you know, the quality that we get.","index":260,"end_time":973.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.84,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, we know it''s never.","index":261,"end_time":975.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s never actually 4k by the time it all is said and done, but it does look much better.","index":262,"end_time":979.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.04,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":263,"end_time":980.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"If you''ve got a folder that would be best to.","index":264,"end_time":982.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll get you one to upload.","index":265,"end_time":983.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It, to pop into it.","index":266,"end_time":984.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.88,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"We can do that.","index":267,"end_time":985.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":984.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":268,"end_time":988.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":988,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, this was.","index":269,"end_time":991.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":990.4,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''ll send you guys just for fun.","index":270,"end_time":993.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"1.","index":271,"end_time":993.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":993.12,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"One example of where I have tested this for work.","index":272,"end_time":998.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":993.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"This is not a terribly good video because it was more just an experiment, but there''s a video embedded in that article that I just dropped in chat that I shot on my phone.","index":273,"end_time":1006.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.25,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And again, it''s not a great video.","index":274,"end_time":1008.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.21,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Just in terms of capture quality, it looks much sharper than, you know, anything that I''ve done through my laptop or Logitech or whatever.","index":275,"end_time":1018.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1010.09,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So do you record the podcast just through your laptop, like, computer or.","index":276,"end_time":1026.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I have.","index":277,"end_time":1027.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.93,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Which is the camera that I''m on right now.","index":278,"end_time":1029.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1027.81,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s a little, you know, Logitech brio that I use for the podcast, which advertises at 4k, but I don''t think it actually captures better than 1080 most of the time.","index":279,"end_time":1039.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.33,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":280,"end_time":1040.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1039.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then this one that you sent us the video of, what did you.","index":281,"end_time":1043.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s my phone.","index":282,"end_time":1044.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.65,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":283,"end_time":1045.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1044.53,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s my iPhone.","index":284,"end_time":1046.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1045.17,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":285,"end_time":1046.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1046.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That looks very nice.","index":286,"end_time":1048.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1046.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And that''s no post production or anything.","index":287,"end_time":1052.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1050.54,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s literally, you know, point, shoot, upload.","index":288,"end_time":1053.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1052.06,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Because that was like somebody asked me to just do that as a fun little test.","index":289,"end_time":1057.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.74,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And it worked for a little bit.","index":290,"end_time":1058.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.26,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That video put that article on page one of Google for, I don''t know, a couple of months for like best MSP tools or some very broad keyword that we were trying to attack.","index":291,"end_time":1066.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.42,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So the problem is we lose those footholds as quickly as we gain them because all these content pieces are just getting recrawled and re indexed like every four seconds.","index":292,"end_time":1075.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1066.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Now that AI is kind of dictating a lot of search results, but in any case, yeah, phones are.","index":293,"end_time":1082.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1075.62,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I mean, I''ve got DSLR cameras all over the place and for this purpose anyway, for like being a foot away, whatever.","index":294,"end_time":1088.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.61,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m.","index":295,"end_time":1089.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1088.61,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m not gonna say that my phone is better than my Nikon for real photography, but for this, the phone, is it best?","index":296,"end_time":1095.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.01,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"For sure.","index":297,"end_time":1095.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1095.25,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Are you wanting these to be like our vertical YouTube shorts or do you want us to do something like embeddable for the blog?","index":298,"end_time":1104.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1096.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it might be worth trying both.","index":299,"end_time":1108.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":300,"end_time":1110.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you''re in 4K and you''re just far enough away, then I''ll try to.","index":301,"end_time":1114.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Frame it so that we can trim for a portrait without making it horrible.","index":302,"end_time":1117.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.15,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":303,"end_time":1118.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1118.03,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I can try to frame it as such.","index":304,"end_time":1120.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1118.55,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Or we can put some synchro bumpers or something if we need to.","index":305,"end_time":1122.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.27,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"They just serve different purposes.","index":306,"end_time":1124.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1123.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like we get people, we get a different audience on YouTube with the shorts, our social audience tends to be mostly kind of prospects and folks that are considering being customers.","index":307,"end_time":1132.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1124.51,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And the blog tends to attract slightly more diverse audience of folks.","index":308,"end_time":1138.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.79,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And the blog videos really help with SEO more than anything, I suppose.","index":309,"end_time":1143.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Also though, like, if we embedded a portrait video into a blog, nobody''s going to give a shit.","index":310,"end_time":1146.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1143.24,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I guess it''s nice to have.","index":311,"end_time":1149.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1146.92,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Looks pretty though.","index":312,"end_time":1150.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1149.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it doesn''t look as pretty.","index":313,"end_time":1153.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.68,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s true, but nice to have for both.","index":314,"end_time":1155.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1153.04,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"If we find ourselves being forced to choose, I''d probably go portrait and.","index":315,"end_time":1159.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1155.36,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And then we''ll, you know, deal with it on the blog if we need to.","index":316,"end_time":1162.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.32,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Being in portrait will not negatively impact SEO.","index":317,"end_time":1166.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1164.16,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So.","index":318,"end_time":1167.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.64,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":319,"end_time":1169.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My dog''s got very excited.","index":320,"end_time":1170.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, no worries.","index":321,"end_time":1172.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.6,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Minor rambling around here.","index":322,"end_time":1174.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1172.48,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"All three of our animals were going ape the other night from the big super moon or whatever.","index":323,"end_time":1179.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.4,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":324,"end_time":1179.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.2,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t know if that''s, like, a thing, but everyone''s just howling and scampering around and going crazy, which is really funny.","index":325,"end_time":1186.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.72,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Zoom does a really good job of blocking it out.","index":326,"end_time":1189.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.25,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t know that we would even hear them.","index":327,"end_time":1191.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1190.09,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"My boss the other day was, like, having, like, sighting put on his house, like, four feet away from where we were talking, and we could hear nothing.","index":328,"end_time":1201.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.89,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And he couldn''t believe it.","index":329,"end_time":1202.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.61,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"He was like, guys, there''s, like, literal jackhammering happening, like, around the corner.","index":330,"end_time":1206.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.65,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You guys really aren''t hearing that.","index":331,"end_time":1208.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.65,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So shout out to Zoom, I guess, for getting better at noise cancellation or whatnot.","index":332,"end_time":1212.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1208.05,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":333,"end_time":1213.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1212.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got a few final updates.","index":334,"end_time":1216.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1214.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sure.","index":335,"end_time":1216.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.54,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Just for your podcast, I think we already talked about this, but we got all those recordings added.","index":336,"end_time":1221.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1217.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":337,"end_time":1222.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1221.98,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"A few episodes and then any recordings we should keep an eye out for.","index":338,"end_time":1226.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1222.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Right now, I''ve got two people queued up for this Friday, so I''ll lob at least one, if not both of those, over the fence, assuming they both show up and they go well and all that.","index":339,"end_time":1234.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1226.86,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":340,"end_time":1235.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1235.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I also got a note which I haven''t taken action on yet.","index":341,"end_time":1238.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.06,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Apple changed some.","index":342,"end_time":1241.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.55,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Something relating to their TNCs.","index":343,"end_time":1244.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1241.99,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Have you guys saw that or dealt with that with other clients at all?","index":344,"end_time":1247.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Related to their what?","index":345,"end_time":1248.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let me go find it.","index":346,"end_time":1250.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.91,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Oh, chaptering.","index":347,"end_time":1254.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.03,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That''s what it''s about.","index":348,"end_time":1254.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.07,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I just haven''t dealt with this yet.","index":349,"end_time":1258.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.19,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"They sent it a week ago.","index":350,"end_time":1259.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1258.43,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It actually looks like not a big deal now that I''ve actually taken a moment to read it.","index":351,"end_time":1263.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.99,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Sounds like Apple is improving their podcast experience, making it easier for you to provide chapters throughout episodes, which is kind of nice.","index":352,"end_time":1270.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1264.15,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Like, throughout notes, presumably you can click to jump or anchor link to different sections of the episode.","index":353,"end_time":1275.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.35,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, timed links.","index":354,"end_time":1276.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.69,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"If you choose not to provide chapters, they''ll automatically create them.","index":355,"end_time":1281.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1278.93,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Great.","index":356,"end_time":1282.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1281.81,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s it.","index":357,"end_time":1284.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1283.89,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And as part of that, they''ve updated a bunch of their TNCs that I apparently have to go in and accept to continue publishing podcasts on Apple.","index":358,"end_time":1291.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.89,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So I just couldn''t remember if I had the credentials to Go log into our Apple listing.","index":359,"end_time":1296.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.17,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That was why I wanted to ask you about this item.","index":360,"end_time":1298.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.29,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I couldn''t remember if that was something I set up or if that was something you guys had set up.","index":361,"end_time":1301.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1298.17,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"That should be something you set up.","index":362,"end_time":1303.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1302.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll take a look.","index":363,"end_time":1305.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.8,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":364,"end_time":1307.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1305.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll have to look into that, though.","index":365,"end_time":1308.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1307.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I hadn''t gotten that notification, but I.","index":366,"end_time":1312.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Will forward you the email in case it is at all helpful.","index":367,"end_time":1314.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.04,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''ll be good to know too, then.","index":368,"end_time":1319.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just last look in here at your.","index":369,"end_time":1321.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Your portal.","index":370,"end_time":1324.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1323.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You can see we''re working on getting that new outreach set up.","index":371,"end_time":1328.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll work on doing those social clips just quick and dirty.","index":372,"end_time":1331.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1328.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If we''re only doing one, this will be less points too.","index":373,"end_time":1333.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''re assuming we were doing a couple more.","index":374,"end_time":1336.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, I mean, let''s start with one as sort of a poc, and then I''m.","index":375,"end_time":1340.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1337.39,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''ll be happy to do a few more, assuming that it looks good.","index":376,"end_time":1343.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1340.39,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":377,"end_time":1343.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":378,"end_time":1344.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1344.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just a good, good test.","index":379,"end_time":1345.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1344.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''re looking good on points right now.","index":380,"end_time":1348.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1346.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So 50 with just negative 4.","index":381,"end_time":1352.984,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1348.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"24.","index":382,"end_time":1353.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.116,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My bad.","index":383,"end_time":1354.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":384,"end_time":1355.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1355.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any other questions?","index":385,"end_time":1356.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1355.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just one other small item, Fireflies, which I''m now looking at here.","index":386,"end_time":1363.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1357.53,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Oh, that''s cool.","index":387,"end_time":1364.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1364.17,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You can.","index":388,"end_time":1365.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1364.89,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"You can talk to it in the meeting.","index":389,"end_time":1366.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.21,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I''m gonna have to play with that.","index":390,"end_time":1367.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1366.49,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":391,"end_time":1368.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.73,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So when people book with me via Savvy Cal, Fireflies gets invited to that meeting, and that seems to show up correctly and join the meeting.","index":392,"end_time":1381.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1370.169,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I have empty recaps, I have no notes, and I have no summaries or.","index":393,"end_time":1385.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1381.69,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I can''t tell if I haven''t granted some sort of permission or connected a dot accordingly or misconfigured something.","index":394,"end_time":1393.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.31,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I would love to be able to leverage those summaries.","index":395,"end_time":1397.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1393.91,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So if that''s something we can look into or if I have done something wrong and you can help me understand what I need to fix, I''m happy to go do it.","index":396,"end_time":1405.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1397.75,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"But I took a look and I didn''t have an obvious answer based on the screens that I was getting to.","index":397,"end_time":1412.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1405.43,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can look into that.","index":398,"end_time":1414.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1413.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, that was like a year ago we set it up, so I''m sure something probably got disconnected.","index":399,"end_time":1420.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1414.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":400,"end_time":1421.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1420.29,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I haven''t used it in quite some time.","index":401,"end_time":1423.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.41,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t really have a problem with, you know, manually taking notes and all of that.","index":402,"end_time":1428.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1424.37,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s helpful to have, though.","index":403,"end_time":1431.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1429.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I understand.","index":404,"end_time":1432.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s just nice to, you know, to not be frantically writing things down.","index":405,"end_time":1437.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.25,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"The other problem that I''ve had with one of my Recent one or two calls with folks that had me kind of want to bubble this up.","index":406,"end_time":1442.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.21,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"My schedule''s been so busy that I''m very often out frantically hanging up with someone and then running to something else.","index":407,"end_time":1449.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.08,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And then like two days later, I have forgotten what the fuck we talked about and don''t have, you know, summary to go back and look at.","index":408,"end_time":1455.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1449.44,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So not urgent, but would be great if we can take a look.","index":409,"end_time":1459.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1455.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"What are you using for your meetings right now?","index":410,"end_time":1462.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Zoom or something else.","index":411,"end_time":1463.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1462.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, yeah.","index":412,"end_time":1465.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.84,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And that''s all working fine.","index":413,"end_time":1466.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1465.92,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Savvycal correctly, you know, spins up a zoom link and all of that, so everything else in that chain seems to be fin.","index":414,"end_time":1472.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1466.76,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"And I get an email after from Fireflies.","index":415,"end_time":1474.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1473.02,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s like, hey, like the meeting just ended, like, whatever, but it''s blank, so it''s like it''s showing up.","index":416,"end_time":1480.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.9,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"It''s just not doing the work, you know, so I''ll give it half credit, but not.","index":417,"end_time":1486.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1480.66,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Not full credit.","index":418,"end_time":1487.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1486.14,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay, well, we''ll look into that.","index":419,"end_time":1489.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1487.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And if we want to just nuke it and start fresh, that''s fine too.","index":420,"end_time":1492.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1490.14,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I don''t need anything historical in there.","index":421,"end_time":1494.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1492.58,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Sometimes I find that to be easier than trying to repair, you know, a busted configuration.","index":422,"end_time":1498.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1494.22,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"So that''s also fine if that''s ends up being the answer.","index":423,"end_time":1501.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1498.54,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":424,"end_time":1502.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1501.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, but that was it.","index":425,"end_time":1504.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1502.98,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"I think everything else is in pretty good.","index":426,"end_time":1505.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1504.02,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Cool.","index":427,"end_time":1506.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":428,"end_time":1506.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we will talk again here soon.","index":429,"end_time":1508.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":430,"end_time":1509.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1508.98,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":431,"end_time":1510.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1509.78,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Thank you both.","index":432,"end_time":1510.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1510.38,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Igor, Nice to meet you.","index":433,"end_time":1511.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1510.82,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Talk to him.","index":434,"end_time":1512.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1511.86,"speaker_name":"Brandon Garcin"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":435,"end_time":1512.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1512.38,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bye.","index":436,"end_time":1513.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1512.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"dateString":"2025-11-12T19:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86432186576?pwd=XxjYEV59FLfPJ9LkkJUeTlFTe1JCaL.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,brandon.garcin@syncromsp.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","brandon.garcin@syncromsp.com","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9ASPHK0AS47Q81N7HBA6KMX","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Secured 3–5 quality podcast guests while keeping scheduling aligned with upcoming show strategy.","Brandon approved targeted Microsoft expert outreach and is prioritizing those leads for interviews.","Agreed to test short social video clips using Brandon''s mobile workflow to streamline production.","Clarified minimal branding requirements; Synchro assets like font kits will be shared to simplify edits.","Discussed restoring Fireflies summary functionality to support faster follow-up amid Brandon’s busy schedule."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think we''ve done a nice job of... reawakening some of these sort of lukewarm connections.","speaker":"Brandon Garcin"},{"quote":"Let''s just make it... quick and dirty and kind of low budget, so that it could be more about... volume and velocity.","speaker":"Brandon Garcin"},{"quote":"If we want to invest more heavily... I''m definitely willing to do that.","speaker":"Brandon Garcin"}],"topics":["podcast","delivery","branding","video","workflow"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Guest Booking and Pipeline Management**\n\nThe guest booking pipeline is stable and well-aligned with evolving content strategy needs for early next year.\n\n- **Brandon Garcin reported having about five 15-minute intro calls and two guests scheduled for recording this Friday** (06:07)  \n    - He highlighted success reengaging lukewarm contacts from past outreach, turning some into confirmed guests.  \n    - Brandon prefers maintaining a pipeline of three to five guests to avoid overload during upcoming holidays and potential show format changes.  \n    - This measured approach supports flexibility for tweaking the podcast direction in 2024 without overcommitting resources.  \n    - The controlled pipeline size balances steady content flow with bandwidth constraints and seasonal audience availability.\n\n- **Igor Zagradjanin presented a researched list of 10 Microsoft-focused expert guests, blending media experts and technical practitioners** (06:55)  \n    - Brandon endorsed the targeted, narrower approach over prior broad outreach, seeing better topic alignment and audience fit.  \n    - Targeted campaigns are expected to yield higher engagement despite requiring more upfront research and personalization.  \n    - Brandon is open to making this Microsoft-focused pipeline a core ongoing strategy, possibly expanding beyond Microsoft later.  \n    - This shift aims to improve guest relevance and podcast resonance with strategic audience segments.\n\n## **Video Content Production and Social Clips Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to produce simple, quick-turnaround social video clips prioritizing volume and ease over high production values.\n\n- **Brandon emphasized a low-effort “point and shoot” video style for social clips, avoiding heavy creative lifts given current bandwidth limits** (10:13)  \n    - He stressed that minimal editing with bumpers, title cards, and on-screen text overlays would suffice to enhance engagement.  \n    - Brandon offered to provide a corporate font kit (Fig Tree) to maintain brand consistency with easy asset integration.  \n    - He prefers using native phone or high-quality camera recordings over platform-based capture for better video quality.  \n    - This approach supports quick content velocity and SEO benefits without taxing internal resources.\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell confirmed producing “quick and dirty” edits and will provide Brandon with an upload folder for raw footage** (16:22)  \n    - The team plans to start with one clip as a proof of concept, then expand if results meet expectations.  \n    - Clips will be formatted for both vertical portrait (YouTube Shorts/social) and blog embedding to reach distinct audiences.  \n    - Brandon advised framing shots to allow trimming for portrait without loss of quality or context.  \n    - This dual-format strategy aims to maximize SEO impact and social reach simultaneously.\n\n## **Podcast Platform and Publishing Updates**\n\nKey administrative and technical updates were addressed to ensure smooth podcast publishing continuity and improved listener experience.\n\n- **Brandon flagged Apple’s updated Terms and Conditions requiring acceptance to continue podcast publishing** (20:36)  \n    - The changes include improved chapter support allowing timed links for easier episode navigation.  \n    - Brandon will check credentials and accept the new TNCs, confirming that he originally set up the Apple listing.  \n    - This update is expected to enhance user experience without significant operational impact.  \n    - Baylee will monitor for any related issues and assist as needed.\n\n- **Baylee confirmed recent podcast recordings were added and noted two guests queued for recording this Friday** (20:16)  \n    - The client portal is being updated with new outreach and social clip assets to streamline workflows.  \n    - The team is tracking resource points and currently remains within budget constraints.  \n    - This infrastructure supports ongoing content delivery and outreach scaling.\n\n## **Meeting Automation and Workflow Improvements**\n\nThere is a need to troubleshoot and restore meeting transcription and summary automation to improve post-call productivity.\n\n- **Brandon reported that Fireflies joins his scheduled Zoom meetings via SavvyCal but does not produce meeting notes or summaries** (22:37)  \n    - He suspects a configuration issue or disconnection since setup was about a year ago.  \n    - Brandon values automated recaps due to his busy schedule and frequent back-to-back calls causing memory gaps.  \n    - Baylee agreed to investigate and possibly reset the integration, noting that starting fresh might be simpler than repairing.  \n    - Restoring this tool would reduce manual note-taking and improve meeting follow-up efficiency.\n\n## **Long-Term Content and Brand Strategy Vision**\n\nThe team is positioning content efforts to support SEO growth and audience engagement through multi-format, branded assets.\n\n- **Brandon emphasized embedding short videos in blog posts to boost SEO and complement written content** (13:14)  \n    - He noted recent Google and AI search trends favor video content alongside community signals for ranking.  \n    - The Synchro brand’s unique AI-generated visuals pose challenges but also offer strong differentiation if leveraged correctly.  \n    - Current focus is on simple, scalable content production before potentially investing in richer creative assets next year.  \n    - This phased approach balances innovation with resource realities and audience expectations.\n\n- **Brandon highlighted the challenge of maintaining high-quality brand visuals due to use of AI tools like Midjourney and Sora** (13:14)  \n    - He wants to avoid large upfront investments in image libraries until there is clearer ROI and bandwidth.  \n    - The team will continue experimenting with brand-aligned fonts and simple overlays to maintain consistency.  \n    - This cautious brand evolution supports flexibility and cost control while testing new content formats.  \n    - The strategy reflects a pragmatic balance between originality and operational feasibility.","outline":null,"keywords":["podcast guest booking","Microsoft expert outreach","social media clips","video production","Apple podcast TNC","meeting transcription"],"overview":"- **Guest Booking Pipeline:** Five intro calls done; two guests confirmed for recording. Stable pipeline aligns with content strategy for next year.  \n- **Microsoft Expert Guests:** List of 10 targeted guests chosen for relevance and better audience fit. Core strategy might expand beyond Microsoft.  \n- **Video Content Production:** Quick, low-effort video style emphasized; minimal editing to enhance engagement, with brand consistency maintained using corporate assets.  \n- **Podcast Platform Updates:** Apple’s new Terms require acceptance for publishing; improved chapter support enhances listener experience, no major operational impact expected.  \n- **Meeting Automation Troubleshooting:** Meeting notes automation not functioning; integration reset may improve efficiency, important for busy schedules.  \n- **Long-Term Content Strategy:** Focus on embedding videos in blogs to improve SEO; testing simple content first before richer investments next year.","action_items":"\n**Brandon Garcin**\nReview and accept updated Apple podcast TNCs to continue publishing (20:36)\nRecord first social media video clip using preferred phone or camera setup and upload to agreed folder (15:21)\nSend example low-effort video to team for reference (16:55)\nMonitor upcoming podcast recordings scheduled for Friday and deliver approved files (20:26)\nForward Apple email to Baylee for reference (21:42)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nProvide Brandon with upload folder/access for social media video clips (16:22)\nFinalize and deliver messaging sequence for guest outreach by the next day (10:02)\nInvestigate and resolve Fireflies transcription issue or reset integration (22:37)\nContinue development of client portal outreach module and social clip production (21:55)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nPrioritize Microsoft expert guest list outreach according to Brandon’s feedback (06:49)\nParticipate in social media clips planning and production workflow (10:17)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"3eef9407-f1cf-45cc-8d23-b25b1f97fb72","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
