-- Meeting: Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new) (2025-11-12 20:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ec1251b4-8dd8-4f12-ba68-1e923a54c460',
    '2025-11-12 20:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9QPW0D0TWKZ25BPQ9CMJS6Y',
    'Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new)',
    '{"Taylor Doerbaum","Michael Jones","Baylee Gunnell"}'::text[],
    1037,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87549285494?pwd=ibWG4xRLddaHqf8JzJ7T48gg886wbu.1',
    '{"id":"01K9QPW0D0TWKZ25BPQ9CMJS6Y","title":"Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new)","summary":{"notes":"## **Survey Launch and Data Collection**\n\nThe team adjusted the survey timeline to maximize responses before the end of the month, aiming for efficient data collection and meaningful insights.  \n\n- **The survey interval was shortened from 14 to 8 days** between initial and reminder messages to complete lists by month-end and improve response rates (02:47)  \n    - This change allows sending reminders earlier, increasing chances of more responses within the month  \n    - Taylor explained this adjustment to fit better with the team’s goal of timely data compilation  \n    - Michael supported flexibility on timing, emphasizing response quality over strict schedules  \n    - Expected outcome is to reach at least **20 responses**, enough to draw solid conclusions on client challenges  \n\n- **Survey responses are tracked centrally in HubSpot**, integrating data from Lemlist and Heyreach2 platforms for unified analysis (08:13)  \n    - Taylor confirmed all form data funnels into HubSpot for streamlined reporting  \n    - Michael praised HubSpot’s ease of use for quick result reviews and assessment  \n    - Initial survey phase yielded **4 responses**, viewed positively as a start by Michael, highlighting statistical value even at low counts  \n    - The team plans to send the compiled report to respondents immediately and invite follow-up participation  \n\n- **Future survey cadence may shift to quarterly or semi-annual to avoid respondent fatigue** with too frequent monthly surveys (06:36)  \n    - Michael raised this as a potential adjustment based on feedback and practical engagement  \n    - This approach aims to maintain survey effectiveness while respecting audience bandwidth  \n\n## **Client List Management and Targeting Strategy**\n\nThe team is refining the client company list for outreach, focusing on relevant industries and appropriate contact roles to optimize engagement quality.  \n\n- **A filtered list excluding irrelevant industries was approved**, improving targeting precision and avoiding unproductive outreach (08:28)  \n    - Michael noted some mismatches in initial industry classifications and welcomed the exclusion of sectors like chemicals and unrelated retail  \n    - Baylee and Taylor are tasked with incorporating company codes and refining the list for future campaigns  \n    - This curated list covers approximately **5,300 companies**, offering a broad yet targeted reach  \n\n- **Company size is used as the main filter instead of revenue, with a focus on firms sized 15 million USD and above** (09:59)  \n    - Baylee highlighted revenue data’s unreliability and the preference for company size as a more accurate metric  \n    - Michael endorsed avoiding mega-companies and focusing on mid-sized firms for better engagement chances  \n    - The list aims to capture the right balance of scale and relevance for business impact  \n\n- **Contact role selection emphasizes key decision-makers like CFOs and CTOs, reflecting evolving organizational structures** (11:50)  \n    - Michael shared insights on unusual titles emerging in larger firms, underscoring the importance of targeting the right roles  \n    - He suggested aiming for at least **four relevant job titles per company** to ensure broad but focused outreach  \n    - A follow-up meeting is planned to review the list and roles to refine messaging and maximize connection effectiveness  \n\n## **Content Strategy for Organic Social Media**\n\nThe existing content library will be repurposed extensively to maintain consistent social media presence while awaiting new material.  \n\n- **Posts are scheduled through December using repurposed content from previous months**, ensuring continuous engagement without needing immediate new topics (13:15)  \n    - Taylor confirmed that new curated posts will conclude this week, then older content will be recycled  \n    - Michael directed to start from the earliest posts to reach new audiences, including those recently added like Josh’s network  \n    - This strategy leverages existing assets, saving time while keeping the brand visible  \n\n- **New content ideas will depend on the completion of ongoing projects**, with sensitivity around timing and confidentiality limiting immediate creation (15:00)  \n    - Michael explained that upcoming articles could form series that mirror website content once projects conclude  \n    - The team agreed to focus on repurposing until fresh material becomes available  \n    - This cautious approach balances content relevance with operational realities  \n\n## **Analytics Reporting and Next Steps**\n\nThe analytics process is advancing, with plans for comprehensive reporting and integration of existing client data to enhance insights.  \n\n- **Taylor will send the first set of survey stats by Friday, covering all platforms and initial responses** to provide a clearer picture of survey performance (02:47)  \n    - This report replaces visuals that could not load due to Google issues during the meeting  \n    - Michael expressed eagerness to review the data and monitor trends as responses grow  \n\n- **A new analyst is working on compiling data from 18-19 existing client data sets**, broadening the analytics base beyond survey results (06:36)  \n    - This additional data will help validate survey findings and enrich overall insight quality  \n    - Michael suggested using AI tools like ChatGPT to streamline report writing and speed delivery  \n    - The target is to produce a report by the **end of November** for distribution to survey participants and internal use  \n\n- **The December survey adjustments will be incorporated smoothly**, including changes to questions and lists as discussed (07:41)  \n    - Michael and Baylee agreed on these updates to improve data accuracy and relevance  \n    - The goal is to maintain momentum and continuously refine survey quality for better business impact  \n\n## **Technical and Operational Coordination**\n\nThe team is managing technical challenges and workflow adjustments to keep outreach and analytics on track despite system limitations and health challenges.  \n\n- **The team encountered domain issues affecting Lemlist dispatches but resolved them quickly**, keeping survey outreach on schedule (04:48)  \n    - Taylor assured that Lemlist is now functioning as planned, with data feeding into HubSpot without issues  \n    - Michael’s review confirmed limited early distribution but expressed confidence in progress  \n\n- **Workload distribution is affected by team health and onboarding of new members**, requiring flexible coordination (01:19)  \n    - Michael noted Josh’s absence due to illness and busy schedules handling new client challenges with legacy systems  \n    - The team is bringing in experts to manage technical complexities, ensuring continuity  \n    - This flexibility supports steady progress despite operational hurdles  \n\n- **Content scheduling and analytics reporting are planned with contingency for system outages**, as seen with Google downtime affecting slide decks (02:38)  \n    - Taylor’s commitment to delivering analytics via email ensures no delay in information flow  \n    - This approach mitigates risk of losing momentum in communications and decision-making  \n    - The team maintains proactive communication to adapt to technical constraints effectively","outline":null,"keywords":["Survey Analytics","Company List","Job Titles","Social Media Content","Client Data Sets","HubSpot Integration"],"overview":"- **Survey Adjustments:** Shortened survey interval to 8 days aims for at least 20 valuable responses by month-end.\n\n- **Centralized Tracking:** All survey data is integrated into HubSpot for streamlined reporting and analysis from multiple platforms.\n\n- **Client Targeting Refinement:** Approved list focuses on 5,300 relevant companies, targeting mid-sized firms for better engagement.\n\n- **Content Strategy:** Scheduled posts through December using repurposed content to maintain engagement until new material is available.\n\n- **Analytics Reporting:** First survey stats report due Friday, with a comprehensive data analysis target by end of November.  \n\n- **Technical Coordination:** Resolved domain issues maintain outreach schedule; flexible workload management supports progress amid team health challenges.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend analytic data and survey stats in a recap email post-meeting and follow up with more detailed survey data on Friday (01:58)\nPrepare backup newsletter draft from last month in case survey stats are not ready (02:30)\nAdjust survey reminder interval from 14 days to 8 days to allow for quicker follow-up and better response timing (03:30)\nContinue compiling and refining the second edition of the company list based on industry filters and job titles for future outreach (08:50)\nSchedule organic social media posts by repurposing older content starting from the beginning of the archive through December (14:40)\n\n**Michael Jones**\nReview incoming survey responses and provide input on company list filters and job titles to maximize outreach quality (08:30)\nCoordinate internally to finalize analytical question sets and reporting process using existing client data sets for November report delivery (06:00)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nAssist with refining company size criterion for targeting due to public data reliability issues and support survey rollout and follow-up as discussed (09:40)\n"},"duration":17.280000686645508,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Michael Jones"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Michael.","index":0,"end_time":9.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you feeling?","index":1,"end_time":12.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You feeling better?","index":2,"end_time":12.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think.","index":3,"end_time":12.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You unwell last time, weren''t you?","index":4,"end_time":14.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I was, yeah, I am.","index":5,"end_time":16.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s still kicking my butt.","index":6,"end_time":17.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know what I got, but I''m better today.","index":7,"end_time":20.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But it has just been lingering for like a week and a half.","index":8,"end_time":23.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":9,"end_time":24.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''s the worst.","index":10,"end_time":25.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I know, I know.","index":11,"end_time":27.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''d rather just have like strep or something and get it over with, but that''s what I usually get.","index":12,"end_time":32.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, must.","index":13,"end_time":34.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Must be a weird chest cold or something.","index":14,"end_time":36.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":15,"end_time":37.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, sometimes these things do.","index":16,"end_time":39.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"They do linger.","index":17,"end_time":40.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So unfortunate but.","index":18,"end_time":42.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But better grateful.","index":19,"end_time":44.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m glad you are feeling better.","index":20,"end_time":45.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":21,"end_time":47.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you doing this week though?","index":22,"end_time":50.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You having a good week?","index":23,"end_time":51.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s been.","index":24,"end_time":52.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Been quiet.","index":25,"end_time":53.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ve been sort of just, well, quiet for me.","index":26,"end_time":55.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Very, very busy for the guys because we are just getting everything going with a new client and so interesting technical challenges which obviously we''re managing to sort of work out.","index":27,"end_time":68.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s good and it''s been interesting to, to sort of see different things that we need to sort out.","index":28,"end_time":75.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s nothing to do with us, it''s to do with the systems that the clients use.","index":29,"end_time":78.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right.","index":30,"end_time":79.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":79.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know, typically we, we find it quite easy to deal with, but then suddenly we''ve got some older systems that are fairly antiquated in the way they do business.","index":31,"end_time":87.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And so we suddenly have to bring in individuals that know what they''re talking about and help us solve the problem, which is good.","index":32,"end_time":93.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''re doing these sorts of things.","index":33,"end_time":96.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So.","index":34,"end_time":96.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":35,"end_time":98.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So these guys are very, very busy.","index":36,"end_time":99.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I don''t know where Josh is.","index":37,"end_time":101.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"He.","index":38,"end_time":101.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"He''s.","index":39,"end_time":102.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think he''s been incredibly busy and he''s a little under the weather as well, so not entirely sure if he''s going to join us.","index":40,"end_time":108.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But yeah, no worries.","index":41,"end_time":110.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":108.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let''s kick on and we''ll, we''ll.","index":42,"end_time":114.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":43,"end_time":114.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"If he joins, he joins.","index":44,"end_time":117.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":45,"end_time":118.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, I''m having.","index":46,"end_time":119.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know if you''ve noticed, but Google is down right now, so none of my decks and anything are loading.","index":47,"end_time":124.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I was in the middle of finishing loading some analytics and wasn''t able to do that.","index":48,"end_time":128.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So after the meeting, I will send all the analytics that we normally go over in my recap email, but the actual slides didn''t have any visuals per se, so we can just walk through it.","index":49,"end_time":138.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":128.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But for the newsletter, I know Bailey met with you last week and went over this, but I think the plan is to just potentially do some survey stats, but if not just repurpose the newsletter draft I had prepared for last month.","index":50,"end_time":151.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can just have that ready to go as backup.","index":51,"end_time":153.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We.","index":52,"end_time":154.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We could promise you the world, but I don''t know.","index":53,"end_time":156.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":154.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s going to have a backup.","index":54,"end_time":158.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":156.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ve got.","index":55,"end_time":159.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve got a backup.","index":56,"end_time":160.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ll use it.","index":57,"end_time":160.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":58,"end_time":161.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s perfect.","index":59,"end_time":162.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we don''t have to stress about delaying it if we don''t get.","index":60,"end_time":165.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Get ourself in time.","index":61,"end_time":166.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":165.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"For sure.","index":62,"end_time":167.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that.","index":63,"end_time":168.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the other thing I wanted to chat through was the survey.","index":64,"end_time":172.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ve launched that.","index":65,"end_time":173.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Since it''s so new, there''s not a ton of stats yet to share.","index":66,"end_time":176.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So on Friday about like early afternoon, I''ll send you guys an email with just going through the stats across all the platforms that we have it running so there''s more data to show.","index":67,"end_time":185.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But something we wanted to run by you.","index":68,"end_time":188.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know you originally wanted the two weeks in between, but Bailey and I were talking about it and we ended switching it to eight days just so we can get through the lists by the end of the month.","index":69,"end_time":197.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":188.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If that works for you.","index":70,"end_time":199.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We think it would just be a little bit more efficient that way.","index":71,"end_time":202.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or it still gives a little over a week instead of the two week mark because then that would kind of make it cutting it close to the end of the month if we want to get some stats in.","index":72,"end_time":211.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s not worry too much about that.","index":73,"end_time":215.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Sorry, I did get distracted.","index":74,"end_time":216.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":215.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Josh is not making the call though, so apologies.","index":75,"end_time":219.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I can''t do two things at the same time.","index":76,"end_time":221.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"As I get older, I can''t do anything.","index":77,"end_time":224.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"My wife will protest.","index":78,"end_time":227.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I probably never could.","index":79,"end_time":228.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So tell me again, are you saying we.","index":80,"end_time":231.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s going to take you a week to get through the list and therefore push out if we have to, before the new list comes in, before we send the reminders.","index":81,"end_time":240.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Is that right?","index":82,"end_time":240.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":241.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ll have.","index":84,"end_time":242.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Originally we were going to have the 14 days in between the first message and second message to each contact, but we just switched it to eight days just so we can get hopefully more responses by the end of the month to kind of send that reminder earlier than 14 days.","index":85,"end_time":255.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But that''s the only adjustment.","index":86,"end_time":257.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Everything else will be the same.","index":87,"end_time":258.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I was looking through obviously HubSpot and I''ve seen four responses.","index":88,"end_time":264.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So am I just.","index":89,"end_time":266.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"This is what I need to understand.","index":90,"end_time":267.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I see.","index":91,"end_time":268.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m assuming there is a list in HubSpot that we send, but there''s also a list that''s gone through Lemlist.","index":92,"end_time":275.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we have Lemlist and Heyreach2 the LinkedIn sequence.","index":93,"end_time":278.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":94,"end_time":279.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":95,"end_time":280.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":96,"end_time":280.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I was looking through LEM list and I didn''t seem.","index":97,"end_time":282.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Not much has gone out through Lemlist just yet from.","index":98,"end_time":285.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Based upon the quick sort of review.","index":99,"end_time":287.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''s correct.","index":100,"end_time":288.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":101,"end_time":288.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we adjusted that earlier.","index":102,"end_time":290.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We had some, some thing we had to fix with a domain.","index":103,"end_time":294.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, that''s why on Friday we''ll have more stats for you on there.","index":104,"end_time":298.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.939,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But everything is working as as planned for the lemlist side of things.","index":105,"end_time":303.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I got four responses.","index":106,"end_time":304.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, and you know, my old researcher mindset would just take that as a statistical valid number and we''ll build a, we''ll build a report out of it, no problem at all.","index":107,"end_time":314.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So no, it''s good that at least four people responded from our existing base of people.","index":108,"end_time":319.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So that''s great news.","index":109,"end_time":320.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So yeah, I''m excited to sort of see what else comes of it.","index":110,"end_time":324.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Let''s not stress too much about obviously with the reminder because if we need another week, whatever.","index":111,"end_time":328.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, at the end of the day, if we get.","index":112,"end_time":331.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''ll make this up 20 responses, that''s sufficient to get a consensus in my opinion because we''re asking the same problem that everyone probably experiences and it''s almost like AI is, is.","index":113,"end_time":348.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Is potential outlier, but everything else is fairly fair or thereabout.","index":114,"end_time":352.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay, don''t stress about that.","index":115,"end_time":355.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ll just let it go and we''ll do it.","index":116,"end_time":359.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So you know, for the next one.","index":117,"end_time":360.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, the December email with the names.","index":118,"end_time":364,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I think hopefully that will make sense and what we''ll do is we''ll try to get to the point where we go, we''ve done the.","index":119,"end_time":373.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I think the report should be an easy fix.","index":120,"end_time":376.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Shouldn''t be that difficult to go ahead and produce.","index":121,"end_time":378.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"If we can go ahead and get something by the end of November, it shouldn''t be that hard to do, to be honest with you.","index":122,"end_time":386.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ll probably steal ChatGPT to do a lot of it and just say here it is and we''ve got a new guy that''s doing a whole bunch of analytics right now from existing clients.","index":123,"end_time":396.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So all this is the analytical questions.","index":124,"end_time":399.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''re going to utilize data from existing clients.","index":125,"end_time":402.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we''ve got 18, 19 data sets that we can go ahead and utilize, which is more than sufficient because there''s a couple in the same industry and then there''s a bit of a broad range.","index":126,"end_time":413.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we should be okay.","index":127,"end_time":414.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we just love to see what other people are saying.","index":128,"end_time":417.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"If we get 20 responses, good stuff that will make it.","index":129,"end_time":422.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I think what we want to do is then produce the report.","index":130,"end_time":424.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then obviously anyone who submitted, they get the report immediately and requested to do the next slot if they want to.","index":131,"end_time":432.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Anybody else says, we''ve got it, which you can''t get it until.","index":132,"end_time":436.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Unless you just go ahead and do the survey.","index":133,"end_time":438.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we''ll try and do it that way and see if that helps us, you know, kickstart some things there after that.","index":134,"end_time":445.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Not entirely sure if we want to.","index":135,"end_time":447.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":445.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We did sort of suggest that some of the questions would be like quarterly or half, half yearly and things like that.","index":136,"end_time":452.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we might just be getting to that point just to do quarterly surveys because no one wants to see one every single month, which is what we''re doing.","index":137,"end_time":460.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I know you had sent that email with the adjustments for the December survey.","index":138,"end_time":465.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m just looking through that now.","index":139,"end_time":467.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we could definitely make those changes.","index":140,"end_time":470.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And yeah, it should be easy enough to, like you said, compile the information that we get and pull that data together.","index":141,"end_time":478.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":142,"end_time":479.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":478.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because the HubSpot is brilliant, by the way.","index":143,"end_time":480.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s really, really good.","index":144,"end_time":481.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s so easy to use.","index":145,"end_time":483.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s like that.","index":146,"end_time":483.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":483.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I can quickly, quickly, you know, assess the results and.","index":147,"end_time":487.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":483.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Love it.","index":148,"end_time":487.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Absolutely love it.","index":149,"end_time":488.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So that''s good stuff.","index":150,"end_time":489.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I''m assuming the LEM list results will go into HubSpot as well.","index":151,"end_time":493.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":152,"end_time":495.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like the form.","index":153,"end_time":496.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The form is going to HubSpot.","index":154,"end_time":497.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":155,"end_time":498.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":156,"end_time":498.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I know I was told that, but I just want to double check.","index":157,"end_time":501.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s where all of the data will be compiled because it''s going to that same HubSpot assessment form.","index":158,"end_time":506.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":159,"end_time":508.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":506.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":160,"end_time":509.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":508.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":161,"end_time":510.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the next thing is just the company list.","index":162,"end_time":513.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we had gone back and forth a little bit about that.","index":163,"end_time":515.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I didn''t know if you wanted to explain anything in person before we go ahead and make any adjustments.","index":164,"end_time":519.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know you had sent over those specific industries, so we''ll just make sure to filter those out for the future.","index":165,"end_time":525.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the company codes you had sent, we had already compiled a bunch of the data in that first list, but we can make sure to include that in this upcoming one.","index":166,"end_time":533.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But before we make that second rendition of it, I didn''t know if you had anything else you wanted to walk through as far as.","index":167,"end_time":539.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":533.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think so I think looking.","index":168,"end_time":541.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":539.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And thank you again, whoever put the list together.","index":169,"end_time":543.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Really, really good.","index":170,"end_time":545.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s great to have the explanation next to it.","index":171,"end_time":547.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It took me a while to go through them, but it doesn''t matter.","index":172,"end_time":550.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It was really good to sort of quickly look at it.","index":173,"end_time":552.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Some of the industry, some of the companies didn''t match the industries, which is fine.","index":174,"end_time":556.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":552.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s not a big deal.","index":175,"end_time":557.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I just had to make a judgment call to say, let''s not try these.","index":176,"end_time":560.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m like chemicals and other bits of food retail, which is not our area.","index":177,"end_time":566.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s not worth it.","index":178,"end_time":568.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"There''s plenty of others that we can go after, you know, to go ahead and do that.","index":179,"end_time":572.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I think that list is a good one to exclude for the future.","index":180,"end_time":575.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then let''s just go ahead and see, you know, how many names we can get out of the thing.","index":181,"end_time":583.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So one of the things I think it''s probably worth, and I didn''t know how you guys categorize it from a revenue or a people point of view, but again, current number we said, I think the 15 million upwards.","index":182,"end_time":596.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Was that correct?","index":183,"end_time":597.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Bailey, remind me.","index":184,"end_time":598.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I have it, I have it written down.","index":185,"end_time":601.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we, we use that, but we found that it was just not accurate.","index":186,"end_time":607.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It was not a very good, like, I think people just don''t have that information like very publicly available.","index":187,"end_time":615.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s why we use mostly company size just as the starting point.","index":188,"end_time":621.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because that, that does seem to be a bit more reliable.","index":189,"end_time":623.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":190,"end_time":624.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":624.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s just stick with that then.","index":191,"end_time":625.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":624.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I totally agree.","index":192,"end_time":626.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So, yeah, I mean, I think, you know, some, like, we want to be careful.","index":193,"end_time":631.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We don''t get too many mega companies, you know, like, we got to be careful on that front.","index":194,"end_time":637.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"The, the sort of 5300ish is a broad range, but that should capture a good number of, of people, of companies, I would think, you know, so I think we should be pretty good.","index":195,"end_time":650.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":637.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I suppose it''s like, you know, it''s almost like depending on how many, how many you guys sort of are able to pull from those industry codes, we can expand upon that.","index":196,"end_time":663.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We can do some work on it.","index":197,"end_time":664.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I don''t know, depends on what we want to do.","index":198,"end_time":666.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because I''m assuming we were probably looking at sort of a minimum of four job titles per company.","index":199,"end_time":673.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So, you know, that''s probably not a bad way of doing it.","index":200,"end_time":679.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So even if we get 100 companies, we still got four.","index":201,"end_time":681.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"If we expand to five job titles, which we could easily do, that''s 500 contacts.","index":202,"end_time":686.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m more interested in companies than contacts in terms of numbers because it''s like we can get 100 companies and we get the right sort of people talking to us or even looking at our stuff.","index":203,"end_time":702.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''s, that''s better than 50 companies and 100 contacts, that sort of thing.","index":204,"end_time":706.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":702.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So, yeah, that would be my, my preference and we can certainly go ahead.","index":205,"end_time":710.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":706.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And once we have the list, I think it''s probably worth having another sit down and just think through the firms, think through who we talk to at the, at the existing companies and just make sure we''re being sensible about the job title because, you know, the larger the firm, interestingly enough, we got some really weird and wonderful job titles turning up, which we never expected.","index":206,"end_time":732.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":710.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And so we had to be sort of go, okay, so which ones do we think?","index":207,"end_time":736.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, I''m always like the cfo, the cto.","index":208,"end_time":740.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"They seem to be more and more involved in these sorts of discussions, you know, because some of them have got.","index":209,"end_time":746.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We found one guy, he''s got a title for both he and technology reports to a cfo.","index":210,"end_time":752.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":211,"end_time":753.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''re sort of seeing.","index":212,"end_time":753.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s anecdotal, but potentially that that could be the direction that they''re going in.","index":213,"end_time":758.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So.","index":214,"end_time":758.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we think, okay, well, you know, where, where do we sort of base our thing?","index":215,"end_time":762.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"CEOs don''t always.","index":216,"end_time":764.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Larger firms just don''t get involved.","index":217,"end_time":765.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":764.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I mean, okay, Andres is an exception to the rule because the person was the CFO before he got promoted.","index":218,"end_time":771.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So there is, there is a line there.","index":219,"end_time":773.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But yeah, I think it''s, it''s, it''s getting the right message, the right person that goes, yeah, I have this problem and we need to solve it.","index":220,"end_time":781.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So, yeah, excited about that one.","index":221,"end_time":784.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":781.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think it''d be good to sort of keep, keep, keep going with a bigger and bigger list as well.","index":222,"end_time":788.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":223,"end_time":791.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yep.","index":224,"end_time":791.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Looking forward to seeing the list.","index":225,"end_time":792.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then we can, we can build it from there.","index":226,"end_time":794.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":227,"end_time":795.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":228,"end_time":796.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll work on getting that second edition together.","index":229,"end_time":799.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the only other thing I wanted to just touch base on was organic social.","index":230,"end_time":804.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I have post scheduled through the end of the month and into December.","index":231,"end_time":807.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think the new, like the new posts that we had curated will end this week, but I repurposed older content through the end of the month, like we had talked about, and into December.","index":232,"end_time":817.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if there was something new that you wanted to have us write about or create images for, we could do that.","index":233,"end_time":823.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But until then, we can just repurposing the content that you were saying, because that''s been working.","index":234,"end_time":828.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So because we''ve been doing this for some time, I would have thought we would have had a couple of months, at least a few months worth of content that we could have repurposed.","index":235,"end_time":837.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we definitely have plenty to keep.","index":236,"end_time":840.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":837.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I would have my opinion.","index":237,"end_time":843.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I would go to the beginning and just keep going until we run out, because.","index":238,"end_time":848.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that.","index":239,"end_time":849.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You know, I''m only going to think of one or two new topics and I can at the moment, I cannot think of anything else that we haven''t already talked about.","index":240,"end_time":856.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So it''s like everything else we''ve talked about in the past has still relevance.","index":241,"end_time":860.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And no one''s going to remember something that we produced six months ago.","index":242,"end_time":865.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":860.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, they read it again.","index":243,"end_time":866.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And as well, let''s not forget we didn''t.","index":244,"end_time":870.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":867.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We only recently added Josh to the distribution.","index":245,"end_time":872.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So, you know, if we start at the beginning and then start sending those things out to him, his, his audience as well, they would have never seen that anyway.","index":246,"end_time":882.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So.","index":247,"end_time":882.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":248,"end_time":883.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll go ahead and do that then we''ll just schedule a bunch out like you said.","index":249,"end_time":886.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Start from the beginning and.","index":250,"end_time":887.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And get those all posted.","index":251,"end_time":889.099,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so.","index":252,"end_time":890.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.099,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":253,"end_time":890.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":890.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":254,"end_time":891.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":890.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because again, I cannot think of anything new right now.","index":255,"end_time":893.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":891.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I really can''t.","index":256,"end_time":895.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":257,"end_time":896.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think a lot of people start checking out too, but it''s just like, yeah, I can''t.","index":258,"end_time":900.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I mean, we''ve.","index":259,"end_time":900.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ve written about everything.","index":260,"end_time":901.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I mean, if I can, I can''t bring up another tariff because, yeah, everyone writes about those things, so.","index":261,"end_time":908.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But I think there''s some other things that.","index":262,"end_time":910.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"What I''m hoping to try and do, and I need to try and wait for these projects to be finished at work.","index":263,"end_time":915.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"There could be some interesting topics and I''m trying to think maybe we could do the same as we did before, like a couple of series, you know, of things, and then we''ll produce an article that goes on the website and then they''re sort of mirrored.","index":264,"end_time":930.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Mirrored in that particular way.","index":265,"end_time":932.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So that could be a way forward.","index":266,"end_time":935.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":932.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But I''m waiting for a couple of these things to be finished to see if we could even talk about it.","index":267,"end_time":940.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And if we can, then that''s great.","index":268,"end_time":942.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ve got enough material, but we''re not there yet and it just could be so sensitive that I can''t write about it anyway.","index":269,"end_time":949,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we''ll see.","index":270,"end_time":950.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":271,"end_time":951.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":950.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay.","index":272,"end_time":952.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":273,"end_time":953.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we could just focus on the repurpose for now and.","index":274,"end_time":955.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":275,"end_time":955.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":276,"end_time":955.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Reconvene whenever.","index":277,"end_time":957.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, yeah, when you.","index":278,"end_time":958.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You sort of say, like, we''re running out, but I would have really thought we must have a few more.","index":279,"end_time":962.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"No, I just only scheduled like report once till the beginning of December in case you did have something new you wanted to post.","index":280,"end_time":968.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But that doesn''t mean we''re out by any means.","index":281,"end_time":971.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Keep going until you say, right, we are now.","index":282,"end_time":974.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":972.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right and then I''ll go, shit.","index":283,"end_time":976.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, easy to do.","index":284,"end_time":980.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll definitely get that, get that scheduled out.","index":285,"end_time":983.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":286,"end_time":984.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":287,"end_time":986.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, that''s everything we had.","index":288,"end_time":987.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll go ahead and set all the stats that I was able to put into the deck and our post meeting recap and we''ll.","index":289,"end_time":993.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll get working on the list and on Friday, I''ll send you some additional data too on all the survey stats that we have in so far for the first week.","index":290,"end_time":1002.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s run, so.","index":291,"end_time":1003.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1002.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":292,"end_time":1004.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1003.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":293,"end_time":1004.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Excited.","index":294,"end_time":1005.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Be interesting to sort of see.","index":295,"end_time":1006.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1005.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"See where it goes and what we can do with it.","index":296,"end_time":1009.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":297,"end_time":1010.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s an exciting thing to see when people respond, so.","index":298,"end_time":1013.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1011,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree.","index":299,"end_time":1014.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I totally agree.","index":300,"end_time":1015.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Fantastic, guys.","index":301,"end_time":1016.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1015.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":302,"end_time":1017.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":303,"end_time":1018.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Look forward to the recap and the Friday one as well, and we''ll take it from there.","index":304,"end_time":1024.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":305,"end_time":1024.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1024.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks, Michael.","index":306,"end_time":1025.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1024.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right.","index":307,"end_time":1026.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1025.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Hope you fully recover soon.","index":308,"end_time":1028.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":309,"end_time":1028.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1028.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":310,"end_time":1029.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1028.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Of course.","index":311,"end_time":1030.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"}],"dateString":"2025-11-12T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87549285494?pwd=ibWG4xRLddaHqf8JzJ7T48gg886wbu.1","participants":["josh@hydrian.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,michael.jones@hydrian.com,taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","josh@hydrian.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","michael.jones@hydrian.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9QPW0D0TWKZ25BPQ9CMJS6Y","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Resolved Lemlist domain issues; full survey campaign functionality now restored and yielding initial responses.","Agreed to repurpose prior newsletter content while awaiting new survey results and design finalization.","Confirmed shift from 14 to 8-day message gap to accelerate survey timeline and meet month-end goals.","Validated HubSpot as central data hub; all platform responses will funnel into single analytics form.","Set plan to repurpose older social content and schedule forward while awaiting new material clearance."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Let''s not stress too much about obviously with the reminder because if we need another week, whatever.","speaker":"Michael Jones"},{"quote":"HubSpot is brilliant, by the way. It''s really, really good.","speaker":"Michael Jones"},{"quote":"I''ll send you some additional data too on all the survey stats that we have in so far.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"topics":["survey","delivery","content","outreach"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Survey Launch and Data Collection**\n\nThe team adjusted the survey timeline to maximize responses before the end of the month, aiming for efficient data collection and meaningful insights.  \n\n- **The survey interval was shortened from 14 to 8 days** between initial and reminder messages to complete lists by month-end and improve response rates (02:47)  \n    - This change allows sending reminders earlier, increasing chances of more responses within the month  \n    - Taylor explained this adjustment to fit better with the team’s goal of timely data compilation  \n    - Michael supported flexibility on timing, emphasizing response quality over strict schedules  \n    - Expected outcome is to reach at least **20 responses**, enough to draw solid conclusions on client challenges  \n\n- **Survey responses are tracked centrally in HubSpot**, integrating data from Lemlist and Heyreach2 platforms for unified analysis (08:13)  \n    - Taylor confirmed all form data funnels into HubSpot for streamlined reporting  \n    - Michael praised HubSpot’s ease of use for quick result reviews and assessment  \n    - Initial survey phase yielded **4 responses**, viewed positively as a start by Michael, highlighting statistical value even at low counts  \n    - The team plans to send the compiled report to respondents immediately and invite follow-up participation  \n\n- **Future survey cadence may shift to quarterly or semi-annual to avoid respondent fatigue** with too frequent monthly surveys (06:36)  \n    - Michael raised this as a potential adjustment based on feedback and practical engagement  \n    - This approach aims to maintain survey effectiveness while respecting audience bandwidth  \n\n## **Client List Management and Targeting Strategy**\n\nThe team is refining the client company list for outreach, focusing on relevant industries and appropriate contact roles to optimize engagement quality.  \n\n- **A filtered list excluding irrelevant industries was approved**, improving targeting precision and avoiding unproductive outreach (08:28)  \n    - Michael noted some mismatches in initial industry classifications and welcomed the exclusion of sectors like chemicals and unrelated retail  \n    - Baylee and Taylor are tasked with incorporating company codes and refining the list for future campaigns  \n    - This curated list covers approximately **5,300 companies**, offering a broad yet targeted reach  \n\n- **Company size is used as the main filter instead of revenue, with a focus on firms sized 15 million USD and above** (09:59)  \n    - Baylee highlighted revenue data’s unreliability and the preference for company size as a more accurate metric  \n    - Michael endorsed avoiding mega-companies and focusing on mid-sized firms for better engagement chances  \n    - The list aims to capture the right balance of scale and relevance for business impact  \n\n- **Contact role selection emphasizes key decision-makers like CFOs and CTOs, reflecting evolving organizational structures** (11:50)  \n    - Michael shared insights on unusual titles emerging in larger firms, underscoring the importance of targeting the right roles  \n    - He suggested aiming for at least **four relevant job titles per company** to ensure broad but focused outreach  \n    - A follow-up meeting is planned to review the list and roles to refine messaging and maximize connection effectiveness  \n\n## **Content Strategy for Organic Social Media**\n\nThe existing content library will be repurposed extensively to maintain consistent social media presence while awaiting new material.  \n\n- **Posts are scheduled through December using repurposed content from previous months**, ensuring continuous engagement without needing immediate new topics (13:15)  \n    - Taylor confirmed that new curated posts will conclude this week, then older content will be recycled  \n    - Michael directed to start from the earliest posts to reach new audiences, including those recently added like Josh’s network  \n    - This strategy leverages existing assets, saving time while keeping the brand visible  \n\n- **New content ideas will depend on the completion of ongoing projects**, with sensitivity around timing and confidentiality limiting immediate creation (15:00)  \n    - Michael explained that upcoming articles could form series that mirror website content once projects conclude  \n    - The team agreed to focus on repurposing until fresh material becomes available  \n    - This cautious approach balances content relevance with operational realities  \n\n## **Analytics Reporting and Next Steps**\n\nThe analytics process is advancing, with plans for comprehensive reporting and integration of existing client data to enhance insights.  \n\n- **Taylor will send the first set of survey stats by Friday, covering all platforms and initial responses** to provide a clearer picture of survey performance (02:47)  \n    - This report replaces visuals that could not load due to Google issues during the meeting  \n    - Michael expressed eagerness to review the data and monitor trends as responses grow  \n\n- **A new analyst is working on compiling data from 18-19 existing client data sets**, broadening the analytics base beyond survey results (06:36)  \n    - This additional data will help validate survey findings and enrich overall insight quality  \n    - Michael suggested using AI tools like ChatGPT to streamline report writing and speed delivery  \n    - The target is to produce a report by the **end of November** for distribution to survey participants and internal use  \n\n- **The December survey adjustments will be incorporated smoothly**, including changes to questions and lists as discussed (07:41)  \n    - Michael and Baylee agreed on these updates to improve data accuracy and relevance  \n    - The goal is to maintain momentum and continuously refine survey quality for better business impact  \n\n## **Technical and Operational Coordination**\n\nThe team is managing technical challenges and workflow adjustments to keep outreach and analytics on track despite system limitations and health challenges.  \n\n- **The team encountered domain issues affecting Lemlist dispatches but resolved them quickly**, keeping survey outreach on schedule (04:48)  \n    - Taylor assured that Lemlist is now functioning as planned, with data feeding into HubSpot without issues  \n    - Michael’s review confirmed limited early distribution but expressed confidence in progress  \n\n- **Workload distribution is affected by team health and onboarding of new members**, requiring flexible coordination (01:19)  \n    - Michael noted Josh’s absence due to illness and busy schedules handling new client challenges with legacy systems  \n    - The team is bringing in experts to manage technical complexities, ensuring continuity  \n    - This flexibility supports steady progress despite operational hurdles  \n\n- **Content scheduling and analytics reporting are planned with contingency for system outages**, as seen with Google downtime affecting slide decks (02:38)  \n    - Taylor’s commitment to delivering analytics via email ensures no delay in information flow  \n    - This approach mitigates risk of losing momentum in communications and decision-making  \n    - The team maintains proactive communication to adapt to technical constraints effectively","outline":null,"keywords":["Survey Analytics","Company List","Job Titles","Social Media Content","Client Data Sets","HubSpot Integration"],"overview":"- **Survey Adjustments:** Shortened survey interval to 8 days aims for at least 20 valuable responses by month-end.\n\n- **Centralized Tracking:** All survey data is integrated into HubSpot for streamlined reporting and analysis from multiple platforms.\n\n- **Client Targeting Refinement:** Approved list focuses on 5,300 relevant companies, targeting mid-sized firms for better engagement.\n\n- **Content Strategy:** Scheduled posts through December using repurposed content to maintain engagement until new material is available.\n\n- **Analytics Reporting:** First survey stats report due Friday, with a comprehensive data analysis target by end of November.  \n\n- **Technical Coordination:** Resolved domain issues maintain outreach schedule; flexible workload management supports progress amid team health challenges.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend analytic data and survey stats in a recap email post-meeting and follow up with more detailed survey data on Friday (01:58)\nPrepare backup newsletter draft from last month in case survey stats are not ready (02:30)\nAdjust survey reminder interval from 14 days to 8 days to allow for quicker follow-up and better response timing (03:30)\nContinue compiling and refining the second edition of the company list based on industry filters and job titles for future outreach (08:50)\nSchedule organic social media posts by repurposing older content starting from the beginning of the archive through December (14:40)\n\n**Michael Jones**\nReview incoming survey responses and provide input on company list filters and job titles to maximize outreach quality (08:30)\nCoordinate internally to finalize analytical question sets and reporting process using existing client data sets for November report delivery (06:00)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nAssist with refining company size criterion for targeting due to public data reliability issues and support survey rollout and follow-up as discussed (09:40)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"db51696c-abcf-4ce2-9283-628b3de712fc","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
    '2025-11-13 18:28:59.304533+00',
    '2025-11-13 18:28:59.304533+00'
  )
  RETURNING meeting_id, contract_id
)
INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new)',
  '## **Survey Launch and Data Collection**

The team adjusted the survey timeline to maximize responses before the end of the month, aiming for efficient data collection and meaningful insights.  

- **The survey interval was shortened from 14 to 8 days** between initial and reminder messages to complete lists by month-end and improve response rates (02:47)  
    - This change allows sending reminders earlier, increasing chances of more responses within the month  
    - Taylor explained this adjustment to fit better with the team’s goal of timely data compilation  
    - Michael supported flexibility on timing, emphasizing response quality over strict schedules  
    - Expected outcome is to reach at least **20 responses**, enough to draw solid conclusions on client challenges  

- **Survey responses are tracked centrally in HubSpot**, integrating data from Lemlist and Heyreach2 platforms for unified analysis (08:13)  
    - Taylor confirmed all form data funnels into HubSpot for streamlined reporting  
    - Michael praised HubSpot’s ease of use for quick result reviews and assessment  
    - Initial survey phase yielded **4 responses**, viewed positively as a start by Michael, highlighting statistical value even at low counts  
    - The team plans to send the compiled report to respondents immediately and invite follow-up participation  

- **Future survey cadence may shift to quarterly or semi-annual to avoid respondent fatigue** with too frequent monthly surveys (06:36)  
    - Michael raised this as a potential adjustment based on feedback and practical engagement  
    - This approach aims to maintain survey effectiveness while respecting audience bandwidth  

## **Client List Management and Targeting Strategy**

The team is refining the client company list for outreach, focusing on relevant industries and appropriate contact roles to optimize engagement quality.  

- **A filtered list excluding irrelevant industries was approved**, improving targeting precision and avoiding unproductive outreach (08:28)  
    - Michael noted some mismatches in initial industry classifications and welcomed the exclusion of sectors like chemicals and unrelated retail  
    - Baylee and Taylor are tasked with incorporating company codes and refining the list for future campaigns  
    - This curated list covers approximately **5,300 companies**, offering a broad yet targeted reach  

- **Company size is used as the main filter instead of revenue, with a focus on firms sized 15 million USD and above** (09:59)  
    - Baylee highlighted revenue data’s unreliability and the preference for company size as a more accurate metric  
    - Michael endorsed avoiding mega-companies and focusing on mid-sized firms for better engagement chances  
    - The list aims to capture the right balance of scale and relevance for business impact  

- **Contact role selection emphasizes key decision-makers like CFOs and CTOs, reflecting evolving organizational structures** (11:50)  
    - Michael shared insights on unusual titles emerging in larger firms, underscoring the importance of targeting the right roles  
    - He suggested aiming for at least **four relevant job titles per company** to ensure broad but focused outreach  
    - A follow-up meeting is planned to review the list and roles to refine messaging and maximize connection effectiveness  

## **Content Strategy for Organic Social Media**

The existing content library will be repurposed extensively to maintain consistent social media presence while awaiting new material.  

- **Posts are scheduled through December using repurposed content from previous months**, ensuring continuous engagement without needing immediate new topics (13:15)  
    - Taylor confirmed that new curated posts will conclude this week, then older content will be recycled  
    - Michael directed to start from the earliest posts to reach new audiences, including those recently added like Josh’s network  
    - This strategy leverages existing assets, saving time while keeping the brand visible  

- **New content ideas will depend on the completion of ongoing projects**, with sensitivity around timing and confidentiality limiting immediate creation (15:00)  
    - Michael explained that upcoming articles could form series that mirror website content once projects conclude  
    - The team agreed to focus on repurposing until fresh material becomes available  
    - This cautious approach balances content relevance with operational realities  

## **Analytics Reporting and Next Steps**

The analytics process is advancing, with plans for comprehensive reporting and integration of existing client data to enhance insights.  

- **Taylor will send the first set of survey stats by Friday, covering all platforms and initial responses** to provide a clearer picture of survey performance (02:47)  
    - This report replaces visuals that could not load due to Google issues during the meeting  
    - Michael expressed eagerness to review the data and monitor trends as responses grow  

- **A new analyst is working on compiling data from 18-19 existing client data sets**, broadening the analytics base beyond survey results (06:36)  
    - This additional data will help validate survey findings and enrich overall insight quality  
    - Michael suggested using AI tools like ChatGPT to streamline report writing and speed delivery  
    - The target is to produce a report by the **end of November** for distribution to survey participants and internal use  

- **The December survey adjustments will be incorporated smoothly**, including changes to questions and lists as discussed (07:41)  
    - Michael and Baylee agreed on these updates to improve data accuracy and relevance  
    - The goal is to maintain momentum and continuously refine survey quality for better business impact  

## **Technical and Operational Coordination**

The team is managing technical challenges and workflow adjustments to keep outreach and analytics on track despite system limitations and health challenges.  

- **The team encountered domain issues affecting Lemlist dispatches but resolved them quickly**, keeping survey outreach on schedule (04:48)  
    - Taylor assured that Lemlist is now functioning as planned, with data feeding into HubSpot without issues  
    - Michael’s review confirmed limited early distribution but expressed confidence in progress  

- **Workload distribution is affected by team health and onboarding of new members**, requiring flexible coordination (01:19)  
    - Michael noted Josh’s absence due to illness and busy schedules handling new client challenges with legacy systems  
    - The team is bringing in experts to manage technical complexities, ensuring continuity  
    - This flexibility supports steady progress despite operational hurdles  

- **Content scheduling and analytics reporting are planned with contingency for system outages**, as seen with Google downtime affecting slide decks (02:38)  
    - Taylor’s commitment to delivering analytics via email ensures no delay in information flow  
    - This approach mitigates risk of losing momentum in communications and decision-making  
    - The team maintains proactive communication to adapt to technical constraints effectively',
  '2025-11-12 20:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send analytic data and survey stats in a recap email post-meeting and follow up with more detailed survey data on Friday (01:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare backup newsletter draft from last month in case survey stats are not ready (02:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Adjust survey reminder interval from 14 days to 8 days to allow for quicker follow-up and better response timing (03:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue compiling and refining the second edition of the company list based on industry filters and job titles for future outreach (08:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Schedule organic social media posts by repurposing older content starting from the beginning of the archive through December (14:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Review incoming survey responses and provide input on company list filters and job titles to maximize outreach quality (08:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate internally to finalize analytical question sets and reporting process using existing client data sets for November report delivery (06:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist with refining company size criterion for targeting due to public data reliability issues and support survey rollout and follow-up as discussed (09:40)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Techmode+ New North (2025-11-12 20:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'b1f3ae44-0316-492e-aef1-bb260b814482',
    '2025-11-12 20:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9QYRQ3505XSEJBGWY4XDH2T',
    'Techmode+ New North',
    '{"Matthew Look","Colin Costigan","Lindsay Hall","Ryan Fisher"}'::text[],
    10840,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NjEzNzdiMDAtMzIyNi00NzgxLWIwOTYtODBjZWQ4NjljZGM3@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4","Oid":"e804fbe9-a623-4d26-a887-992e62fb92d1"}',
    '{"id":"01K9QYRQ3505XSEJBGWY4XDH2T","title":"Techmode+ New North","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and SEO Performance**\n\nThe team confirmed steady growth in keyword rankings, demonstrating progress in content marketing efforts.  \n\n- **Tech Mode currently ranks for 301 keywords**, up from about 180 keywords a few months ago, showing clear improvement in organic search visibility (02:18)  \n    - Lindsay Hall highlighted this positive trend as a sign of growing content impact  \n    - Compared to competitors, RingCentral ranks for around **80,000 keywords** and 8x8 ranks for about **60,000 keywords**, underscoring the gap Tech Mode aims to close  \n    - Matthew Look emphasized the need to keep increasing output, using his combined AI and manual writing system to produce blog posts in about **15 minutes** each  \n    - This scalable content approach is expected to accelerate keyword growth and improve competitive positioning  \n\n- The team discussed a strategic shift toward targeted blog posts focused on competitor replacement topics to capture organic traffic more effectively (25:14)  \n    - Matthew proposed creating **four blog posts about replacing RingCentral** to tap into organic search interest where competitors aggressively bid on ads  \n    - Colin Costigan noted that \"top 10 alternatives\" style articles perform well and could help Tech Mode rank for these competitive themes  \n    - The approach offers a lower-cost alternative to bidding wars in paid ads, leveraging organic content to disrupt competitor dominance  \n    - The team agreed this strategy could bypass heavy ad spend and attract high-intent visitors through relevant, well-placed blog content  \n\n## **Advertising Campaign Management and Optimization**\n\nThe meeting addressed critical updates and decisions around Google Ads campaigns, focusing on efficiency and budget controls.  \n\n- The team gained **admin access to Google Performance Max (PMAX)** campaigns and implemented lead scoring to improve ad targeting and conversion quality (07:20)  \n    - Colin explained the new automation will flag unqualified leads and report them back to Google to reduce wasted spending on low-value traffic  \n    - High-quality leads will be scored as valuable conversions to help Google''s AI optimize for better prospects moving forward  \n    - Matthew supported this feedback loop to enhance campaign ROI despite some skepticism about AI accuracy in lead classification  \n\n- The **RingCentral paid search campaign was reviewed and deemed ineffective**, leading to the decision to pause it (20:18)  \n    - Over **six weeks, 13 clicks cost nearly $300 with zero conversions**, and the campaign was already optimized to a **98% score**  \n    - Colin noted the competition from RingCentral and 8x8 bid aggressively, pushing Tech Mode’s ads lower in placement and reducing click-through rates  \n    - Matthew and Lindsay agreed the limited budget meant continuing the campaign risked wasting funds better used elsewhere  \n    - Pausing will free resources potentially toward content marketing and other campaigns with stronger returns  \n\n- The team discussed the **removal of Google Ads’ account-level daily or monthly spend caps**, which complicates budget control (13:04)  \n    - Colin confirmed Google replaced this with daily campaign limits only, removing a fail-safe against overspending  \n    - Matthew stressed the need to find alternative controls or monitoring to prevent runaway budgets in future campaign disruptions  \n    - Colin committed to researching and reporting back on any possible workarounds or tools to manage overall spend caps  \n\n- Adding **site links to the PMAX campaign was approved** to enhance ad assets and improve click engagement (16:50)  \n    - Lindsay noted existing site links have generated some clicks, and Google suggested adding up to 12 site links per campaign  \n    - Colin confirmed site links are present but can be expanded, supporting the team’s plan to bolster ad visibility and user navigation  \n\n## **Lead Tracking and Reporting Improvements**\n\nEfforts are underway to enhance lead source accuracy and reporting consistency across marketing channels.  \n\n- Lindsay raised concerns about incomplete lead source data affecting the accuracy of lead reports, especially for non-paid sources (09:00)  \n    - She struggles to get organic and direct leads to appear reliably in tracking reports despite manual source corrections  \n    - Colin suggested that the system might prioritize the most recent traffic source over the original, shifting the attribution logic  \n    - They agreed to investigate further with specific lead examples Lindsay will provide via email for deeper troubleshooting  \n\n- The team confirmed the **fix of a Gravity Forms AJAX issue** that previously allowed form submissions without required emails, improving lead data quality (08:41)  \n    - This correction is expected to reduce incomplete or junk leads entering the system  \n    - Lindsay expressed confidence this fix resolves prior form inconsistencies  \n\n## **Operational Resource Management and Workflows**\n\nThe team reviewed current resource balances and discussed maintaining clear communication on workload and priorities.  \n\n- Colin reported a **positive balance of 28 points** available for website management and ads, with additional points ready for new campaigns or landing pages (30:18)  \n    - This points system tracks workload and capacity for Tech Mode’s outsourced support, ensuring clarity on available resources  \n    - Matthew requested ongoing updates on point status at the start of future calls to better plan and allocate work  \n    - The team agreed to potentially task Colin with exploring new campaign opportunities after pausing the RingCentral campaign  \n\n- Colin shared personal scheduling notes, indicating unavailability during Thanksgiving week due to travel (33:57)  \n    - The team acknowledged and planned around this absence smoothly  \n\n## **Competitive and Market Insights**\n\nDiscussions revealed key market dynamics influencing Tech Mode’s marketing and product positioning strategies.  \n\n- The **paid search landscape for RingCentral-related keywords is dominated by RingCentral and Dial Pad**, with few other advertisers and mostly organic content filling the rest of the search results (24:18)  \n    - Matthew observed competitor ad budgets are significantly higher, making direct paid competition costly and inefficient for Tech Mode  \n    - Organic articles and community posts (e.g., Reddit threads) rank highly and attract attention, presenting an opportunity for Tech Mode to target these spaces with relevant content  \n    - Colin noted the unusual speed at which Reddit posts can rank on Google, highlighting the importance of monitoring emerging organic channels  \n\n- Privacy and data restrictions, such as the shift from Universal Analytics to GA4, have reduced visibility into search term data and campaign insights (22:42)  \n    - Lindsay and Colin agreed this complicates marketing efforts and requires adapting tracking and attribution methods going forward  \n    - They anticipate more stringent compliance laws resembling Europe’s GDPR by 2028, increasing the need for creative data strategies  \n\n## **Team Collaboration and Culture**\n\nThe team maintained a positive and adaptive culture while balancing workload and project priorities.  \n\n- Matthew and Colin shared personal stories and humor about self-driving cars and golf, fostering camaraderie and morale (03:33, 31:24)  \n- Lindsay expressed appreciation for AI tools that save time on content creation and link-building, supporting efficiency gains (28:13)  \n- The group discussed travel and personal plans openly, reinforcing a supportive and flexible team environment (33:53)","outline":null,"keywords":["PMAX campaign","lead tracking","Google Ads budget","RingCentral replacement","blog posts","keyword rankings"],"overview":"- **Keyword Growth:** Tech Mode now ranks for **301 keywords**, up from **180**, enhancing organic search visibility.  \n\n- **Competitor Strategies:** Proposed four blog posts on replacing **RingCentral**, aiming to attract organic traffic and reduce ad spend.  \n\n- **Ad Campaign Changes:** The **RingCentral paid search campaign** paused after **13 clicks costing nearly $300 with zero conversions**.  \n\n- **Budget Control Issues:** Google removed account-level spend caps, complicating budget management for future campaigns.  \n\n- **Lead Tracking Improvements:** Fix on Gravity Forms AJAX issue now improves lead data quality and reduces junk leads.  \n\n- **Market Landscape Insights:** Paid search for RingCentral keywords dominated by **RingCentral and Dial Pad**, emphasizing need for organic content strategies.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide guidance on how to set daily or monthly budget caps or alternatives in Google Ads after confirmation (12:30)\nSend updates via email regarding progress on lead source tracking and form link best practices (09:04)\nContinue monitoring and reporting point balances and campaign management progress on subsequent calls (29:59)\nAssist with adding more site links to the PMAX campaign as discussed (18:50)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nIdentify specific example leads to help diagnose lead source reporting discrepancies and email Colin with details (11:20)\nAdd additional site links (approximately 2 or more) to the PMAX Google Ads campaign (19:30)\nWrite four blog posts focusing on ''RingCentral replacement'' topics to improve organic search rankings (26:30)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nContinue producing blog content using AI-assisted tools to support content marketing efforts (03:14)\nBegin drafting the specified RingCentral replacement blog posts as next content project (26:27)\n"},"duration":180.6699981689453,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Matthew Look"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"id":3,"name":"Ryan Fisher"}],"sentences":[{"text":"We got a pretty big amount of snow over the weekend, but been sunny the last couple days.","index":0,"end_time":5.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But it still hasn''t all melted off yet so, you know, otherwise can''t complain.","index":1,"end_time":11.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.88,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But I will anyways.","index":2,"end_time":12.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Welcome back from your vacation, Colin.","index":3,"end_time":17.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15.919,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"At.","index":4,"end_time":19.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your super woke company that gives the government holiday.","index":5,"end_time":23.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":24.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''S what we have, man.","index":7,"end_time":28.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s all government holidays.","index":8,"end_time":30.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":9,"end_time":31.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We don''t have the typical.","index":10,"end_time":33.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know how many agencies you''ve worked with, but agencies typically do like half of December.","index":11,"end_time":38.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They just take off.","index":12,"end_time":39.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do not do that.","index":13,"end_time":41.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we''re in the wrong business.","index":14,"end_time":44.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.13,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, I''m getting pretty good at this marketing thing.","index":15,"end_time":46.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.41,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Lindsay, you and I, let''s just go into business and we can start taking half of December off.","index":16,"end_time":50.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.41,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Sign me up.","index":17,"end_time":52.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.29,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Sign me up.","index":18,"end_time":53.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":53.24,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I will take off half of December.","index":19,"end_time":55.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":53.84,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That would be fine.","index":20,"end_time":57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":56.04,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"How are you guys doing?","index":21,"end_time":59.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good for being a holiday yesterday, Ryan.","index":22,"end_time":61.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.56,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It sure wasn''t slow.","index":23,"end_time":62.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It was not.","index":24,"end_time":64.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":63.4,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It was not.","index":25,"end_time":66.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":65.56,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Service was busy all day.","index":26,"end_time":68.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''s typical.","index":27,"end_time":71.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":68.92,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Any fun stories from yesterday, Ryan?","index":28,"end_time":73.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, nothing major.","index":29,"end_time":77.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":76.28,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Like everyone''s coming with a nugget of look how ridiculous this person was.","index":30,"end_time":84.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, usually they can''t talk about that when I''m on the call though.","index":31,"end_time":88.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":85.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Are they talking about you, Matt?","index":32,"end_time":91.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re specifically talking about me.","index":33,"end_time":92.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.4,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s exactly why.","index":34,"end_time":93.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''Ll go through the updates that we have.","index":35,"end_time":100.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the resources page, Lindsey was updated so all tags will show.","index":36,"end_time":104.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can just show a quick preview view of that.","index":37,"end_time":106.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So instead of like the priority five, if they do hit view all, it will expand and show many, many topics.","index":38,"end_time":113.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Love that.","index":39,"end_time":114.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":114.28,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And so it''s fit on mobile and everything.","index":40,"end_time":118.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll say if you want us to limit any of these, just let me know.","index":41,"end_time":121.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this is all categories that are currently in there.","index":42,"end_time":125.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":123.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s pretty freaking good.","index":43,"end_time":129,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, you guys are writing a lot about a lot of different things.","index":44,"end_time":133.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Look at us go.","index":45,"end_time":136.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.59,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I wrote two today.","index":46,"end_time":137.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":47,"end_time":139.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":138.71,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So just as a thought, we''re ranking for like 301 keywords.","index":48,"end_time":144.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":139.27,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And I was like, oh, we''re doing pretty good, right?","index":49,"end_time":146.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":144.39,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Like that''s good.","index":50,"end_time":146.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":146.27,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You know, I''m looking at stuff going up.","index":51,"end_time":148.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":146.99,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Ring social ranks for 80,000 keywords.","index":52,"end_time":151.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":148.87,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":152.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just to put things in perspective.","index":54,"end_time":154.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":152.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I gotta get to writing.","index":55,"end_time":155.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.47,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, keep writing.","index":56,"end_time":157.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.07,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That''s all we can do.","index":57,"end_time":159.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":158.07,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Keep writing.","index":58,"end_time":160.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":159.51,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"How many we ranked for?","index":59,"end_time":162.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.51,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"301.","index":60,"end_time":164.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":163.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I mean that''s something.","index":61,"end_time":166.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.95,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Gotta start somewhere.","index":62,"end_time":167.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.07,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s better than we were a few months ago.","index":63,"end_time":169.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":167.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We were, you know, like 180something a few months ago.","index":64,"end_time":171.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":169.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So.","index":65,"end_time":172.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.99,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"How many can you see?","index":66,"end_time":176.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.19,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How many eight by eights rating for?","index":67,"end_time":177.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s like 60,000.","index":68,"end_time":179.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s less than ring central, but it''s still a lot.","index":69,"end_time":182.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.63,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"God damn it.","index":70,"end_time":184.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.43,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"See if I can pull that up.","index":71,"end_time":186.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":185.51,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m gonna take all of December off and just write.","index":72,"end_time":188.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.59,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, says it''s cool.","index":73,"end_time":192.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":74,"end_time":192.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got my system down now, Colin.","index":75,"end_time":197.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I got.","index":76,"end_time":197.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.51,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I use tofu and then I have an AI agent too that I use.","index":77,"end_time":201.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.83,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But I use the two of them together to basically pump out a blog post in about 15 minutes.","index":78,"end_time":206.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.19,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s like vibe coding but for writing blogs.","index":79,"end_time":208.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, kind of.","index":80,"end_time":210.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It kind of is.","index":81,"end_time":213.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Let''s just have all of these LLMs talk to each other.","index":82,"end_time":215.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t quite get it to do.","index":83,"end_time":217.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.4,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I can''t get either one of them to do exactly what I want in itself.","index":84,"end_time":220.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But if I use the two and I''m the manual, I just got to get a robot to sit in my computer and key that shit in together.","index":85,"end_time":227.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean we got self driving cars and all sorts of stuff so I don''t imagine we''re too far away from robots.","index":86,"end_time":232.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, my self driving car tried to kill me the other day.","index":87,"end_time":235.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.44,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t know how well that''s working.","index":88,"end_time":237.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":235.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Wait, do you have a Tesla?","index":89,"end_time":239.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I don''t.","index":90,"end_time":241.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.48,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I have a GM car and it''s got self driving on highway.","index":91,"end_time":244.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s got self driving all the time, but it really works decent on the highway.","index":92,"end_time":248.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.87,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But did not want to move over for those barrels.","index":93,"end_time":251.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like the barrels were closing in and shutting my lane down and it was standing right there.","index":94,"end_time":256.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And when you grab the wheel when it''s driving you like gotta like.","index":95,"end_time":258.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like a fighter pilot trying to pull up, you know, you gotta like wrestle it away from it and then it''s like oh, you want it?","index":96,"end_time":264.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.87,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right, I''ll give it to you.","index":97,"end_time":265.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.75,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But it''s really like that.","index":98,"end_time":268.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.95,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You like you''re pulling that thing up trying to get it back.","index":99,"end_time":271.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Because self driving does not like to.","index":100,"end_time":273.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.43,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"To give up early.","index":101,"end_time":274.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Give it up.","index":102,"end_time":275.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Say I also have a GM car.","index":103,"end_time":277.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":275.72,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s not that fancy.","index":104,"end_time":278.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.36,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It doesn''t have full self drive, it just has lane assist.","index":105,"end_time":280.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.36,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So every time I try to try and change lanes without my blinker, it''s like oh, you don''t want to do that.","index":106,"end_time":285.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":281.16,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So I have to like.","index":107,"end_time":286.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":285.24,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, like really?","index":108,"end_time":287.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.2,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, like it now I really wanna, I really want to.","index":109,"end_time":290.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.72,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Please don''t stop me.","index":110,"end_time":291.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":290.8,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, I turned that off in my wife''s car because it kept vibrating different sides of the seat.","index":111,"end_time":296.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it does that.","index":112,"end_time":299,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I was talking about waymos though, Matt.","index":113,"end_time":302.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Self driving cars, the ones that are truly no one in them doing anything.","index":114,"end_time":307.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think I get in one.","index":115,"end_time":309,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":307.64,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Honestly, I don''t think I would.","index":116,"end_time":310.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":309,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":117,"end_time":313.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve seen some of the videos online.","index":118,"end_time":315.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.2,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean the thing of it, I could talk about all this kind of for a while but it were all those self driving things work well as long as everybody''s not self driving.","index":119,"end_time":323.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":315.56,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":120,"end_time":324.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.12,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Because other humans correct for the errors of the self driving cars.","index":121,"end_time":328.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Which works fine today.","index":122,"end_time":329.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.13,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But when they''re all self driving cars it''s going to be a fucking mess because you see self driving cars cut people off and you know, do all kinds of crazy shit.","index":123,"end_time":337.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That I saw a video, it was like 30 Waymo cars all trying to pull into the same airport parking lot and like they all got stuck there for like two hours because they were just like beeping at each other.","index":124,"end_time":349.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":337.89,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But like no one''s doing anything because they''re kind of it.","index":125,"end_time":352.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.33,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"They''re being too polite to each other.","index":126,"end_time":353.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":354.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":354.05,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"What I''ve also noticed is especially if you drive it on the highway, self driving does not give a shit about what''s in the road unless it''s a human.","index":128,"end_time":360.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like it could be a big piece of fucking metal.","index":129,"end_time":363.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.01,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It is not sliding left or right.","index":130,"end_time":365.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s going to run that shit right over.","index":131,"end_time":366.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Animal doesn''t care.","index":132,"end_time":368.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.09,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All that shit.","index":133,"end_time":369.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.85,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s just going to destroy your tires.","index":134,"end_time":371.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So yeah, I''ll describe myself.","index":135,"end_time":375.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.97,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":136,"end_time":375.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.09,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, same.","index":137,"end_time":376.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other we did swap out the Amazon connect pages.","index":138,"end_time":380.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lindsey.","index":139,"end_time":381.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome, thank you.","index":140,"end_time":382.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":381.84,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So that''s up to date and we ran through and we put the old one to draft just in case there''s anything any reason to check it but.","index":141,"end_time":389.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we ran the URL through Ahrefs to make sure there''s no broken links from anything.","index":142,"end_time":395.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":143,"end_time":396.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.84,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So we''re all set there.","index":144,"end_time":397.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Quick question about that.","index":145,"end_time":398.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":397.76,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Related to links, should I be doing just like slash and then like the link or should I be hard coding like a whole link?","index":146,"end_time":404.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":398.8,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Techmo.com like when I''m creating links on the website this.","index":147,"end_time":407.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":404.72,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Is that going to cause problems for me later if they''re.","index":148,"end_time":409.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.63,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":149,"end_time":410.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You should be able to just do a slash or if you''re doing links also the page should pop up when you''re putting in a URL.","index":150,"end_time":416.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, when I, you.","index":151,"end_time":418.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":417.23,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"When I do the like when I build a link in the WordPress or whatever, you know, I usually do a search to find the page that I want.","index":152,"end_time":424.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.19,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That is what is hard coding the link.","index":153,"end_time":427.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":425.31,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s not putting the slash like it''s doing the slash, but it''s doing the www.techmode it''s doing the whole thing.","index":154,"end_time":432.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":427.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So I just want to make sure that wasn''t gonna cause a problem.","index":155,"end_time":434.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Problem.","index":156,"end_time":434.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":434.29,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, slash works if it''s like still techmode.com.","index":157,"end_time":437.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"right.","index":158,"end_time":437.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":159,"end_time":438.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":437.77,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And then for the PMAX stuff, since we, since Google decided that they were done messing with everyone and we have admin access again, we did set up the lead scoring for the crap leads that had come in.","index":160,"end_time":455.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re also going to build an automation for it.","index":161,"end_time":457.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we''re going to do is anytime that you guys mark a lead unqualified and they are from Google Ads, it''ll automatically go into a spreadsheet and report back to Google Ads.","index":162,"end_time":467.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pmax.","index":163,"end_time":467.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":164,"end_time":468.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.19,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So what do we gain by that?","index":165,"end_time":471.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.15,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What do we gain by doing those report backs?","index":166,"end_time":474.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So basically since PMAX is, it''s all AI and machine learning, so it is understanding who is a valued conversion versus who is not.","index":167,"end_time":484.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re basically saying all these ones that have come in that are junk are 0 out of 100 don''t show to people like that anymore.","index":168,"end_time":490.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":484.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then when we have quality conversions come in and we rank them 100 because they became a very high paying customer to tech mode, then it''ll replicate those leads.","index":169,"end_time":499.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":170,"end_time":500.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.19,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And basically, so Google''s going to be like, don''t, we''re going to be like, don''t show it to scammers.","index":171,"end_time":508.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And then the scammers are going to be like, oh, oh, I''m a scammer.","index":172,"end_time":512.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.15,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s going to know who''s a scammer and who''s not.","index":173,"end_time":514.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.83,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I guess it''s, it''s all some hypothetical bullshit.","index":174,"end_time":517.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.83,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So we''ll see what happens.","index":175,"end_time":518.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Can''t hurt to report it.","index":176,"end_time":520.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.48,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I''m in.","index":177,"end_time":521.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.64,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":178,"end_time":521.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Lindsay, we also fixed the, there was a gravity form AJAX issue that was not requiring the email.","index":179,"end_time":528,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we fixed that.","index":180,"end_time":528.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":181,"end_time":530.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":529.4,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":182,"end_time":531.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":530.52,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That should take care, Chris.","index":183,"end_time":533.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.44,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That should take care of those funky forms that we were getting where they weren''t.","index":184,"end_time":536.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":533.52,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"They didn''t have to like fill in all the information.","index":185,"end_time":539.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":537.32,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Right.","index":186,"end_time":540.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That should fix that issue.","index":187,"end_time":541.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.84,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And that is everything that I had from last week and this morning.","index":188,"end_time":547.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, Lindsay, I think that was all of your email as well.","index":189,"end_time":551.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":190,"end_time":553.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":552.93,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Let me see, let me see.","index":191,"end_time":554.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.53,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right.","index":192,"end_time":557.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":557.01,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Blog topics.","index":193,"end_time":558.209,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":557.41,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yes.","index":194,"end_time":558.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.209,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Amazon.","index":195,"end_time":559.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.85,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yes.","index":196,"end_time":559.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":559.49,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":197,"end_time":560.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.13,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Leads not popping up.","index":198,"end_time":564.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.85,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yes.","index":199,"end_time":564.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":564.49,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":200,"end_time":566.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":566.29,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"In the email that I sent you the other day, I mentioned asking questions about the different source fields that you guys are using, like in your like form processes and stuff like that.","index":201,"end_time":578.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.09,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m having a hard time getting accurate and complete data on all of the leads that we have coming in.","index":202,"end_time":586.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":579.21,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So through the various different sources, whether they''re direct, they came from an ad or whatever, I''m having a hard time getting them all to show up in my lead report that I''ve created.","index":203,"end_time":599.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.29,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":204,"end_time":600.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":600.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just was curious if it''s related to the source.","index":205,"end_time":605.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.44,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Do you have an example of someone that should be in a list and they''re not?","index":206,"end_time":609.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, I should have known you were going to ask me that.","index":207,"end_time":612.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.4,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Can read me like a book.","index":208,"end_time":617.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I shouldn''t know when you were going to ask me that.","index":209,"end_time":620.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.08,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m going to have to find one.","index":210,"end_time":621.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.28,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But just for example, I will show you the report that I built and maybe we''ll be able to tell a little bit from there.","index":211,"end_time":629.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":623.14,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So, lead report this month.","index":212,"end_time":634.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":631.38,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"These.","index":213,"end_time":636.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.62,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So far there''s been five of them and they''ve all come from paid search.","index":214,"end_time":642.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":636.02,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But I want.","index":215,"end_time":643.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.58,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''ve had a couple that came in from, you know, organic or direct, and I want to be able to get them to show up here.","index":216,"end_time":650.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.46,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Now, I did go in and change their original.","index":217,"end_time":653.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.02,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Like have their original traffic source set to the correct source, whether it was direct or whatever it was.","index":218,"end_time":659.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.14,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But they are still not showing up in my lead form.","index":219,"end_time":661.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.42,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So the paid search, whatever the tracking that you guys have set up on, that is working fantastically, But I want my other lead sources to have fantastic tracking as well.","index":220,"end_time":674.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.7,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":675.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My gut is that it''s.","index":222,"end_time":677.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It might be someone that.","index":223,"end_time":678.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not their original, but it''s.","index":224,"end_time":681.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They converted most recently.","index":225,"end_time":684.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it might be a latest traffic source.","index":226,"end_time":686.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":227,"end_time":687.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687.11,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So checking that right now.","index":228,"end_time":690.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":689.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Organic, that''s.","index":229,"end_time":692.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.109,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s something I didn''t think of.","index":230,"end_time":693.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.51,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So that''ll send me in a new direction.","index":231,"end_time":695.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":693.83,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":232,"end_time":695.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":695.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I should be able to add that.","index":233,"end_time":705.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":704.56,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Sorry, are you still looking at that?","index":234,"end_time":743.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.85,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":235,"end_time":744.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Didn''t change the numbers too much.","index":236,"end_time":746.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to identify a person that I can like work backwards.","index":237,"end_time":752.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll find a person and an email about you.","index":238,"end_time":755.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.49,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Email.","index":239,"end_time":755.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.52,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Email you about this separately.","index":240,"end_time":757.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.83,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":758.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another question that we had for this meeting today is, is there a way to cap our overall budget, overall daily spend or monthly spend on AdWords separate from the individual campaigns?","index":242,"end_time":773.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":759.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So I know that we.","index":243,"end_time":775.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.15,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You used to be able to set like an account limit per day or an account limit per month.","index":244,"end_time":779.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.19,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Is that still a feature?","index":245,"end_time":781.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":779.83,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Because we were not able to find it.","index":246,"end_time":783.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":781.51,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m fairly certain it is.","index":247,"end_time":785.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt and I both googled it and got different answers and neither.","index":248,"end_time":792.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":788.79,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Neither one of them correct.","index":249,"end_time":793.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":792.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":250,"end_time":794.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.07,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Google did not tell us where to change it within itself.","index":251,"end_time":797.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.03,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It Google Totally effed up.","index":252,"end_time":799.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.79,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I''d love to be able to set just like a cap as kind of like a fail safe.","index":253,"end_time":807.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.23,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Like just.","index":254,"end_time":807.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":807.47,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":255,"end_time":808.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s because they changed it to their.","index":256,"end_time":810.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":808.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a daily spend limit instead of like, don''t go over this and you have to do like Daily Times 30 to come to that number.","index":257,"end_time":818.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you just find out where it''s at and let us know?","index":258,"end_time":822.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":259,"end_time":822.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way, I mean, we don''t need you to change it.","index":260,"end_time":825.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Just get it to us.","index":261,"end_time":826.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That way we can dick with it and play with it again.","index":262,"end_time":829.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''re just thinking down the road like that, you know, the screw up with Google ever happens.","index":263,"end_time":833.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.4,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Something like that happens again, we want to be able to have like a fail safe capability.","index":264,"end_time":838,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Mm.","index":265,"end_time":838.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because ideally we don''t want to spend all our daily budgets every day by.","index":266,"end_time":843.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":840.47,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":267,"end_time":846.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They removed the account wide budget cap.","index":268,"end_time":849.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why we can''t find it.","index":269,"end_time":851.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":849.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":270,"end_time":851.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":851.27,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":271,"end_time":853.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":852.31,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"They did it just before they shut us all down for seven days so they could hit their quarterly numbers.","index":272,"end_time":858.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"There were some horror stories of people whose budget completely spiraled out of control and got absolutely no answers.","index":273,"end_time":865.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.63,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No response from Google.","index":274,"end_time":867.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.99,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Did.","index":275,"end_time":868.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.89,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Did our tickets just get closed and that was it?","index":276,"end_time":871.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.93,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No explanation or nothing said anything?","index":277,"end_time":873.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.09,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, they said that they would, you know, somebody would message me back in a couple of days.","index":278,"end_time":877.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.37,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I then responded to that and like added some more information.","index":279,"end_time":880.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":877.89,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No one ever responded to that.","index":280,"end_time":882.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":881.09,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And I haven''t received any notice that my ticket was closed either.","index":281,"end_time":885.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.73,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Like literally nothing.","index":282,"end_time":887.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":885.81,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So.","index":283,"end_time":889.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":888.93,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I know you guys are.","index":284,"end_time":891.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, you were sending me some articles too.","index":285,"end_time":893.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":891.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were fine and we were sending each other.","index":286,"end_time":894.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were like, what is going on?","index":287,"end_time":895.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were we the.","index":288,"end_time":897.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Let me guess.","index":289,"end_time":897.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.2,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We were the only ones that you had that were affected by that.","index":290,"end_time":900.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin, I can neither confirm nor deny that.","index":291,"end_time":902.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Close.","index":292,"end_time":906.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":905.96,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Line it up.","index":293,"end_time":908.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.04,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Congratulations to Tech Mode.","index":294,"end_time":912.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":295,"end_time":914.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":913.96,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So thankfully we were in a decent position to not have our budget go out of control.","index":296,"end_time":918.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.52,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, that''s just good management by us to be ready to go, but it''d be nice to have that extra fail safe in and that''s what I''m hoping for.","index":297,"end_time":926.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep, I''m with you.","index":298,"end_time":928.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":927,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then today we would also like to discuss the RingCentral campaign past performance and whether or not we think it makes sense to keep it going.","index":299,"end_time":938.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.12,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You want to pull that up and share it?","index":300,"end_time":941.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.64,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Sure.","index":301,"end_time":942.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":941.72,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You want to do that or do you want to do those pmax ad links first?","index":302,"end_time":948.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":945.56,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We can do the PMAX ad links first.","index":303,"end_time":951.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.64,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Google AdWords so very kindly offered me A suggestion to add site links to the pmax campaign.","index":304,"end_time":961.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":951.64,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It popped up this little thingy here.","index":305,"end_time":964.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":962.04,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So then I hovered over it like, oh, what''s this?","index":306,"end_time":966.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":964.24,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It wants me to put site links on that ad.","index":307,"end_time":969.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.36,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Is there a reason why we don''t have any now or should I just go ahead and add them?","index":308,"end_time":973.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":969.64,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":309,"end_time":974.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":310,"end_time":975.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s prompting me for a password.","index":311,"end_time":976.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"99% sure that we.","index":312,"end_time":981,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, my God.","index":313,"end_time":981.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Two factor authentication, that we set those up with site links.","index":314,"end_time":987.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m surprised that it''s saying there''s not.","index":315,"end_time":990.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It says that there''s not.","index":316,"end_time":994.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":992.48,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Oh, my goodness.","index":317,"end_time":1002.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, now I gotta wait for this code to come through.","index":318,"end_time":1011.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1009.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":319,"end_time":1014.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you click on the settings cog to the left when you''re hovering over the PMAX campaign, it''s like just to the left of that pop up next to the pencil.","index":320,"end_time":1025.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":321,"end_time":1026.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1025.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":322,"end_time":1049.939,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1049.779,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I finally got my two factor to work.","index":323,"end_time":1051.379,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1049.939,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s interesting.","index":324,"end_time":1077.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1076.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sorry.","index":325,"end_time":1079.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you go back to the campaigns page and just click on the pmax and then on the left side should switch to show.","index":326,"end_time":1093.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1079.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":327,"end_time":1093.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Assets.","index":328,"end_time":1094.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then click there.","index":329,"end_time":1096.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1095.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then if you filter for site links, there are campaign site links.","index":330,"end_time":1102.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why I was confused that it''s showing but there''s nothing.","index":331,"end_time":1107.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if I clicks on them.","index":332,"end_time":1109.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.26,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":333,"end_time":1118.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1117.62,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But we can certainly add more.","index":334,"end_time":1125.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1124.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, should we.","index":335,"end_time":1134.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1133.38,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"If it''s given us a suggestion, I would say yes.","index":336,"end_time":1137.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.3,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''ve had some clicks on the site links that exist there already, so I''d say probably, yeah.","index":337,"end_time":1142.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.99,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Download.","index":338,"end_time":1168.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I can go and do that.","index":339,"end_time":1173.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1171.52,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That.","index":340,"end_time":1173.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.04,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m not going to do that from this screen.","index":341,"end_time":1174.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.24,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So I''ll add at least two.","index":342,"end_time":1177.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1175.92,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s suggesting six and I see four there.","index":343,"end_time":1179.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1177.44,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":344,"end_time":1184.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you can go as many as 12.","index":345,"end_time":1185.964,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1184.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"12 in one ad is what they let you do.","index":346,"end_time":1188.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.116,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"My goodness.","index":347,"end_time":1189.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1188.44,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":348,"end_time":1189.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In a campaign.","index":349,"end_time":1190.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oops, sorry.","index":350,"end_time":1192.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1191.11,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, let''s go back to campaigns and take a look at Ringcentral.","index":351,"end_time":1201.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1195.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Do we want a bigger date range than just November?","index":352,"end_time":1207.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Could you just add October as Well?","index":353,"end_time":1211.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A whopping a 13.","index":354,"end_time":1219.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That''s clicks.","index":355,"end_time":1222.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1221.6,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Meanwhile, ago, Colin, you and I.","index":356,"end_time":1224.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.2,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And I don''t have it here.","index":357,"end_time":1225.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I have it on a sticky note at the other house.","index":358,"end_time":1227.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.4,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But we had talked about, you know, a search being worth it at a certain dollar, you know, a certain amount.","index":359,"end_time":1231.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1227.04,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"This one does not seem to be performing for shit.","index":360,"end_time":1236,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":361,"end_time":1236.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s as optimized as it can get.","index":362,"end_time":1238.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"98.","index":363,"end_time":1242.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1241.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":364,"end_time":1242.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know that we can do much better than that.","index":365,"end_time":1244.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I just imagine that competitive like RingCentral and 8x8 and all like they''re just bidding like crazy on these things.","index":366,"end_time":1249.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":367,"end_time":1251.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1251.39,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So we''ve had 13 clicks, 0 conversions, and we''ve spent almost $300.","index":368,"end_time":1256.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1251.75,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"In six weeks.","index":369,"end_time":1259.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.67,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s correct.","index":370,"end_time":1260.829,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1260.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":371,"end_time":1263.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know that this campaign is the best.","index":372,"end_time":1265.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1264.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":373,"end_time":1266.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How much have we spent on this one, Lindsey?","index":374,"end_time":1269.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1267.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"$274.07.","index":375,"end_time":1273.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.71,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So 45 bucks a week.","index":376,"end_time":1276.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.62,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So it''s not like it''s costing us a ton, but I mean, it is pissing away money that we potentially could move somewhere else.","index":377,"end_time":1281.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1276.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yes.","index":378,"end_time":1284.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1283.86,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And almost every click costs us more than what we currently have our daily budget set at.","index":379,"end_time":1290.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.5,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So should we just pause this campaign?","index":380,"end_time":1292.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.42,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yes.","index":381,"end_time":1292.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there any benefit to not pause?","index":382,"end_time":1294.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.98,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, is there any reason we need it?","index":383,"end_time":1295.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.42,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t think it''s doing much for us.","index":384,"end_time":1299.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1297.54,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No.","index":385,"end_time":1299.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1299.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, we put a lot of effort into this one, obviously by our optimization score, but obviously we just can''t compete.","index":386,"end_time":1304.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1299.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Either that or, I mean, you know, you throw a $4,000 a month budget at it, and just to watch the thing destroy your bank account, that feels what this.","index":387,"end_time":1315.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1304.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s what this would feel like.","index":388,"end_time":1316.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1315.26,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I think what I see with 2000 impressions and only 13 clicks, you guys are probably popping up like 4th below, like RingCentral 8 by 8 of I whoever''s bidding on these things.","index":389,"end_time":1325.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1316.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does it show what page we''re showing up on?","index":390,"end_time":1327.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.79,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It does not.","index":391,"end_time":1328.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1328.19,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Motherfucker.","index":392,"end_time":1331.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.43,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Why not?","index":393,"end_time":1331.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They hold.","index":394,"end_time":1331.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They holding back.","index":395,"end_time":1332.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, they don''t tell us that information.","index":396,"end_time":1335.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1333.23,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No, not that I''m aware of.","index":397,"end_time":1338.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1336.11,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No.","index":398,"end_time":1338.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1338.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I think they kind of used to.","index":399,"end_time":1344.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1343.31,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I don''t know, they used to show a lot more information in, especially in Google Analytics.","index":400,"end_time":1349.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1344.71,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You could tie adwords and analytics together and get a lot more information.","index":401,"end_time":1353.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.87,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And I don''t remember what year it was.","index":402,"end_time":1354.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.48,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Maybe like 2015.","index":403,"end_time":1355.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1354.84,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"They were just like, no, you don''t get any of it anymore.","index":404,"end_time":1359.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1355.96,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And the entire SEO industry went crazy.","index":405,"end_time":1361.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1359.24,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it was actually more recent because there was one.","index":406,"end_time":1364.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1362.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They switched from they Sunset Universal analytics and moved to GA4, and that''s when they just decided to get rid of a bunch of stuff.","index":407,"end_time":1369.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1364.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they used to show you what people''s search terms were like, what people typed in and stuff in Google Analytics.","index":408,"end_time":1376.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.56,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I don''t do that anymore.","index":409,"end_time":1377.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1376.76,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, but now people need privacy or something.","index":410,"end_time":1379.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Weird.","index":411,"end_time":1381.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1381.33,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Weird.","index":412,"end_time":1383.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1383.25,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I think.","index":413,"end_time":1384.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1384.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think by 2028, we''re going to have similar compliance laws as Europe.","index":414,"end_time":1389.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1385.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, California is already on the fast track.","index":415,"end_time":1391.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1389.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just makes our job a little more difficult, that''s all.","index":416,"end_time":1398.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1396.53,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Just more pieces to the puzzle.","index":417,"end_time":1401.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we are going to pause this campaign yes.","index":418,"end_time":1406.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1403.33,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Alrighty.","index":419,"end_time":1413.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1413.28,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, it''s just not performing well at all.","index":420,"end_time":1421.839,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1416.64,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So, Ringcentral campaign.","index":421,"end_time":1428.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1422.4,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Sorry, guys, my computer just went to sleep out of nowhere.","index":422,"end_time":1432.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1430.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Oh.","index":423,"e