 so fucking easy, so quick.","index":500,"end_time":1679.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1671.53,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, you saw me pump out those two.","index":501,"end_time":1681.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"One to you today that were one said UCAs, and then I basically just changed it all to say voip.","index":502,"end_time":1686.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, that took me five minutes to completely modify that article to change one or the blog post from one to the other.","index":503,"end_time":1692.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it''s definitely helpful.","index":504,"end_time":1695.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1693.44,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Again, it''s putting links in there too, which is great.","index":505,"end_time":1698.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1695.44,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s saving me a lot of time.","index":506,"end_time":1701.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1699.92,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, that was it on that one.","index":507,"end_time":1703.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1702.56,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So we''re going to pause that one and maybe we just take that.","index":508,"end_time":1706.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1703.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"When we write four blog posts, we see what happens at that point, it doesn''t really cost us anything other than my time.","index":509,"end_time":1712.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1706.56,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Reason number one, it sucks.","index":510,"end_time":1716.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1715.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Reason number two, they''re not us.","index":511,"end_time":1720.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1719.13,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I mean, I could put links into the.","index":512,"end_time":1722.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1721.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What was that website that Colin?","index":513,"end_time":1724.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1722.85,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"His consumer.","index":514,"end_time":1725.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1724.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"His consumers.","index":515,"end_time":1726.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1725.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I can do Reddit threads for days.","index":516,"end_time":1729.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1727.85,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":517,"end_time":1730.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1729.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They''ve all.","index":518,"end_time":1730.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1730.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"There are people on Reddit haters.","index":519,"end_time":1733.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1730.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, they''re haters in general, but.","index":520,"end_time":1735.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1733.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Mm.","index":521,"end_time":1736.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1736.16,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You should see that guy that kept leaving comments on Your guys Google business.","index":522,"end_time":1742.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1737.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You should see if he.","index":523,"end_time":1743.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1742.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you can hire him to go after Ringcentral.","index":524,"end_time":1745.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1743.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They went after us on Yelp too, Colin and I went at him.","index":525,"end_time":1750,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1747.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m like, this Yelp.","index":526,"end_time":1751.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1750.4,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No one gives a about Yelp.","index":527,"end_time":1753.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1751.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like, I can.","index":528,"end_time":1753.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1753.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I can be myself on Yelp.","index":529,"end_time":1755.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1753.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I can be myself.","index":530,"end_time":1757.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1756.16,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No one goes to look up businesses on yo.","index":531,"end_time":1761.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1759.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Not anymore, hopefully.","index":532,"end_time":1764.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1762.49,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But we need to rank a bunch of other stuff so that our Yelp page doesn''t rank.","index":533,"end_time":1768.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1764.73,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So no one sees that.","index":534,"end_time":1771.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1770.17,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But at one point, Yelp sold for like, a billion dollars.","index":535,"end_time":1774.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1771.93,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Didn''t.","index":536,"end_time":1775.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1774.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Was crazy.","index":537,"end_time":1777.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1776.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, people were acting crazy based on their, like, reviewer status, thinking they were somebody, you know, out here being rude to people.","index":538,"end_time":1785.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1778.17,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, we''re getting good with that one.","index":539,"end_time":1787.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1786.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So that was my.","index":540,"end_time":1788.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1787.57,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That was what I wanted to touch on.","index":541,"end_time":1789.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay, so go ahead and go to your next item, Lindsey, which was something.","index":542,"end_time":1792.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1790.12,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"To do with checking points.","index":543,"end_time":1795.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1792.68,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Checking points again.","index":544,"end_time":1796.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1795.56,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":545,"end_time":1797.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.48,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How are we doing on points?","index":546,"end_time":1798.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1797.08,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"What does that look like?","index":547,"end_time":1799.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1798.36,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Can we stay tracking those, Colin, so that we know where we''re at and what we got going on?","index":548,"end_time":1802.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1799.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We kind of gotten away from that, and it came up this week that we want to make sure we''re tracking.","index":549,"end_time":1806.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1802.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t want to get in a spot where we''re in a hole again like last time, and I don''t want to get.","index":550,"end_time":1810.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1806.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And if we aren''t using you as much as we need to, then maybe we''ll start pushing more stuff your way.","index":551,"end_time":1815.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1810.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":552,"end_time":1816.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.28,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Pull that up.","index":553,"end_time":1819.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1818.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":554,"end_time":1835.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1835.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we actually have a positive balance.","index":555,"end_time":1837.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1835.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have 28 points in working, and that is, like, for managing the website and checking in on the ads and things like that.","index":556,"end_time":1847.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1839.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have other points available for any new landing pages, any new campaigns we can help out on.","index":557,"end_time":1852.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1847.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, just keep us around.","index":558,"end_time":1855.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1854.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Just keep us start out the calls going forward with the information.","index":559,"end_time":1859.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1855.81,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I''ll do that.","index":560,"end_time":1860.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1859.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No problem.","index":561,"end_time":1864.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1863.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, maybe if we''re ending this Ringcentral campaign, maybe we''ll.","index":562,"end_time":1871.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1868.45,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"If we got spare points, let''s send.","index":563,"end_time":1873.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1871.97,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Maybe we''ll send you on a goose chase to see what addition.","index":564,"end_time":1875.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1873.53,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"A new campaign we should maybe do come back.","index":565,"end_time":1878.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1876.19,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like a wild goose chase.","index":566,"end_time":1879.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1878.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":567,"end_time":1880.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1880.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You golf at all, Colin?","index":568,"end_time":1885.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1884.59,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Do I golf?","index":569,"end_time":1887.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1886.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":570,"end_time":1887.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1887.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":571,"end_time":1888.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1887.59,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Do you?","index":572,"end_time":1888.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1888.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Met with my dad yesterday.","index":573,"end_time":1890.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1889.07,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Speaking of a wild goose chase.","index":574,"end_time":1891.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1890.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"He killed this year.","index":575,"end_time":1892.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.35,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"He killed two.","index":576,"end_time":1893.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.47,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"He killed two gooses.","index":577,"end_time":1894.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1893.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Golfing.","index":578,"end_time":1895.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1894.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Golf.","index":579,"end_time":1896.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1895.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Geese golfing.","index":580,"end_time":1897.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1896.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That''s impressive.","index":581,"end_time":1898.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1897.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Two geese golfing.","index":582,"end_time":1899.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1898.59,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":583,"end_time":1901.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1900.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The first time we weren''t married yet, but the first time I took my wife golfing, she hit a shot and we Were playing on the Eastern shore of Maryland.","index":584,"end_time":1910.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1902.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s a lot of geese, and it goes over this hill, and then we just see feathers pop up.","index":585,"end_time":1916.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1910.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, I don''t think she killed it because we didn''t see anything laying down.","index":586,"end_time":1923.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1918.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, my goodness.","index":587,"end_time":1924.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1923.84,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":588,"end_time":1926.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1926,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, we should get around to golfing.","index":589,"end_time":1927.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1926.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re gonna come to Michigan?","index":590,"end_time":1929.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1928.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Hey, man, if you want to play some golf, I''ll come to.","index":591,"end_time":1932.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1930.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll go anywhere.","index":592,"end_time":1933.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1932.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let''s do it.","index":593,"end_time":1935.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You, me, we''ll get Ryan out there.","index":594,"end_time":1936.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1935.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''ll take you.","index":595,"end_time":1937.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1936.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''ll give you the up north.","index":596,"end_time":1938.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1937.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Up north Michigan experience.","index":597,"end_time":1939.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1938.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Love it.","index":598,"end_time":1941,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1940.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably maybe in a few months when it warms up.","index":599,"end_time":1944.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1941.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not.","index":600,"end_time":1944.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1944.08,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Dude, not a few months.","index":601,"end_time":1945.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1944.4,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Maybe six months.","index":602,"end_time":1946.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1945.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll say.","index":603,"end_time":1947.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1946.12,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I would kill for it to be just a few months before we''re golfing again.","index":604,"end_time":1950.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1947.56,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":605,"end_time":1951.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1951.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I am going to ship my clubs down to Florida for March.","index":606,"end_time":1955,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1952.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Ryan.","index":607,"end_time":1955.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1955,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''d looked at it.","index":608,"end_time":1957,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1955.48,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m jealous.","index":609,"end_time":1957.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1957.08,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"It''s actually probably.","index":610,"end_time":1960.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1958.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I looked at it briefly.","index":611,"end_time":1961.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1960.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I haven''t really dug into it a whole lot, Colin.","index":612,"end_time":1963.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1961.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But, you know, we were just going to rent clubs, and I''m like, man, I could probably just because I didn''t want to take them with us.","index":613,"end_time":1968.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1963.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m like, I probably just ship them cheaper, but it looks like it''s like 100 bucks on the high end each way.","index":614,"end_time":1973.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1968.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve heard great things.","index":615,"end_time":1975.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1973.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And since my wife only uses, like four clubs, I could probably just throw a small bag inside of my bag and shove her four clubs in mine and call it done.","index":616,"end_time":1984.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1977.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":617,"end_time":1985.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1984.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s your three wood.","index":618,"end_time":1987.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1985.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s your five wood.","index":619,"end_time":1988.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1987.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you and Michelle carve out a week for my family to come down and visit you?","index":620,"end_time":1992.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1988.81,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"You know, Ryan, you are always welcome.","index":621,"end_time":1994.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1992.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think we told you that, didn''t we?","index":622,"end_time":1996.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1995.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, probably.","index":623,"end_time":1997.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1996.97,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I did for sure.","index":624,"end_time":1999.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1998.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Come on down, though.","index":625,"end_time":2000.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1999.85,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We had to rent a house.","index":626,"end_time":2002.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2001.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''re taking the dog.","index":627,"end_time":2003.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2002.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So we''re driving, which is terrible because I don''t drive anywhere.","index":628,"end_time":2005.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2003.09,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I always try to fly.","index":629,"end_time":2007.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2006.41,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But we have three dogs, so we had to find somewhere dog friendly.","index":630,"end_time":2013.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2009.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So the house we got.","index":631,"end_time":2014.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2013.57,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And we have to have a yard because we have dogs.","index":632,"end_time":2017.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2015.01,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So the house we got is like ginormous because it was one of the few we could find with a yard that would allow us to bring dogs.","index":633,"end_time":2023.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2017.81,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Nice.","index":634,"end_time":2025.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2024.77,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So, I mean, I probably got.","index":635,"end_time":2026.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2025.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No kidding, Ryan.","index":636,"end_time":2027.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2026.929,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We probably got four spare bedrooms.","index":637,"end_time":2029.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2027.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":638,"end_time":2030.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2029.65,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yep.","index":639,"end_time":2031.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2031.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll be there.","index":640,"end_time":2032.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2031.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Come on down.","index":641,"end_time":2034.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2033.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''ll do it.","index":642,"end_time":2035.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2034.93,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I do want to check.","index":643,"end_time":2038.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2037.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Thanksgiving week, I''m actually out the entire week mother effort.","index":644,"end_time":2043.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2038.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Jesus.","index":645,"end_time":2045.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2044.63,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I cancel that week.","index":646,"end_time":2047.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2046.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, what time is what time?","index":647,"end_time":2049.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2048.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Thanksgiving dinner at your house, calling.","index":648,"end_time":2051.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2049.67,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''re all coming up.","index":649,"end_time":2052.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2051.35,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, well, so I''ll be.","index":650,"end_time":2054.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2053.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to Florida because my father in law is getting married.","index":651,"end_time":2059.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2055.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re flying back to do Thanksgiving with my mom.","index":652,"end_time":2062.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2059.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re just gonna finally sit at home, probably for like a day before having to go back to work.","index":653,"end_time":2067.359,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2063.199,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds like a whole lot of fun.","index":654,"end_time":2069.679,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2068.399,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":655,"end_time":2070.399,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2069.999,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Taking the baby on the plane for the first time.","index":656,"end_time":2072.159,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2070.399,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''ll be great.","index":657,"end_time":2073.359,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2072.639,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Well, at least you''ll probably be able to fly.","index":658,"end_time":2074.839,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2073.359,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s good news.","index":659,"end_time":2075.599,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2074.839,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m hoping so.","index":660,"end_time":2077.199,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2076.239,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, all I see is horror.","index":661,"end_time":2079.159,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2077.199,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Stories that''ll be wrapped.","index":662,"end_time":2080.679,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2079.159,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Looks like that''ll be wrapped up today.","index":663,"end_time":2081.919,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2080.679,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Nice.","index":664,"end_time":2083.199,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2082.719,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Too much.","index":665,"end_time":2083.999,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2083.439,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, anything else on your list, Lindsey?","index":666,"end_time":2089.519,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2087.519,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think that''s everything that I had notes for for today.","index":667,"end_time":2093.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2091.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":668,"end_time":2094.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2093.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will work through those and I''ll send you guys some email updates.","index":669,"end_time":2098.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2095.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, did I miss anything?","index":670,"end_time":2099.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2098.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No.","index":671,"end_time":2101.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2100.87,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You''re gonna send us the stuff on how to limit our total budget per day.","index":672,"end_time":2104.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2101.43,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yes, Colin.","index":673,"end_time":2105.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2104.95,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I got everything on my list.","index":674,"end_time":2108.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2107.59,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That was everything.","index":675,"end_time":2109.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2108.71,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":676,"end_time":2110.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2109.59,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, thanks, guys.","index":677,"end_time":2111.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2110.71,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you very much.","index":678,"end_time":2113.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2111.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-11-12T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"lhall@techmode.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NjEzNzdiMDAtMzIyNi00NzgxLWIwOTYtODBjZWQ4NjljZGM3@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4\",\"Oid\":\"e804fbe9-a623-4d26-a887-992e62fb92d1\"}","participants":["cquigley@techmode.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,monica.chinsami@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,lhall@techmode.com,michael.lewis@techmode.com,mlook@techmode.com,rfisher@techmode.com","cquigley@techmode.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","monica.chinsami@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","michael.lewis@techmode.com","mlook@techmode.com","rfisher@techmode.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9QYRQ3505XSEJBGWY4XDH2T","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Shipped updated resources page with full mobile support; Lindsay confirmed tags now display correctly.","Set up automation to feed lead quality data back into PMAX to optimize conversion targeting.","Resolved AJAX bug in Gravity Forms that prevented required fields from validating properly.","Paused underperforming RingCentral campaign after $274 spend yielded zero conversions.","Agreed to pursue organic blog strategy targeting RingCentral replacement keywords next week."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We did set up the lead scoring for the crap leads that had come in.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"So should we just pause this campaign?","speaker":"Matthew Look"},{"quote":"Top five reasons to replace your RingCentral.","speaker":"Lindsay Hall"}],"topics":["delivery","ads","automation","performance","SEO"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and SEO Performance**\n\nThe team confirmed steady growth in keyword rankings, demonstrating progress in content marketing efforts.  \n\n- **Tech Mode currently ranks for 301 keywords**, up from about 180 keywords a few months ago, showing clear improvement in organic search visibility (02:18)  \n    - Lindsay Hall highlighted this positive trend as a sign of growing content impact  \n    - Compared to competitors, RingCentral ranks for around **80,000 keywords** and 8x8 ranks for about **60,000 keywords**, underscoring the gap Tech Mode aims to close  \n    - Matthew Look emphasized the need to keep increasing output, using his combined AI and manual writing system to produce blog posts in about **15 minutes** each  \n    - This scalable content approach is expected to accelerate keyword growth and improve competitive positioning  \n\n- The team discussed a strategic shift toward targeted blog posts focused on competitor replacement topics to capture organic traffic more effectively (25:14)  \n    - Matthew proposed creating **four blog posts about replacing RingCentral** to tap into organic search interest where competitors aggressively bid on ads  \n    - Colin Costigan noted that \"top 10 alternatives\" style articles perform well and could help Tech Mode rank for these competitive themes  \n    - The approach offers a lower-cost alternative to bidding wars in paid ads, leveraging organic content to disrupt competitor dominance  \n    - The team agreed this strategy could bypass heavy ad spend and attract high-intent visitors through relevant, well-placed blog content  \n\n## **Advertising Campaign Management and Optimization**\n\nThe meeting addressed critical updates and decisions around Google Ads campaigns, focusing on efficiency and budget controls.  \n\n- The team gained **admin access to Google Performance Max (PMAX)** campaigns and implemented lead scoring to improve ad targeting and conversion quality (07:20)  \n    - Colin explained the new automation will flag unqualified leads and report them back to Google to reduce wasted spending on low-value traffic  \n    - High-quality leads will be scored as valuable conversions to help Google''s AI optimize for better prospects moving forward  \n    - Matthew supported this feedback loop to enhance campaign ROI despite some skepticism about AI accuracy in lead classification  \n\n- The **RingCentral paid search campaign was reviewed and deemed ineffective**, leading to the decision to pause it (20:18)  \n    - Over **six weeks, 13 clicks cost nearly $300 with zero conversions**, and the campaign was already optimized to a **98% score**  \n    - Colin noted the competition from RingCentral and 8x8 bid aggressively, pushing Tech Mode’s ads lower in placement and reducing click-through rates  \n    - Matthew and Lindsay agreed the limited budget meant continuing the campaign risked wasting funds better used elsewhere  \n    - Pausing will free resources potentially toward content marketing and other campaigns with stronger returns  \n\n- The team discussed the **removal of Google Ads’ account-level daily or monthly spend caps**, which complicates budget control (13:04)  \n    - Colin confirmed Google replaced this with daily campaign limits only, removing a fail-safe against overspending  \n    - Matthew stressed the need to find alternative controls or monitoring to prevent runaway budgets in future campaign disruptions  \n    - Colin committed to researching and reporting back on any possible workarounds or tools to manage overall spend caps  \n\n- Adding **site links to the PMAX campaign was approved** to enhance ad assets and improve click engagement (16:50)  \n    - Lindsay noted existing site links have generated some clicks, and Google suggested adding up to 12 site links per campaign  \n    - Colin confirmed site links are present but can be expanded, supporting the team’s plan to bolster ad visibility and user navigation  \n\n## **Lead Tracking and Reporting Improvements**\n\nEfforts are underway to enhance lead source accuracy and reporting consistency across marketing channels.  \n\n- Lindsay raised concerns about incomplete lead source data affecting the accuracy of lead reports, especially for non-paid sources (09:00)  \n    - She struggles to get organic and direct leads to appear reliably in tracking reports despite manual source corrections  \n    - Colin suggested that the system might prioritize the most recent traffic source over the original, shifting the attribution logic  \n    - They agreed to investigate further with specific lead examples Lindsay will provide via email for deeper troubleshooting  \n\n- The team confirmed the **fix of a Gravity Forms AJAX issue** that previously allowed form submissions without required emails, improving lead data quality (08:41)  \n    - This correction is expected to reduce incomplete or junk leads entering the system  \n    - Lindsay expressed confidence this fix resolves prior form inconsistencies  \n\n## **Operational Resource Management and Workflows**\n\nThe team reviewed current resource balances and discussed maintaining clear communication on workload and priorities.  \n\n- Colin reported a **positive balance of 28 points** available for website management and ads, with additional points ready for new campaigns or landing pages (30:18)  \n    - This points system tracks workload and capacity for Tech Mode’s outsourced support, ensuring clarity on available resources  \n    - Matthew requested ongoing updates on point status at the start of future calls to better plan and allocate work  \n    - The team agreed to potentially task Colin with exploring new campaign opportunities after pausing the RingCentral campaign  \n\n- Colin shared personal scheduling notes, indicating unavailability during Thanksgiving week due to travel (33:57)  \n    - The team acknowledged and planned around this absence smoothly  \n\n## **Competitive and Market Insights**\n\nDiscussions revealed key market dynamics influencing Tech Mode’s marketing and product positioning strategies.  \n\n- The **paid search landscape for RingCentral-related keywords is dominated by RingCentral and Dial Pad**, with few other advertisers and mostly organic content filling the rest of the search results (24:18)  \n    - Matthew observed competitor ad budgets are significantly higher, making direct paid competition costly and inefficient for Tech Mode  \n    - Organic articles and community posts (e.g., Reddit threads) rank highly and attract attention, presenting an opportunity for Tech Mode to target these spaces with relevant content  \n    - Colin noted the unusual speed at which Reddit posts can rank on Google, highlighting the importance of monitoring emerging organic channels  \n\n- Privacy and data restrictions, such as the shift from Universal Analytics to GA4, have reduced visibility into search term data and campaign insights (22:42)  \n    - Lindsay and Colin agreed this complicates marketing efforts and requires adapting tracking and attribution methods going forward  \n    - They anticipate more stringent compliance laws resembling Europe’s GDPR by 2028, increasing the need for creative data strategies  \n\n## **Team Collaboration and Culture**\n\nThe team maintained a positive and adaptive culture while balancing workload and project priorities.  \n\n- Matthew and Colin shared personal stories and humor about self-driving cars and golf, fostering camaraderie and morale (03:33, 31:24)  \n- Lindsay expressed appreciation for AI tools that save time on content creation and link-building, supporting efficiency gains (28:13)  \n- The group discussed travel and personal plans openly, reinforcing a supportive and flexible team environment (33:53)","outline":null,"keywords":["PMAX campaign","lead tracking","Google Ads budget","RingCentral replacement","blog posts","keyword rankings"],"overview":"- **Keyword Growth:** Tech Mode now ranks for **301 keywords**, up from **180**, enhancing organic search visibility.  \n\n- **Competitor Strategies:** Proposed four blog posts on replacing **RingCentral**, aiming to attract organic traffic and reduce ad spend.  \n\n- **Ad Campaign Changes:** The **RingCentral paid search campaign** paused after **13 clicks costing nearly $300 with zero conversions**.  \n\n- **Budget Control Issues:** Google removed account-level spend caps, complicating budget management for future campaigns.  \n\n- **Lead Tracking Improvements:** Fix on Gravity Forms AJAX issue now improves lead data quality and reduces junk leads.  \n\n- **Market Landscape Insights:** Paid search for RingCentral keywords dominated by **RingCentral and Dial Pad**, emphasizing need for organic content strategies.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide guidance on how to set daily or monthly budget caps or alternatives in Google Ads after confirmation (12:30)\nSend updates via email regarding progress on lead source tracking and form link best practices (09:04)\nContinue monitoring and reporting point balances and campaign management progress on subsequent calls (29:59)\nAssist with adding more site links to the PMAX campaign as discussed (18:50)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nIdentify specific example leads to help diagnose lead source reporting discrepancies and email Colin with details (11:20)\nAdd additional site links (approximately 2 or more) to the PMAX Google Ads campaign (19:30)\nWrite four blog posts focusing on ''RingCentral replacement'' topics to improve organic search rankings (26:30)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nContinue producing blog content using AI-assisted tools to support content marketing efforts (03:14)\nBegin drafting the specified RingCentral replacement blog posts as next content project (26:27)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"2607a0f7-fcf5-4c14-bea1-8f1822c8ff33","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
