    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82164087465?pwd=HIMrVfQh9H8oWdIxFsR0aU3slIkuOP.1',
    '{"id":"01K9CWN2TT45F8EFDGR8XWNVNK","title":"EASE // MiD - Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Video Production and Content Delivery**\n\nThe team must accelerate video production to demonstrate value and avoid budget cuts by December (12:00).\n\n- **Josh Santo emphasized the urgency to complete all videos by December** to prove ROI and avoid losing funding (12:00)  \n    - Videos are now a CEO-level priority, driven by sales feedback highlighting their need to sell better  \n    - Josh plans to deliver a clear path for video rollout, prioritizing product overview and action plans first  \n    - The team acknowledged multiple revisions and recording delays but committed to speeding up final edits  \n    - Success will be measured by video completion and their impact on internal buy-in and sales enablement\n\n- **Josh clarified the preferred video production approach uses his original screen recordings with voiceover overlays** rather than recreating content from scratch (06:20)  \n    - The recordings include background clutter requiring cropping but preserve authentic user interactions for clarity  \n    - Editing will focus on zooming, highlighting key actions, and timing adjustments to sync audio and video  \n    - This approach reduces production time while maintaining instructional quality and user engagement  \n    - Baylee confirmed the team’s familiarity with the platform will help speed up editing and storyboarding\n\n## **Contractual and Budgetary Considerations**\n\nBudget tightening threatens video projects, with decisions expected soon after the recent board meeting (12:00).\n\n- **Josh reported ownership will cut budgets, likely targeting video content unless value is proven fast** (12:00)  \n    - Andrea is advocating for both podcast and video contracts, but videos are at higher risk of cuts post-delivery  \n    - The board met recently, with guidance expected imminently, and Josh anticipates clearer direction next week  \n    - Josh requested contract cancellation terms refresh to prepare for possible cuts (13:00)  \n    - Baylee detailed the renewal and notice periods: podcast contract renews December 8th with 45-day notice by January 22nd; video contract renews January 13th with notice by November 29th (15:29)\n\n- **The team agreed to push all resources toward completing videos quickly to maximize retention chances** (14:28)  \n    - Andrea’s fight for the podcast contract creates some stability there, but video contracts remain uncertain  \n    - Josh stressed the need to “drop everything” to finish videos as soon as possible for CEO and board visibility  \n    - Baylee offered flexibility on deadlines and promised to alert Justin and Tristan about the urgency  \n    - The goal is to deliver a strong finish that could influence budget decisions favorably\n\n## **Video Editing and Workflow Adjustments**\n\nThe video team will prioritize efficient editing using existing screen captures paired with voiceovers, requiring careful timing and visual focus (06:20).\n\n- **Josh highlighted challenges syncing his longer explanatory video tracks with shorter scripted voiceovers** (10:14)  \n    - Editors will need to speed up or slow down clips and use zooms or highlights to emphasize key steps  \n    - Josh’s verbal notes in videos guide editors on the intended emphasis and flow for better viewer understanding  \n    - Baylee suggested starting with stock footage and text introductions before jumping into platform demos  \n    - A preliminary storyboard review will ensure screenshots and scenes align with script and user experience goals\n\n- **The team decided to avoid recreating videos from scratch in Adobe Illustrator** and instead crop and polish Josh’s original recordings (07:05)  \n    - This reduces workload and speeds turnaround while preserving authentic demonstrations  \n    - Some scenes require minor “Hollywood magic,” such as swapping out placeholders with real photos or cutting unwanted desktop backgrounds  \n    - Baylee confirmed the video team’s familiarity with platform nuances will help maintain quality under tighter timelines  \n    - Josh’s latest comments cover scenes 6–10, providing detailed context and editing notes for the next production phase (07:41)\n\n## **Product and Outreach Campaign Updates**\n\nProgress continues on podcasts, blog posts, and outreach campaigns, with approvals and feedback loops mostly complete (01:11).\n\n- **Baylee reported the episode with Ed Rocha Live was completed and a new episode submitted for production** (01:18)  \n    - The blog post with Ed has been sent for Josh’s feedback on titles and copy to finalize  \n    - Video clips are being updated in line with the latest content and outreach strategy  \n    - The outreach campaign assets received Josh’s approval; new campaigns will replace existing ones in Heyreach and Lemlist (02:05)  \n    - Storyboard updates and voiceover re-recordings are underway based on recent feedback to improve quality and alignment\n\n- **Josh confirmed sales team feedback on action plans has been incorporated, with no further pending edits** (02:43)  \n    - He will now record the necessary videos for audits, inspections, and on-the-job training modules by Friday (04:01)  \n    - Product overview videos will follow a similar process, using his screen recordings plus voiceovers for clearer messaging (04:05)  \n    - This alignment streamlines content production and ensures consistent messaging across training materials\n\n## **Strategic Focus and Long-term Vision**\n\nThe team is focused on stabilizing content production to support sales and internal buy-in during a challenging budget cycle (18:05).\n\n- **Josh shared that the new CEO’s direct feedback to sales prioritized videos as a key sales enablement tool** (18:05)  \n    - This creates a narrow window to prove video content’s value and secure ongoing investment  \n    - Delivery of high-quality, impactful videos can shift budget decisions away from cuts  \n    - The team aims to “tie the bow” on existing video projects to present a strong, finished product  \n    - Baylee recognized the importance of this moment and committed to expediting delivery without sacrificing quality\n\n- **Josh framed this period as temporary “until the grip gets unloosened,” acknowledging the need for agility and readiness** (17:48)  \n    - The focus is on quick wins that demonstrate clear business impact  \n    - Maintaining the podcast contract is seen as a valuable anchor amid uncertainty  \n    - The video team''s responsiveness to rapid feedback and revision cycles is critical to success  \n    - This mindset reflects a pragmatic approach to navigating leadership changes and budget pressures","outline":null,"keywords":["Video Production","Action Plans","Product Overview","Budget Cuts","Contract Renewal","Outreach Campaign"],"overview":"- **Accelerate Video Production:** All videos must be completed by December to demonstrate value and avoid budget cuts.  \n- **Editing Strategy:** Use original screen recordings with voiceovers to speed up production while ensuring instructional quality.  \n- **Budget Risk:** Video content is at high risk of cuts unless value is proven quickly; focus all resources on video completion.  \n- **Project Deadlines:** Contract renewals: podcast on December 8th with notice by January 22nd, video on January 13th with notice by November 29th.  \n- **Sales Integration:** Sales team feedback is incorporated, with a focus on producing videos for audits and training modules.  \n- **Long-term Focus:** Deliver impactful videos to influence budget decisions while navigating current financial pressures and leadership changes.","action_items":"\n**Josh Santo**\nComplete final video recordings for audits, inspections, and on the job training content by Friday (03:58)\nProvide any further feedback required for blog post titles and video clip updates (01:33)\nRecord videos with clear demonstrations for product overview scenes, ensuring notes on desired focus and actions are clear for editors (07:45)\nFinalize voiceover recordings to sync with edited demo footage, especially for product overview and action plans (09:53)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nIncorporate Josh’s feedback into blog post titles and copy, update video clips accordingly (01:33)\nUpload approved outreach campaign materials to Heyreach and Lemlist, pause existing campaigns as directed (01:48)\nRevise storyboard with new screen recordings and synchronize with voiceover re-recordings (02:06)\nConfirm script edits for job training and action plans, then coordinate video production with Josh’s recordings and instructions (03:12)\nAdjust video editing approach to use Josh’s screen recordings directly with cropping and emphasis effects rather than recreations in Adobe Illustrator (06:59)\nManage timing adjustments for video edits to align voiceover with demo footage speed changes (10:00)\nPrepare and circulate updated storyboard for review before video production advances (11:00)\nReview contract details with client and communicate cancellation deadlines to internal teams (14:27)\nPrioritize rapid completion of product and action plans videos to meet December deadline (12:00)\n"},"duration":19.100000381469727,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Josh Santo"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Swag.","index":0,"end_time":0.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, it is cool.","index":1,"end_time":4.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":2,"end_time":5.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Look cool here in the mornings, but beautiful now.","index":3,"end_time":9.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":4,"end_time":10.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Warming up as the sun out.","index":5,"end_time":13.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a beautiful day.","index":6,"end_time":17.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Like it''s one of those why I''m in, why am I inside, what am I doing with my life kind of days.","index":7,"end_time":25.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":8,"end_time":29.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What time do you usually get off?","index":9,"end_time":31.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"6Ish.","index":10,"end_time":34.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, so it was like the sun down by then or almost.","index":11,"end_time":38.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":12,"end_time":39.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''S like midnight by then, basically.","index":13,"end_time":44.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"With the lighting outside.","index":14,"end_time":46.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":15,"end_time":47.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Man, that part''s pretty rough.","index":16,"end_time":50.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":17,"end_time":52.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So.","index":18,"end_time":53.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":54.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, cool.","index":20,"end_time":57.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":21,"end_time":58.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Gotta at least get outside on the weekends.","index":22,"end_time":61.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know.","index":23,"end_time":65.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yep.","index":24,"end_time":66.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we will get into it.","index":25,"end_time":71.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":26,"end_time":71.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I can tell you''ve been busy this week.","index":27,"end_time":73.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve been moving on a lot of things.","index":28,"end_time":75.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":76.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So we''ll just go through our.","index":30,"end_time":79.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Our normal updates today.","index":31,"end_time":81.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":79.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we were able to get that episode with a Ed Rocha Live and we saw that you submitted another one, so we''re working on that.","index":32,"end_time":90.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":82.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":33,"end_time":91.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then we also just barely sent over that blog post with Ed.","index":34,"end_time":98.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think we just need your feedback on the titles and any of the copy.","index":35,"end_time":102.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''re working on updating the video clips.","index":36,"end_time":105.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":37,"end_time":106.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So then for the outreach campaign, we saw you just approved everything.","index":38,"end_time":111.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":108.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll get that all uploaded into heyreach and Lemlist and then I think we''ll pause the campaigns currently running and replace them with this new one.","index":39,"end_time":121.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Unless you want them to go together.","index":40,"end_time":124.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All the new ones.","index":41,"end_time":125.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":42,"end_time":128.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then currently just working on updating that storyboard with those new screen recordings you sent over.","index":43,"end_time":139.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then the voiceover artist is re recording the script based on the most recent feedback.","index":44,"end_time":145.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":45,"end_time":146.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then got all of these scripts.","index":46,"end_time":151.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":148.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we just barely sent over this on the job training with some edits.","index":47,"end_time":157.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think we''re just looking for your final feedback on these.","index":48,"end_time":161.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":49,"end_time":164.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think I gave stuff for Action Plans.","index":50,"end_time":167.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":164.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I don''t think there''s anything pending there.","index":51,"end_time":170.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I haven''t seen anything on the.","index":52,"end_time":174.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":53,"end_time":175.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":54,"end_time":180.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we were waiting.","index":55,"end_time":181.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Did your sales team have feedback?","index":56,"end_time":184.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is that what it was, that they needed to review things?","index":57,"end_time":187.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I already took them through stuff and.","index":58,"end_time":191.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":59,"end_time":191.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Incorporated.","index":60,"end_time":192.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So the action plans.","index":61,"end_time":194.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I don''t think there''s anything needed on Action Plans.","index":62,"end_time":195.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think the audits and inspections.","index":63,"end_time":197.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think I had made some comments and then.","index":64,"end_time":204.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think I made some comments.","index":65,"end_time":209.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":207.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I guess at this point it''s.","index":66,"end_time":211.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"If y'' all have gone through it, then I need to go in and do the videos for it.","index":67,"end_time":216.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":68,"end_time":218.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It looks like we''ve updated it.","index":69,"end_time":220.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":70,"end_time":221.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":71,"end_time":221.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, so then I''ll.","index":72,"end_time":226.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I''ll need to do the.","index":73,"end_time":227.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The video pieces for it.","index":74,"end_time":230.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then on the job training would be all of it.","index":75,"end_time":234.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Like, edit it and then videos for it.","index":76,"end_time":238.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":77,"end_time":239.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":78,"end_time":241.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":79,"end_time":241.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Friday.","index":80,"end_time":242.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":81,"end_time":245.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then should we follow the same process?","index":82,"end_time":247.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Product overview.","index":83,"end_time":248.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Oh, I was expecting same process for product overview.","index":84,"end_time":251.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":85,"end_time":252.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good to know.","index":86,"end_time":254.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re.","index":87,"end_time":254.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good to know.","index":88,"end_time":258.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think I was initially under the impression that we would, like, exactly use your screen recording and, like, you would read the script as you went through things.","index":89,"end_time":267.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But.","index":90,"end_time":269.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But that''s okay.","index":91,"end_time":269.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll switch gears then.","index":92,"end_time":272.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It is, like, definitely more work to do what we''re doing for the product video for these two.","index":93,"end_time":278.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll need to adjust the points a little bit for that.","index":94,"end_time":282.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But you''ve got stuff available since it''s been taking a bit longer than expected.","index":95,"end_time":287.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, so to clarify, I''m thinking my video recording just matched with the voice artists doing the recording, like, doing the voiceover.","index":96,"end_time":302.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So, like.","index":97,"end_time":303.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, like, the videos that I''ve recorded and I talk through it in the video, like, take the video and, you know, there''s some editing needed in the video.","index":98,"end_time":313.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Like, for example, all of them are going to have a background that we don''t really want to show up.","index":99,"end_time":318.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Like, you know, because if you pull up the example from the Action Plans or even the most recent document, I can.","index":100,"end_time":324.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The where is it?","index":101,"end_time":327.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think it was the other one.","index":102,"end_time":330.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is it for Acti