cuts (13:00)  \n    - Baylee detailed the renewal and notice periods: podcast contract renews December 8th with 45-day notice by January 22nd; video contract renews January 13th with notice by November 29th (15:29)\n\n- **The team agreed to push all resources toward completing videos quickly to maximize retention chances** (14:28)  \n    - Andrea’s fight for the podcast contract creates some stability there, but video contracts remain uncertain  \n    - Josh stressed the need to “drop everything” to finish videos as soon as possible for CEO and board visibility  \n    - Baylee offered flexibility on deadlines and promised to alert Justin and Tristan about the urgency  \n    - The goal is to deliver a strong finish that could influence budget decisions favorably\n\n## **Video Editing and Workflow Adjustments**\n\nThe video team will prioritize efficient editing using existing screen captures paired with voiceovers, requiring careful timing and visual focus (06:20).\n\n- **Josh highlighted challenges syncing his longer explanatory video tracks with shorter scripted voiceovers** (10:14)  \n    - Editors will need to speed up or slow down clips and use zooms or highlights to emphasize key steps  \n    - Josh’s verbal notes in videos guide editors on the intended emphasis and flow for better viewer understanding  \n    - Baylee suggested starting with stock footage and text introductions before jumping into platform demos  \n    - A preliminary storyboard review will ensure screenshots and scenes align with script and user experience goals\n\n- **The team decided to avoid recreating videos from scratch in Adobe Illustrator** and instead crop and polish Josh’s original recordings (07:05)  \n    - This reduces workload and speeds turnaround while preserving authentic demonstrations  \n    - Some scenes require minor “Hollywood magic,” such as swapping out placeholders with real photos or cutting unwanted desktop backgrounds  \n    - Baylee confirmed the video team’s familiarity with platform nuances will help maintain quality under tighter timelines  \n    - Josh’s latest comments cover scenes 6–10, providing detailed context and editing notes for the next production phase (07:41)\n\n## **Product and Outreach Campaign Updates**\n\nProgress continues on podcasts, blog posts, and outreach campaigns, with approvals and feedback loops mostly complete (01:11).\n\n- **Baylee reported the episode with Ed Rocha Live was completed and a new episode submitted for production** (01:18)  \n    - The blog post with Ed has been sent for Josh’s feedback on titles and copy to finalize  \n    - Video clips are being updated in line with the latest content and outreach strategy  \n    - The outreach campaign assets received Josh’s approval; new campaigns will replace existing ones in Heyreach and Lemlist (02:05)  \n    - Storyboard updates and voiceover re-recordings are underway based on recent feedback to improve quality and alignment\n\n- **Josh confirmed sales team feedback on action plans has been incorporated, with no further pending edits** (02:43)  \n    - He will now record the necessary videos for audits, inspections, and on-the-job training modules by Friday (04:01)  \n    - Product overview videos will follow a similar process, using his screen recordings plus voiceovers for clearer messaging (04:05)  \n    - This alignment streamlines content production and ensures consistent messaging across training materials\n\n## **Strategic Focus and Long-term Vision**\n\nThe team is focused on stabilizing content production to support sales and internal buy-in during a challenging budget cycle (18:05).\n\n- **Josh shared that the new CEO’s direct feedback to sales prioritized videos as a key sales enablement tool** (18:05)  \n    - This creates a narrow window to prove video content’s value and secure ongoing investment  \n    - Delivery of high-quality, impactful videos can shift budget decisions away from cuts  \n    - The team aims to “tie the bow” on existing video projects to present a strong, finished product  \n    - Baylee recognized the importance of this moment and committed to expediting delivery without sacrificing quality\n\n- **Josh framed this period as temporary “until the grip gets unloosened,” acknowledging the need for agility and readiness** (17:48)  \n    - The focus is on quick wins that demonstrate clear business impact  \n    - Maintaining the podcast contract is seen as a valuable anchor amid uncertainty  \n    - The video team''s responsiveness to rapid feedback and revision cycles is critical to success  \n    - This mindset reflects a pragmatic approach to navigating leadership changes and budget pressures","outline":null,"keywords":["Video Production","Action Plans","Product Overview","Budget Cuts","Contract Renewal","Outreach Campaign"],"overview":"- **Accelerate Video Production:** All videos must be completed by December to demonstrate value and avoid budget cuts.  \n- **Editing Strategy:** Use original screen recordings with voiceovers to speed up production while ensuring instructional quality.  \n- **Budget Risk:** Video content is at high risk of cuts unless value is proven quickly; focus all resources on video completion.  \n- **Project Deadlines:** Contract renewals: podcast on December 8th with notice by January 22nd, video on January 13th with notice by November 29th.  \n- **Sales Integration:** Sales team feedback is incorporated, with a focus on producing videos for audits and training modules.  \n- **Long-term Focus:** Deliver impactful videos to influence budget decisions while navigating current financial pressures and leadership changes.","action_items":"\n**Josh Santo**\nComplete final video recordings for audits, inspections, and on the job training content by Friday (03:58)\nProvide any further feedback required for blog post titles and video clip updates (01:33)\nRecord videos with clear demonstrations for product overview scenes, ensuring notes on desired focus and actions are clear for editors (07:45)\nFinalize voiceover recordings to sync with edited demo footage, especially for product overview and action plans (09:53)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nIncorporate Josh’s feedback into blog post titles and copy, update video clips accordingly (01:33)\nUpload approved outreach campaign materials to Heyreach and Lemlist, pause existing campaigns as directed (01:48)\nRevise storyboard with new screen recordings and synchronize with voiceover re-recordings (02:06)\nConfirm script edits for job training and action plans, then coordinate video production with Josh’s recordings and instructions (03:12)\nAdjust video editing approach to use Josh’s screen recordings directly with cropping and emphasis effects rather than recreations in Adobe Illustrator (06:59)\nManage timing adjustments for video edits to align voiceover with demo footage speed changes (10:00)\nPrepare and circulate updated storyboard for review before video production advances (11:00)\nReview contract details with client and communicate cancellation deadlines to internal teams (14:27)\nPrioritize rapid completion of product and action plans videos to meet December deadline (12:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"d0aa467f-cf15-4109-a1b5-61349147bc3d","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
