WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '6a9f190a-9e44-4b24-8f1d-d82022950bb9',
    '2025-11-13 13:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9CPB1NNGDX2ZNS6ZAF4G6K4',
    'Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
    '{"Monique King","Nathalie Mintjens","Shane Billings","derey"}'::text[],
    854,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83663022990?pwd=R1aTMdTGv2yblYfzlB6Wv1Sup4Z47U.1',
    '{"id":"01K9CPB1NNGDX2ZNS6ZAF4G6K4","title":"Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing and Lead Nurture Strategy**\n\nThe team is advancing a multi-layered nurture strategy to engage middle-funnel prospects and increase lead conversions.\n\n- **Nathalie Mintjens outlined a refresh of the ABM campaign with new display ads, email sequences, and personalized landing pages for DSOs and Billers by late November** (00:38)  \n    - New ad creatives will be ready by the **13th**, emails by the **17th**, and landing pages by the **24th** of November.  \n    - The landing pages include a dedicated page outlining the **free trial offer** to facilitate conversions.  \n    - This refresh aims to boost engagement, as the current ABM campaign shows declining website clicks nearing its end.  \n    - The updated campaign will use targeted display and LinkedIn ads to push the free trial to warmed leads.  \n\n- **Shane Billings emphasized that the free trial should focus on the prospect’s hardest office to communicate with, encouraging a meaningful test of the product** (01:26)  \n    - This approach targets problem areas for the prospect, increasing trial relevance and likelihood of conversion.  \n    - Monique King clarified trial flexibility, affirming no limits on locations but encouraging focus on challenging offices.  \n    - Nathalie will explore embedding this messaging either in the trial offer or sales process to maximize impact.  \n\n- **The nurture sequence will escalate engagement by targeting contacts who click emails or visit the website with a more direct follow-up pushing the free trial** (09:46)  \n    - Engagement data includes website visits and email clicks, allowing precise retargeting.  \n    - Shane confirmed the second email sequence targets those who show meaningful interaction to deepen interest.  \n    - Complementing emails, targeted LinkedIn ads will use uploaded account and contact lists to reinforce messaging.  \n\n- **LinkedIn ads show improved efficiency, with cost per click dropping from $13.70 last year to $9.80 after refining the audience** (11:41)  \n    - This indicates better audience relevance and suggests further creative updates will reduce costs even more.  \n    - The team expects the refreshed campaign and nurture layers to reverse the recent decline in website traffic and lead engagement.  \n\n## **Sales and Trial Offer Execution**\n\nThe sales approach will focus on enabling prospects to trial the product in their most problematic office to prove value quickly.\n\n- **Shane Billings stressed the importance of prospects “kicking the tires” on their hardest office, allowing them to test the product where it matters most** (01:56)  \n    - This strategy aims to surface tangible pain points and demonstrate product effectiveness.  \n    - It also avoids overwhelming prospects with full multi-location trials, which can dilute focus and results.  \n    - Sales messaging will encourage prospects to pick their most challenging office while keeping trial access flexible.  \n\n- **Monique King confirmed ongoing outreach to key contacts, but noted that Maria from iMed claims remains unresponsive despite multiple attempts** (03:26)  \n    - This limits progress with that prospect, signaling a need to shift focus or escalate.  \n    - The team will continue pursuing alternative leads and nurture paths.  \n\n- **Shane highlighted the need to increase demos as the critical bottom-line metric, noting current demo volume is insufficient** (13:22)  \n    - The free trial offer and refreshed nurture campaign are expected to drive demo bookings by creating stronger interest.  \n    - Monique and Dave agreed that the planned initiatives align well with this goal.  \n\n## **Customer and Consultant Engagement**\n\nThe team is proactively engaging customers and consultants to deepen relationships and build pipeline.\n\n- **23 contacts who agreed to case studies received survey emails via Zoho CRM for feedback and testimonials** (09:11)  \n    - Shane will monitor responses to his @gripon.com email and coordinate next steps as needed.  \n    - This effort supports building credibility and content for marketing materials.  \n\n- **A consultant expressed interest in joining the podcast, initiating a new engagement opportunity** (04:00)  \n    - Monique currently lacks capacity to host but Shane offered to coordinate and possibly participate.  \n    - Podcasts are scheduled Wednesdays at 6 PM Eastern, aiming for efficient scheduling between Shane and Brad.  \n    - Nathalie will facilitate introduction emails and coordinate initial meetings to explore topics and collaboration.  \n\n- **LinkedIn outreach yielded several positive networking replies, suggesting growing interest in meetings and potential partnerships** (04:00)  \n    - These responses create fresh touchpoints for pipeline development and brand awareness.  \n\n## **Contract and Client Transition Communication**\n\nThe team is preparing messaging for clients affected by contract changes with third parties.\n\n- **Nathalie is crafting an email sequence for eAssist indirect clients to inform them about continuing service options directly with the company** (07:11)  \n    - Shane advised clear communication about data ownership and potential service interruptions due to contract terms.  \n    - Messaging will balance politeness with urgency, noting the possible end date of eAssist service and encouraging transition.  \n    - This sequence is on hold pending resolution of intellectual property negotiations currently handled by legal teams.  \n\n- **Shane flagged that contract negotiations have a sticking point on intellectual property, which could affect service continuity** (08:26)  \n    - The legal discussions must conclude favorably for the transition plan to proceed.  \n    - Nathalie will keep the messaging draft ready to deploy immediately if service termination occurs.  \n\n## **Operational Coordination and Follow-up**\n\nThe team is maintaining close communication to ensure follow-ups and task completion.\n\n- **Dave confirmed connection with Monique last week but has not yet reached Hannah despite email and text attempts** (12:56)  \n    - Shane recommended adding phone calls with voicemail to improve contact chances.  \n\n- **Nathalie will send recap emails after the meeting and follow up immediately on the consultant introduction and campaign asset deliveries** (13:46)  \n    - She will CC Shane to keep him in the loop for prompt responses and coordination.  \n\n- **Monique and Dave both agreed with the planned marketing and nurture strategies, ensuring alignment across the team** (11:02)  \n\n- **Shane emphasized the urgency of increasing demos to drive business growth, framing it as the team''s main goal** (13:22)","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","Nurture Strategy","Free Trial Offer","Podcast Scheduling","LinkedIn Ads","Customer Survey"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Refresh:** New ads, emails, and landing pages launching between November 13 and 24 to boost engagement and conversions.  \n- **Free Trial Focus:** Trials target the most challenging offices for prospects, enhancing relevance and increasing conversion likelihood.  \n- **Enhanced Nurture Sequence:** Retargeting active leads with tailored follow-ups to encourage trial sign-ups and demo bookings.  \n- **Cost per Click Improvement:** LinkedIn ads efficiency increased, reducing cost per click from $13.70 to $9.80 after audience refinement.  \n- **Client Communication Plans:** Email sequence for eAssist clients in progress, balancing urgency with politeness amid contract negotiations.  \n- **Demos as Key Metric:** Emphasis on increasing demos to drive growth, aligning initiatives to boost interest and bookings.","action_items":"\n**Monique King**\nContinue follow-up attempts with Maria from iMed claims (03:26)\nCoordinate podcast communications including connecting Shane and the consultant for an introductory call (06:55)\nAssist with new customer nurture email list and sequences, especially indirect eAssist client messaging (07:26)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nSend recap of meeting to Shane and potentially to other stakeholders (00:01)\nWork on integrating Shane’s feedback about free trial targeting into marketing materials and sales processes (02:09)\nDraft emails and creative assets for ABM campaign refresh with deadlines: ads by Nov 13, email sequences by Nov 17, landing pages by Nov 24 (07:01)\nPrepare email sequence for eAssist indirect clients to communicate service transition while awaiting legal clearance (07:33)\nMonitor and alert Shane of any case study survey responses from contacts (09:11)\nImplement multi-layer nurture strategy using engagement data to trigger emails and ad campaigns promoting the free trial offer (09:46)\nFollow up with Shane on responses to podcast-related communications and send all discussed assets once finalized (13:54)\n\n**Shane Billings**\nMonitor responses to customer survey and case study invitation emails sent via Zoho CRM (09:35)\nProvide feedback or approval on drafted email sequences for indirect clients and nurture campaigns (07:26)\nParticipate in podcast recordings on Wednesdays at 6 PM Eastern coordinating with Brad (05:20)\nCoordinate with Brad to confirm availability for podcast sessions and introductory meetings with podcast guests (06:15)\n\n**David Edmund Reynolds**\nContinue efforts to contact Hannah via email, text, and phone call for outreach follow-up (13:04)\n"},"duration":14.239999771118164,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Monique King"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Shane Billings"},{"id":3,"name":"derey"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Saw that.","index":0,"end_time":0.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Okay.","index":1,"end_time":0.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.48,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":2,"end_time":1.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, we can get started.","index":3,"end_time":3.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I can also send him a recap afterwards.","index":4,"end_time":6.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":5,"end_time":8.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.6,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Oh, here he is.","index":6,"end_time":15.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hi, Shane.","index":7,"end_time":25.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How are you?","index":8,"end_time":26.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":26.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Good.","index":9,"end_time":27.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.45,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"How are you?","index":10,"end_time":28.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Good.","index":11,"end_time":29.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":28.81,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I was able to sneak away.","index":12,"end_time":30.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":29.17,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Great.","index":13,"end_time":31.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''re just about to get started.","index":14,"end_time":34.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Good.","index":15,"end_time":35.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":35.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"All right, so just looking at your points coming up.","index":16,"end_time":41.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So since last meeting put quite a few more things into working to complete in November.","index":17,"end_time":48.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So first of all, is this re engagement or our nurture strategy that we talked about?","index":18,"end_time":53.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":49.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So making sure that we''re continuing to nurture that middle of the funnel.","index":19,"end_time":58.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll have some display ads that we''re working on, as well as an email sequence and then creating new web pages.","index":20,"end_time":65.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So one for DSOs and Billers as we refresh the ABM campaign so that they can have more personalized landing pages as well as a landing page that outlines the free trial offer.","index":21,"end_time":77.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So while we''re running those display ads, somewhere where people can land as well as the November newsletter.","index":22,"end_time":83.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I.","index":23,"end_time":87.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":86.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"For the.","index":24,"end_time":88.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":88.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"For the free trial, one of.","index":25,"end_time":91.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":89,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"One of the thoughts I had was that that they should trial us on the office that they struggle to communicate with the most.","index":26,"end_time":99.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.84,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You know, I don''t know if that''s something to consider in the.","index":27,"end_time":104.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.2,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"In the.","index":28,"end_time":105.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":104.76,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"In the free offer month.","index":29,"end_time":108.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":106.76,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Mm.","index":30,"end_time":109.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":31,"end_time":112.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":112.07,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":114.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll let you guys stew on that.","index":33,"end_time":119.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.87,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s the right message.","index":34,"end_time":122.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":121.11,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I honestly don''t.","index":35,"end_time":123.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.67,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But when people say, hey, let me try trial with an office, I. I say, yeah, pick your hardest office.","index":36,"end_time":128.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.67,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":130.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":38,"end_time":131.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll see how we can bake that in.","index":39,"end_time":133.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Or maybe it''s something that happens in the sales process.","index":40,"end_time":136.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It could be.","index":41,"end_time":137.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.2,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":42,"end_time":138.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.68,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I can highlight that.","index":43,"end_time":141.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.4,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"So, Shane, what you''re saying is like, let''s say like with that other RCM company, right, they had like 50 locations.","index":44,"end_time":152.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.92,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Essentially, we were going to let them trial all 50 locations, but, like, that just doesn''t really make a ton of sense.","index":45,"end_time":160.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.52,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"So pick one.","index":46,"end_time":161.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.32,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"You broke.","index":47,"end_time":167.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":166.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You broke up there at the end for me.","index":48,"end_time":168.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":167.11,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I''m going through kind of a little gray spot right now.","index":49,"end_time":173.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.67,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"So what you''re saying is if they have multiple locations, we.","index":50,"end_time":178.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.99,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"They can only trial.","index":51,"end_time":180.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.79,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"They could trial as as many as they want.","index":52,"end_time":184.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m not going to put a limit on it, but what I want them to do is feel like they can kick the tires.","index":53,"end_time":189.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":184.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":54,"end_time":192.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.08,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":55,"end_time":192.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.16,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Like really try us out.","index":56,"end_time":193.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.76,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like we''re supposed to solve a problem.","index":57,"end_time":195.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":193.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What problem do you have?","index":58,"end_time":196.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":195.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And put us on your hardest office anyway.","index":59,"end_time":202.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":196.44,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":60,"end_time":205.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":204.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then real quick, Monique, what happened?","index":61,"end_time":209.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.68,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Did we ever get in touch again with Maria.","index":62,"end_time":213,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.64,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Did she ever get back with us?","index":63,"end_time":214.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"She did not know.","index":64,"end_time":216.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.33,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Okay.","index":65,"end_time":217.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":216.85,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And she''s not answering your phone calls.","index":66,"end_time":219.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.41,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Correct.","index":67,"end_time":221.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.61,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"I''ve left a message and she''s not retarded.","index":68,"end_time":223.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.09,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Super.","index":69,"end_time":224.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":70,"end_time":226.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.97,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Is that the iMed claims one?","index":71,"end_time":231.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yes, that''s the one.","index":72,"end_time":234.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.65,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Okay.","index":73,"end_time":237.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"There were.","index":74,"end_time":240.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.73,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"I did see a few more positive replies come through this week on LinkedIn.","index":75,"end_time":244.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Seemed like a couple of them were interested in meeting or looking to set up a time to meet.","index":76,"end_time":250.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then those were just for the networking meetings.","index":77,"end_time":253.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":251.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we did receive a reply on email from a consultant that''s open to joining the podcast as a guest.","index":78,"end_time":261.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So here I''m wondering what''s the best way to go about it?","index":79,"end_time":265.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because the emails are coming from Monique.","index":80,"end_time":268.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that''s the name that she recognized.","index":81,"end_time":271.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":272.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.56,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Monique, are you open to doing podcasts?","index":83,"end_time":275.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Sorry, I''m on mute.","index":84,"end_time":279.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.32,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"I don''t have the capacity at the moment.","index":85,"end_time":282.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.16,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Okay.","index":86,"end_time":283.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.56,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"To do them.","index":87,"end_time":283.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.04,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"So.","index":88,"end_time":284.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.4,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Yeah, I apologize for that.","index":89,"end_time":287.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.52,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":90,"end_time":288.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":288.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That is a challenge for me and Brad as well.","index":91,"end_time":291.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":288.88,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right now.","index":92,"end_time":292.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":291.48,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I think I have more capacity than Brad, but I would like to be on the call because I guess if we have to, I''ll just do it, I guess coordinate between me and whoever''s responding.","index":93,"end_time":308.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":294.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":312.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":95,"end_time":313.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do you have a calendly link or something, Shane, that we could.","index":96,"end_time":316.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t really.","index":97,"end_time":318.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.69,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":98,"end_time":320.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But.","index":99,"end_time":321.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":320.65,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But the evenings are basically what.","index":100,"end_time":322.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":321.05,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The evenings are basically what?","index":101,"end_time":327.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":326.37,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"When.","index":102,"end_time":328.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":327.93,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"When I. Wednesday evening is when Brad and I tell you what, Wednesday evening.","index":103,"end_time":334.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":330.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I say evening, it''s like, I think we schedule it for six.","index":104,"end_time":337.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.93,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":105,"end_time":339.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.329,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And so six Eastern.","index":106,"end_time":342.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.09,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So let''s just say Wednesdays evenings at six.","index":107,"end_time":345.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.85,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then I''ll just do my best to get Brad.","index":108,"end_time":347.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.97,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"If he can''t, then we''ll try to, you know, let''s find a Wednesday evening at 6.","index":109,"end_time":357.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":347.73,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So I guess.","index":110,"end_time":358.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, so here''s what I''m thinking.","index":111,"end_time":360.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Email me and Brad, say you''ve got a consultant that''s interested in a podcast.","index":112,"end_time":364.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":360.62,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then say, I hear you guys do Wednesdays at 6.","index":113,"end_time":370.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.5,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Which one works for you?","index":114,"end_time":371.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then that.","index":115,"end_time":372.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''ll get me going with Brad.","index":116,"end_time":373.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":372.1,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":117,"end_time":375.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"In her reply, it sounded like she just wants to meet at first.","index":118,"end_time":380.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like, not for the recording, but just to discuss, like, what it could be about.","index":119,"end_time":384.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe do some intros.","index":120,"end_time":386.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, are you talking.","index":121,"end_time":388.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So not just the.","index":122,"end_time":389.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.15,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So she''s actually thinking about selling or distributing.","index":123,"end_time":393.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.229,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I should say no, just to meet you before the actual podcast.","index":124,"end_time":399.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":125,"end_time":399.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":399.11,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Then, yeah, just like, just shoot me in her email and say, hey, want to connect the two of you?","index":126,"end_time":406.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then I''ll Say sometime next week?","index":127,"end_time":409.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":406.78,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Most likely would be.","index":128,"end_time":411.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":409.94,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''d be a bit more available.","index":129,"end_time":413.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.94,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":130,"end_time":414.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.06,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"Okay.","index":131,"end_time":415.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.1,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yep.","index":132,"end_time":415.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So in other words, she just wants to chat.","index":133,"end_time":417.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.3,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":134,"end_time":418.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":135,"end_time":419.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":419.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, happy to.","index":136,"end_time":420.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":419.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":137,"end_time":421.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":138,"end_time":422.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for the ABM refresh, so just have some dates here of when we''ll have everything to you.","index":139,"end_time":429.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll have the new ad creatives on the 13th, email sequence on the 17th, and then those new landing pages on the 24th.","index":140,"end_time":437.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then also received your note about the e assist indirect clients.","index":141,"end_time":442.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll work on doing that.","index":142,"end_time":444.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Crafting the email sequence.","index":143,"end_time":446.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":144,"end_time":447.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.73,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Essentially just saying that they don''t have to stop their service.","index":145,"end_time":450.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.449,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They can get it directly with you.","index":146,"end_time":452.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":147,"end_time":453.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.45,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Something like, you know, I don''t know how we say this in a.","index":148,"end_time":459.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"In a polite way, but this has chosen to end service on such and such a date.","index":149,"end_time":464.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":459.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You know, we''re sad to see him go or something.","index":150,"end_time":468.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":465.97,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":151,"end_time":468.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.41,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then whatever, you know, like to get them to say, hey, but you can continue the service uninterrupted.","index":152,"end_time":476.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.89,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Well, it will.","index":153,"end_time":477.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.41,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s actually kind of tricky.","index":154,"end_time":479.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It won''t be uninterrupted because they easist owns the data, so they''ll lose their data.","index":155,"end_time":485.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.49,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s the first thing they should be aware of.","index":156,"end_time":486.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":485.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like, you should store off any data that.","index":157,"end_time":488.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.98,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That you find or you should, you know, make notes of any data that you need.","index":158,"end_time":494.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.14,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":159,"end_time":495.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":495.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But then we''re happy to continue, you know, service for you.","index":160,"end_time":501.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m sure you''ll figure out the right wording.","index":161,"end_time":504.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":162,"end_time":505.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And to be clear, they haven''t backed out, but we are negotiating right now, and there''s a sticking point on I.","index":163,"end_time":517.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":506.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"On our intellectual property.","index":164,"end_time":519.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.5,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And if we don''t come to a conclusion, I don''t know what''s going to happen.","index":165,"end_time":523.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But right now our.","index":166,"end_time":524.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":523.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Our lawyers are talking.","index":167,"end_time":526.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":168,"end_time":527.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.299,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":169,"end_time":529.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll get this crafted just in case.","index":170,"end_time":532.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But yeah, it won''t go anywhere until we have your green light.","index":171,"end_time":536.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll let you know.","index":172,"end_time":538.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, you should hold on to it.","index":173,"end_time":540.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.98,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I just want it to be like, as soon as they back out, then I''m going to send this out.","index":174,"end_time":546.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":546.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Or if they do, they may never back out.","index":176,"end_time":549.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":550.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":178,"end_time":551.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":550.7,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":179,"end_time":552.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":180,"end_time":555.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''ll send that over once we have the draft and then for the customer survey.","index":181,"end_time":559.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we sent the email to 23contacts who said yes to doing the case study.","index":182,"end_time":565.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So those went through Zoho CRM.","index":183,"end_time":569.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So from your email, Shane, So just for you to monitor if you get any responses to your email.","index":184,"end_time":574.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Which email is that?","index":185,"end_time":576.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":575.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"My Gripon email.","index":186,"end_time":577.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":576.83,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":187,"end_time":578.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":578.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Shane, @g gripon.com okay, if I get.","index":188,"end_time":580.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":578.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Any responses, I''ll let you know.","index":189,"end_time":582.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":580.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":190,"end_time":585.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.51,"speaker_name":"Monique King"},{"text":"And then looking at the nurture strategy that we talked about last week.","index":191,"end_time":590.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So there are three layers that I''m kind of thinking about.","index":192,"end_time":593.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So once we have people that show a certain level of engagement through all that data we''ve been sharing, like website visits, email clicks, stuff like tha