INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
  '## **Marketing and Lead Nurture Strategy**

The team is advancing a multi-layered nurture strategy to engage middle-funnel prospects and increase lead conversions.

- **Nathalie Mintjens outlined a refresh of the ABM campaign with new display ads, email sequences, and personalized landing pages for DSOs and Billers by late November** (00:38)  
    - New ad creatives will be ready by the **13th**, emails by the **17th**, and landing pages by the **24th** of November.  
    - The landing pages include a dedicated page outlining the **free trial offer** to facilitate conversions.  
    - This refresh aims to boost engagement, as the current ABM campaign shows declining website clicks nearing its end.  
    - The updated campaign will use targeted display and LinkedIn ads to push the free trial to warmed leads.  

- **Shane Billings emphasized that the free trial should focus on the prospect’s hardest office to communicate with, encouraging a meaningful test of the product** (01:26)  
    - This approach targets problem areas for the prospect, increasing trial relevance and likelihood of conversion.  
    - Monique King clarified trial flexibility, affirming no limits on locations but encouraging focus on challenging offices.  
    - Nathalie will explore embedding this messaging either in the trial offer or sales process to maximize impact.  

- **The nurture sequence will escalate engagement by targeting contacts who click emails or visit the website with a more direct follow-up pushing the free trial** (09:46)  
    - Engagement data includes website visits and email clicks, allowing precise retargeting.  
    - Shane confirmed the second email sequence targets those who show meaningful interaction to deepen interest.  
    - Complementing emails, targeted LinkedIn ads will use uploaded account and contact lists to reinforce messaging.  

- **LinkedIn ads show improved efficiency, with cost per click dropping from $13.70 last year to $9.80 after refining the audience** (11:41)  
    - This indicates better audience relevance and suggests further creative updates will reduce costs even more.  
    - The team expects the refreshed campaign and nurture layers to reverse the recent decline in website traffic and lead engagement.  

## **Sales and Trial Offer Execution**

The sales approach will focus on enabling prospects to trial the product in their most problematic office to prove value quickly.

- **Shane Billings stressed the importance of prospects “kicking the tires” on their hardest office, allowing them to test the product where it matters most** (01:56)  
    - This strategy aims to surface tangible pain points and demonstrate product effectiveness.  
    - It also avoids overwhelming prospects with full multi-location trials, which can dilute focus and results.  
    - Sales messaging will encourage prospects to pick their most challenging office while keeping trial access flexible.  

- **Monique King confirmed ongoing outreach to key contacts, but noted that Maria from iMed claims remains unresponsive despite multiple attempts** (03:26)  
    - This limits progress with that prospect, signaling a need to shift focus or escalate.  
    - The team will continue pursuing alternative leads and nurture paths.  

- **Shane highlighted the need to increase demos as the critical bottom-line metric, noting current demo volume is insufficient** (13:22)  
    - The free trial offer and refreshed nurture campaign are expected to drive demo bookings by creating stronger interest.  
    - Monique and Dave agreed that the planned initiatives align well with this goal.  

## **Customer and Consultant Engagement**

The team is proactively engaging customers and consultants to deepen relationships and build pipeline.

- **23 contacts who agreed to case studies received survey emails via Zoho CRM for feedback and testimonials** (09:11)  
    - Shane will monitor responses to his @gripon.com email and coordinate next steps as needed.  
    - This effort supports building credibility and content for marketing materials.  

- **A consultant expressed interest in joining the podcast, initiating a new engagement opportunity** (04:00)  
    - Monique currently lacks capacity to host but Shane offered to coordinate and possibly participate.  
    - Podcasts are scheduled Wednesdays at 6 PM Eastern, aiming for efficient scheduling between Shane and Brad.  
    - Nathalie will facilitate introduction emails and coordinate initial meetings to explore topics and collaboration.  

- **LinkedIn outreach yielded several positive networking replies, suggesting growing interest in meetings and potential partnerships** (04:00)  
    - These responses create fresh touchpoints for pipeline development and brand awareness.  

## **Contract and Client Transition Communication**

The team is preparing messaging for clients affected by contract changes with third parties.

- **Nathalie is crafting an email sequence for eAssist indirect clients to inform them about continuing service options directly with the company** (07:11)  
    - Shane advised clear communication about data ownership and potential service interruptions due to contract terms.  
    - Messaging will balance politeness with urgency, noting the possible end date of eAssist service and encouraging transition.  
    - This sequence is on hold pending resolution of intellectual property negotiations currently handled by legal teams.  

- **Shane flagged that contract negotiations have a sticking point on intellectual property, which could affect service continuity** (08:26)  
    - The legal discussions must conclude favorably for the transition plan to proceed.  
    - Nathalie will keep the messaging draft ready to deploy immediately if service termination occurs.  

## **Operational Coordination and Follow-up**

The team is maintaining close communication to ensure follow-ups and task completion.

- **Dave confirmed connection with Monique last week but has not yet reached Hannah despite email and text attempts** (12:56)  
    - Shane recommended adding phone calls with voicemail to improve contact chances.  

- **Nathalie will send recap emails after the meeting and follow up immediately on the consultant introduction and campaign asset deliveries** (13:46)  
    - She will CC Shane to keep him in the loop for prompt responses and coordination.  

- **Monique and Dave both agreed with the planned marketing and nurture strategies, ensuring alignment across the team** (11:02)  

- **Shane emphasized the urgency of increasing demos to drive business growth, framing it as the team''s main goal** (13:22)',
  '2025-11-13 13:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Continue follow-up attempts with Maria from iMed claims (03:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate podcast communications including connecting Shane and the consultant for an introductory call (06:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist with new customer nurture email list and sequences, especially indirect eAssist client messaging (07:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Send recap of meeting to Shane and potentially to other stakeholders (00:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Work on integrating Shane’s feedback about free trial targeting into marketing materials and sales processes (02:09)","completed":false},{"text":"Draft emails and creative assets for ABM campaign refresh with deadlines: ads by Nov 13, email sequences by Nov 17, landing pages by Nov 24 (07:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare email sequence for eAssist indirect clients to communicate service transition while awaiting legal clearance (07:33)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and alert Shane of any case study survey responses from contacts (09:11)","completed":false},{"text":"Implement multi-layer nurture strategy using engagement data to trigger emails and ad campaigns promoting the free trial offer (09:46)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with Shane on responses to podcast-related communications and send all discussed assets once finalized (13:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor responses to customer survey and case study invitation emails sent via Zoho CRM (09:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback or approval on drafted email sequences for indirect clients and nurture campaigns (07:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Participate in podcast recordings on Wednesdays at 6 PM Eastern coordinating with Brad (05:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Brad to confirm availability for podcast sessions and introductory meetings with podcast guests (06:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue efforts to contact Hannah via email, text, and phone call for outreach follow-up (13:04)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: WFF // New North - Biweekly meeting (NEW) (2025-11-13 16:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '66a4318e-0698-422f-854d-3aeb4c4bd804',
    '2025-11-13 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9T9KM3SD535W3JSHKRXJ3GA',
    'WFF // New North - Biweekly meeting (NEW)',
    '{"Nina Belina","Baylee Gunnell","Christine Saur"}'::text[],
    1189,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89888531857?pwd=uck8EReGIMbbBMaTStifswLMDDbrpP.1&jst=2',
    '{"id":"01K9T9KM3SD535W3JSHKRXJ3GA","title":"WFF // New North - Biweekly meeting (NEW)","summary":{"notes":"## **Advertising Spend and Budget Management**\n\nThe team confirmed the **monthly advertising budget is $2,000**, split between **$1,500 for Google Ads** and **$500 for AdRoll** (01:15).  \n- Christine raised concerns after seeing a **$2,500 figure in QuickBooks**, prompting a follow-up to reconcile discrepancies between reported and actual spend.  \n- Baylee clarified that **ad spend for November has only reached about $400 so far**, indicating no overspending to date.  \n- Nina explained AdRoll’s weekly charges vary due to ad frequency and engagement but assured the **monthly spend does not exceed the $500 budget** (16:38).  \n- Baylee and Nina will provide a detailed explanation of AdRoll’s billing and campaign performance in a follow-up email to clear up confusion (19:17).\n\n## **Google Ads and Campaign Performance**\n\nGoogle Ads have generated **16 conversions so far in November**, showing a downward trend compared to previous months (02:58).  \n- Baylee attributed this partly to increased competition for key terms like \"we fix freight\" and recent campaign shifts including a new Costco distribution center focus.  \n- Christine noted overall business is slow due to tariffs impacting transport volumes, matching last year’s trend but below usual holiday season expectations (04:32).  \n- The Costco campaign has produced **8 conversions with a lower cost per lead**, suggesting early success despite Christine’s initial doubts about its relevance (05:48).  \n- The team agreed to monitor this campaign closely over the next few weeks to decide if budget should be shifted toward it or reverted to existing campaigns (06:40).  \n- Nina recommended increasing budget allocation to Costco campaigns since early data shows promising engagement and specificity against competitors (10:54).  \n- She also suggested refining landing pages to focus more on top services like lumper services and pallet restocking to better convert interested visitors (11:50).\n\n## **AdRoll Campaigns and Brand Awareness**\n\nAdRoll campaigns are not strong drivers of direct conversions but generate significant **impressions and clicks**, boosting brand awareness in a niche market (07:49).  \n- Baylee reported a positive uptick in clicks after refreshing image ads with Christine’s preferred creatives (07:47).  \n- Christine shared anecdotal evidence that brand trust is critical, as customers frequently mention encountering less credible competitors (08:29).  \n- The team agreed to create a dedicated landing page for AdRoll traffic to better explain services and build trust without increasing ad spend, using existing campaign points (09:07).  \n- Christine approved a trial run for this landing page to improve visitor experience and form submission rates (10:06).\n\n## **Lead Tracking and Data Transparency**\n\nChristine requested visibility into who is submitting leads from the Costco campaign to validate genuine interest and filter out low-quality submissions (07:05).  \n- Baylee confirmed that lead details can be extracted from HubSpot and committed to sharing this data after the meeting (07:40).  \n- This transparency will help assess campaign effectiveness and client quality, supporting budget decisions and campaign tuning.\n\n## **Long-term Engagement and New Channel Exploration**\n\nThe team discussed longer-term engagement strategies including event swag for the February women’s conference and social media expansion (12:17).  \n- Christine confirmed interest in launching a TikTok presence, acknowledging its growing importance for reach, though no specific examples or plans currently exist (12:46).  \n- Nina offered to research TikTok accounts in the logistics space to identify best practices and potential content directions (13:22).  \n- This signals a gradual move toward more diversified digital engagement to capture emerging audience segments.\n\n## **Dashboard Monitoring and Keyword Strategy**\n\nNina summarized the dashboard showing stable visitor numbers and lead flow despite slight Google Ads conversion dips early in the month (13:59).  \n- She emphasized maintaining focus on top-performing keywords and adjusting campaigns to reflect changing competitive pressures and seasonal patterns (15:47).  \n- The team plans to keep a close watch on budget pacing and keyword effectiveness, adjusting spend to maximize return during slow market periods (15:55).  \n- Baylee and Nina will continue providing detailed reporting and flag any discrepancies for prompt resolution.","outline":null,"keywords":["Google Ads","AdRoll","Costco Campaign","Advertising Budget","Landing Page","TikTok Marketing"],"overview":"- **Monthly Advertising Budget:** Set at $2,000; $1,500 for Google Ads, $500 for AdRoll, despite QuickBooks reporting $2,500.  \n- **Google Ads Performance:** 16 conversions in November; downtrend due to competition and seasonal tariff impacts noted.  \n- **Costco Campaign Success:** 8 conversions at lower cost per lead; early positive engagement prompts possible budget shift discussions.  \n- **AdRoll Effectiveness:** Generates impressions and clicks for brand awareness; need dedicated landing page for improved trust without extra spend.  \n- **Lead Tracking Needs:** Request for lead visibility from Costco campaign to ensure quality submissions; data to be extracted from HubSpot.  \n- **Future Engagement Strategies:** Interest in TikTok and event promotion; researching best practices for broader digital outreach and audience capture.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nProvide detailed HubSpot report showing lead identities and engagement from Costco campaign to Christine Saur (07:40)\nCreate and implement a dedicated landing page for AdRoll traffic using accumulated points; start trial phase (09:57)\nFollow up with Christine Saur on final budget reconciliation and detailed ad spend analysis in recap email (19:17)\nResearch TikTok logistics marketing accounts as examples to propose potential content and strategy (13:28)\nMonitor Google Ads and Costco campaign performance closely over coming weeks and advise on budget reallocation as needed (06:39)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nCollaborate with Baylee to send lead data from HubSpot and conduct TikTok account research (07:40)\nSupport creation and optimization of landing pages specific to high-performing freight services for better user experience and conversion (11:51)\nContinue analyzing dashboard and keyword performance, recommending budget and targeting adjustments (15:47)\n\n**Christine Saur**\nInvestigate QuickBooks ad spend data discrepancy for potential miscategorization or errors (01:49)\nMonitor ad campaign effectiveness and share feedback or anomalies to marketing team (00:00)\n"},"duration":19.809999465942383,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":1,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":2,"name":"Christine Saur"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":0.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.64,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":1,"end_time":2.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Pretty good.","index":2,"end_time":4.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3.44,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"How are you?","index":3,"end_time":4.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":4.12,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, doing great.","index":4,"end_time":6.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I wanted to introduce you to someone else on the team.","index":5,"end_time":9.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I say this, I''m not leaving.","index":6,"end_time":12.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m just bringing on additional support.","index":7,"end_time":14.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, not going anywhere.","index":8,"end_time":18.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m going to be with you for a while.","index":9,"end_time":19.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But Nina is a really talented content strategist.","index":10,"end_time":23.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"She''s been helping on the back end for a while now, so just wanted to introduce you to her.","index":11,"end_time":29.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ll probably be seeing some messages from her, but you''re just going to love working with her.","index":12,"end_time":34.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s nice to meet you, Dana.","index":13,"end_time":36.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":35.46,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Nice to meet you as well.","index":14,"end_time":38.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.98,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":15,"end_time":41.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.14,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Is Andy.","index":16,"end_time":42.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.86,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Andy''s not here yet, right?","index":17,"end_time":43.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":42.5,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Nope.","index":18,"end_time":44.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, Don just texted.","index":19,"end_time":47.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.22,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Said he won''t be able to join because he''s having computer issues.","index":20,"end_time":50.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":47.3,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Man, always a computer issue.","index":21,"end_time":54.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Frustrating.","index":22,"end_time":56.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Quite often.","index":23,"end_time":58.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":57.81,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s all good.","index":24,"end_time":61.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But I have not heard anything from Andy.","index":25,"end_time":64.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.73,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"I. I did want to ask you.","index":26,"end_time":66.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":64.69,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"I think what I looked at was our latest total spend was 2,500amonth on.","index":27,"end_time":72.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.05,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"On just the ads.","index":28,"end_time":73.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":72.01,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Is that correct?","index":29,"end_time":74.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":73.41,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Let me get the exact number real quick.","index":30,"end_time":79.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I believe your Overall budget is 2000amonth.","index":31,"end_time":90.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we do 1500 on Google Ads and 500 on AdRoll.","index":32,"end_time":95.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I saw something the other day.","index":33,"end_time":100.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":99.28,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"It was a 2500.","index":34,"end_time":101.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.56,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So we do 2000.","index":35,"end_time":102.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":101.6,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay.","index":36,"end_time":103.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":102.96,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Where.","index":37,"end_time":104.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Where did you see it?","index":38,"end_time":105.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think it was in our QuickBooks software.","index":39,"end_time":111.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.09,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":40,"end_time":113.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I was wondering about that because that seems a little high.","index":41,"end_time":120.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.05,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"You know, I think 2000 seems a little high, but, you know, I. I really need some input from Andy on that, and he''s not here, so.","index":42,"end_time":128.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":121.17,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, it look.","index":43,"end_time":130.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t.","index":44,"end_time":132.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it should just be $2,000 a month.","index":45,"end_time":134.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think so far in November, we''ve only spent about $400 on ads.","index":46,"end_time":142.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I. Yeah, yeah, we have.","index":47,"end_time":146.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":142.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We haven''t gone over that, at least from what I can see on my end.","index":48,"end_time":150.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":49,"end_time":152.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":151.72,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"All right.","index":50,"end_time":153.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":152.84,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m gonna have to dig into that a little bit further as far as, you know, what I was looking at that they categorize, maybe that they''re putting something in the wrong.","index":51,"end_time":161.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":153.2,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":164.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":164.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let us know if.","index":53,"end_time":166.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":165.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":166.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.08,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"If there''s an issue there.","index":55,"end_time":167.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":56,"end_time":169.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.52,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":170.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we''ll just get into our stats and stuff.","index":58,"end_time":175.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":59,"end_time":176.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":175.8,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So we''ll start off with just our ad performance, looking at Google Ads and Ad Roll.","index":60,"end_time":184.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We also have a few.","index":61,"end_time":185.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just recommendations on a few other things we can work on, and then we''ll take a look at the client portal.","index":62,"end_time":192.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So starting off with Google Ads, we''ve seen 16 conversions so far this month, this is a bit of a downward trend we''re noticing, and this could be due to a couple things, like noticing some increased competition on the we fix freak keywords.","index":63,"end_time":212.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Also, we changed your campaign set up recently to also test for the Costco distribution centers.","index":64,"end_time":221.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Could also be related to seasonality.","index":65,"end_time":224.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is there, like, anything on your end that you.","index":66,"end_time":227.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You feel like maybe has changed that might contribute to this here?","index":67,"end_time":234.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I''m really kind of screwing with this right now.","index":68,"end_time":237.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":234.6,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We are down overall, just across the board, even with our regular customers that we have.","index":69,"end_time":243.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.96,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"But.","index":70,"end_time":244.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"No, the ads have not been performing as well as in the past.","index":71,"end_time":250.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.56,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Recently.","index":72,"end_time":250.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.08,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":73,"end_time":251.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":251.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think we had previously talked that, like, November and December usually are pretty busy because, like, there''s more product moving for the holidays.","index":74,"end_time":263.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is that typically true or, like, because of tariffs, Is there just less movement?","index":75,"end_time":271.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s less movement because of the tariffs.","index":76,"end_time":275.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.79,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"You know, I''m kind of looking at what''s going on and in respect to what happened last year, like, trying to do a comparison on that.","index":77,"end_time":284.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":275.39,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And.","index":78,"end_time":284.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.27,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And we seem to be tracking pretty close to last year.","index":79,"end_time":289.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.55,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"But, you know, overall business is very slow lately, and we''ve not been really making our numbers daily.","index":80,"end_time":295.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.51,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So I think that people were trying to.","index":81,"end_time":299.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.07,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"The retailers were trying to get everything in place before the tariffs took effect.","index":82,"end_time":304.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.86,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And so there''s decreased activity as far as transportation and movement on it.","index":83,"end_time":312.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.42,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":313.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because you were really busy this summer.","index":85,"end_time":315.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, yes, we had a great, great summer.","index":86,"end_time":318.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.74,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":87,"end_time":318.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":318.02,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":88,"end_time":318.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":89,"end_time":319.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.1,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Well, I''m not sure that targeting the Costco distribution centers is going to work out for us either, because, you know, a lot of those places like.","index":90,"end_time":329.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.82,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Like with us in the Costco that''s local to us, a lot of those places have local, established rework facilities.","index":91,"end_time":337.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":329.47,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay.","index":92,"end_time":338.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, I. I don''t think that, you know, necessarily targeting those areas is.","index":93,"end_time":343.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.71,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Is really, you know, the best plane.","index":94,"end_time":348.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.87,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, well, jumping into that, we''ve seen eight conversions for that so far this month just on our Costco campaign.","index":95,"end_time":357.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And the cost per lead seems to be a bit lower than what we have running on the other things.","index":96,"end_time":364.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it seems to be doing decently well compared to the other campaigns.","index":97,"end_time":371.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sorry, what''s that?","index":98,"end_time":372.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":99,"end_time":373.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":372.67,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":100,"end_time":373.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.31,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"That''s good performance.","index":101,"end_time":375.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":374.67,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"It seems to be off to a good start.","index":102,"end_time":378.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But I think we just need to keep a close eye on it over the next few weeks to see if I either.","index":103,"end_time":385.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If it continues to do well, like, maybe we move some of the budget from the other campaigns here or if it''s.","index":104,"end_time":392.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If we''re Noticing it''s not as good, then we can turn this off and go back to what we were doing before.","index":105,"end_time":398.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":106,"end_time":400.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":399.4,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"But really good signals to get started.","index":107,"end_time":402.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It usually takes about two weeks for a campaign to get warmed up and we''ve like, hit that and now it''s.","index":108,"end_time":407.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It seems to be getting some good leads.","index":109,"end_time":410.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like the, the data there.","index":110,"end_time":415.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.94,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Do you know who is driving that?","index":111,"end_time":418.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.74,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Like, what.","index":112,"end_time":419.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.9,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Who would have clicked and filled out the form?","index":113,"end_time":424.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.9,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We could go into HubSpot.","index":114,"end_time":426.579,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Are you looking, like, for a specific name of who?","index":115,"end_time":428.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.579,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I''m just looking at like, for specifically the Costco campaigns.","index":116,"end_time":433.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":429.46,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Who.","index":117,"end_time":433.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.22,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Who was clicking on that just to see if, you know, that''s something that we''re actually able to pick up rather than somebody just, you know, sending in the form because we don''t get all the forms that they send in.","index":118,"end_time":444.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.58,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":445.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.77,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So if I''m understanding, like, can.","index":120,"end_time":451.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can we pinpoint who in HubSpot has filled out a form from this campaign?","index":121,"end_time":457.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":122,"end_time":459.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.65,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yes.","index":123,"end_time":459.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":124,"end_time":460.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":459.93,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we should be able to find that in HubSpot.","index":125,"end_time":462.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we''ll just need to send that over to you in our email afterwards.","index":126,"end_time":466.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can let you know who that is.","index":127,"end_time":467.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":128,"end_time":468.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.91,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"I would like to see that.","index":129,"end_time":469.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.47,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":130,"end_time":470.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then next, just looking at AdRoll, getting a lot of impressions here.","index":131,"end_time":476.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We did update the image ads just based on what we talked about last week, putting some of your favorite ones in there, and have seen a bit of an increase in the clicks on this as well.","index":132,"end_time":488.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah, seems to be doing pretty good so far.","index":133,"end_time":492.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This isn''t a great campaign for conversions, but it does generate a lot of awareness, which I feel like is helpful in this industry because not everyone is in need of freight services all the time, but when they need it, then they can remember.","index":134,"end_time":509.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You just had a guy this morning who tell me, he was like, I assume that you''re licensed and insured and, you know, all this was like, of course we are.","index":135,"end_time":519.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":509.31,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":136,"end_time":520.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.03,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And he said, he said, I talked to a lot of shady people before I found you guys.","index":137,"end_time":525.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.39,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Wow.","index":138,"end_time":526.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":139,"end_time":526.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.43,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So I was like, okay.","index":140,"end_time":528.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.83,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"All right.","index":141,"end_time":528.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.31,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So there are other people that are coming up though.","index":142,"end_time":531.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.91,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"You know, when, when you''re doing a search for something like this, if you talk to a lot of shady people, like, I''m wondering how they''re out there advertising what''s going on there.","index":143,"end_time":540.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.79,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve talked to a lot of shady people recently too.","index":144,"end_time":543.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.23,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We''ve had a lot of people coming through that are just scams.","index":145,"end_time":546.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":544.03,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, that''s unfortunate.","index":146,"end_time":549.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then next, something we would recommend, and this is specifically for the AdRoll campaigns running right now, we''re just going to your Contact Us page.","index":147,"end_time":563.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We.","index":148,"end_time":563.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It would be beneficial to create a dedicated landing page.","index":149,"end_time":567.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have pages like this right now for the Google Ads campaigns, basically like outlining your specific services.","index":150,"end_time":574.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we think it would be good just to have a bit more context about who you are.","index":151,"end_time":580.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What you do see still have a form there so people can fill it out, but just build it out a bit more to improve that experience.","index":152,"end_time":587.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":590.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is that something you think you''d want to do?","index":154,"end_time":595.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And does that increase our ad spend?","index":155,"end_time":600.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.08,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"No, no, we''ll just charge some points for it.","index":156,"end_time":603.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":600.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But you have the points available to do it.","index":157,"end_time":606.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, if we have the points available, it is something that you would recommend, I think.","index":158,"end_time":611.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.76,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Can, can we, can we try.","index":159,"end_time":612.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":611.8,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Can we give it a trial run?","index":160,"end_time":614.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.09,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":615.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, let''s do that.","index":162,"end_time":616.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":615.73,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll get started on that.","index":163,"end_time":618.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then another great thing we''ve noticed is your emergency card has seen a lot more downloads since we added it to the banner of your website and have launched some new ads on AdRoll as well.","index":164,"end_time":634.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":620.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve had 39 over the last 30 days.","index":165,"end_time":638.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":634.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So take seems to be doing pretty well.","index":166,"end_time":639.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, those are good numbers.","index":167,"end_time":642.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640.54,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s looking really good.","index":168,"end_time":643.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":642.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, then I''ll just kick it over to Nina now to go over some of our last items.","index":169,"end_time":652.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we already discussed that the Costco campaign is working really well.","index":170,"end_time":657.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean, especially because it''s relatively new and we usually have a time when the algorithm is learning about the campaign.","index":171,"end_time":664.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So to have already eight leads when it''s just starting, it''s a really good sign for the future.","index":172,"end_time":669.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We would recommend thinking about maybe allocating more of the budget to the Costco campaign, because if you have something that''s specific and you see that it''s working, it''s always good to push it in that direction, rather to keep it at the general, general field.","index":173,"end_time":687.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Especially because you mentioned that there are people who are also trying to compete for the same keywords or are popping off to people who are looking for fight services.","index":174,"end_time":697.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.32,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So, you know, to just be more specific and if it''s geographical, for example, such as Costco, then that also is a good sign on what people are looking for for the landing pages.","index":175,"end_time":709.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.28,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bailey said since we have some specific keywords that people are usually targeting, so lumper services, pallet restocking, warehouse stamp agencies, it would be good to make it a little bit more specific to our top performing services.","index":176,"end_time":725.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.27,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So not just the contact page, but something that really speaks to the people who are looking for the service and Also to give us, you know, the, to show them that we really are who we say we are.","index":177,"end_time":737.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.15,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Especially because you said that there are people who seem a little bit shady and are offering the same services for the pending actions.","index":178,"end_time":747.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We have the women''s conference, which is in February, so we still have time to pick the item that we want to have a Swag.","index":179,"end_time":756.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.96,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And for TikTok, you mentioned that it''s something that you would like to try.","index":180,"end_time":760.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.56,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So is it something that you still have in mind or.","index":181,"end_time":763.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But maybe in the future.","index":182,"end_time":764.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"That for some time I''m wondering why it''s never been implemented.","index":183,"end_time":769.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":766.88,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We, we.","index":184,"end_time":770.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.84,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We do want to do the TikTok and you know, because that''s, that''s what people are using out there.","index":185,"end_time":778.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.44,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"You know, if we could get it more coverage better.","index":186,"end_time":780.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.28,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And do you have any examples that you noticed that you liked from the logistics sector?","index":187,"end_time":786.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.52,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Do you want us to find them?","index":188,"end_time":789.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Maybe an example of, of an account that''s.","index":189,"end_time":795.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"That''s similar to what you would like to achieve?","index":190,"end_time":797.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.45,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Oh, of, of a TikTok account?","index":191,"end_time":800.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.33,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":801.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.65,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"No, we.","index":193,"end_time":802.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.01,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"I do not.","index":194,"end_time":803.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.77,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":195,"end_time":804.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":803.93,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"I can''t speak for Andy, but I.","index":196,"end_time":806.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.81,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"No, on this end.","index":197,"end_time":808.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":807.05,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"No, we can look into it.","index":198,"end_time":810.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.17,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":199,"end_time":811.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":810.73,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":200,"end_time":814.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":813.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then last we''ll just take a look at the dashboard to see where we''re at with points, with everything.","index":201,"end_time":820.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":815.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m going to stop sharing and just let.","index":202,"end_time":822.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nah.","index":203,"end_time":823.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Share this.","index":204,"end_time":824.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":205,"end_time":824.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My.","index":206,"end_time":825.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know how that bar moves sometimes.","index":207,"end_time":828.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":208,"end_time":828.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"To stop sharing.","index":209,"end_time":830.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just second.","index":210,"end_time":832.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":831.73,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":211,"end_time":840.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.41,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for the last 30 days we had a good amount of visitors and as you can see, the leads are still performing fine.","index":212,"end_time":858.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.26,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The only things that we mentioned from the Google Ads campaign that we saw a slight decrease.","index":213,"end_time":863.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It''s still the beginning of the month, so it could be that it''s just, you know, early days, but it''s something to keep in mind and to keep a lookout on the competitors and the keywords that we''re going for for the web page, I think that the slight changes that we suggested, for example, as the landing page, to speak a little bit more about the service, since that''s the landing page that most people are coming to, which is Contact us, will also be a really good value for the visitor to sign actually contact to fill in the form.","index":214,"end_time":902.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.1,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And the second page is Fright Solutions.","index":215,"end_time":907.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.83,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So it''s obvious that people are looking for a little bit more information on the company and for the Google Ads impressions is what we talked about is how the keywords are performing, who our main competitors are and also to keep in mind that it''s it, it does seem like it''s a little bit less than previous months, but at the same time it is the two months that we would expect more from logistics.","index":216,"end_time":937.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.83,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So just what we always do is we keep, keep our eye on the budget and also keep an eye on which keywords are performing well and which aren''t.","index":217,"end_time":947.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":938.05,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then, you know, being, focusing more on the ones that are performing that are dedicated to the services and also for the ad cost.","index":218,"end_time":962.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.29,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean you can see everything from here.","index":219,"end_time":964.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.72,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But also let us know if you noticed anything that you mentioned on the beginning that it might seem like it''s not the same number and we will look into it and let you know if it''s the same from our side.","index":220,"end_time":979.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So the ad roll with 594 because they, they charge like different amounts every week.","index":221,"end_time":988.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.85,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And it, it''s just like, you know, I''d have to go through the, the, the checkbook and find out how much we''re actually paying them because it''s not, it''s not like a set amount.","index":222,"end_time":997.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":988.41,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Oh, it definitely, it''s a set amount, but it depends on the frequency of which the ads are shown.","index":223,"end_time":1005.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.25,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for example, if you have one day that does not require them to be, have a bigger spend lower than for example, as a day where, when it''s a little bit more frequent.","index":224,"end_time":1018.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, so does that, is that something that we drive or is that, is.","index":225,"end_time":1023.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.79,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"That it depends on the, on the audience and you know, the interest in, for example, in the keywords or in the ads or just how, how well it''s performing that day.","index":226,"end_time":1035.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s, it''s all part of their algorithm.","index":227,"end_time":1038.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can''t really control it.","index":228,"end_time":1040.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We just set like what the budget is and then it''s not going to be consistent every day or every week.","index":229,"end_time":1046.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And also the algorithm keeps learning.","index":230,"end_time":1050.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1048.06,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So every, you know, two weeks, every month, it will learn more and more from the audience and show it to the right people who are interested.","index":231,"end_time":1058.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.94,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So the more interest we get in our ads on AdRoll, the more they charge that particular period.","index":232,"end_time":1070.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1061.18,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Is that, is that what you''re for ad?","index":233,"end_time":1073.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1070.64,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"No, it should be a set amount.","index":234,"end_time":1075.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":235,"end_time":1077.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1077.44,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Because it''s not a set amount.","index":236,"end_time":1079.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1077.88,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"That''s what I''m saying though.","index":237,"end_time":1080.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1079.4,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"When, what they charge different amounts every week?","index":238,"end_time":1083.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1080.4,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, it, it varies on how the ads, how often the ads are shown and like how often people are reacting.","index":239,"end_time":1093.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1083.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can send you an article that like talks about it in more detail, but like it should never go over what your budget is.","index":240,"end_time":1102.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1094,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, but the actual amount they charge every week is going to be different.","index":241,"end_time":1106.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Right.","index":242,"end_time":1107.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1107.36,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"All right, fair enough.","index":243,"end_time":1110.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1107.84,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":244,"end_time":1111.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s.","index":245,"end_time":1111.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s complicated.","index":246,"end_time":1112.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s weird.","index":247,"end_time":1113.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1112.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It is complicated.","index":248,"end_time":1114.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.84,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"594.","index":249,"end_time":1116.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.68,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"When our budget, you told me is 500.","index":250,"end_time":1119.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1116.88,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, well, and that''s because this is looking at the last 30 days.","index":251,"end_time":1124.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So in, like, if we went from November 1st to November 30th, it won''t go over 500.","index":252,"end_time":1134.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1126.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But, like, the last two weeks of October might be higher, but, like, if you look month to month, it won''t go over 500.","index":253,"end_time":1142.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1134.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is October 14th to November 12th, so it could be that it''s starting with the more expensive week and ending with the expensive week, so.","index":254,"end_time":1152.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1142.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Right.","index":255,"end_time":1152.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1152.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":256,"end_time":1153.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1152.75,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, we can follow up with more information, too, in our.","index":257,"end_time":1161.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1157.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"In our recap email.","index":258,"end_time":1163.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, any other questions, Chris?","index":259,"end_time":1169.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''re good.","index":260,"end_time":1172.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1171.62,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":261,"end_time":1173.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1172.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, thanks so much for hopping on.","index":262,"end_time":1175.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1173.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And.","index":263,"end_time":1175.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we''ll follow up tomorrow with the remaining details.","index":264,"end_time":1179.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":265,"end_time":1180.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1179.94,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":266,"end_time":1181.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1180.42,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":267,"end_time":1181.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.14,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":268,"end_time":1182.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":269,"end_time":1183.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.74,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"See ya.","index":270,"end_time":1183.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1183.22,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"}],"dateString":"2025-11-13T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89888531857?pwd=uck8EReGIMbbBMaTStifswLMDDbrpP.1&jst=2","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,donhill@dedicatedtg.com,chris@wefixfreight.com,andrew@cashtoclose.net,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","donhill@dedicatedtg.com","chris@wefixfreight.com","andrew@cashtoclose.net","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9T9KM3SD535W3JSHKRXJ3GA","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.77,"bullets":["Clarified ad budget is $2,000/month; discrepancy may stem from QuickBooks categorization.","Noted decline in ad conversions likely due to tariffs and increased competition on key terms.","Eight early conversions on Costco campaign show promise; team will monitor for optimization.","AdRoll performing well on impressions; proposal to add landing pages to boost conversions.","Consensus to trial TikTok marketing and finalize women’s conference swag by February."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Overall business is very slow lately, and we''ve not been really making our numbers daily.","speaker":"Christine Saur"},{"quote":"So far in November, we''ve only spent about $400 on ads.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"Costco campaign is working really well... it''s a really good sign for the future.","speaker":"Nina Belina"}],"topics":["ads","performance","budget","strategy","campaign"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Advertising Spend and Budget Management**\n\nThe team confirmed the **monthly advertising budget is $2,000**, split between **$1,500 for Google Ads** and **$500 for AdRoll** (01:15).  \n- Christine raised concerns after seeing a **$2,500 figure in QuickBooks**, prompting a follow-up to reconcile discrepancies between reported and actual spend.  \n- Baylee clarified that **ad spend for November has only reached about $400 so far**, indicating no overspending to date.  \n- Nina explained AdRoll’s weekly charges vary due to ad frequency and engagement but assured the **monthly spend does not exceed the $500 budget** (16:38).  \n- Baylee and Nina will provide a detailed explanation of AdRoll’s billing and campaign performance in a follow-up email to clear up confusion (19:17).\n\n## **Google Ads and Campaign Performance**\n\nGoogle Ads have generated **16 conversions so far in November**, showing a downward trend compared to previous months (02:58).  \n- Baylee attributed this partly to increased competition for key terms like \"we fix freight\" and recent campaign shifts including a new Costco distribution center focus.  \n- Christine noted overall business is slow due to tariffs impacting transport volumes, matching last year’s trend but below usual holiday season expectations (04:32).  \n- The Costco campaign has produced **8 conversions with a lower cost per lead**, suggesting early success despite Christine’s initial doubts about its relevance (05:48).  \n- The team agreed to monitor this campaign closely over the next few weeks to decide if budget should be shifted toward it or reverted to existing campaigns (06:40).  \n- Nina recommended increasing budget allocation to Costco campaigns since early data shows promising engagement and specificity against competitors (10:54).  \n- She also suggested refining landing pages to focus more on top services like lumper services and pallet restocking to better convert interested visitors (11:50).\n\n## **AdRoll Campaigns and Brand Awareness**\n\nAdRoll campaigns are not strong drivers of direct conversions but generate significant **impressions and clicks**, boosting brand awareness in a niche market (07:49).  \n- Baylee reported a positive uptick in clicks after refreshing image ads with Christine’s preferred creatives (07:47).  \n- Christine shared anecdotal evidence that brand trust is critical, as customers frequently mention encountering less credible competitors (08:29).  \n- The team agreed to create a dedicated landing page for AdRoll traffic to better explain services and build trust without increasing ad spend, using existing campaign points (09:07).  \n- Christine approved a trial run for this landing page to improve visitor experience and form submission rates (10:06).\n\n## **Lead Tracking and Data Transparency**\n\nChristine requested visibility into who is submitting leads from the Costco campaign to validate genuine interest and filter out low-quality submissions (07:05).  \n- Baylee confirmed that lead details can be extracted from HubSpot and committed to sharing this data after the meeting (07:40).  \n- This transparency will help assess campaign effectiveness and client quality, supporting budget decisions and campaign tuning.\n\n## **Long-term Engagement and New Channel Exploration**\n\nThe team discussed longer-term engagement strategies including event swag for the February women’s conference and social media expansion (12:17).  \n- Christine confirmed interest in launching a TikTok presence, acknowledging its growing importance for reach, though no specific examples or plans currently exist (12:46).  \n- Nina offered to research TikTok accounts in the logistics space to identify best practices and potential content directions (13:22).  \n- This signals a gradual move toward more diversified digital engagement to capture emerging audience segments.\n\n## **Dashboard Monitoring and Keyword Strategy**\n\nNina summarized the dashboard showing stable visitor numbers and lead flow despite slight Google Ads conversion dips early in the month (13:59).  \n- She emphasized maintaining focus on top-performing keywords and adjusting campaigns to reflect changing competitive pressures and seasonal patterns (15:47).  \n- The team plans to keep a close watch on budget pacing and keyword effectiveness, adjusting spend to maximize return during slow market periods (15:55).  \n- Baylee and Nina will continue providing detailed reporting and flag any discrepancies for prompt resolution.","outline":null,"keywords":["Google Ads","AdRoll","Costco Campaign","Advertising Budget","Landing Page","TikTok Marketing"],"overview":"- **Monthly Advertising Budget:** Set at $2,000; $1,500 for Google Ads, $500 for AdRoll, despite QuickBooks reporting $2,500.  \n- **Google Ads Performance:** 16 conversions in November; downtrend due to competition and seasonal tariff impacts noted.  \n- **Costco Campaign Success:** 8 conversions at lower cost per lead; early positive engagement prompts possible budget shift discussions.  \n- **AdRoll Effectiveness:** Generates impressions and clicks for brand awareness; need dedicated landing page for improved trust without extra spend.  \n- **Lead Tracking Needs:** Request for lead visibility from Costco campaign to ensure quality submissions; data to be extracted from HubSpot.  \n- **Future Engagement Strategies:** Interest in TikTok and event promotion; researching best practices for broader digital outreach and audience capture.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nProvide detailed HubSpot report showing lead identities and engagement from Costco campaign to Christine Saur (07:40)\nCreate and implement a dedicated landing page for AdRoll traffic using accumulated points; start trial phase (09:57)\nFollow up with Christine Saur on final budget reconciliation and detailed ad spend analysis in recap email (19:17)\nResearch TikTok logistics marketing accounts as examples to propose potential content and strategy (13:28)\nMonitor Google Ads and Costco campaign performance closely over coming weeks and advise on budget reallocation as needed (06:39)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nCollaborate with Baylee to send lead data from HubSpot and conduct TikTok account research (07:40)\nSupport creation and optimization of landing pages specific to high-performing freight services for better user experience and conversion (11:51)\nContinue analyzing dashboard and keyword performance, recommending budget and targeting adjustments (15:47)\n\n**Christine Saur**\nInvestigate QuickBooks ad spend data discrepancy for potential miscategorization or errors (01:49)\nMonitor ad campaign effectiveness and share feedback or anomalies to marketing team (00:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"5e40dc39-7555-45b0-a7e6-6028fc1aa75e","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
