WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ff2ef389-756d-4ece-b525-93fab32170d6',
    '2025-11-13 15:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9SY9A9FBTYKXF7EWDNCTCSQ',
    'New North x Planon Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Lauren Poirier","Taylor Doerbaum","Baylee Gunnell"}'::text[],
    1195,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1',
    '{"id":"01K9SY9A9FBTYKXF7EWDNCTCSQ","title":"New North x Planon Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Data Privacy Agreement (DPA) and Vendor Coordination**\n\nThe team agreed to prioritize securing a signed **Data Privacy Agreement (DPA)** with **AdRoll** to avoid further delays in the campaign (03:27).\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum** will follow up with AdRoll immediately to confirm the necessity of the DPA and push for its signing.\n- **Lauren Poirier** will consult her legal team and notify Taylor if the DPA requirement changes, ensuring the process keeps moving without unnecessary slowdowns.\n- This step is critical to resume campaign activities and secure compliance, reflecting the company’s cautious approach to vendor agreements.\n- Prompt resolution of this will prevent bottlenecks in campaign execution and maintain momentum on partnership deliverables.\n\n## **ABM Campaign Strategy and Lead Quality Goals**\n\nThe ABM campaign’s core objective is to generate **high-quality, engaged leads**, specifically those who book demos or fill out contact forms, rather than just accruing new names or low-engagement form fills (09:08).\n\n- **Lauren Poirier** clarified that the 2024 North American KPI target for **new names is just over 4,000**, a number nearly met, but the campaign’s focus narrows to leads with strong engagement.\n- The original target of **175 demo requests** was based on a September launch, but delays shifted the start to mid-October, pausing the campaign and affecting expectations.\n- With only about **one month of active campaign time expected in December**, the team discussed resetting goals to a more achievable range of **40 to 50 qualified leads** for that month.\n- **Baylee Gunnell** emphasized the campaign is still a test run meant to establish a baseline, with plans to refine messaging and offers based on early performance data.\n- Flexibility in incentives is limited by company policy, so the team must find creative ways to drive genuine interest without discounts or direct offers.\n- The campaign’s success will influence future partnership decisions and budget allocations, underscoring the importance of early momentum despite the late start.\n\n## **Campaign Execution and Asset Updates**\n\nThe team is finalizing creative assets and landing page materials to quickly relaunch the ABM campaign once approvals are secured (03:27).\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum** received updated designs Tuesday and completed a review incorporating feedback from **Roderick**, who provided detailed, helpful notes to improve social posts and landing pages.\n- Landing page edits are nearly complete, with some minor feedback about header design arcs resolved; final asset delivery is imminent.\n- The animated video requires additional clarification on change priorities; **Lauren Poirier** is awaiting specifics from Roderick’s team to avoid unnecessary revisions.\n- Brand consistency requests include keeping the logo visible throughout the video and integrating more brand colors, which may require design adjustments.\n- Once assets are sent, Lauren plans to replace existing materials swiftly to avoid further delays.\n- The team recognizes internal review processes have slowed progress, but they remain committed to moving forward efficiently.\n\n## **Data Tracking and Reporting Improvements**\n\nThe data reporting infrastructure for the campaign has been clarified and improved to ensure accurate lead tracking and transparency (16:21).\n\n- The **Data Box Dashboard** was confirmed as the accurate source for lead tracking despite discrepancies with **Lemlist’s** email metrics, which measure recipients differently.\n- The lead list spreadsheet has been updated to include **separate first and last name fields** and added the **title** attribute to better qualify leads.\n- Taylor will send Lauren the updated dashboard and lead list link with a detailed explanation to ensure clear understanding.\n- These data improvements will support better measurement once the campaign resumes, enabling more informed decision-making.\n- The current campaign pause means some dashboard stats appear irregular, but they will normalize once activities restart.\n\n## **Organizational Changes and Future Planning**\n\nThe team acknowledged the impact of recent personnel changes and shifting responsibilities on campaign management and future initiatives (10:07).\n\n- With **Pauline’s departure**, managing the **North American LinkedIn campaign** internally is no longer feasible, so the team expects to discontinue that effort next year.\n- Lauren confirmed the overall KPIs will remain unchanged and likely increase by **15-20%** next year, maintaining pressure for strong lead generation.\n- Delays in case study approvals continue to stall content marketing efforts, reflecting ongoing operational challenges.\n- The team agreed to maintain close communication through the project management platform and email to keep all stakeholders aligned on next steps and feedback.\n- These changes reinforce the need for adaptable planning and prioritizing key campaigns like ABM to maximize impact with available resources.","outline":null,"keywords":["AdRoll","Data Processing Agreement","ABM campaign","lead quality","animated video feedback","DataBox dashboard"],"overview":"- **Data Privacy Agreement (DPA):** Securing a signed DPA with AdRoll is essential to resume campaign activities promptly.  \n- **ABM Campaign Focus:** Targeting **high-quality leads** rather than just new names, aiming for **40 to 50 qualified leads** in December.  \n- **Campaign Delays:** Original demo request target shifted due to delays; new expectations revised for more achievable outcomes.  \n- **Asset Updates:** Finalizing creative assets for a quick campaign relaunch; internal review processes have slowed delivery times.  \n- **Data Tracking Improvements:** Enhanced lead tracking with updated dashboard; discrepancies noted with Lemlist metrics but will normalize once the campaign resumes.  \n- **Organizational Changes Impact:** Personnel changes affect campaign management; KPIs are likely to increase by **15-20%** next year for strong lead generation.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nForward AdRoll’s email and documentation regarding DPA to Lauren for internal review (04:40)\nFollow up again with AdRoll to confirm if the DPA can be signed and keep Lauren updated (18:29)\nReview latest design updates incorporating Rodrick’s feedback and Lou’s adjustments, then send revised assets to Lauren for final approval (05:03)\nAfter review, provide Lauren with detailed update and link to DataBox dashboard and the enhanced Excel lead list including title separation (17:46)\nContinue coordinating campaign relaunch details and keep Lauren informed about ABM campaign status and adjustments (13:49)\n\n**Lauren Poirier**\nConfirm with internal team if DPA signature is required, and inform Taylor if it can be waived (04:40)\nAssess which animated video edits are mandatory versus optional based on Rodrick’s team feedback; communicate clarified requirements to Taylor (06:21)\nConduct final review of landing page edits, focusing on non-design related feedback from Rodrick, and confirm readiness to relaunch ABM campaign (15:31)\nCommunicate any additional priorities or issues arising via team communication channels as they come up (19:29)\n"},"duration":19.920000076293945,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"id":1,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey there, Lauren.","index":0,"end_time":117.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.72,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"How are you?","index":1,"end_time":118.519,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":117.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":119,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you?","index":3,"end_time":119.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":119,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":4,"end_time":120.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I just found out I actually broke a bone in my arm last weekend.","index":5,"end_time":125.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Oh, my goodness.","index":6,"end_time":126.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, but I''m.","index":7,"end_time":127.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m not in a cast or anything, so I really can''t complain.","index":8,"end_time":131.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":9,"end_time":132.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Was it like a fracture or something?","index":10,"end_time":134.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a.","index":11,"end_time":135.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"A small fracture on the bone that is in your forearm.","index":12,"end_time":140.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s where it kind of butts up against your elbow.","index":13,"end_time":143.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And I. I fell roller skating and so that was.","index":14,"end_time":147.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I was gonna say.","index":15,"end_time":147.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you have a cool story?","index":16,"end_time":148.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s a cool story.","index":17,"end_time":149.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Kind of embarrassing.","index":18,"end_time":151.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No, I''m just glad it''s not worse.","index":19,"end_time":155.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a bummer.","index":20,"end_time":156.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s almost.","index":21,"end_time":157.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I feel like sometimes worse when you don''t have a cast because then it doesn''t prevent you from using it and then you can make it worse.","index":22,"end_time":163.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":23,"end_time":163.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then people think you''re lying too.","index":24,"end_time":165.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like I''m telling my.","index":25,"end_time":167.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"My manager, but it''s fine.","index":26,"end_time":171.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"How''s your going?","index":27,"end_time":172.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.39,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Good.","index":28,"end_time":173.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":173.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Doing good.","index":29,"end_time":174.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":30,"end_time":176.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Can''t believe it''s already kind of the middle of November.","index":31,"end_time":179.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":176.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s just flying by.","index":32,"end_time":179.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It really is month two, really.","index":33,"end_time":183.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.43,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I feel like the time in between Halloween and Christmas just always like flies by, so.","index":34,"end_time":188.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then somehow January through March is like twice the length of time that it actually.","index":35,"end_time":193.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":188.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know, it drags.","index":36,"end_time":195.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So true.","index":37,"end_time":196.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All the fun, like holidays and all the things you look forward to are like over.","index":38,"end_time":200.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s kind of.","index":39,"end_time":201.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We need to.","index":40,"end_time":202.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"In the middle of February, I think, to get us through winter.","index":41,"end_time":205.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know, right?","index":42,"end_time":206.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That is true.","index":43,"end_time":207.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s like no holidays for a while.","index":44,"end_time":209.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":207.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right, let me pull up our agenda.","index":45,"end_time":216.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just to start out, I''ve been going back and forth with AdRoll, their support team, just trying to get a clear answer on the dpa.","index":46,"end_time":225.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It looks like I just got an email that came in, so I''m trying to read through this.","index":47,"end_time":229.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Bailey, I''m not sure if you''re familiar with these different types of services and if we would do one of them, but we obviously wouldn''t be doing this one with a minimum monthly spend of 5,000.","index":48,"end_time":241.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then it looks like they have the self serve.","index":49,"end_time":247.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks like they just explain kind of how it works where you have control over everything.","index":50,"end_time":254.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They haven''t answered like directly the DPA question.","index":51,"end_time":260.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if your team just maybe wants to go through what is in here and see if you still need the DPA question or DPA signed, I can forward this to you with all the information.","index":52,"end_time":271.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So yeah, it may just be a matter of it''s not like a necessary document for either side.","index":53,"end_time":279.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":274.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, please send that to me.","index":54,"end_time":281.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m pretty sure our team''s going to say that we need the DPA signed.","index":55,"end_time":286.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So if you could send that to me and just in the meantime go back to them and say, yeah, yeah, we still need a DPA just to keep that process rolling.","index":56,"end_time":293.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":57,"end_time":294.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll follow up with them and.","index":58,"end_time":296.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"See if they, my team says otherwise.","index":59,"end_time":297.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll let you know when we can call it off, but I just don''t want to have more of a slowdown than we have to.","index":60,"end_time":303.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":61,"end_time":304.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can definitely do that.","index":62,"end_time":305.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as design updates, I got your design updates Tuesday and then I just got them back from our designer this morning.","index":63,"end_time":314.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''ll be going through and checking them over before sending them back to you.","index":64,"end_time":317.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I just asked him to use that feedback that we got from Rodrick to apply it to the most recent edits we did to for the second half of the social post.","index":65,"end_time":325.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So hopefully to alleviate some back and forth.","index":66,"end_time":328.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But Roderick is super helpful, so I just want to say thank you for passing stuff over to him because I know in the meeting he said like, let me know if you have any questions.","index":67,"end_time":335.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the feedback that he gives is super helpful.","index":68,"end_time":338.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I know Lou is like making notes on the side too for future projects that are similar with that feedback.","index":69,"end_time":344.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So thank you for that that was.","index":70,"end_time":346.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Glad it was helpful.","index":71,"end_time":347.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":72,"end_time":349.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I will send those over to you once I review them.","index":73,"end_time":351.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The video, I just want to see if you had any feedback on the animated video.","index":74,"end_time":356.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I sent this to Roderick.","index":75,"end_time":359.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.65,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"He responded with one of his team members feedback and it was a lot.","index":76,"end_time":363.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''ve gone back and asked, can you tell me what is absolutely necessary versus what is just nice to have?","index":77,"end_time":370.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Because I don''t want to ask you guys to do more changes than we really need to.","index":78,"end_time":373.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''m waiting to hear back from him.","index":79,"end_time":376.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m expecting, hoping he''ll respond today or tomorrow and I''ll get that over to you.","index":80,"end_time":381.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":81,"end_time":382.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if it''s easier for them to just do it scene by scene, like in that frame link, we send it, like if there''s particular points that might be easier for them and then for our design team too, if it''s like particular sections, like a more broad edit.","index":82,"end_time":396.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I think they were mostly broad edits.","index":83,"end_time":399.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"One was they don''t want the logo to, you know, kind of disappear and then come back.","index":84,"end_time":403.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.52,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They want it to be present the whole time.","index":85,"end_time":405.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":403.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":86,"end_time":406.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Another piece of feedback was on the colors, they asked if we could use more of our brand colors.","index":87,"end_time":412.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.6,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t know how difficult that is for your team to change.","index":88,"end_time":415.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So things like that that were kind of throughout the whole video, rather than, like, one specific thing.","index":89,"end_time":421.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But I''ll.","index":90,"end_time":422.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll let you know.","index":91,"end_time":423.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll send that feedback once I find out what''s required to change for us to be able to use the video.","index":92,"end_time":428.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that sounds good.","index":93,"end_time":431.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll look forward to getting that feedback and making those adjustments.","index":94,"end_time":434.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":95,"end_time":435.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":96,"end_time":436.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I appreciate your flexibility.","index":97,"end_time":437.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m frustrated that we have to make.","index":98,"end_time":440.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"These changes, but now I understand.","index":99,"end_time":442.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know it''s not your fault.","index":100,"end_time":443.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You got a lot of internal reviews.","index":101,"end_time":445.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":102,"end_time":446.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":103,"end_time":447.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So then just the rest of the time, I just want to spend talking through the ABM campaign.","index":104,"end_time":451.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just from what we''ve noticed from the feedback that you and Pauline had originally was that this ABM campaign is kind of like, the biggest part of our partnership here, and it''ll kind of determine the future.","index":105,"end_time":464.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so we just want to make sure that we''re yielding the best results for you out of the ABM campaign.","index":106,"end_time":468.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It sounds like depending on how this does and how many leads you get is how, like, the partnership will continue.","index":107,"end_time":473.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we met with Tristan, one of the owners here, who we did the onboarding with, Me and him did with you guys.","index":108,"end_time":479.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we were just going back through to make sure that we had, like, all the priorities and goals in place.","index":109,"end_time":486.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And something that we wanted to align on is originally, when we went through the marketing roadmap together back in March, the goal was to get leads of, like, new names.","index":110,"end_time":499.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That was our benchmark, new names across.","index":111,"end_time":502.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we wanted to, like, confirm with you if this is still the goal.","index":112,"end_time":506.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, is it new?","index":113,"end_time":507.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":506.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"New names?","index":114,"end_time":508.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":507.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are we wanting.","index":115,"end_time":510.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we talked about this, too, where we launched the ABM campaign later than we thought.","index":116,"end_time":514.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that number has altered a few times because of when we actually launched the campaign.","index":117,"end_time":519.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":514.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I believe we wanted to make it 175 back in September, but it didn''t launch till mid October, and now it''s paused.","index":118,"end_time":526.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we want to just make sure that we''re all on the same page with what is the main goal of this campaign?","index":119,"end_time":531.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":526.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is it new names?","index":120,"end_time":533.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is it particular leads?","index":121,"end_time":534.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And what would those leads qualify as?","index":122,"end_time":537.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is that like somebody booking a demo through one of those landing pages?","index":123,"end_time":540.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is that somebody just responding to a form fill?","index":124,"end_time":543.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we just wanted to hear from you, like, what would qualify a lead to be a lead?","index":125,"end_time":547.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":543.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":126,"end_time":548.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So just to Clarify first that 3100 leads the new names, that is one of our KPIs that we have across North America.","index":127,"end_time":557.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that was the KPI in 2024 for.","index":128,"end_time":559.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"For new names this year, it''s, I think, a little over 4,000, which we''ve pretty much already met.","index":129,"end_time":564.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.66,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The goal for the ABM campaign is just really high quality, really engaged leads.","index":130,"end_time":571.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So booking a demo request, filling out a contact us form, that would be, in our opinion, like, the best.","index":131,"end_time":580.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The best outcome.","index":132,"end_time":581.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''ve had a lot of leads that have filled out a form to get like one white paper or two white papers, and we haven''t had a lot of success with leads that have only done a couple things.","index":133,"end_time":597.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.37,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think for us, yeah, filling out a demo request form or a contact Us form would be the best outcome.","index":134,"end_time":605.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes a lot of sense.","index":135,"end_time":609.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think it''s been a little tricky, as we''ve all talked about, since we''re launching so late in the year.","index":136,"end_time":616.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And now we''re like, it''s not running right now because we''re redoing a lot of the branding and things like that.","index":137,"end_time":622.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll probably need to, like, reconvene on what that number is going to be.","index":138,"end_time":627.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But with, like, Pauline not here anymore, how is that changing your role?","index":139,"end_time":633.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":627.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is this still a big number for you to achieve or do you know what''s changing there?","index":140,"end_time":639.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":634.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You mean the KPI?","index":141,"end_time":641.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s not changing.","index":142,"end_time":644,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And it will probably increase by 15 to 20%.","index":143,"end_time":647.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":648.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":648.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s the same.","index":145,"end_time":650.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I totally understand.","index":146,"end_time":652.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"You know, we''re not launching until at least mid November.","index":147,"end_time":655.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''re not going to get 175 demo requests completely.","index":148,"end_time":659.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think we can definitely talk about what''s more reasonable from what you guys, from your experience, what you expect.","index":149,"end_time":667.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like, if, let''s say we only run for the month of December, how many leads, with a score of at least 10, do you anticipate?","index":150,"end_time":676.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.91,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I would like to continue into the new year with you guys.","index":151,"end_time":682.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And, you know, since we''re getting started so late, it''d be a shame not to continue.","index":152,"end_time":686.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''m working through that with our global team, I think.","index":153,"end_time":692.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So.","index":154,"end_time":692.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"175 if we began in September.","index":155,"end_time":694.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So November, December, that''s four months.","index":156,"end_time":697.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that''s what, less than 50 new names per month?","index":157,"end_time":703.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like, let''s say 40.","index":158,"end_time":705.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So would it be reasonable to set a goal of 40 to 50 leads in the month of December if we start before December begins?","index":159,"end_time":715.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We can definitely try.","index":160,"end_time":719.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":718.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"December is always just one of those months.","index":161,"end_time":724.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":720.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That is, you just don''t know what''s gonna happen.","index":162,"end_time":728.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":724.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s really hard to say.","index":163,"end_time":730.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And, like, part of our philosophy with ABM is that we should, like, adjust and learn from things.","index":164,"end_time":738.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.769,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like, we launched this preliminary campaign, and, like, we learn a lot.","index":165,"end_time":742.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":166,"end_time":743.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":742.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, this messaging worked really well.","index":167,"end_time":744.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":743.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This didn''t hit so well.","index":168,"end_time":746.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":744.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, let''s adjust and see how.","index":169,"end_time":748.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How it performs the next time.","index":170,"end_time":750.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":748.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I feel like we don''t have a lot of opportunity to, like, learn and adjust as we''re going.","index":171,"end_time":755.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll definitely do as much as we can, but it''s hard to put a number on it since this is, like, our test.","index":172,"end_time":760.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, we''re almost setting a baseline here to see what we can do, and then from there, we can have a better idea of what.","index":173,"end_time":767.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What''s more realistic.","index":174,"end_time":769.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Right.","index":175,"end_time":770.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":176,"end_time":772.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No, that makes sense.","index":177,"end_time":773.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":772.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know you guys can''t make any promises, especially with the holidays.","index":178,"end_time":775.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.01,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s.","index":179,"end_time":776.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s tough.","index":180,"end_time":777.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.56,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think, from my perspective, we just need to get going and see, you know, how things go.","index":181,"end_time":785.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.32,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If we get, you know, a handful of people who end up being passed off to sales and go on to have a demo that''s, I think, a big success for one month of work.","index":182,"end_time":796.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":183,"end_time":797.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Whether my superiors see it that way or not is a different question.","index":184,"end_time":802.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":798.32,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But, yeah, I can definitely explain to them, like, a lot of the holdups here were because of our internal approvals and things like that.","index":185,"end_time":810.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''m definitely aware of that.","index":186,"end_time":812.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.7,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":187,"end_time":815.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":814.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''ll work through this.","index":188,"end_time":817.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":815.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We want this to be successful, so we''ll just try and get this launched as soon as possible, and then we''ll.","index":189,"end_time":824.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":817.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll readjust goals once we''re able to get it to run for a little bit.","index":190,"end_time":828.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":824.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":191,"end_time":830.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.1,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":831.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.5,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And like Bailey said, too, when we.","index":193,"end_time":833.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can have it running for a little bit, we can learn more about how certain sequences are performing or what is resonating with the ICP that we''re targeting.","index":194,"end_time":841.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":833.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then eventually, we could maybe talk about tweaking the sequence a little bit based on the feedback that we see or the data that comes in and potentially give a, you know, stronger incentive in an offer within the sequence.","index":195,"end_time":854.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we have, like, checklists that we''re offering and prep guides and things, and then at the end, we have, like, a custom demo offer, but sometimes we just tweak that.","index":196,"end_time":865.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":854.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, one of my other clients are working on tweaking to make a more compelling offer for the ICP now that it''s been running for a while.","index":197,"end_time":870.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s something that we can revisit, too.","index":198,"end_time":872.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In the future, once we have it rolling for a little bit and see how it''s performing.","index":199,"end_time":875.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that sounds good.","index":200,"end_time":878.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":876.32,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s hard because we can''t.","index":201,"end_time":881.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''ve.","index":202,"end_time":882.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''ve had the idea in the past of, you know, at trade shows or whatever, like if you book a demo, we''ll give you a certain percentage off.","index":203,"end_time":888.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.44,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"You know, it''s tricky, but we''re not.","index":204,"end_time":890.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Allowed to do that.","index":205,"end_time":891.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So it''s like, it''s hard to find something that it''s exciting.","index":206,"end_time":895.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.44,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":207,"end_time":896.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"For sure.","index":208,"end_time":897.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that does.","index":209,"end_time":898.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":897.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know a lot of clients have talked about that as well, because you don''t want to look desperate to and be like, oh, we''ll give you, you know, whatever to do that.","index":210,"end_time":904.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":898.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And you also don''t want to get someone booking a demo just for XYZ that you''re offering.","index":211,"end_time":908.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You want to make sure that they''re an actual client potential.","index":212,"end_time":911.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":213,"end_time":912.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, we''ll just look to hopefully launch this soon.","index":214,"end_time":916.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.749,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know I sent over the landing page edits.","index":215,"end_time":920.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t think we got any feedback on those.","index":216,"end_time":921.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":920.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So did those look good to go then?","index":217,"end_time":924.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":922.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because I know that that''s probably one of the biggest things we''re waiting on to relaunch.","index":218,"end_time":929.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is that correct?","index":219,"end_time":929.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":929.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, the assets and the landing page.","index":220,"end_time":934.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":931.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Edit.","index":221,"end_time":934.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Edit.","index":222,"end_time":935.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.72,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":223,"end_time":935.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Check Roderick''s email.","index":224,"end_time":936.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.44,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think he did provide some feedback, but it was not really relevant to the design.","index":225,"end_time":942.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":226,"end_time":944.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":943.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we just need to get those last minute asset updates to you and then we should be good to go.","index":227,"end_time":950.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And like I said, I have those ready to go.","index":228,"end_time":952.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":950.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So after this meeting, I''ll just be reviewing them with what Lou made the adjustments and then I''ll send those over to you for you guys to get a final.","index":229,"end_time":960.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Final review.","index":230,"end_time":960.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":231,"end_time":961.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just check.","index":232,"end_time":962.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Checking his email to make sure.","index":233,"end_time":964.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, his.","index":234,"end_time":966.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"His feedback was that there were too many arcs because they were on the header of the.","index":235,"end_time":975.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":966.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that was the original landing page edit.","index":236,"end_time":978.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think we sent that back now, so it should be good.","index":237,"end_time":980.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":978.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Go.","index":238,"end_time":981.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":239,"end_time":981.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":981.49,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yep.","index":240,"end_time":982.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":981.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll take a look at that again.","index":241,"end_time":983.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But yeah, so there''s that.","index":242,"end_time":985.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":983.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then I know at one point you guys were working on the data box dashboard.","index":243,"end_time":992.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"You know what, what went wrong there with the data import.","index":244,"end_time":994.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":992.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then you were updating the Excel lead list sheet, adding title, breaking up first name, last name.","index":245,"end_time":1000.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.25,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Have you guys done that?","index":246,"end_time":1001.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.13,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s actually complete.","index":247,"end_time":1002.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1001.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know, Bailey, if you reviewed that last week, I think I had a slide.","index":248,"end_time":1006.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1003.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I have to find it.","index":249,"end_time":1007.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, we made the adjustments.","index":250,"end_time":1009.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"To the Data Box Dashboard.","index":251,"end_time":1010.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1009.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I have a longer explanation too, that I can send to you.","index":252,"end_time":1014.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1010.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"With.","index":253,"end_time":1015.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Working with our developer, the Data Box Dashboard has been correct the whole time.","index":254,"end_time":1019.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1015.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The way that Lemlist, which is our email platform, tracks like leads is different than what we have in the Data Box Dashboard because we''re actually tracking direct leads.","index":255,"end_time":1028.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And the way Lemlist does it, it''s like by recipient.","index":256,"end_time":1031.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it was just confusing the way you look at it.","index":257,"end_time":1033.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So they''re two different sets of data.","index":258,"end_time":1035.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"One''s not wrong and one''s not right, or both wrong.","index":259,"end_time":1038.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the Data Box Dashboard is correct.","index":260,"end_time":1040.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The LEMLA side of things is just a different kind of metric that they track.","index":261,"end_time":1044.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But Databox will still be the correct place to look.","index":262,"end_time":1047.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1044.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So nothing had to change necessarily in the Data Box.","index":263,"end_time":1049.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1047.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We just wanted to confirm that the data was matching and that is correct.","index":264,"end_time":1053.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1049.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as the leads list, we did make that adjustment to have the first name and last name separate.","index":265,"end_time":1058.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''ll go ahead and send that link back over to you after this with a little bit longer explanation of that in the link to the dashboard.","index":266,"end_time":1063.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because the ABM campaign''s not running right now.","index":267,"end_time":1066.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1064.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s probably going to look a little wonky, but once we have that back up and running, all those stats will resume.","index":268,"end_time":1071.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1066.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yeah, everything''s good to go on the Dashboard and the lead spreadsheet as well.","index":269,"end_time":1076.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":270,"end_time":1077.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And you added title to that too, right?","index":271,"end_time":1079.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":1080.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1079.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, I can send you that link.","index":273,"end_time":1083.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1080.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":274,"end_time":1084.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":275,"end_time":1084.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.51,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Once you send back those assets, I can get those replaced hopefully very soon.","index":276,"end_time":1090,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":277,"end_time":1090.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1090.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":278,"end_time":1092.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And I know we have an email string with Merit talking about payment info, the ABM ads, which obviously is a step after getting it going again.","index":279,"end_time":1101.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes, yeah, we''ve got that.","index":280,"end_time":1103.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1101.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then we''re working on the DPA for ad roll, so.","index":281,"end_time":1107.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1103.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":282,"end_time":1109.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1107.52,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll forward that email to you that I got from them and then I''ll respond and just ask again if they could sign the dpa.","index":283,"end_time":1115.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They have it now, so just have to ask them if they can, if that''s something that they can sign.","index":284,"end_time":1119.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1115.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":285,"end_time":1121.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just checking my notes to see if there''s anything I forgot to mention, just to let you know.","index":286,"end_time":1131.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1122.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So next year, I know we talked about doing the North American LinkedIn.","index":287,"end_time":1134.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Now that we don''t have Pauline, I don''t think it''s going to be just within our, you know, ability to manage that too.","index":288,"end_time":1141.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think, just so you''re aware, we''ll probably not be doing that.","index":289,"end_time":1145.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1142.31,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I haven''t heard anything on the case studies?","index":290,"end_time":1148.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.7,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Unfortunately, on approvals from others.","index":291,"end_time":1152.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1148.5,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a bummer.","index":292,"end_time":1154.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1152.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s just such a struggle to get.","index":293,"end_time":1156.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, you agree?","index":294,"end_time":1157.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1156.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It really is.","index":295,"end_time":1158.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1157.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That was a while ago now, too.","index":296,"end_time":1159.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1158.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s a bummer.","index":297,"end_time":1160.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1159.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know.","index":298,"end_time":1161.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1160.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then we talked about the video.","index":299,"end_time":1163.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1162.54,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Video edits.","index":300,"end_time":1165.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1164.7,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":301,"end_time":1167.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think that''s everything on my side.","index":302,"end_time":1169.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.74,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":303,"end_time":1170.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if you have anything else that comes up right here on team, so we could communicate that way, but.","index":304,"end_time":1174.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1170.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I''ll keep you in the loop with our edits on our side of things in the DPA as well.","index":305,"end_time":1179.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I''ll go ahead and forward that to you right now so you can have that after this meeting.","index":306,"end_time":1182.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":307,"end_time":1183.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.6,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":308,"end_time":1184.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":309,"end_time":1185.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":310,"end_time":1186.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1185.479,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If your arm feels better.","index":311,"end_time":1187.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1186.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":312,"end_time":1188.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Bye.","index":313,"end_time":1189.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"}],"dateString":"2025-11-13T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com,pauline.perenack@planonsoftware.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com","pauline.perenack@planonsoftware.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9SY9A9FBTYKXF7EWDNCTCSQ","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Clarified ABM campaign success metrics as high-quality leads like demo requests or contact form fills.","Identified necessary animated video fixes including logo visibility and brand color alignment.","Resolved data syncing issues; Databox confirmed as accurate metric source, Lemlist used differently.","Agreed to aim for 40–50 new leads in December, with flexibility due to late launch timing.","Confirmed updated assets and dashboard are ready for relaunch; final reviews happening this week."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We just want to make sure that we''re yielding the best results for you out of the ABM campaign.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"I would like to continue into the new year with you guys.","speaker":"Lauren Poirier"},{"quote":"We''ll readjust goals once we''re able to get it to run for a little bit.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["delivery","launch","campaign","data","ABM"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Data Privacy Agreement (DPA) and Vendor Coordination**\n\nThe team agreed to prioritize securing a signed **Data Privacy Agreement (DPA)** with **AdRoll** to avoid further delays in the campaign (03:27).\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum** will follow up with AdRoll immediately to confirm the necessity of the DPA and push for its signing.\n- **Lauren Poirier** will consult her legal team and notify Taylor if the DPA requirement changes, ensuring the process keeps moving without unnecessary slowdowns.\n- This step is critical to resume campaign activities and secure compliance, reflecting the company’s cautious approach to vendor agreements.\n- Prompt resolution of this will prevent bottlenecks in campaign execution and maintain momentum on partnership deliverables.\n\n## **ABM Campaign Strategy and Lead Quality Goals**\n\nThe ABM campaign’s core objective is to generate **high-quality, engaged leads**, specifically those who book demos or fill out contact forms, rather than just accruing new names or low-engagement form fills (09:08).\n\n- **Lauren Poirier** clarified that the 2024 North American KPI target for **new names is just over 4,000**, a number nearly met, but the campaign’s focus narrows to leads with strong engagement.\n- The original target of **175 demo requests** was based on a September launch, but delays shifted the start to mid-October, pausing the campaign and affecting expectations.\n- With only about **one month of active campaign time expected in December**, the team discussed resetting goals to a more achievable range of **40 to 50 qualified leads** for that month.\n- **Baylee Gunnell** emphasized the campaign is still a test run meant to establish a baseline, with plans to refine messaging and offers based on early performance data.\n- Flexibility in incentives is limited by company policy, so the team must find creative ways to drive genuine interest without discounts or direct offers.\n- The campaign’s success will influence future partnership decisions and budget allocations, underscoring the importance of early momentum despite the late start.\n\n## **Campaign Execution and Asset Updates**\n\nThe team is finalizing creative assets and landing page materials to quickly relaunch the ABM campaign once approvals are secured (03:27).\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum** received updated designs Tuesday and completed a review incorporating feedback from **Roderick**, who provided detailed, helpful notes to improve social posts and landing pages.\n- Landing page edits are nearly complete, with some minor feedback about header design arcs resolved; final asset delivery is imminent.\n- The animated video requires additional clarification on change priorities; **Lauren Poirier** is awaiting specifics from Roderick’s team to avoid unnecessary revisions.\n- Brand consistency requests include keeping the logo visible throughout the video and integrating more brand colors, which may require design adjustments.\n- Once assets are sent, Lauren plans to replace existing materials swiftly to avoid further delays.\n- The team recognizes internal review processes have slowed progress, but they remain committed to moving forward efficiently.\n\n## **Data Tracking and Reporting Improvements**\n\nThe data reporting infrastructure for the campaign has been clarified and improved to ensure accurate lead tracking and transparency (16:21).\n\n- The **Data Box Dashboard** was confirmed as the accurate source for lead tracking despite discrepancies with **Lemlist’s** email metrics, which measure recipients differently.\n- The lead list spreadsheet has been updated to include **separate first and last name fields** and added the **title** attribute to better qualify leads.\n- Taylor will send Lauren the updated dashboard and lead list link with a detailed explanation to ensure clear understanding.\n- These data improvements will support better measurement once the campaign resumes, enabling more informed decision-making.\n- The current campaign pause means some dashboard stats appear irregular, but they will normalize once activities restart.\n\n## **Organizational Changes and Future Planning**\n\nThe team acknowledged the impact of recent personnel changes and shifting responsibilities on campaign management and future initiatives (10:07).\n\n- With **Pauline’s departure**, managing the **North American LinkedIn campaign** internally is no longer feasible, so the team expects to discontinue that effort next year.\n- Lauren confirmed the overall KPIs will remain unchanged and likely increase by **15-20%** next year, maintaining pressure for strong lead generation.\n- Delays in case study approvals continue to stall content marketing efforts, reflecting ongoing operational challenges.\n- The team agreed to maintain close communication through the project management platform and email to keep all stakeholders aligned on next steps and feedback.\n- These changes reinforce the need for adaptable planning and prioritizing key campaigns like ABM to maximize impact with available resources.","outline":null,"keywords":["AdRoll","Data Processing Agreement","ABM campaign","lead quality","animated video feedback","DataBox dashboard"],"overview":"- **Data Privacy Agreement (DPA):** Securing a signed DPA with AdRoll is essential to resume campaign activities promptly.  \n- **ABM Campaign Focus:** Targeting **high-quality leads** rather than just new names, aiming for **40 to 50 qualified leads** in December.  \n- **Campaign Delays:** Original demo request target shifted due to delays; new expectations revised for more achievable outcomes.  \n- **Asset Updates:** Finalizing creative assets for a quick campaign relaunch; internal review processes have slowed delivery times.  \n- **Data Tracking Improvements:** Enhanced lead tracking with updated dashboard; discrepancies noted with Lemlist metrics but will normalize once the campaign resumes.  \n- **Organizational Changes Impact:** Personnel changes affect campaign management; KPIs are likely to increase by **15-20%** next year for strong lead generation.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nForward AdRoll’s email and documentation regarding DPA to Lauren for internal review (04:40)\nFollow up again with AdRoll to confirm if the DPA can be signed and keep Lauren updated (18:29)\nReview latest design updates incorporating Rodrick’s feedback and Lou’s adjustments, then send revised assets to Lauren for final approval (05:03)\nAfter review, provide Lauren with detailed update and link to DataBox dashboard and the enhanced Excel lead list including title separation (17:46)\nContinue coordinating campaign relaunch details and keep Lauren informed about ABM campaign status and adjustments (13:49)\n\n**Lauren Poirier**\nConfirm with internal team if DPA signature is required, and inform Taylor if it can be waived (04:40)\nAssess which animated video edits are mandatory versus optional based on Rodrick’s team feedback; communicate clarified requirements to Taylor (06:21)\nConduct final review of landing page edits, focusing on non-design related feedback from Rodrick, and confirm readiness to relaunch ABM campaign (15:31)\nCommunicate any additional priorities or issues arising via team communication channels as they come up (19:29)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"dfc0a494-e55b-4492-a4df-a4f7ab6c727e","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
