    1954,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88101950404?pwd=QpFPtp65X6pjfifn5alUnYOkaTzNpP.1',
    '{"id":"01K933NRBVK8ETEM23MNKZWKSC","title":"Tristan Pelligrino and Kyley Crews","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Development and Copywriting Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to prioritize finalizing the **homepage** and **platform pages** by the end of this month to align content development with design and build schedules (05:18).  \n- **Kyley Crews** emphasized starting with the homepage to establish alignment before moving through the sitemap sequentially, focusing on platform content first as it’s the most urgent.  \n- **Jenny Vance** proposed dedicating a full day offline for Kyley to concentrate on platform content next week, minimizing distractions from Slack and other communications, to speed the drafting process.  \n- The strategy involves iterative internal reviews and just-in-time content delivery to keep momentum while allowing flexibility for refinement.  \n- This focused content sprint approach aims to deliver platform pages as a batch, enabling smooth transition into solution and industry pages by targeting completion around the **25th of the month**.\n\nThe team plans to leverage AI tools like **Twain** for customizing industry pages based on a single well-written template, reducing workload for repetitive content while maintaining tone consistency (08:54).  \n- This reuse strategy was suggested to mitigate the daunting volume of industry-specific pages and speed up production.  \n- Collaboration with the KG team will help integrate AI prompts for effective content generation, streamlining writing and editing efforts.  \n- This approach supports scalability and faster delivery without compromising content quality or voice.\n\n## **Design and User Experience Planning**\n\nThe group confirmed a process to pair wireframes with corresponding copy drafts to ensure design and content flow naturally together before development begins (02:01).  \n- Each sitemap page includes low-fidelity wireframe blocks with guidelines on content length, purpose, and visual elements to inform copywriting.  \n- The plan is to receive a **Figma design mockup** of the homepage after copy approval, providing a visual checkpoint before building starts (17:01).  \n- This step will allow stakeholders to review integrated copy and design, ensuring components like navigation and footer are reusable across pages.  \n- Early parallel development of reusable components will accelerate build timelines once content is finalized.\n\nThe team is working on sourcing authentic, branded photography to enhance the site’s visual appeal and reflect company culture (18:05).  \n- A photo contest yielded a large volume of employee-submitted pictures, supplemented by professional headshots and nature shots to reinforce the brand’s natural, human feel.  \n- **Jenny Vance** highlighted the need for explicit permission when using images featuring faces, maintaining legal and ethical standards.  \n- Organic, candid images such as the “Power Rangers” team group shot are prioritized for their genuine cultural resonance.  \n- These assets will be curated and edited to balance quality with authenticity, supporting the site’s storytelling approach.\n\n## **Project Timelines and Collaboration Cadence**\n\nThe team agreed to weekly check-ins on **Fridays at 12:30 PM**, starting the **14th**, to monitor progress and adjust plans as needed (29:55).  \n- Kyley’s morning schedule is busy, so Friday afternoons were chosen for consistent, manageable status updates.  \n- Deliverables such as the homepage copy draft are expected this week, with design feedback and iteration scheduled for early next week (29:20).  \n- The cadence supports rapid turnaround while accommodating individual workloads and external dependencies.\n\nCollaboration will include close coordination with internal experts like **Jenny B.** for technical platform details and **Brianna** for design elements such as screen grab styles (11:15, 13:39).  \n- Jenny B. is tasked to provide high-level bullet points for the platform features by early next week to inform content creation.  \n- Brianna is handling decisions on visual presentation preferences (e.g., monitor displays vs. isolated images) to balance aesthetics and usability.  \n- This cross-functional cooperation is designed to reduce bottlenecks and ensure content accuracy and design consistency.\n\n## **Scope and Budget Alignment on Design Assets**\n\nThe team clarified the budget and scope for redesigning key resources like **Tier 2 guide** and **Brickwork guide**, agreeing on a design cost of approximately **$3,500** for both combined, not per guide, which is roughly half of earlier misestimated figures (23:38).  \n- This budget includes adapting existing content into new designs rather than full rewrites, optimizing cost-efficiency.  \n- The guides will be designed primarily in **InDesign**, with options to create **Canva templates** for internal reuse and easy updates by marketing teams (26:25).  \n- Designing reusable templates for documents, landing pages, and social media posts is under consideration to support ongoing content needs.  \n- The team also discussed the possibility of engaging external designers billed at **$90 per hour**, providing flexibility for additional workload without doubling internal costs.\n\nNon-website assets such as offsite **ebooks, videos, and checklists** fall outside the current scope for redesign but may be revisited later based on business priorities (21:26).  \n- Case study pages and blog posts will be reformatted within the new website design template, ensuring brand consistency while keeping content intact.  \n- Decisions on how to handle existing video content and resource-heavy items will be made in future planning discussions.  \n- This delineation helps manage workload and budget by focusing immediate efforts on core website content and design.\n\n## **Strategic Vision and Market Positioning**\n\nThe team presented the website redesign as a subtle but important update aimed at better reflecting the company’s brand soul and improving user engagement without a major PR push (15:05).  \n- **Jenny Vance** shared that leadership and stakeholders responded positively to early design concepts, showing excitement about the refreshed look and feel.  \n- The target launch date is set for **December 15th**, with a fallback to year-end if needed, balancing quality with timely delivery.  \n- This update addresses current issues where content and design lack alignment, especially on product and solution pages, improving clarity and brand cohesion.  \n- The goal is to increase meaningful visitor engagement rather than focusing on volume or broad marketing blitzes.\n\nThe redesign supports longer-term business goals by creating a scalable framework for content and design that can adapt as new products and solutions evolve (16:39).  \n- The integration of AI-assisted content generation and reusable design templates is part of a strategic push to improve efficiency and maintain brand voice.  \n- The approach also anticipates future needs for modular content updates, enabling faster response to market changes or customer feedback.  \n- This positions the company competitively by enhancing digital presence without overextending resources.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Enhancements**\n\nThe team emphasized process discipline around “heads down” days for content creation to maximize efficiency and minimize context switching (12:20).  \n- Jenny recommended strict offline periods with Slack and email turned off, allowing focused work punctuated by brief check-ins as needed.  \n- This method showed prior success in accelerating draft completion and is planned to continue for upcoming platform content sprints.  \n- The approach reflects a shift toward more deliberate work cycles to improve quality and speed, reducing iterative back-and-forth delays.\n\nQuality assurance will include early internal reviews with technical experts to validate content accuracy before wider circulation (25:20).  \n- Kyley is coordinating with technical team members, including one in Japan with a different timezone, to finalize copy this week.  \n- This early vetting minimizes rework during design and development phases, keeping the project on track.  \n- The team also plans to use shared Google Docs with embedded notes to streamline collaboration and feedback incorporation.\n\nThe workflow from content to design to build will be tightly integrated, with each major section receiving a design iteration before moving to development (29:20).  \n- This phased handoff allows for clear approvals and reduces risks of misalignment between content and visual design.  \n- Developers will start building reusable components like navigation and footers based on early design approvals, enabling parallel progress.  \n- This operational setup aims to shorten overall project timelines while maintaining high quality and cross-team visibility.","outline":null,"keywords":["sitemap","copywriting","design workflow","Figma","platform features","content development"],"overview":"- **Content Development Priority:** Finalize homepage and platform pages by end of month to align with design schedules.  \n- **AI Tools Adoption:** Utilize AI tools like Twain to streamline industry page creation, reducing repetitive workload while maintaining tone.  \n- **Weekly Check-ins:** Establish Friday check-ins starting on the 14th to monitor status and adjust plans efficiently.  \n- **Budget Clarity:** Confirmed design cost of $3,500 for Tier 2 and Brickwork guides, optimizing redesign efforts without full rewrites.  \n- **Launch Target:** Website redesign targeted for December 15th, aiming to enhance brand presence and user engagement.  \n- **Process Discipline:** Emphasize focused work periods to improve content creation efficiency and minimize distractions.","action_items":"\n**Kyley Crews**\nDraft homepage content and platform section copy, aiming for completion within the month; share Google Docs draft with notes and input for review (10:44)\nCoordinate with Jenny B. to obtain high-level feature bullets for platform pages by early next week to support detailed copywriting (11:40)\nFinalize the copy review with the technical team, including feedback from an expert in Japan, and send to Tristan for design handoff this week (25:10)\n\n**Jenny Vance**\nDiscuss with Jenny B. to secure platform feature bullet points to assist Kyley’s copy development and confirm photography approach for screen grabs (11:37)\nProvide access to the photo contest folder for marketing use, and manage permissions for photos featuring team members (18:20)\nProduce a statement of work draft for the ebook design project focused on Tier 2 and Brickwork guides and coordinate budget discussions accordingly (29:00)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nShare Figma designs of homepage for review prior to launching development and deliver reusable visual components for build commencement (17:10)\nDraft the statement of work for the ebook redesign project reflecting agreed budgets and scope and provide to Jenny for approval (25:40)\nSchedule and conduct weekly Friday check-ins starting December 14th at 12:30 PM for progress updates and feedback (29:40)\n"},"duration":32.56999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Kyley Crews"},{"id":1,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":2,"name":"Jenny Vance"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It was really good.","index":0,"end_time":0.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"I drove, though, so it was.","index":1,"end_time":4.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.84,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"It was a lot.","index":2,"end_time":4.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.08,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Where was, where was the meeting?","index":3,"end_time":7.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It was in Banning Mills in Georgia.","index":4,"end_time":11.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.48,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"It was about an hour outside of Atlanta.","index":5,"end_time":14.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.84,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"It was really, really cool.","index":6,"end_time":16.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15.68,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"And we got to do ziplining.","index":7,"end_time":18.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.76,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":18.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Which was very fun.","index":9,"end_time":20.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.96,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"But it''s about a 9 hour, 9 or 10 hour drive for me.","index":10,"end_time":25.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.2,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Okay.","index":11,"end_time":26.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Where are you coming from?","index":12,"end_time":27.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Indianapolis, Indiana.","index":13,"end_time":29.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.88,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Okay.","index":14,"end_time":30.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But they let me bring my son and my husband, so it made more sense to drive.","index":15,"end_time":37.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.08,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":37.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"At least that''s what I told myself.","index":17,"end_time":39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.6,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":40.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Until you''re in the car for nine hours with everyone, but.","index":19,"end_time":42.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, that''s good.","index":20,"end_time":44.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Glad it worked out.","index":21,"end_time":45.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a.","index":22,"end_time":47.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s a good trip to get everyone together.","index":23,"end_time":48.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How many folks from.","index":24,"end_time":50.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"From NCAMP?","index":25,"end_time":50.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''d say there were at least 50 of us.","index":26,"end_time":54.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.37,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Okay.","index":27,"end_time":55.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Very.","index":28,"end_time":55.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Give or take.","index":29,"end_time":56.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.81,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"It was most of the company.","index":30,"end_time":59.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.73,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"A few people weren''t there for various reasons, but, yeah, I think most of us were.","index":31,"end_time":65.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.09,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"All right.","index":32,"end_time":68.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":67.489,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, good stuff.","index":33,"end_time":68.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, glad we, you know, you''re able to get this time on the board.","index":34,"end_time":73.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know when we talked last, we wanted to use today to, you know, get a sense of the sitemap and kind of next steps, how we can pass the baton back and forth between copy and design and get a sense of all that.","index":35,"end_time":89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But where would you like to start?","index":36,"end_time":91.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What''s the best approach for you?","index":37,"end_time":94.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, I opened the Octopus sitemap and I know the first thing up is kind of the homepage, so.","index":38,"end_time":105.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.72,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"So we can look there.","index":39,"end_time":108.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.06,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Oh, and here''s Jenny.","index":40,"end_time":112.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yes, I can share my screen.","index":41,"end_time":115.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hello.","index":42,"end_time":119.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":119.34,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Sorry I''m late.","index":43,"end_time":120.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":119.98,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Oh, no, that''s all right.","index":44,"end_time":121.939,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":121.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How you doing, Jenny?","index":45,"end_time":122.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":121.939,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We were just chatting about the exciting week you all had last week.","index":46,"end_time":126.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it was fun.","index":47,"end_time":128.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":126.82,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":48,"end_time":129.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":49,"end_time":133.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, Kyle.","index":50,"end_time":134.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":134.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Got the sitemap pulled up here.","index":52,"end_time":137.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The main thing, I think, at least from our perspective, and I don''t know how you typically do copy on your side, but what we can do is with this site map, all of these pages are broken out with really some guidelines or parameters.","index":53,"end_time":155.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":139.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so each block has the intended vision for.","index":54,"end_time":161.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s like a low fidelity wireframe as far as, like how we envision designing that component.","index":55,"end_time":167.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You''ll see with features to be either a screenshot or an image that you see in a lot of cases.","index":56,"end_time":173.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, if we have a stat section, this is where it would get broken out into thirds, include a background image, etc.","index":57,"end_time":182.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We want to give some indication as to how these would be constructed.","index":58,"end_time":186.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then you have that in the back of your mind and then within each Block.","index":59,"end_time":190.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We also provide some parameters to work from, you know, what the purpose of the section is, you know, the headline, obviously, and then a general estimation of the length of the copy that we would fit from a design standpoint.","index":60,"end_time":206.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s how each of these major pages are laid out there and what we can do.","index":61,"end_time":212.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Kylie and I''ll be interested to hear your thoughts.","index":62,"end_time":214.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But you can just work in like a Google Docs format if you like, just title the section, you know, put it in a table or just, you know, a headline based on this.","index":63,"end_time":224.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And as long as it flows like we have on the, the wireframe side, we''ll be able to, you know, line those up and then the, the wireframe plus the copy document will give us the inputs we need for the design file that we''ll create from there.","index":64,"end_time":238.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":65,"end_time":239,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So how''s that sound?","index":66,"end_time":240.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":239.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, that works for me.","index":67,"end_time":242.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.92,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"And, and what do you feel as far as, do you want to do homepage first and then we work through that, or do you want to do a couple, like, how do you envision maybe batching these or what does your bandwidth look like there?","index":68,"end_time":255.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I definitely want to start with the homepage and make sure that we''re all, you know, kind of aligned on how that''s going to look.","index":69,"end_time":264.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.5,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah, and then my instinct was that we would just go to like, go through the site map, essentially.","index":70,"end_time":273.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.42,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"So try to cover the platform first.","index":71,"end_time":275.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.3,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"That seems, you know, the next most imperative, and then just work left to right.","index":72,"end_time":281.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.02,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I agree.","index":73,"end_time":283.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And, and that might be the best way to do.","index":74,"end_time":285.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We do the homepage, knock that out and then maybe we do the platform section first and then we can move on to solutions, maybe batch it that way.","index":75,"end_time":294.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we''ll know how we want to speak about the platform.","index":76,"end_time":298.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.23,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"That will inform how we will, you know, translate it into the solutions in the industries.","index":77,"end_time":303.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.43,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":78,"end_time":305.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":79,"end_time":306.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And for our planning purposes, how do you feel, time frame wise, what does bandwidth look like on your side?","index":80,"end_time":313.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And.","index":81,"end_time":313.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And just some general timelines there.","index":82,"end_time":315.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re kind of busy.","index":83,"end_time":320.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.15,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"I would love to get like the homepage and the platform done this month.","index":84,"end_time":326.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.07,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Does that seem reasonable, Jenny?","index":85,"end_time":328.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.71,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"I''ll probably have to work with Jenny B on platform stuff.","index":86,"end_time":333.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.11,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"So, yeah, we might have to like, kind of see.","index":87,"end_time":339.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.31,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Kylie, I know you''ve got a couple other things in flight.","index":88,"end_time":342.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.55,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"We might have to see if we can like, give you a day to go offline or so and try to power through some build and then, you know, we can obviously do some review.","index":89,"end_time":358.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.15,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But I think we might need to set a goal week by week.","index":90,"end_time":360.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.48,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I talked Tristan about like let''s see if we can get Homepage drafted and at least for internal approval this week and get that through so that we''re, you know, seeing if we can kind of release that for build.","index":91,"end_time":375.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":363.04,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I would hope early next week and then next week maybe we shift into platform with there''s significant work on platform because it''s three pages.","index":92,"end_time":386.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":376.64,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Right.","index":93,"end_time":386.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.15,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I think that probably will take the longest overall if, if we kind of took you offline for a day next week and try to get that maybe we pick a mid week day and just like turn off slack and try to get to work and you know, you can always do some just in time release stuff to me and Jenny when you have things written.","index":94,"end_time":414.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.63,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And then I mean part of me and you, you and I can litigate this a little bit Offline is like what if we could do platform next week and give you enough time to just go offline for a day and dedicate to that.","index":95,"end_time":432.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.03,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I would think that would be easier than smaller iterative movement.","index":96,"end_time":438.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":434.39,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that makes sense.","index":97,"end_time":442.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.01,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"And then the week following we''re you know, trying to drive into and we might be able to use like a little bit more AI support but we try to knock out maybe like by industry, by reputation.","index":98,"end_time":462.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.29,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Then I think, Tristan, like those are our major content deliverables if I''m remembering correctly.","index":99,"end_time":468.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.09,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I don''t think there''s a lot of content outside of that other than maybe if you scroll over where we would be writing a lot of like net new content other than the our story page.","index":100,"end_time":481.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.54,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s the bulk of it Jenny, for sure.","index":101,"end_time":487.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":485.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Case studies if you want to, you know, obviously we can work with what we have.","index":102,"end_time":493.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I don''t know if there''s any adjustments there.","index":103,"end_time":495.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There is a case studies like page but it''s mostly curating existing pieces, you know, just lining it up and like there''s a feature content piece or case study here, filter functionality.","index":104,"end_time":509.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":495.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So not a lot of content on this page.","index":105,"end_time":511.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I think those are, those are really the main, main sections.","index":106,"end_time":516.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Events is a new section that we''ll want to think through.","index":107,"end_time":521.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":516.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And, and, and I don''t even know if that''s a copy situation.","index":108,"end_time":525.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s more about like what is the data, you know, like what are the events and how you describe them.","index":109,"end_time":530.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s probably going to be the big, big piece there.","index":110,"end_time":533.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":111,"end_time":534.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.31,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"The other thing I''m thinking, Kylie, is like for the buy industry pages, if we write one then we might be able to use Twain to do some customization on the others like that might be something interesting to vet with our kg since he already has some industry customization set up in there.","index":112,"end_time":555.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.95,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So we might be able to like say rewrite this for this industry, but keep the same basic pattern.","index":113,"end_time":563.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.92,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So we might be able to like bump it into that, especially if we''re feeding it some of the other prompts that you have in tone.","index":114,"end_time":574.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":564.8,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But if you write one page, I feel a lot more confident that we could rinse and repeat for a few of the other pages.","index":115,"end_time":580.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.64,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So that I would hope would take less time than how daunting it looks in there, because I am sure that does look a little daunting.","index":116,"end_time":593.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":583.26,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But my hope would be that we can get through just looking at the calendar that like, if we can try to get through getting the content all the way through the solutions into the ideometry team''s hands by like the 25th.","index":117,"end_time":613.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.42,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I know it''s aggressive, but I.","index":118,"end_time":618.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.47,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"My hope is if we can give you a day, a week where we leave you alone and let you just really focus and then drive, it would be way more effective than iterative movement trying to tune in, tune out, and we just communicate with the marketing team and say like, these are days where we need to leave Kylie alone.","index":119,"end_time":640.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.87,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So.","index":120,"end_time":641.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.57,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Okay.","index":121,"end_time":642.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.77,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Thoughts on that?","index":122,"end_time":645.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":644.37,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s a good idea.","index":123,"end_time":648.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.53,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"I''m looking through like the wireframe for the compliance platform and kind of trying to figure out a little bit where I should go to get the basis or just like what we want to include.","index":124,"end_time":665.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.41,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"But it has like the features we want to highlight.","index":125,"end_time":669.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.69,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"So I''m wondering if we have information about that like in the knowledge center that would be useful for me.","index":126,"end_time":674.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.37,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"The solutions page, you mean on epgr?","index":127,"end_time":678.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.69,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah, Let me pull it.","index":128,"end_time":680.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Compliance.","index":129,"end_time":682.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, as piece here.","index":130,"end_time":683.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I think Jenny B.","index":131,"end_time":687.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":685.69,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Would be pretty critical on this, so I believe.","index":132,"end_time":693.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":688.01,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And you might be able to kind of have her frame out some important like high level bullets for those sections while you''re working on the homepage.","index":133,"end_time":706.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":695.54,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So that might be an ask that we could do for this week and I could, I could get with her tomorrow on that because I have my one on one.","index":134,"end_time":715.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.02,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Let me just add it to our agenda.","index":135,"end_time":717.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.78,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"All right, give me a second.","index":136,"end_time":740.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.03,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":137,"end_time":740.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.43,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":138,"end_time":759.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.04,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I''ll talk with her about that tomorrow and see if she can get us those bullets by early next week so that you can have a dedicated day.","index":139,"end_time":768.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":759.72,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And then, yeah, I would just say pretty if I''m you, Kylie, I do hard rules where to everyone else you''re on a vacation day or personal day.","index":140,"end_time":780.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.37,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Right.","index":141,"end_time":781.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.85,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"It''s like you''re just heads down off slack, turn it like completely, you know, sign out or turn it off on your computer and your phone and if you want to like zoom out for a break and check in, cool.","index":142,"end_time":794.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":781.09,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"You know, but that would be my recommendation because just seeing how quickly you move through content and then I would be happy to ideate with you, jump on the phone, talk through things to help you get started.","index":143,"end_time":811.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.69,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So happy to do that as well.","index":144,"end_time":815.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":812.63,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And I''m sure Jenny B.","index":145,"end_time":816.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":815.31,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Would be happy to do that if that''d be helpful.","index":146,"end_time":819.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":816.43,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":147,"end_time":820.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.99,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"I''m actually going through right now too and putting this first section into a Google Doc so that she has the notes for a starting point and she can put notes in.","index":148,"end_time":832.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.59,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"I think that''ll be helpful.","index":149,"end_time":834.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.24,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"But yeah, once we have like some of the detail and I know she was going to meet with Brianna today about how we want to do like our screen grabs and so I think that''s another key component we need to get locked down.","index":150,"end_time":849.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks, Kylie.","index":151,"end_time":851.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I was, I was going to ask about that.","index":152,"end_time":852.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":851.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is the best way to get those.","index":153,"end_time":854.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":855.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because each section, you know, the vision is to have one.","index":155,"end_time":858.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":156,"end_time":859.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.76,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I think Jenny goes back and forth about wanting them like displayed on a monitor or just on their own.","index":157,"end_time":866.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.44,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"So I''m hoping that that''s what she''s going to get figured out today.","index":158,"end_time":869.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.52,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"I hope it''s just on their own.","index":159,"end_time":872.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":870.84,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah, well, she really likes the monitor.","index":160,"end_time":877.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.12,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"But that''s just a lot of monitors on.","index":161,"end_time":880.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s a lot of monitors.","index":162,"end_time":882.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.08,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"I''m like, we need to be a little sparing with it.","index":163,"end_time":886.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.6,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"But yeah, I''m hoping that Briana can help with some of the, like the orange outlines and we''ll be able to find a middle ground.","index":164,"end_time":894.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.84,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah, and, and how, and even take a step back.","index":165,"end_time":899.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How did everything go last week when.","index":166,"end_time":902.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":899.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"When y'' all presented the materials and such?","index":167,"end_time":905.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I thought it went well.","index":168,"end_time":907.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":905.82,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I, I think I still on the PowerPoint, I like the brand guidelines version so much that that''s like legitimately what I want on a PowerPoint.","index":169,"end_time":920.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":908.62,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And so I just took screenshots of a lot of the elements of it.","index":170,"end_time":926.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":920.74,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I didn''t show the full homepage because we haven''t edited the content.","index":171,"end_time":931.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":926.78,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"What I found, whenever I''ve show is that they''re immediately distracted by the content.","index":172,"end_time":936.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":931.26,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I took this section of the screenshots and showed it and just kind of said this is what the, you know, topography element would look like and some of the movement.","index":173,"end_time":947.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.4,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And since Brianna and our team had helped with that, I thought that''d be useful.","index":174,"end_time":951.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":947.32,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And it generally seemed like everyone was pretty excited.","index":175,"end_time":954.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":951.76,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So they''re already asking about, you know, slide deck revisions and things that they can use.","index":176,"end_time":960.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":954.52,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So, um, I kind of rolled it out as a.","index":177,"end_time":963.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":960.6,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"In an ideal world, we launched December 15th.","index":178,"end_time":967.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":964.63,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"If we.","index":179,"end_time":968.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.59,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I would still be happy if we launch by end of year.","index":180,"end_time":971.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":969.03,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"We''re not planning on doing like a big PR push.","index":181,"end_time":974.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":971.55,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"It''s more of a subtle change and to drive more of like the engagement that people have with our website, the content and so forth.","index":182,"end_time":983.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":975.11,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So explain some of those whys.","index":183,"end_time":985.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.39,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I showed like the before on our website, some of the problems we were facing with the look and feel kind of not having much of our soul present and the products and solution pages not being aligned.","index":184,"end_time":999.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.99,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I think that setup also kind of helped with the.","index":185,"end_time":1001.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":999.05,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Here''s why we''re doing this.","index":186,"end_time":1002.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.57,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And yeah, so overall it seemed positive.","index":187,"end_time":1008.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1005.13,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"People are asking when they can start using things.","index":188,"end_time":1012.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1008.97,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I think they''re excited about the design change.","index":189,"end_time":1015.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.97,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So that''s pretty fun.","index":190,"end_time":1017.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.61,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah, overall really good.","index":191,"end_time":1020.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1019.25,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"All right.","index":192,"end_time":1021.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":193,"end_time":1022.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":194,"end_time":1022.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And.","index":195,"end_time":1022.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And our thought is, Kylie, once I would envision maybe with the homepage we could deliver that in Figma.","index":196,"end_time":1029.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Would you all like to see that?","index":197,"end_time":1031.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1030.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That way you.","index":198,"end_time":1032.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You see the, the new copy design laid in and we have it in Figma before we go to build.","index":199,"end_time":1038.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1032.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Would that be a good approach for you just to make sure we have a stepping stone there?","index":200,"end_time":1042.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yep, that would be great.","index":201,"end_time":1044.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1043.71,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll do that.","index":202,"end_time":1046.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1045.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then what I would like is if we''re get a thumbs up on the Figma, we can go ahead and start to build the, the homepage.","index":203,"end_time":1053.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1046.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because there''s a lot of just key like reusable components that we can start to construct.","index":204,"end_time":1059.549,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, as the other pages get written, like obviously the nav and how that''s constructed footer and some just other components that we''ll reuse so we can start to.","index":205,"end_time":1069.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1059.549,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To get, you know, the, the train moving there on development side and held up.","index":206,"end_time":1074.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":207,"end_time":1076.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1075.2,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"The other thing, a couple updates.","index":208,"end_time":1078.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1076.24,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So we did a photo contest because we were at this very natural location.","index":209,"end_time":1083.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1078.6,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":210,"end_time":1084.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1083.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we do have.","index":211,"end_time":1086.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1085.36,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Now there''s a lot of junk that got dropped into this folder, but there are some interesting photos that I think we could use kind of as stock photography stuff.","index":212,"end_time":1096.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1086.28,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I just wanted to.","index":213,"end_time":1098.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.4,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I''m happy to give you access to that.","index":214,"end_time":1100.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1098.84,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I say when we have faces, I just want to validate that it''s okay to use, but otherwise.","index":215,"end_time":1108.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1100.88,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And we will also get some professional photography.","index":216,"end_time":1111.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1109.04,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So we had a professional photographer come out, do some head shots.","index":217,"end_time":1116.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.96,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And then we.","index":218,"end_time":1117.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1116.16,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"She also did like a couple group photos and she tried to take some like nature based photos that we could also use.","index":219,"end_time":1126.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1118,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I''m hoping that that gives us a good repository.","index":220,"end_time":1129.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1126.23,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Kind of in theme with our team, we just said you all have your phones, they take pretty good pictures at this point.","index":221,"end_time":1135.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.35,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So like, yeah, let''s do a contest to see who has the best photo that they can capture.","index":222,"end_time":1141.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1135.75,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But there''s some interesting ones in there for sure.","index":223,"end_time":1144.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1141.95,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So yeah, I.","index":224,"end_time":1149.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1146.23,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Did you have a winner of the contest?","index":225,"end_time":1152.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Not yet.","index":226,"end_time":1152.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1152.31,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I haven''t gone through them all yet.","index":227,"end_time":1154.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1152.83,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"We''re gonna go through and kind of put them into a like contenders folder because it''s.","index":228,"end_time":1163.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1154.27,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"It is just a lot of stuff right now.","index":229,"end_time":1165.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1163.07,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But there''s also I''m sure like your team might be able to grab them and edit some.","index":230,"end_time":1170.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1165.03,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"That we had one woman who edited them and they look great and then a lot of people who didn''t.","index":231,"end_time":1175.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1170.31,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But if there are any that are interesting, I think that''s another option is you can always grab and edit those photos.","index":232,"end_time":1182.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1175.75,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I''ll send you a link to that drive.","index":233,"end_time":1185.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1183.29,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And the only thing I''d say is if we''re going to use a header that has someone''s face in it, I want to get permission to use that.","index":234,"end_time":1193.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.57,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But yeah, and then there''s some things that we can use a spotter on our team and our culture page.","index":235,"end_time":1201.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1195.21,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Like our technical program manager team, they''ve all.","index":236,"end_time":1205.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1201.45,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"They call themselves the Power Rangers and they all have like a thing.","index":237,"end_time":1210.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.84,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So they took a picture with Power Ranger shirts on.","index":238,"end_time":1213.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1210.68,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"It''s kind of silly, but I definitely want that on the website.","index":239,"end_time":1216.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1213.16,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah, that organic stuff, you can''t, you can''t really cheat that stuff.","index":240,"end_time":1220.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1217.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, like when you have some of the.","index":241,"end_time":1222.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Some almost organic nature of it will come through too.","index":242,"end_time":1228.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1222.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So even if they''re not perfectly, you know, composed, we can work with some of that.","index":243,"end_time":1233.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1228.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":244,"end_time":1233.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":245,"end_time":1234.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":246,"end_time":1235.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.88,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":247,"end_time":1236.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1235.64,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So.","index":248,"end_time":1236.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1236.2,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And then the other thing we were curious about I think is just figuring out one of the things that I wanted to make sure I understood in the context of our agreement is we have a lot of content on our site that has existing like old design.","index":249,"end_time":1255.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1237.24,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Right.","index":250,"end_time":1256.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1255.96,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"How does that transition in this engagement scope of ideometry?","index":251,"end_time":1262.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1256.52,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Because you''re going to build subpage, right?","index":252,"end_time":1264.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1262.37,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"We''re going to start to look at design of a subpage.","index":253,"end_time":1267.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.97,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I would assume soon.","index":254,"end_time":1268.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1267.45,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"We''ll probably see a design for the resources page at some point.","index":255,"end_time":1274.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.69,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But I''m curious where those other things fall that hit into landing pages and so forth.","index":256,"end_time":1282.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1274.85,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And what of Those fall in scope and what doesn''t.","index":257,"end_time":1286.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1282.93,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":1287.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So like anything like the case study page would be obviously reformatted to a new design.","index":259,"end_time":1292.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1287.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think anything that''s off site, like an ebook or a resource or a checklist guide, that''s what we wouldn''t go in and redesign all of those.","index":260,"end_time":1301.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So if there are important items, which I know we were going to talk about that too, that the Tier 2 guide, we can talk about how you want to handle that.","index":261,"end_time":1309.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.129,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So those key resources I would rebrand probably video content''s also another big one that, you know, if we do use existing videos, they will be off brand if we insert those.","index":262,"end_time":1321.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1310.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I don''t know how you want to handle those.","index":263,"end_time":1323.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1321.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That is outside of what we have.","index":264,"end_time":1326.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1324.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, anything like a case study page.","index":265,"end_time":1328.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1326.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because we''re taking the content and fitting it into the new website design.","index":266,"end_time":1333.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that works.","index":267,"end_time":1334.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1333.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, any of the blog posts and all those will be fit into a template.","index":268,"end_time":1339.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1335.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Obviously all the product pages will be redone.","index":269,"end_time":1343.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1340.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I would just say the best thing is like any off site content that''s a resource or something like that, we would need to think about how you all want to fit those in.","index":270,"end_time":1351.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1343.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":271,"end_time":1353.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1352.54,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":1353.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.18,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I think the only thing I was thinking about with the Tier 2 guide, it is something we want to do.","index":273,"end_time":1358.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.74,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"It''s having.","index":274,"end_time":1361.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1358.94,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"It feels heavy for 5k like that.","index":275,"end_time":1365.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1361.5,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"That feels really heavy to get that done.","index":276,"end_time":1367.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.3,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I think that''s the only thing I''m worried about.","index":277,"end_time":1372.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1370.5,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Our designer resources.","index":278,"end_time":1376.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1375.22,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"90 bucks an hour.","index":279,"end_time":1378.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1376.94,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And we have another external resource that''s offered her time at $90 an hour, even if we want to, you know, try a different designer.","index":280,"end_time":1387.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1378.34,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So, and I''m trying to think like overall time on this.","index":281,"end_time":1392.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1387.22,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I could certainly see it being, you know, a 20, 25 hour project, but like still pretty reasonable at that rate for us to go with another designer.","index":282,"end_time":1405.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1392.34,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So that''s kind of what we''re working against.","index":283,"end_time":1407.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1405.73,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And it.","index":284,"end_time":1408.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1407.37,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"It''s hard to justify double to do that.","index":285,"end_time":1412.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1408.25,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I don''t know.","index":286,"end_time":1414.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1413.37,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I just want to put that forward.","index":287,"end_time":1416.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1414.73,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":1418.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So just real quick.","index":289,"end_time":1419.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the ebooks we do have, they''re 3,500 apiece.","index":290,"end_time":1424.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1419.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That includes copy and design.","index":291,"end_time":1425.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1424.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the design would be about half of that.","index":292,"end_time":1427.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1425.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I think like when we were talking about, we were like 3,000, 3,500 for design of two of those.","index":293,"end_time":1433.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I just want to make sure we''re on the same page.","index":294,"end_time":1435.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1433.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":295,"end_time":1436.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1435.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It wouldn''t be five for.","index":296,"end_time":1437.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For one.","index":297,"end_time":1437.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":298,"end_time":1439.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1438.74,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And also Kylie has the.","index":299,"end_time":1441.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1439.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The content, which is copy.","index":300,"end_time":1442.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":301,"end_time":1443.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1442.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Piece of that.","index":302,"end_time":1443.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1443.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":303,"end_time":1444.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1443.74,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"It''s Already done and a bit most.","index":304,"end_time":1447.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1444.82,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Of the design iteration in terms of flow that we could use it.","index":305,"end_time":1451.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1447.46,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Like there might be some template changes that you''re wanting kindly in there.","index":306,"end_time":1454.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1451.82,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I know you''re hoping for that.","index":307,"end_time":1456.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.9,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Okay, so just.","index":308,"end_time":1459.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1458.22,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I''m saying because I obviously Misheard last time, 3500 would be the design for both the Tier 2 guide and the brickwork guide.","index":309,"end_time":1466.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1459.26,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":310,"end_time":1467.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1467.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because we, I mean, we would draw a line about half of what it would be for the whole thing.","index":311,"end_time":1472.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1467.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":312,"end_time":1473.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1472.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, let me just put.","index":313,"end_time":1474.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1473.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Put that in what I had real quick.","index":314,"end_time":1476.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me look at something.","index":315,"end_time":1477.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because they will be complementary assets.","index":316,"end_time":1482.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1480.01,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"So once, you know, we have one design, it shouldn''t take as much for the subsequent design.","index":317,"end_time":1487.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.17,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"But there are different parts of them that, you know, need to be built out graphically.","index":318,"end_time":1492.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1487.93,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"So.","index":319,"end_time":1493.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.97,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, what I have, it''s.","index":320,"end_time":1496.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1494.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s 30 points for ebook with design, so we''d be about half of that.","index":321,"end_time":1500.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1496.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So 1500 for the design.","index":322,"end_time":1502.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1500.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":323,"end_time":1505.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1502.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":324,"end_time":1505.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1505.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":325,"end_time":1506.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1506.17,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I mean, that feels reasonable.","index":326,"end_time":1509.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1507.93,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Sorry, I misheard and I thought it was like 5 or 6k and somehow in my mind.","index":327,"end_time":1513.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1509.41,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I feel like 3500 is reasonable.","index":328,"end_time":1516.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1513.69,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Kylie, if you want to get to work on that with Tristan.","index":329,"end_time":1519.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1516.29,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":330,"end_time":1520.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.01,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"The copy in review with our technical folks, my goal is to have that so I can send it to you yet this week, Tristan.","index":331,"end_time":1529.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.73,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Okay.","index":332,"end_time":1529.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1529.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"One of them is in Japan, so he''s going to finish it his tomorrow, which is.","index":333,"end_time":1535.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1530.49,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":334,"end_time":1537.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1535.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, how do you want to do that, Jen?","index":335,"end_time":1539.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1538.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You want me to write up a statement of work for that separate piece?","index":336,"end_time":1543.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1539.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is there anything else you want to put into that?","index":337,"end_time":1545.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1543.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The only other thing I would consider is like, like if we want to do other templates that we could pass on to our other designers to kind of like iterate or do.","index":338,"end_time":1562.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1547.21,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"That''s the only other thing that, like how, how much do we kind of drive into template versions so that we have kind of a resource available and now we''re just doing iterations or updates through Canva or Adobe.","index":339,"end_time":1584.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1566.81,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah, that is the one thing I would like these all designed in InDesign.","index":340,"end_time":1589.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1585.45,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Not think much.","index":341,"end_time":1591.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1590.49,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah, we can, we can do that.","index":342,"end_time":1594.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1592.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And we also can do like Canva template.","index":343,"end_time":1598.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1594.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We do that a lot because there''s internal teams that, you know, even if they''re social media posts or things like that, we can, you know, the hardest thing in Canva is just separating out layers and making sure that it jives with Canva and folks have the ability to change text components and things like that.","index":344,"end_time":1614.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1598.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we can build those for you.","index":345,"end_time":1616.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1614.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s an idea.","index":346,"end_time":1617.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1616.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That way you have something to work from.","index":347,"end_time":1619.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1617.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, we could even do the same thing with, like, the PowerPoint slide, which.","index":348,"end_time":1624.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1620.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Which we can build out.","index":349,"end_time":1626.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1624.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, video content''s another piece if you want logo animations or anything.","index":350,"end_time":1632.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1628.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, all that stuff is things we can do.","index":351,"end_time":1635.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Basically build like a graphics package that you can reuse it sounds like, internally.","index":352,"end_time":1640.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So happy to do all that stuff.","index":353,"end_time":1642.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1640.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just off the top of my head, it''s probably some things that could get done as far as, like, a package that could be repurposed internally.","index":354,"end_time":1649.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1642.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":355,"end_time":1651.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1650.91,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I''m gonna have to hop for a call where I have a hard stop, but I''d say, Tristan, for time, let''s do the 3K.","index":356,"end_time":1660.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1652.43,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"And then I think we need to just kind of line out what are some of the other resources and how that might align to points.","index":357,"end_time":1668.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1660.99,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But I could see us possibly moving down the path of, like, okay, what are some of the other things where we definitely need another design for it, and then do we just invest in that and, you know, get a little help on the case studies front on an ebook revision?","index":358,"end_time":1687.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1670.27,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Right.","index":359,"end_time":1687.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1687.26,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I think we probably have a few other things that we could, once we go through this, like, not saying it''s immediately easy, but we''re not doing a full rewrite like these two guides, and we''re really just applying a new design to it so that it can make that transition and still feel connected and then have some materials for social posts that are ready to go, some other kind of, like, templates that we can use for documents, and maybe like a landing page template.","index":360,"end_time":1722.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1687.62,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"We just did a deal room kind of template for a customer, and I could see us, you know, maybe even looking at a design for that.","index":361,"end_time":1733.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1723.34,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"So I think we just need to look at a few of those other elements.","index":362,"end_time":1736.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1733.27,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"But I. I''m not gonna be able to make a decision here in the last minute of our call if that''s.","index":363,"end_time":1740.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1736.23,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":364,"end_time":1741.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1740.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No worries.","index":365,"end_time":1742.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1741.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, you.","index":366,"end_time":1743.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1742.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You want to start?","index":367,"end_time":1743.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1743.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I can write up the two ebooks.","index":368,"end_time":1745.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1743.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s tier two.","index":369,"end_time":1746.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1745.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And what''s the other one?","index":370,"end_time":1747.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1746.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just so I can.","index":371,"end_time":1748.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1747.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Rick.","index":372,"end_time":1748.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1748.35,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Okay.","index":373,"end_time":1749.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1749.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":374,"end_time":1749.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1749.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":375,"end_time":1750.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1749.87,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yep.","index":376,"end_time":1753.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1752.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I''ll get that written up and get that over to you.","index":377,"end_time":1755.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1753.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then Kylie and Jenny, if you want to jump, I''ll just wrap with Kylie here for a second.","index":378,"end_time":1759.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1755.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":379,"end_time":1760.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1759.78,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Thanks, Guy.","index":380,"end_time":1760.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1760.22,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Yep.","index":381,"end_time":1761.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1760.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And Kylie, what we''ll do, you''re working on homepage.","index":382,"end_time":1765.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1762.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''ll be the primary one that we''ll get started.","index":383,"end_time":1767.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1765.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll turn around the design for that one, and I think for each of the major sections, we''ll probably return a design so we can get the thumbs up there before we build.","index":384,"end_time":1777.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1767.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we''ll be on lookout for the homepage, it sounds like this week.","index":385,"end_time":1781.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1777.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we can work on design early next week.","index":386,"end_time":1784.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1781.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then I think we probably should have, like, a check in at some point.","index":387,"end_time":1787.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1784.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":388,"end_time":1789.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.51,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"See where things are.","index":389,"end_time":1790.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1789.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"When do you want to do that?","index":390,"end_time":1791.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Next week to see where we are.","index":391,"end_time":1793.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"My.","index":392,"end_time":1796.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1795.71,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"The beginnings of my weeks are crazy.","index":393,"end_time":1800.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1797.79,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Okay, so maybe in the interest of just making it easier moving forward, can we touch base on Fridays?","index":394,"end_time":1807.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1800.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s see.","index":395,"end_time":1809.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1808.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You want to do 14th at.","index":396,"end_time":1811.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1809.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me see here.","index":397,"end_time":1813.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1812.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because we can do.","index":398,"end_time":1817.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1816.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m literally open all day.","index":399,"end_time":1821.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.31,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"All I have is feeding my son at four different times.","index":400,"end_time":1825.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1821.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":401,"end_time":1826.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1825.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":402,"end_time":1826.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1826.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How old''s your son?","index":403,"end_time":1827.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1826.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''ll be nine months next week.","index":404,"end_time":1830.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1828.07,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Oh, very nice.","index":405,"end_time":1831.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1830.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m an old man.","index":406,"end_time":1833.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I have three older kids, so well past those days.","index":407,"end_time":1836.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1833.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I remember not sleeping much back then.","index":408,"end_time":1838.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1836.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":409,"end_time":1839.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1839.19,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":410,"end_time":1840.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1840.43,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"That''s the thing.","index":411,"end_time":1841.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1840.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"But he is, like, the cutest thing in the world.","index":412,"end_time":1843.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1841.31,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":413,"end_time":1844.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1843.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it''s a great, great time.","index":414,"end_time":1846.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Nine months.","index":415,"end_time":1848.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1847.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is he.","index":416,"end_time":1848.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1848.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is he, like, taking a step or crawling around?","index":417,"end_time":1851.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1848.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, he.","index":418,"end_time":1852.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1851.63,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"He rolls and he boot scoots.","index":419,"end_time":1854.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1852.59,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"He''s long.","index":420,"end_time":1855.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1854.59,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"He is a long boy.","index":421,"end_time":1857.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1855.869,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"And so the, like, crawling is a little delayed, I think.","index":422,"end_time":1862.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1858.11,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"But he likes to stand.","index":423,"end_time":1864.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1862.75,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"He just doesn''t move standing.","index":424,"end_time":1866.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.43,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"My.","index":425,"end_time":1867.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1866.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"My daughter scooted so she would, like, move her legs so she would scoot from.","index":426,"end_time":1871.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1867.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what we call it, the boot scoot.","index":427,"end_time":1873.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1871.5,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah, she did that.","index":428,"end_time":1874.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1873.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I don''t even think she walked to, like, 14 months, 15 months.","index":429,"end_time":1877.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1874.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, it was.","index":430,"end_time":1878.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1877.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We were even worried.","index":431,"end_time":1878.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1878.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re like, I don''t know what''s going on.","index":432,"end_time":1880.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1878.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And doctors are like, hey, she''s getting from A to B with no problem right now.","index":433,"end_time":1885.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1880.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So they''ll.","index":434,"end_time":1885.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1885.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"He''s like, they''ll figure it out.","index":435,"end_time":1886.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1885.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":436,"end_time":1887.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1886.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":437,"end_time":1887.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1887.26,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"Okay.","index":438,"end_time":1888.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1887.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s one of the things.","index":439,"end_time":1889.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1888.7,"speaker_name":"Jenny Vance"},{"text":"I''m kind of glad I had him when I was older, because I feel like 20s.","index":440,"end_time":1893.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1889.5,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Kylie would have had more anxiety.","index":441,"end_time":1895.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1893.28,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":442,"end_time":1895.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1895.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m like, yeah, he''ll be fine.","index":443,"end_time":1897.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1895.8,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a good mindset to have, because they all will be fine.","index":444,"end_time":1902.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1897.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":445,"end_time":1902.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1902.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so I''ve got Kylie at 12:30 to 1.","index":446,"end_time":1908.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1904.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Does that work on Friday?","index":447,"end_time":1909.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1908.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll send that your way.","index":448,"end_time":1911.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1909.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I''ve got that on the 14th.","index":449,"end_time":1913.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll just be on the lookout for the copy in the.","index":450,"end_time":1917.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1914.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"In the interim, and then I''ll get that statement work for the design piece over to Jenny today and go from there.","index":451,"end_time":1923.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1917.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":452,"end_time":1924.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1923.94,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"And I have that copy almost final.","index":453,"end_time":1926.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1924.46,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"It''s like a 21 page Google Doc, and there''s lots of, like, notes about where I think things could be designed out, but mostly I trust your judgment, so.","index":454,"end_time":1937.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1927.98,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":455,"end_time":1938.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1937.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I''m excited about them.","index":456,"end_time":1940.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1939.66,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":457,"end_time":1942.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1941.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, thanks for your time, Kylie.","index":458,"end_time":1943.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1942.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":459,"end_time":1944.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1943.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll chat soon.","index":460,"end_time":1945.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1944.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, good deal.","index":461,"end_time":1946.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1945.82,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"},{"text":"Bye.","index":462,"end_time":1947.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1946.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley Crews"}],"dateString":"2025-11-04T16:30:00.000Z","host_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88101950404?pwd=QpFPtp65X6pjfifn5alUnYOkaTzNpP.1","participants":["jenny.vance@encamp.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,kyley.crews@encamp.com","jenny.vance@encamp.com","kyley.crews@encamp.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K933NRBVK8ETEM23MNKZWKSC","organizer_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Aligned on homepage and platform copy timeline; homepage draft targeted for internal approval this week.","Jenny proposed Kylie take one full offline day to complete platform section draft efficiently.","Tristan to deliver homepage in Figma prior to build; design approval triggers development start.","Confirmed ebook design pricing at $1500 each; Kylie finalizing copy for delivery this week.","Team plans weekly Friday check‑ins to track content and design progress through November 25 milestone."],"highlights":[{"quote":"My hope is if we can give you a day, a week where we leave you alone... it would be way more effective.","speaker":"Jenny Vance"},{"quote":"Once we get a thumbs up on the Figma, we can go ahead and start to build the homepage.","speaker":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"quote":"People are asking when they can start using things... I think they''re excited about the design change.","speaker":"Jenny Vance"}],"topics":["delivery","content","design","timeline"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T23:11:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Development and Copywriting Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to prioritize finalizing the **homepage** and **platform pages** by the end of this month to align content development with design and build schedules (05:18).  \n- **Kyley Crews** emphasized starting with the homepage to establish alignment before moving through the sitemap sequentially, focusing on platform content first as it’s the most urgent.  \n- **Jenny Vance** proposed dedicating a full day offline for Kyley to concentrate on platform content next week, minimizing distractions from Slack and other communications, to speed the drafting process.  \n- The strategy involves iterative internal reviews and just-in-time content delivery to keep momentum while allowing flexibility for refinement.  \n- This focused content sprint approach aims to deliver platform pages as a batch, enabling smooth transition into solution and industry pages by targeting completion around the **25th of the month**.\n\nThe team plans to leverage AI tools like **Twain** for customizing industry pages based on a single well-written template, reducing workload for repetitive content while maintaining tone consistency (08:54).  \n- This reuse strategy was suggested to mitigate the daunting volume of industry-specific pages and speed up production.  \n- Collaboration with the KG team will help integrate AI prompts for effective content generation, streamlining writing and editing efforts.  \n- This approach supports scalability and faster delivery without compromising content quality or voice.\n\n## **Design and User Experience Planning**\n\nThe group confirmed a process to pair wireframes with corresponding copy drafts to ensure design and content flow naturally together before development begins (02:01).  \n- Each sitemap page includes low-fidelity wireframe blocks with guidelines on content length, purpose, and visual elements to inform copywriting.  \n- The plan is to receive a **Figma design mockup** of the homepage after copy approval, providing a visual checkpoint before building starts (17:01).  \n- This step will allow stakeholders to review integrated copy and design, ensuring components like navigation and footer are reusable across pages.  \n- Early parallel development of reusable components will accelerate build timelines once content is finalized.\n\nThe team is working on sourcing authentic, branded photography to enhance the site’s visual appeal and reflect company culture (18:05).  \n- A photo contest yielded a large volume of employee-submitted pictures, supplemented by professional headshots and nature shots to reinforce the brand’s natural, human feel.  \n- **Jenny Vance** highlighted the need for explicit permission when using images featuring faces, maintaining legal and ethical standards.  \n- Organic, candid images such as the “Power Rangers” team group shot are prioritized for their genuine cultural resonance.  \n- These assets will be curated and edited to balance quality with authenticity, supporting the site’s storytelling approach.\n\n## **Project Timelines and Collaboration Cadence**\n\nThe team agreed to weekly check-ins on **Fridays at 12:30 PM**, starting the **14th**, to monitor progress and adjust plans as needed (29:55).  \n- Kyley’s morning schedule is busy, so Friday afternoons were chosen for consistent, manageable status updates.  \n- Deliverables such as the homepage copy draft are expected this week, with design feedback and iteration scheduled for early next week (29:20).  \n- The cadence supports rapid turnaround while accommodating individual workloads and external dependencies.\n\nCollaboration will include close coordination with internal experts like **Jenny B.** for technical platform details and **Brianna** for design elements such as screen grab styles (11:15, 13:39).  \n- Jenny B. is tasked to provide high-level bullet points for the platform features by early next week to inform content creation.  \n- Brianna is handling decisions on visual presentation preferences (e.g., monitor displays vs. isolated images) to balance aesthetics and usability.  \n- This cross-functional cooperation is designed to reduce bottlenecks and ensure content accuracy and design consistency.\n\n## **Scope and Budget Alignment on Design Assets**\n\nThe team clarified the budget and scope for redesigning key resources like **Tier 2 guide** and **Brickwork guide**, agreeing on a design cost of approximately **$3,500** for both combined, not per guide, which is roughly half of earlier misestimated figures (23:38).  \n- This budget includes adapting existing content into new designs rather than full rewrites, optimizing cost-efficiency.  \n- The guides will be designed primarily in **InDesign**, with options to create **Canva templates** for internal reuse and easy updates by marketing teams (26:25).  \n- Designing reusable templates for documents, landing pages, and social media posts is under consideration to support ongoing content needs.  \n- The team also discussed the possibility of engaging external designers billed at **$90 per hour**, providing flexibility for additional workload without doubling internal costs.\n\nNon-website assets such as offsite **ebooks, videos, and checklists** fall outside the current scope for redesign but may be revisited later based on business priorities (21:26).  \n- Case study pages and blog posts will be reformatted within the new website design template, ensuring brand consistency while keeping content intact.  \n- Decisions on how to handle existing video content and resource-heavy items will be made in future planning discussions.  \n- This delineation helps manage workload and budget by focusing immediate efforts on core website content and design.\n\n## **Strategic Vision and Market Positioning**\n\nThe team presented the website redesign as a subtle but important update aimed at better reflecting the company’s brand soul and improving user engagement without a major PR push (15:05).  \n- **Jenny Vance** shared that leadership and stakeholders responded positively to early design concepts, showing excitement about the refreshed look and feel.  \n- The target launch date is set for **December 15th**, with a fallback to year-end if needed, balancing quality with timely delivery.  \n- This update addresses current issues where content and design lack alignment, especially on product and solution pages, improving clarity and brand cohesion.  \n- The goal is to increase meaningful visitor engagement rather than focusing on volume or broad marketing blitzes.\n\nThe redesign supports longer-term business goals by creating a scalable framework for content and design that can adapt as new products and solutions evolve (16:39).  \n- The integration of AI-assisted content generation and reusable design templates is part of a strategic push to improve efficiency and maintain brand voice.  \n- The approach also anticipates future needs for modular content updates, enabling faster response to market changes or customer feedback.  \n- This positions the company competitively by enhancing digital presence without overextending resources.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Enhancements**\n\nThe team emphasized process discipline around “heads down” days for content creation to maximize efficiency and minimize context switching (12:20).  \n- Jenny recommended strict offline periods with Slack and email turned off, allowing focused work punctuated by brief check-ins as needed.  \n- This method showed prior success in accelerating draft completion and is planned to continue for upcoming platform content sprints.  \n- The approach reflects a shift toward more deliberate work cycles to improve quality and speed, reducing iterative back-and-forth delays.\n\nQuality assurance will include early internal reviews with technical experts to validate content accuracy before wider circulation (25:20).  \n- Kyley is coordinating with technical team members, including one in Japan with a different timezone, to finalize copy this week.  \n- This early vetting minimizes rework during design and development phases, keeping the project on track.  \n- The team also plans to use shared Google Docs with embedded notes to streamline collaboration and feedback incorporation.\n\nThe workflow from content to design to build will be tightly integrated, with each major section receiving a design iteration before moving to development (29:20).  \n- This phased handoff allows for clear approvals and reduces risks of misalignment between content and visual design.  \n- Developers will start building reusable components like navigation and footers based on early design approvals, enabling parallel progress.  \n- This operational setup aims to shorten overall project timelines while maintaining high quality and cross-team visibility.","outline":null,"keywords":["sitemap","copywriting","design workflow","Figma","platform features","content development"],"overview":"- **Content Development Priority:** Finalize homepage and platform pages by end of month to align with design schedules.  \n- **AI Tools Adoption:** Utilize AI tools like Twain to streamline industry page creation, reducing repetitive workload while maintaining tone.  \n- **Weekly Check-ins:** Establish Friday check-ins starting on the 14th to monitor status and adjust plans efficiently.  \n- **Budget Clarity:** Confirmed design cost of $3,500 for Tier 2 and Brickwork guides, optimizing redesign efforts without full rewrites.  \n- **Launch Target:** Website redesign targeted for December 15th, aiming to enhance brand presence and user engagement.  \n- **Process Discipline:** Emphasize focused work periods to improve content creation efficiency and minimize distractions.","action_items":"\n**Kyley Crews**\nDraft homepage content and platform section copy, aiming for completion within the month; share Google Docs draft with notes and input for review (10:44)\nCoordinate with Jenny B. to obtain high-level feature bullets for platform pages by early next week to support detailed copywriting (11:40)\nFinalize the copy review with the technical team, including feedback from an expert in Japan, and send to Tristan for design handoff this week (25:10)\n\n**Jenny Vance**\nDiscuss with Jenny B. to secure platform feature bullet points to assist Kyley’s copy development and confirm photography approach for screen grabs (11:37)\nProvide access to the photo contest folder for marketing use, and manage permissions for photos featuring team members (18:20)\nProduce a statement of work draft for the ebook design project focused on Tier 2 and Brickwork guides and coordinate budget discussions accordingly (29:00)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nShare Figma designs of homepage for review prior to launching development and deliver reusable visual components for build commencement (17:10)\nDraft the statement of work for the ebook redesign project reflecting agreed budgets and scope and provide to Jenny for approval (25:40)\nSchedule and conduct weekly Friday check-ins starting December 14th at 12:30 PM for progress updates and feedback (29:40)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"129f4195-6fdd-4b88-96dd-bb360cecf568","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
