    '{"id":"01K8X8X8T9QJAT3MKRNG0ZF3ZQ","title":"PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Campaigns and Lead Generation**\n\nThe team is advancing targeted campaigns to increase qualified leads through webinars, LinkedIn outreach, and optimized landing pages.  \n\n- **Podcast episodes featuring Jameson and Tom are live on Spotify, Apple, and YouTube** to support brand awareness and engagement (08:00)  \n    - The team is building a flexible ad and landing page framework to quickly adjust webinar promotions based on lead volume.  \n    - Josh Reinhard emphasized maintaining a **biweekly webinar cadence** unless no attendees join, ensuring consistent lead flow.  \n    - Sam Lieberman highlighted the need for a streamlined landing page form integrated with GoToWebinar to reduce barriers for registrants and ease updates.  \n    - Colin Costigan committed to improving form design and spacing issues, noting HubSpot’s template code affects editing flexibility.  \n\n- **LinkedIn outreach uses an automated process that sends connection requests and notifies sales when accepted without immediate messaging** (15:20)  \n    - Josh Reinhard and Sam Lieberman confirmed accepted connections do not receive emails unless there is ongoing conversation.  \n    - They agreed to use a shared Slack channel to notify when prospects respond, so those leads can be manually removed from email campaigns to avoid overlap.  \n    - Colin Costigan plans to automate removal from email cadence only after actual responses, preserving email contact if prospects do not engage further.  \n    - They discussed the lack of native integration for LinkedIn conversations in HubSpot, and Colin committed to building an API to sync HeyReach activity with HubSpot for better lead tracking and follow-up visibility.  \n\n- **Lead gen ads targeting HR professionals are showing promising results with cost per lead 22% below industry benchmarks, despite high competition and expense in this audience segment** (29:12)  \n    - Programmatic display ads delivered **23 clicks last week at $9 per click**, slightly down but still contributing to brand awareness.  \n    - Josh Reinhard shared progress with a large multi-location client, emphasizing the value of financial services engagements as tougher but high impact.  \n    - Colin noted the importance of expanding audiences carefully to maintain cost efficiency while increasing reach.  \n\n## **Website Content and User Experience Updates**\n\nThe team is prioritizing a comprehensive website overhaul focused on clarity, education, and lead conversion across key pages.  \n\n- **A project plan is in place to update core pages including homepage, pricing, industry-specific pages, HR leader persona, and employee portals** to improve SEO, content clarity, and user experience (21:50)  \n    - Content will emphasize features like no setup cost, pay-for-active-users pricing, and seamless integrations to reduce friction and highlight value.  \n    - Colin Costigan will draft initial copy for review by Sam Lieberman and Josh Reinhard, integrating industry insights and personas from the benchmark report.  \n    - The employee page will reduce demo form usage by providing relevant information directly, helping existing clients onboard more easily.  \n    - Josh raised concerns about engineering needs and historic reasons why these updates hadn’t been made earlier, prompting a review of technical feasibility.  \n\n- **Improvements will include adding testimonials, demo videos, and cross-linking to increase engagement and lower bounce rates** (24:00)  \n    - Colin plans to add detailed integration lists and clarify which third-party tools are supported, working with the team to confirm accuracy.  \n    - Josh advised caution about naming integrations like Workday due to lack of formal partnership agreements, suggesting a risk-tolerant approach pending legal input from Rob Whalen.  \n    - The team agreed to proceed with listing integrations until told otherwise, balancing marketing impact with potential legal risks.  \n\n## **Sales and CRM Process Enhancements**\n\nThe meeting surfaced key improvements for tracking sales activity and lead data management to align outreach efforts and measure results.  \n\n- **HubSpot contact lists for active customers need review and cleanup before the upcoming November email campaigns** to ensure accurate targeting and avoid gaps (13:00)  \n    - Josh Reinhard requested Steve begin creating and verifying lists, as Daniela’s absence has left uncertainty around current tagging and contact associations.  \n    - Sam offered to pull associated contacts first, then hand off to Steve for refinement, highlighting the urgency given campaign timelines.  \n    - The first email is planned for the week of **November 17th**, timed to avoid conflict with open enrollment and holiday distractions, followed by two more emails spaced every two weeks (12:00).  \n\n- **Sales leadership emphasized the need for transparency on LinkedIn prospect engagement within HubSpot to track follow-up and progress on leads** (31:00)  \n    - Manual notes are currently used to record LinkedIn conversations, but an API integration with HeyReach will automate this and provide real-time visibility into lead status.  \n    - Colin committed to building this integration to improve accountability and coordination between LinkedIn outreach and email nurture campaigns.  \n    - The Slack channel for LinkedIn responses will serve as a real-time alert system for sales directors to act promptly and avoid duplicate outreach.  \n\n- **Points-based billing for website updates will be flexible, allowing the team to “eat ahead” on points to prioritize lead generation over strict allocation concerns** (26:30)  \n    - Colin reassured that contract updates allow flexibility, so the team can focus on impact rather than immediate point exhaustion.  \n    - Josh welcomed this approach, seeing it as necessary to address recent drops in web traffic and form fills.  \n\n## **Operational and Technical Integration Planning**\n\nThe team is aligning on automation, system integration, and process workflows to support scalable marketing and sales execution.  \n\n- **Automation rules will remove prospects from email sequences only after active LinkedIn conversation responses, preserving engagement while avoiding contact overlap** (17:00)  \n    - Colin explained current automation limitations prevent fully automatic removal without human input, so Slack notifications will trigger manual updates.  \n    - Josh and Sam agreed this hybrid approach balances automation benefits with necessary sales judgment.  \n\n- **HeyReach and HubSpot will be integrated using an API/webhook to sync LinkedIn activities directly into CRM records** for more accurate tracking and faster follow-up (20:00)  \n    - Colin will manage API creation and coordinate with Sam and Josh to test and optimize data flows.  \n    - This integration aims to eliminate manual note-taking and improve visibility of warm leads across platforms.  \n\n- **HubSpot landing page templates and forms require technical review and redesign to fix spacing, text formatting, and editing constraints caused by back-end code** (10:30)  \n    - Colin identified HubSpot’s Hubble coding and style sheets as factors limiting text edits, committing to investigate and improve template flexibility.  \n    - This will enable faster updates and better UX for promotional pages tied to webinars and demos.  \n\n- **The team discussed careful handling of integrations listed on the website to avoid legal issues due to lack of formal partnerships** (24:30)  \n    - Josh recommended involving Rob Whalen before finalizing integration lists to manage risk.  \n    - The group agreed to proceed with displaying integrations cautiously and ready to remove if challenged.  \n\n## **Client and Team Coordination**\n\nImproved communication and role clarity are emphasized to ensure smooth campaign execution and client engagement.  \n\n- **Josh Reinhard will invite Dan into the LinkedIn Slack notification channel to ensure all sales directors have visibility on inbound leads** (14:30)  \n    - This will help coordinate outreach efforts and avoid missed responses or duplicated contacts.  \n\n- **Sam Lieberman and Josh Reinhard stressed the importance of tracking and verifying follow-up activity on leads generated via LinkedIn and other channels** (31:00)  \n    - The API integration with HeyReach will support this by logging conversations and responses in HubSpot automatically.  \n    - Manual oversight remains important until the integration is fully operational.  \n\n- **Nina was introduced as a new team member supporting Colin on PTO Exchange projects and will join future calls** to enhance collaboration and oversight (04:20).  \n\n- **Colin will share screenshots and updates regarding specific lead responses, such as Banner Health directing outreach to corporate contacts, ensuring sales follow-ups are appropriately routed** (31:30).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn ABM","HubSpot integration","webinar campaigns","website content strategy","lead generation","PTO Exchange"],"overview":"- **Targeted Campaigns:** Focus on webinars and LinkedIn for increasing qualified leads; biweekly webinars maintained unless no attendees join.  \n- **Lead Generation Ads:** Ads for HR professionals show cost per lead 22% below benchmarks; recent programmatic ads had 23 clicks at $9 each.  \n- **Website Overhaul:** Comprehensive updates planned for core pages to improve SEO, clarity, and lead conversion, emphasizing value features.  \n- **Sales Engagement Tracking:** HubSpot contact lists need review before November campaigns; first email sent week of November 17th.  \n- **System Integration:** API is being developed to sync LinkedIn data with HubSpot for better lead tracking and visibility.  \n- **Client Coordination:** New team member Nina will support projects; Josh to invite Dan for enhanced oversight on leads.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nAdd Nina Belina to future calls and coordinate her onboarding (04:23)\nDuplicate existing landing page template for quick webinar campaign updates; improve form design and integration with GoToWebinar (09:41)\nCreate API key and build HubSpot integration to sync LinkedIn conversations and lead data from HeyReach (20:01)\nDevelop website content documents for homepage, pricing, industries, HR, employee pages for review by PTO Exchange (21:00)\nAdd points tracking column to project plans and manage scope within contract constraints (26:08)\nShare links and screenshots of LinkedIn leads and responses, including Banner Health communication, with Josh and Sam (30:38)\n\n**Sam Lieberman**\nProvide feedback on landing page forms and copy improvements, focusing on form shortening and user experience (09:41)\nPull list of active customer contacts associated with deals in HubSpot and provide to Steve for validation and refinement (13:38)\nWork with Colin on defining integration partners authorized for website mentions, consulting legal experts like Rob Whalen (24:17)\nMonitor HubSpot entries for LinkedIn lead follow-ups and ensure sales director activity is documented (31:53)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nInvite Dan to LinkedIn outreach Slack channel for real-time notifications and coordination (14:33)\nCoordinate with Steve to confirm HubSpot contact tagging accuracy and clarify lists for campaign emails (13:10)\nSupport sending survey emails according to agreed schedule starting week of Nov 17, avoiding Thanksgiving (12:09)\nEnsure sales directors are logging LinkedIn lead follow-up activity into HubSpot manually if necessary (31:53)\n\n**Steve**\nPrepare and validate HubSpot contact list of active customers linked to deals for campaign targeting (13:38)\n"},"duration":32.310001373291016,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"id":2,"name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":182.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, it.","index":1,"end_time":204.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Sam.","index":2,"end_time":254.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":3,"end_time":256.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.1,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":4,"end_time":258.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about you guys?","index":5,"end_time":259.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doing good.","index":6,"end_time":261.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":7,"end_time":262.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":8,"end_time":264.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":266.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to introduce Nina.","index":10,"end_time":267.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":266.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know I mentioned her on our last call, but she joined the team.","index":11,"end_time":272.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":267.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s been working in the background with me on a lot of things.","index":12,"end_time":274.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":272.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"PTO exchange.","index":13,"end_time":275.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so she''ll be joining our calls also moving forward.","index":14,"end_time":277.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice to meet you as well.","index":15,"end_time":282.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.02,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":16,"end_time":284.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was a little worried when you guys joined.","index":17,"end_time":286.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":284.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You didn''t sound super excited, so I.","index":18,"end_time":287.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was wondering if anything was going on.","index":19,"end_time":288.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":287.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got some outside of work stuff I''m dealing with, unfortunately.","index":20,"end_time":295.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":290.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, I''m sorry to hear that.","index":21,"end_time":297.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":296.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":22,"end_time":298.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if there''s always anything, I can see you, Colin.","index":23,"end_time":302.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":299.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Great.","index":24,"end_time":303.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":25,"end_time":304.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":303.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":304.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":304.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably just to rub it in my face that Washington sucks.","index":27,"end_time":307.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":304.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, I wouldn''t do that.","index":28,"end_time":310,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":307.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just saw a metric we.","index":29,"end_time":312.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":310.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We spent $69 million this year on injured players.","index":30,"end_time":316.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":312.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s not good.","index":31,"end_time":319.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s a Josh Harris team for you.","index":32,"end_time":322.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.24,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"They love a big contract for a bad player or an injured player.","index":33,"end_time":329.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, Dan Snyder days.","index":34,"end_time":332.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":330.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It is better than Dan Snyder.","index":35,"end_time":334.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":333.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I will say is I think we got.","index":36,"end_time":337.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":334.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our defense was not good last year either, and I think we got lucky.","index":37,"end_time":340.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":337.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then they were like, yeah, let''s just keep signing older players that may need to come out of retirement.","index":38,"end_time":347.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":340.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was the old Dan Snyder move, though.","index":39,"end_time":350.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":347.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let''s get.","index":40,"end_time":351.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s get lavar Arrington.","index":41,"end_time":353.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let''s get.","index":42,"end_time":354.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s true.","index":43,"end_time":354.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":354.01,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The Sixers have been.","index":44,"end_time":356.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Had a decent start, though.","index":45,"end_time":358.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.13,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Turning my tune on Josh Harris.","index":46,"end_time":360.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.65,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Now he''s focusing his efforts on the.","index":47,"end_time":365.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":363.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"On the skin, on the Commanders.","index":48,"end_time":367.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":365.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yes.","index":49,"end_time":368.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He took his eye off the Sixers and.","index":50,"end_time":370.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And now they''re good.","index":51,"end_time":371.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":371.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just need him to buy another team.","index":53,"end_time":374.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":373.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":54,"end_time":376.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.81,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"3.","index":55,"end_time":376.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.41,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":56,"end_time":377.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t even know if he can buy.","index":57,"end_time":378.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.17,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"What''s he got?","index":58,"end_time":378.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He''s got a baseball team.","index":59,"end_time":380.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":378.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think he''s got my baseball team.","index":60,"end_time":381.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":380.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, he''s got the Devils, the Commanders and the Sixers.","index":61,"end_time":384.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.57,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, you got to get like the.","index":62,"end_time":386.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like the Orioles.","index":63,"end_time":388.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because he likes.","index":64,"end_time":389.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"He doesn''t like to be in the same market, but he likes to be close enough that it pisses the fans off.","index":65,"end_time":393.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I think there''s a certain.","index":66,"end_time":396.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.2,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think there''s a rule you can''t be in the same city, but I. I think it depends on the league.","index":67,"end_time":401.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.04,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":68,"end_time":402.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t know how it works, but.","index":69,"end_time":404.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.24,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, he''s.","index":70,"end_time":405.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.56,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He loves the.","index":71,"end_time":405.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.16,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The Eastern Seaboard sports franchises.","index":72,"end_time":408.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.8,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, that Mid Atlantic.","index":73,"end_time":409.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep, exactly.","index":74,"end_time":411.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He''s probably gotta recoup Some.","index":75,"end_time":413.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":411.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, he spent $6 billion.","index":76,"end_time":415.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":413.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if you guys.","index":77,"end_time":419.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He spent.","index":78,"end_time":420.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It ended up being 6.05 billion.","index":79,"end_time":422.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":420.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And he said the last point zero five was the most painful.","index":80,"end_time":425.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":422.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Didn''t Dan Snyder buy it for like under a billion dollars or something?","index":81,"end_time":430.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.04,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, oh yeah, it was like a.","index":82,"end_time":432.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He made out like a bandit on that sale.","index":83,"end_time":436,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.76,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"100 and he lives in.","index":84,"end_time":437.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":436.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He used to not live very far.","index":85,"end_time":440.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":438.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He lived in Bethesda, but.","index":86,"end_time":442.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":440.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that''s a nice area.","index":87,"end_time":444.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He moved to London.","index":88,"end_time":445.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":444.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get as far away as possible.","index":89,"end_time":448.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":447.1,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think everyone hated him.","index":90,"end_time":450.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":448.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had friends that lived in his neighborhood and they were like, apparently he was a real piece of work.","index":91,"end_time":455.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":450.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like if you were coming by to do work on his house, you couldn''t park in his driveway because he would sue your company if like oil or something leaked out of your car.","index":92,"end_time":464.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":456.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s not good.","index":93,"end_time":466.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Dan Snyder.","index":94,"end_time":468.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":95,"end_time":469.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let''s dive into this.","index":96,"end_time":470.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":469.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a lot of exciting things to go through.","index":97,"end_time":473.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":471.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for just some other project updates, obviously we have the podcast episode Live with Jameson and Tom, both on Spotify and Apple as well as YouTube.","index":98,"end_time":484.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":475.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we are building a framework so that we can quickly spin up ads and just tweaks to the landing page for the webinars that you guys are hosting so that we can create, you know, consistent amount of people coming to those.","index":99,"end_time":497.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":485.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys are evaluating right now whether two weeks is the right pace or maybe a month.","index":100,"end_time":502.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":497.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think leads will probably be the.","index":101,"end_time":504.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":503.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Biggest driver of that.","index":102,"end_time":506.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know how many people are willing.","index":103,"end_time":507.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":506.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To join the call.","index":104,"end_time":508.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":105,"end_time":508.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":508.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s like, we talked about this yesterday.","index":106,"end_time":510.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":508.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re basically like for the time being, if anybody joins, we''re going to keep doing them every two weeks.","index":107,"end_time":516.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If we run into a week where nobody joins, then then maybe we''ll.","index":108,"end_time":521.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":516.959,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''ll re evaluate.","index":109,"end_time":522.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":521.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But even one person showing up is like, that''s great.","index":110,"end_time":526.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":522.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s basically a demo.","index":111,"end_time":527.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":526.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, exactly.","index":112,"end_time":528.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":527.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s like someone setting up a meeting with us.","index":113,"end_time":530.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":114,"end_time":531.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And yeah, Colin, we have a landing page, you know, already made if you want to take some copy or inspiration from that.","index":115,"end_time":540.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.09,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I guess the only thing for us is like that form that''s attached to the landing page is like integrated with, with GoToWebinar.","index":116,"end_time":551.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.53,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So it''s easy for us to just update to the.","index":117,"end_time":554.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The next scheduled landing page.","index":118,"end_time":557.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.79,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And like I just changed the date or whatever.","index":119,"end_time":559.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.07,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So it just needs to be easy to update because like right after the webinar I just update with the next date so that we can like, we use the same link over and over, like, it''s just the same page.","index":120,"end_time":571.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.19,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I just update the go.","index":121,"end_time":572.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.27,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So that way the sales directors, like, I''m not sending them new links every time.","index":122,"end_time":576.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.95,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, they''re just using the same landing page over and over again to.","index":123,"end_time":579.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.83,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"To send it out.","index":124,"end_time":581.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":125,"end_time":583.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the one we''re going to create a duplicate of.","index":126,"end_time":585.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":583.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":587.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.06,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And.","index":128,"end_time":587.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.5,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, and if you.","index":129,"end_time":588.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.82,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But if you want to, like, give us some feedback on, like, the.","index":130,"end_time":593.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.82,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The form.","index":131,"end_time":594.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.74,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You know, we were talking about maybe making some of the forms a little bit shorter just so that we get, you know, less lower the barrier to entry for people to register and stuff.","index":132,"end_time":606.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":595.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You know, there''s like, a few things that we.","index":133,"end_time":609.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We want.","index":134,"end_time":610.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.86,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We definitely want to ask, but.","index":135,"end_time":612.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.34,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, like, I think we can probably improve upon this form.","index":136,"end_time":617.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think.","index":137,"end_time":618.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":617.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Phone number.","index":138,"end_time":618.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.38,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":139,"end_time":620.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":619.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Phone number.","index":140,"end_time":620.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":620.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":141,"end_time":623.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":623.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just, like, spacing and just having more of a design tied to this and everything like that too.","index":142,"end_time":628.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":623.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''d like a more.","index":143,"end_time":630.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":628.7,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"A better design.","index":144,"end_time":631.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And I don''t know if you guys can take a look at this or let us know with the new template or whatever.","index":145,"end_time":638.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The spacing in all of our landing pages is, like, very weird in that you''re talking about this, the.","index":146,"end_time":647.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.67,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Well, that.","index":147,"end_time":648.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.51,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That at the top, but also in the text that we do, like, depending on whether it''s like a paragraph text or like a heading text, like, I can''t get it to just, like, enter one line and BeSpace.","index":148,"end_time":664.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.11,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, it''s too big, then it''s too small.","index":149,"end_time":665.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.09,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And HubSpot, you know, has some editing features on the text, but it''s, like, not that great.","index":150,"end_time":670.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.69,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Also, there''s, like, back end code on the templates that I think affects the.","index":151,"end_time":675.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.61,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The HubSpot editor, too.","index":152,"end_time":677.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.57,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So, like, it is difficult to manage the text on our.","index":153,"end_time":681.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"On our landing pages.","index":154,"end_time":682.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":155,"end_time":683.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":683.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m sure, you know, like, HubSpot''s got their own coding language called Hubble, and there''s probably, like, a style sheet or something that''s attached to the template code.","index":156,"end_time":693.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":683.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll definitely take a look at that.","index":157,"end_time":694.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":158,"end_time":696.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.37,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":159,"end_time":699.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Josh, I wanted to ask if you''ve had a chance to review since we''ve updated the pagination on this.","index":160,"end_time":704.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":699.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Survey.","index":161,"end_time":704.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did last week, I thought everything looked great.","index":162,"end_time":712.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":163,"end_time":713.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so November 15th is when we''re shooting, or, you know, not the 15th.","index":164,"end_time":718.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":713.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''ll be a Saturday.","index":165,"end_time":719.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":718.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So next week would be the first.","index":166,"end_time":724.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":723.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Time we would send this out.","index":167,"end_time":725.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can we do it the week of the 17th instead?","index":168,"end_time":729.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, this would be coming out of.","index":169,"end_time":731.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":729.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Out of your HubSpot to active customers.","index":170,"end_time":733.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":731.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So whenever you guys want to send.","index":171,"end_time":735.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":733.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That email, I think the week of the 17th gets.","index":172,"end_time":739.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":735.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s a lot of people that are in open enrollment right now.","index":173,"end_time":741.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think the closer we get to Thanksgiving without it being the week of Thanksgiving gives people a little bit more opportunity to actually respond.","index":174,"end_time":750.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":175,"end_time":752.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":751.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":176,"end_time":752.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":752.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we.","index":177,"end_time":752.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":752.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to do another one the week after Thanksgiving and then one kind.","index":178,"end_time":758.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":752.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of before the holiday break in December.","index":179,"end_time":760.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, if we do it the week of the 17th, the week of the 1st, and then like the week of the 15th.","index":180,"end_time":766.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Spread them out every other week.","index":181,"end_time":768.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":766.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":769.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Perfect.","index":183,"end_time":771.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":184,"end_time":772.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so, Sam, we just have to figure out what.","index":185,"end_time":779.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What list are we pulling from, like, from HubSpot for our active customers to get it sent to?","index":186,"end_time":783.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":779.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we probably want Steve to start creating that.","index":187,"end_time":788.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":188,"end_time":791.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.84,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Are the.","index":189,"end_time":791.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.2,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":190,"end_time":793.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.16,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, are the deals in HubSpot all tagged with the appropriate contacts or.","index":191,"end_time":797.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.52,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"No?","index":192,"end_time":797.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.68,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":193,"end_time":800.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":799.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s a question for Steve.","index":194,"end_time":802.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":800.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That was something I think I thought Daniela was doing.","index":195,"end_time":804.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but I guess we don''t really know at this point.","index":196,"end_time":810.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":808.2,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I mean, she''s been gone for a while, right.","index":197,"end_time":813.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Then if not, then Steve has, you know, a week and a half.","index":198,"end_time":818.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":814.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well.","index":199,"end_time":818.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.19,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Well, I can.","index":200,"end_time":819.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.67,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I can pull a list of all the associated contacts with, like, active customers deals and then give that to Steve and.","index":201,"end_time":829.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.39,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And he.","index":202,"end_time":829.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.03,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He can go through it and, you know, if he needs to add some, he can add some or.","index":203,"end_time":834.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.59,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Or subtract some.","index":204,"end_time":835.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.39,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":836.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, that''s probably a conversation we should have internally, but if we don''t have a list of our clients and who''s the appropriate contacts, we got a big.","index":206,"end_time":846.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":837.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We got bigger issues.","index":207,"end_time":847.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, let''s talk to Steve.","index":208,"end_time":850.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":209,"end_time":851.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys, the new campaign is live.","index":210,"end_time":855.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":853.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":211,"end_time":857.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.7,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We got another submission the other day.","index":212,"end_time":859.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":857.1,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":213,"end_time":860.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The LinkedIn ads and everything are being set up and launched today as well.","index":214,"end_time":865.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":861.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Josh, obviously, I added you into that channel for the notifications.","index":215,"end_time":871.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":865.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can add Dan.","index":216,"end_time":872.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":871.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":217,"end_time":873.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":873.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Have you seen some of the messages coming through already?","index":218,"end_time":876.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":874.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I saw the one that came through from Dan last night.","index":219,"end_time":881.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":877.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":883.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then one came through.","index":221,"end_time":884.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":883.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, one came through two hours ago.","index":222,"end_time":887.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":885.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":223,"end_time":888.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":887.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So.","index":224,"end_time":889.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":888.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So where are we at right now?","index":225,"end_time":890.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Are they getting.","index":226,"end_time":890.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":890.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Are they still getting the automated messaging for now or.","index":227,"end_time":896.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No.","index":228,"end_time":896.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":896.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, yeah, that''s the message I have above that last one.","index":229,"end_time":898.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":896.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s still a few, like, lingering from the old campaign, but the way that this new one is set up is it runs a ch.","index":230,"end_time":904.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":898.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually, we have it right here on the slide.","index":231,"end_time":906.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":905.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It runs a check of.","index":232,"end_time":907.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":906.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you already connected with them?","index":233,"end_time":909.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":907.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If so, we send like a.","index":234,"end_time":912.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":910.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, we just created a benchmark report.","index":235,"end_time":914.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":912.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me know if you want to check it out.","index":236,"end_time":915.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":914.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we couldn''t get the notification to send a Slack because they''re already connected with you.","index":237,"end_time":919.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":916.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if they aren''t a connection already, we just send.","index":238,"end_time":923.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":921.009,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We view their profile and send a connection request.","index":239,"end_time":925.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":923.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as soon as they accept it, you get notified in Slack they get no messages automatically.","index":240,"end_time":929.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":925.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My question is that happening right now?","index":241,"end_time":939.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":936.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yes.","index":242,"end_time":939.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the.","index":243,"end_time":940.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Those two that came through into that Slack channel have not gotten any messaging from.","index":244,"end_time":945.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Hey, Reach.","index":245,"end_time":947.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, they should not have.","index":246,"end_time":949.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can check on Sarah.","index":247,"end_time":950.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had another one of Dan''s messages actually pulled up.","index":248,"end_time":952.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now.","index":249,"end_time":959.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":959.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sarah did not receive a message.","index":250,"end_time":961.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":959.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that was the latest one that.","index":251,"end_time":966.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":965.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Came in as connection request accepted.","index":252,"end_time":968.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":966.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":253,"end_time":973.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.03,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I guess the larger conversation we want to have about with these LinkedIn messages and the ABM campaigns and everything that you guys are doing.","index":254,"end_time":984.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.71,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So we''re trying to figure out a little bit more about like our process and making sure that we''re tracking activity in HubSpot and getting everything marked down as, you know, MQL, SQL, things like that.","index":255,"end_time":998.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":985.1,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So when there''s a LinkedIn connection request and it''s accepted, are they still getting emails from us as well?","index":256,"end_time":1011.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":999.26,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"They would be.","index":257,"end_time":1013.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1012.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can automate basically taking them out.","index":258,"end_time":1016.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1013.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of the email cadence.","index":259,"end_time":1017.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1016.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But today they still get the email cadence even.","index":260,"end_time":1021.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.08,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, as of right now.","index":261,"end_time":1022.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1021.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":262,"end_time":1023.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":1023.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.08,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay.","index":264,"end_time":1024.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.56,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So can we use the same channel, the same mid PTO exchange ABM that like if Dan or I or whenever we hire another sales director is engaging with them on LinkedIn and now they''ve like responded to us and they''re going that we can just send an email to that Slack channel to remove them from the, the email campaign so that they''re not like talking to us over here and then getting an email over there.","index":265,"end_time":1057.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1024.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That would just seem disjointed.","index":266,"end_time":1058.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Is there.","index":267,"end_time":1059.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":268,"end_time":1059.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":269,"end_time":1060.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or is there a better way to do it than that?","index":270,"end_time":1062.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1060.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we could do it automatically where like as soon as a connection request is accepted.","index":271,"end_time":1067.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also have any response notifications coming in.","index":272,"end_time":1071.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1068.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can say if either of.","index":273,"end_time":1074.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1073.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those happen removed from the email campaign.","index":274,"end_time":1076.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we probably only want them removed if there''s a response though.","index":275,"end_time":1081.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1077.94,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like if you send them a message and they don''t respond, we still want email.","index":276,"end_time":1089.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.06,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We.","index":277,"end_time":1090.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1090.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, we still want them to.","index":278,"end_time":1091.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1090.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s the thing.","index":279,"end_time":1092.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1091.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We still want them to be getting the email in that case.","index":280,"end_time":1094.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1092.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But if they''re going back and forth with us, then we want to take them out.","index":281,"end_time":1098.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":282,"end_time":1099.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unfortunately, there''s no automated way we can do that because the automations turn off as soon as like they respond in the conversations.","index":283,"end_time":1105.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I figured.","index":284,"end_time":1107.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1106.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But is.","index":285,"end_time":1108.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1107.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So can we use that Slack channel for that purpose and then it''s just a message to you to.","index":286,"end_time":1113.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":287,"end_time":1116.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":288,"end_time":1118.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.98,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The, the, the other thing that I was curious, is there a way to get the LinkedIn conversation into HubSpot or.","index":289,"end_time":1134.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1121.37,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"No, I think so.","index":290,"end_time":1136.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The, the issue that we''re running into, Colin, is that we''re, we''re leaning a little heavily or more heavily into LinkedIn and like chatting people on LinkedIn, things like that.","index":291,"end_time":1150.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1138.41,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And I can''t see in HubSpot when we get a conversion on LinkedIn or like a message that the sales director is taking any appropriate follow up.","index":292,"end_time":1163.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.49,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Now we were talking about like them just going in and manually like writing a note saying like, hey, following up on LinkedIn, you know, talk to them about this.","index":293,"end_time":1172.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1163.53,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But if there''s a way to automate it so that it''s like, hey, I can see that Dan has a warm lead from LinkedIn.","index":294,"end_time":1180.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1173.29,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He''s following up and then you know, we''re making sure that they''re trying to connect over email or trying to schedule a meeting.","index":295,"end_time":1188.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.08,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like we just need to see that the director is getting the lead and taking the appropriate action to follow up and if it''s doesn''t come over.","index":296,"end_time":1200.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, um, yeah, so I can actually, we can build an API key or just create an API key and connect, hey, reach to HubSpot.","index":297,"end_time":1209.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1201.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other thing is Sam, you also always have access to heyreach.","index":298,"end_time":1214.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1211.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can send you the login if you need it as well.","index":299,"end_time":1216.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1214.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I agree that HubSpot would be cleaner for that.","index":300,"end_time":1219.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1216.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Hub, yeah, HubSpot is typically how we track all that.","index":301,"end_time":1224.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.49,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So yeah, we can.","index":302,"end_time":1225.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1224.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll build this API and connect it.","index":303,"end_time":1227.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1225.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To your HubSpot account.","index":304,"end_time":1228.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1227.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that would be even better.","index":305,"end_time":1231.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1229.79,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And it''ll get automatically updated like when they send new messages and stuff.","index":306,"end_time":1236.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1231.87,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, it''ll be a, it''ll be a web hook.","index":307,"end_time":1238.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1236.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll.","index":308,"end_time":1238.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1238.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Based on triggers, you know, that we identify.","index":309,"end_time":1240.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1238.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll pass that information back and forth.","index":310,"end_time":1243.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1240.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, perfect.","index":311,"end_time":1244.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.63,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s good than we thought, Sam.","index":312,"end_time":1247.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1244.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s way better than we thought.","index":313,"end_time":1249.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.63,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll have to see if there''s.","index":314,"end_time":1250.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.23,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Any limitations in there and maybe we have to do some custom development.","index":315,"end_time":1252.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1250.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, that''s the plan.","index":316,"end_time":1254.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1253.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, just let us know yeah if you need anything from us.","index":317,"end_time":1260.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.75,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Will do the thing that I will need to work with you guys on and we''ll be like writing some starter Page copy, but I''ll need to work with or we''ll need to work with you guys on making sure it''s honed into industries and the HR page and the employees page, things like that.","index":318,"end_time":1275.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1260.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But Sam, like we talked about, we built out a project plan for the pages and their, like, priorities.","index":319,"end_time":1283.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1276.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have the homepage baked in here and some suggestions on what we''d like to do from a content, a design and user experience and SEO perspective.","index":320,"end_time":1292.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1284.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Same with the pricing page, like just emphasizing the no setup cost, paying for active users, easy to integrate.","index":321,"end_time":1301.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1293.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually showing like how the integrations work.","index":322,"end_time":1306.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1303.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Industry pages, so healthcare, financial services, nonprofits, manufacturing, professional services and higher education.","index":323,"end_time":1313.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1308.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I grabbed that from the industries that you guys provided for the benchmark report.","index":324,"end_time":1317.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1314.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty good HR leader Persona page.","index":325,"end_time":1321.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1318.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So explain the benefits in a way that also resonates, that resonates with people who are already signed up with you and maybe just need to educate their team a little bit better or that also have not signed up and are.","index":326,"end_time":1333.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1322.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just doing some research.","index":327,"end_time":1334.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The employee page for employees where their company is already enrolled with BTO Exchange so that they stop filling out the requested demo form.","index":328,"end_time":1342.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1335.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":329,"end_time":1344.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1344.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Now is that going to mess with, like, do we need something from engineering to make that happen, Sam, in what regards?","index":330,"end_time":1352.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1344.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":331,"end_time":1354.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just feel like if it was that easy to have a separate page, why, like, why haven''t we done it before?","index":332,"end_time":1358.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1354.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, we have a separate page now.","index":333,"end_time":1362.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1360.7,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"People don''t go to it.","index":334,"end_time":1363.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1362.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s the only thing.","index":335,"end_time":1364.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.66,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s like we, we can, like when you go to the requested demo, there is a, it''s like a, there''s a link on there that says like client support.","index":336,"end_time":1372.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1364.66,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But yeah, like head to this page for support requests.","index":337,"end_time":1377.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1374.92,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I, I, Are you going to put that in the top menu navigation, Colin?","index":338,"end_time":1381.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.96,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean like a facelift to it and some more information about the.","index":339,"end_time":1387.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1382.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actual tool before just submitting.","index":340,"end_time":1389.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1387.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I''m having issues.","index":341,"end_time":1390.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1389.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only, yeah, the only thing is like that form is specifically set up with automation to notify our like, customer team.","index":342,"end_time":1402.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1391.4,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So you just have to continue using that form.","index":343,"end_time":1404.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1402.26,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can use this form, no problem.","index":344,"end_time":1406.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1404.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we have to build new automation.","index":345,"end_time":1409.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1407.06,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"No, yeah, we can.","index":346,"end_time":1410.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1410.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we can build this form, no problem.","index":347,"end_time":1412.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1410.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or use this form, no problem.","index":348,"end_time":1413.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1412.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just want to add more content.","index":349,"end_time":1415.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1413.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And design to the page.","index":350,"end_time":1416.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1415.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":351,"end_time":1418.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1417.22,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":352,"end_time":1419.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.58,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And then we also talked a lot about like integrations and so I think we need to like spell out more of the integrations that you guys or the tools you guys are able to integrate with.","index":353,"end_time":1429.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1420.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll need to work with you.","index":354,"end_time":1433.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1432.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys to establish what that list is.","index":355,"end_time":1435.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1433.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then upgrading the webinar page like we already talked about, and then just kind of across the site, more links to other pages, showing some videos, demos.","index":356,"end_time":1446.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1437.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Testimonials, and other things to just kind of incorporate and beef up the content across the site.","index":357,"end_time":1451.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1446.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":358,"end_time":1453.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1453.03,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"This all sounds perfect.","index":359,"end_time":1455.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1453.59,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"One thing just to keep in mind, and I don''t want to be, like, putting up roadblocks for stuff, but from the integration perspective, one of the things we have to be just cognizant of, I guess, is like, we.","index":360,"end_time":1473.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1457.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I. I don''t know how much we''re going to be able to use Workday''s name on our website, but we may already do that.","index":361,"end_time":1484.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1473.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But, you know, typically, work day or all of them.","index":362,"end_time":1491.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1486.65,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All of them.","index":363,"end_time":1491.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1491.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m just using that as an example.","index":364,"end_time":1493.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1491.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, okay, you know, we don''t have, like, partnership agreements with anyone except for ukg.","index":365,"end_time":1499.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1493.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, you know, I. I want to get that on there as much as we can.","index":366,"end_time":1504.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1500.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just have to be a little cautious of it or make the decision that we don''t mind having it up there until we get our hand slapped.","index":367,"end_time":1510.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But that''s something that we need to consider when we''re talking about this kind of stuff.","index":368,"end_time":1516.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1511.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How do you feel about it, Josh?","index":369,"end_time":1517.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.29,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I mean, personally, I don''t mind doing it until we get our hand slapped, but I think we probably will get slapped at some point.","index":370,"end_time":1525.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1518.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But that.","index":371,"end_time":1529.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"My.","index":372,"end_time":1529.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1529.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I. I think it''s worth doing it that way, but I.","index":373,"end_time":1533.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1529.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I think there''s probably a conversation we should be, like, looping, you know, some of the other.","index":374,"end_time":1538.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1533.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"More like Rob.","index":375,"end_time":1542.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1541.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like Rob Whalen.","index":376,"end_time":1543.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1542.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Really?","index":377,"end_time":1543.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1543.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":378,"end_time":1544.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1543.92,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Making a decision like this.","index":379,"end_time":1546.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1545.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, well, let''s talk to Rob about it.","index":380,"end_time":1549.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1547.6,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But I.","index":381,"end_time":1549.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1549.36,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Lean to your side, too.","index":382,"end_time":1551.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1550.08,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, until they say take it off.","index":383,"end_time":1553,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1551.44,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, let''s just do it.","index":384,"end_time":1554.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1553,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But let''s see what Rob has to say.","index":385,"end_time":1556.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1554.36,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":386,"end_time":1556.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1556.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":387,"end_time":1556.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1556.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":388,"end_time":1557.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1556.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Cool.","index":389,"end_time":1558.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1557.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think it''s really strong content to have because people might be doing searches of, like, you know, tools that integrate with xyz and you.","index":390,"end_time":1566.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1558.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys want to pop up for those.","index":391,"end_time":1567.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1566.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":392,"end_time":1567.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":393,"end_time":1569.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1568.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I guess.","index":394,"end_time":1571.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1570.97,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":395,"end_time":1572.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.61,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Colin.","index":396,"end_time":1572.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1572.33,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I guess next step on all this stuff, like, what do you need from us?","index":397,"end_time":1577.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1572.89,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You know, do you guys get started and.","index":398,"end_time":1579.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1577.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And we''ll let us know.","index":399,"end_time":1581.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1579.85,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, what.","index":400,"end_time":1581.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"How do we get the ball rolling on this stuff?","index":401,"end_time":1583.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.85,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":402,"end_time":1584.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1584.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to start creating content documents with the copy from our first pass.","index":403,"end_time":1587.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1584.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll.","index":404,"end_time":1588.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1587.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll give that to you guys to review.","index":405,"end_time":1590.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1588.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll get all of this loaded into Pulse, so you can see live view of like, how everything''s funneling through when we need you to review stuff.","index":406,"end_time":1598.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1590.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have placeholder dates in here as well.","index":407,"end_time":1602.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1599.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re always looking to beat those.","index":408,"end_time":1603.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1602.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But did add padding in case there''s.","index":409,"end_time":1605.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1603.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like a lot of back and forth on content.","index":410,"end_time":1607.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How does this work from like a points perspective of our monthly stuff?","index":411,"end_time":1614.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1610.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So because we''re going to attack several pages at once, it''s going to be less than like the 12 points per page.","index":412,"end_time":1622.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1616.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can add in, I can create a column for points, but I know that we just updated our contract as well, so I wouldn''t be worried.","index":413,"end_time":1632.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1624.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"About where points stand right now.","index":414,"end_time":1634.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1632.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, Well, I just didn''t know.","index":415,"end_time":1636.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1634.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I didn''t know if you''re like the way the process works.","index":416,"end_time":1639.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1636.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like you normally, like, you spec it out and then like almost like provide a quote or is it more just.","index":417,"end_time":1644.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1639.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, I mean, so we can eat ahead on points, right?","index":418,"end_time":1648.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1644.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we''re in a contract, we can eat ahead on the, on the points.","index":419,"end_time":1651.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1648.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like I said to you guys, you know, when, when I took over the account from Spencer, main priority was getting leads, not being worried about the.","index":420,"end_time":1660.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1652.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Amount of work that we''re doing.","index":421,"end_time":1661.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think this is, this is all the better.","index":422,"end_time":1664.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1662.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":423,"end_time":1665.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1664.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, not only from the campaigns we''re running, but from, know, Sam basically explaining, like, we''re seeing drops in web traffic, we''re seeing a lot of drops in form fills and we need to.","index":424,"end_time":1675.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1665.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Make some comprehensive updates.","index":425,"end_time":1676.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1675.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":426,"end_time":1677.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we need it.","index":427,"end_time":1678.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1677.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, this is all great stuff.","index":428,"end_time":1680.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is going to be great.","index":429,"end_time":1683.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1680.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So awesome.","index":430,"end_time":1684.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1683.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":431,"end_time":1687.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just from an analytics perspective, last week on the lead gen forums, we saw five opens but no one finished filling it out.","index":432,"end_time":1696.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1687.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have also put in an extended, an expanded audience.","index":433,"end_time":1700.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1696.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that''s in its learning phase right now.","index":434,"end_time":1703.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1700.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, sticking mainly to the HR professionals because that''s where we''ve seen the most traction so far besides Adventist, which was.","index":435,"end_time":1711.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1703.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you for the update, Josh.","index":436,"end_time":1712.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1711.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was all awesome to hear.","index":437,"end_time":1714.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1712.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I heard back.","index":438,"end_time":1716.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1714.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":439,"end_time":1716.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1716.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think I just sent you after I had the first meeting.","index":440,"end_time":1718.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1716.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I heard back from her after she met with her cfo and they want to keep the conversation going and we''re going to schedule more time, so.","index":441,"end_time":1725.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1719.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":442,"end_time":1726.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1726.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, great.","index":443,"end_time":1728.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1726.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s.","index":444,"end_time":1728.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1728.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a big network.","index":445,"end_time":1729.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1728.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":446,"end_time":1730.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1730.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":447,"end_time":1731.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1731.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, they''ve got a lot of locations.","index":448,"end_time":1733.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1731.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think they have 61 just in Maryland.","index":449,"end_time":1734.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1733.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, it''s a great.","index":450,"end_time":1738.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1736.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s.","index":451,"end_time":1739.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1738.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s just like a Perfect.","index":452,"end_time":1740.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1739.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Perfect fit.","index":453,"end_time":1741.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1740.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And getting.","index":454,"end_time":1741.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Getting in with finances typically tougher, but when we do, it''s.","index":455,"end_time":1746.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s a really good.","index":456,"end_time":1747.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1746.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The shorter road.","index":457,"end_time":1748.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1747.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":458,"end_time":1749.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1749.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So really good stuff.","index":459,"end_time":1752.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1751.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":460,"end_time":1753.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1752.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The audience that we''re tapping into with HR professionals is expensive, but we are actually kind of kicking butt and keeping cost per lead at 22% below the industry benchmark.","index":461,"end_time":1762.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1753.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s a great metric to see.","index":462,"end_time":1764.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1763.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We love that.","index":463,"end_time":1767.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1765.77,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And then from the ad roll perspective, which is a programmatic display, again, more brand awareness.","index":464,"end_time":1772.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1768.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are seeing clicks.","index":465,"end_time":1774.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1772.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It did go down slightly.","index":466,"end_time":1776.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1774.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had 23 last week, but at.","index":467,"end_time":1778.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1776.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A cost per click of $9.","index":468,"end_time":1779.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1778.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":469,"end_time":1784.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1782.68,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And that is everything that we had.","index":470,"end_time":1787.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1785.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":471,"end_time":1790.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t have any questions.","index":472,"end_time":1791.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.68,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Excited to start working on some of this website stuff?","index":473,"end_time":1796.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.8,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":474,"end_time":1797.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1797.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like I said, we''ll start putting together some documents with content and share those with you and get pulse updated to reflect this timeline.","index":475,"end_time":1806.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1797.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also established that API between heyreach and HubSpot.","index":476,"end_time":1810.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1806.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And other than that, we''re rocking and rolling.","index":477,"end_time":1813.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1811.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Josh, on your end, if you just want to invite Dan to that channel, I think that would be a good idea.","index":478,"end_time":1819.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1813.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He did get a reply from an old, like, someone just accepted, like an old connection request and they said, like, you need to reach out to someone else on our team.","index":479,"end_time":1832.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1819.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hold on, let me pull this up.","index":480,"end_time":1835.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1834.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That.","index":481,"end_time":1838.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1837.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The most recent one that came into that.","index":482,"end_time":1840.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1838.22,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That channel.","index":483,"end_time":1841.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1840.54,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"No, it wasn''t in that.","index":484,"end_time":1844.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1843.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where was that?","index":485,"end_time":1846.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1845.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just had it pulled up.","index":486,"end_time":1849.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1848.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":487,"end_time":1854.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1853.5,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think our biggest thing with all this LinkedIn stuff is, like, we need to make sure that, like, we''re tracking that Dan and Josh are responding to these people.","index":488,"end_time":1865.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1854.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And if.","index":489,"end_time":1865.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1865.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"If, you know, hey, reach out to XYZ.","index":490,"end_time":1868.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1866.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"They''re doing that.","index":491,"end_time":1869.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1868.85,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And we can see that in HubSpot and if they''re not, we can see that in HubSpot as well.","index":492,"end_time":1874.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1869.85,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Where did that reply go?","index":493,"end_time":1889.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1888.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do need to jump because I got to get onto a client onboarding call of a new client that''s just starting with us.","index":494,"end_time":1899.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1894.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was.","index":495,"end_time":1900.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1899.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll find the message and send you guys a screenshot.","index":496,"end_time":1902.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1900.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was like Banner Health and she said, you need to reach out to Banner Corporate.","index":497,"end_time":1905.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1902.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that went to Dan.","index":498,"end_time":1907.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1905.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I would just say, like, yeah.","index":499,"end_time":1909.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1907.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you let me know who.","index":500,"end_time":1910.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1909.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Who at corporate message?","index":501,"end_time":1913.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1911.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool, Cool.","index":502,"end_time":1915.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1913.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right.","index":503,"end_time":1915.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1915.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you, Colin.","index":504,"end_time":1916.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1915.67,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":505,"end_time":1917.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1916.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, actually, I found it.","index":506,"end_time":1919.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1917.75,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He.","index":507,"end_time":1919.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1919.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He did respond with that.","index":508,"end_time":1920.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1919.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He.","index":509,"end_time":1921.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1920.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He misspelled it, but he.","index":510,"end_time":1922.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1921.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He asked if they had a contact.","index":511,"end_time":1923.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1922.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":512,"end_time":1925.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1924.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, good.","index":513,"end_time":1927.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1926.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See you guys.","index":514,"end_time":1927.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1927.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":515,"end_time":1928.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1927.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":516,"end_time":1929.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1928.51,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Nice to meet you, Nina.","index":517,"end_time":1930.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1929.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, Take care, Nina.","index":518,"end_time":1933.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1931.43,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"See you.","index":519,"end_time":1933.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1933.27,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"}],"dateString":"2025-11-06T18:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,sam@ptoexchange.com,josh@ptoexchange.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","sam@ptoexchange.com","josh@ptoexchange.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K8X8X8T9QJAT3MKRNG0ZF3ZQ","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Launched new ABM LinkedIn campaign; early engagement tracked, Slack channel used for coordination.","Agreed to API integration between Heyreach and HubSpot to automate LinkedIn lead sync.","Set multi-phase website upgrade plan targeting SEO, design, integration visibility, and page UX.","Planned survey email sends for Nov 17, Dec 1, and Dec 15 to optimize open enrollment timing.","Maintaining 22% lower cost-per-lead than industry benchmark on HR professional ad targeting."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We are actually kind of kicking butt and keeping cost per lead at 22% below the industry benchmark.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"This is all great stuff. This is going to be great.","speaker":"Josh Reinhard"},{"quote":"Excited to start working on some of this website stuff?","speaker":"Sam Lieberman"}],"topics":["delivery","leadgen","ABM","integrations","campaigns","linkedin"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-11T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Campaigns and Lead Generation**\n\nThe team is advancing targeted campaigns to increase qualified leads through webinars, LinkedIn outreach, and optimized landing pages.  \n\n- **Podcast episodes featuring Jameson and Tom are live on Spotify, Apple, and YouTube** to support brand awareness and engagement (08:00)  \n    - The team is building a flexible ad and landing page framework to quickly adjust webinar promotions based on lead volume.  \n    - Josh Reinhard emphasized maintaining a **biweekly webinar cadence** unless no attendees join, ensuring consistent lead flow.  \n    - Sam Lieberman highlighted the need for a streamlined landing page form integrated with GoToWebinar to reduce barriers for registrants and ease updates.  \n    - Colin Costigan committed to improving form design and spacing issues, noting HubSpot’s template code affects editing flexibility.  \n\n- **LinkedIn outreach uses an automated process that sends connection requests and notifies sales when accepted without immediate messaging** (15:20)  \n    - Josh Reinhard and Sam Lieberman confirmed accepted connections do not receive emails unless there is ongoing conversation.  \n    - They agreed to use a shared Slack channel to notify when prospects respond, so those leads can be manually removed from email campaigns to avoid overlap.  \n    - Colin Costigan plans to automate removal from email cadence only after actual responses, preserving email contact if prospects do not engage further.  \n    - They discussed the lack of native integration for LinkedIn conversations in HubSpot, and Colin committed to building an API to sync HeyReach activity with HubSpot for better lead tracking and follow-up visibility.  \n\n- **Lead gen ads targeting HR professionals are showing promising results with cost per lead 22% below industry benchmarks, despite high competition and expense in this audience segment** (29:12)  \n    - Programmatic display ads delivered **23 clicks last week at $9 per click**, slightly down but still contributing to brand awareness.  \n    - Josh Reinhard shared progress with a large multi-location client, emphasizing the value of financial services engagements as tougher but high impact.  \n    - Colin noted the importance of expanding audiences carefully to maintain cost efficiency while increasing reach.  \n\n## **Website Content and User Experience Updates**\n\nThe team is prioritizing a comprehensive website overhaul focused on clarity, education, and lead conversion across key pages.  \n\n- **A project plan is in place to update core pages including homepage, pricing, industry-specific pages, HR leader persona, and employee portals** to improve SEO, content clarity, and user experience (21:50)  \n    - Content will emphasize features like no setup cost, pay-for-active-users pricing, and seamless integrations to reduce friction and highlight value.  \n    - Colin Costigan will draft initial copy for review by Sam Lieberman and Josh Reinhard, integrating industry insights and personas from the benchmark report.  \n    - The employee page will reduce demo form usage by providing relevant information directly, helping existing clients onboard more easily.  \n    - Josh raised concerns about engineering needs and historic reasons why these updates hadn’t been made earlier, prompting a review of technical feasibility.  \n\n- **Improvements will include adding testimonials, demo videos, and cross-linking to increase engagement and lower bounce rates** (24:00)  \n    - Colin plans to add detailed integration lists and clarify which third-party tools are supported, working with the team to confirm accuracy.  \n    - Josh advised caution about naming integrations like Workday due to lack of formal partnership agreements, suggesting a risk-tolerant approach pending legal input from Rob Whalen.  \n    - The team agreed to proceed with listing integrations until told otherwise, balancing marketing impact with potential legal risks.  \n\n## **Sales and CRM Process Enhancements**\n\nThe meeting surfaced key improvements for tracking sales activity and lead data management to align outreach efforts and measure results.  \n\n- **HubSpot contact lists for active customers need review and cleanup before the upcoming November email campaigns** to ensure accurate targeting and avoid gaps (13:00)  \n    - Josh Reinhard requested Steve begin creating and verifying lists, as Daniela’s absence has left uncertainty around current tagging and contact associations.  \n    - Sam offered to pull associated contacts first, then hand off to Steve for refinement, highlighting the urgency given campaign timelines.  \n    - The first email is planned for the week of **November 17th**, timed to avoid conflict with open enrollment and holiday distractions, followed by two more emails spaced every two weeks (12:00).  \n\n- **Sales leadership emphasized the need for transparency on LinkedIn prospect engagement within HubSpot to track follow-up and progress on leads** (31:00)  \n    - Manual notes are currently used to record LinkedIn conversations, but an API integration with HeyReach will automate this and provide real-time visibility into lead status.  \n    - Colin committed to building this integration to improve accountability and coordination between LinkedIn outreach and email nurture campaigns.  \n    - The Slack channel for LinkedIn responses will serve as a real-time alert system for sales directors to act promptly and avoid duplicate outreach.  \n\n- **Points-based billing for website updates will be flexible, allowing the team to “eat ahead” on points to prioritize lead generation over strict allocation concerns** (26:30)  \n    - Colin reassured that contract updates allow flexibility, so the team can focus on impact rather than immediate point exhaustion.  \n    - Josh welcomed this approach, seeing it as necessary to address recent drops in web traffic and form fills.  \n\n## **Operational and Technical Integration Planning**\n\nThe team is aligning on automation, system integration, and process workflows to support scalable marketing and sales execution.  \n\n- **Automation rules will remove prospects from email sequences only after active LinkedIn conversation responses, preserving engagement while avoiding contact overlap** (17:00)  \n    - Colin explained current automation limitations prevent fully automatic removal without human input, so Slack notifications will trigger manual updates.  \n    - Josh and Sam agreed this hybrid approach balances automation benefits with necessary sales judgment.  \n\n- **HeyReach and HubSpot will be integrated using an API/webhook to sync LinkedIn activities directly into CRM records** for more accurate tracking and faster follow-up (20:00)  \n    - Colin will manage API creation and coordinate with Sam and Josh to test and optimize data flows.  \n    - This integration aims to eliminate manual note-taking and improve visibility of warm leads across platforms.  \n\n- **HubSpot landing page templates and forms require technical review and redesign to fix spacing, text formatting, and editing constraints caused by back-end code** (10:30)  \n    - Colin identified HubSpot’s Hubble coding and style sheets as factors limiting text edits, committing to investigate and improve template flexibility.  \n    - This will enable faster updates and better UX for promotional pages tied to webinars and demos.  \n\n- **The team discussed careful handling of integrations listed on the website to avoid legal issues due to lack of formal partnerships** (24:30)  \n    - Josh recommended involving Rob Whalen before finalizing integration lists to manage risk.  \n    - The group agreed to proceed with displaying integrations cautiously and ready to remove if challenged.  \n\n## **Client and Team Coordination**\n\nImproved communication and role clarity are emphasized to ensure smooth campaign execution and client engagement.  \n\n- **Josh Reinhard will invite Dan into the LinkedIn Slack notification channel to ensure all sales directors have visibility on inbound leads** (14:30)  \n    - This will help coordinate outreach efforts and avoid missed responses or duplicated contacts.  \n\n- **Sam Lieberman and Josh Reinhard stressed the importance of tracking and verifying follow-up activity on leads generated via LinkedIn and other channels** (31:00)  \n    - The API integration with HeyReach will support this by logging conversations and responses in HubSpot automatically.  \n    - Manual oversight remains important until the integration is fully operational.  \n\n- **Nina was introduced as a new team member supporting Colin on PTO Exchange projects and will join future calls** to enhance collaboration and oversight (04:20).  \n\n- **Colin will share screenshots and updates regarding specific lead responses, such as Banner Health directing outreach to corporate contacts, ensuring sales follow-ups are appropriately routed** (31:30).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn ABM","HubSpot integration","webinar campaigns","website content strategy","lead generation","PTO Exchange"],"overview":"- **Targeted Campaigns:** Focus on webinars and LinkedIn for increasing qualified leads; biweekly webinars maintained unless no attendees join.  \n- **Lead Generation Ads:** Ads for HR professionals show cost per lead 22% below benchmarks; recent programmatic ads had 23 clicks at $9 each.  \n- **Website Overhaul:** Comprehensive updates planned for core pages to improve SEO, clarity, and lead conversion, emphasizing value features.  \n- **Sales Engagement Tracking:** HubSpot contact lists need review before November campaigns; first email sent week of November 17th.  \n- **System Integration:** API is being developed to sync LinkedIn data with HubSpot for better lead tracking and visibility.  \n- **Client Coordination:** New team member Nina will support projects; Josh to invite Dan for enhanced oversight on leads.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nAdd Nina Belina to future calls and coordinate her onboarding (04:23)\nDuplicate existing landing page template for quick webinar campaign updates; improve form design and integration with GoToWebinar (09:41)\nCreate API key and build HubSpot integration to sync LinkedIn conversations and lead data from HeyReach (20:01)\nDevelop website content documents for homepage, pricing, industries, HR, employee pages for review by PTO Exchange (21:00)\nAdd points tracking column to project plans and manage scope within contract constraints (26:08)\nShare links and screenshots of LinkedIn leads and responses, including Banner Health communication, with Josh and Sam (30:38)\n\n**Sam Lieberman**\nProvide feedback on landing page forms and copy improvements, focusing on form shortening and user experience (09:41)\nPull list of active customer contacts associated with deals in HubSpot and provide to Steve for validation and refinement (13:38)\nWork with Colin on defining integration partners authorized for website mentions, consulting legal experts like Rob Whalen (24:17)\nMonitor HubSpot entries for LinkedIn lead follow-ups and ensure sales director activity is documented (31:53)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nInvite Dan to LinkedIn outreach Slack channel for real-time notifications and coordination (14:33)\nCoordinate with Steve to confirm HubSpot contact tagging accuracy and clarify lists for campaign emails (13:10)\nSupport sending survey emails according to agreed schedule starting week of Nov 17, avoiding Thanksgiving (12:09)\nEnsure sales directors are logging LinkedIn lead follow-up activity into HubSpot manually if necessary (31:53)\n\n**Steve**\nPrepare and validate HubSpot contact list of active customers linked to deals for campaign targeting (13:38)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"c7f5fe33-f049-4392-8ea9-c8a97b127511","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
