)
INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Marketing Campaigns and Lead Generation**

The team is advancing targeted campaigns to increase qualified leads through webinars, LinkedIn outreach, and optimized landing pages.  

- **Podcast episodes featuring Jameson and Tom are live on Spotify, Apple, and YouTube** to support brand awareness and engagement (08:00)  
    - The team is building a flexible ad and landing page framework to quickly adjust webinar promotions based on lead volume.  
    - Josh Reinhard emphasized maintaining a **biweekly webinar cadence** unless no attendees join, ensuring consistent lead flow.  
    - Sam Lieberman highlighted the need for a streamlined landing page form integrated with GoToWebinar to reduce barriers for registrants and ease updates.  
    - Colin Costigan committed to improving form design and spacing issues, noting HubSpot’s template code affects editing flexibility.  

- **LinkedIn outreach uses an automated process that sends connection requests and notifies sales when accepted without immediate messaging** (15:20)  
    - Josh Reinhard and Sam Lieberman confirmed accepted connections do not receive emails unless there is ongoing conversation.  
    - They agreed to use a shared Slack channel to notify when prospects respond, so those leads can be manually removed from email campaigns to avoid overlap.  
    - Colin Costigan plans to automate removal from email cadence only after actual responses, preserving email contact if prospects do not engage further.  
    - They discussed the lack of native integration for LinkedIn conversations in HubSpot, and Colin committed to building an API to sync HeyReach activity with HubSpot for better lead tracking and follow-up visibility.  

- **Lead gen ads targeting HR professionals are showing promising results with cost per lead 22% below industry benchmarks, despite high competition and expense in this audience segment** (29:12)  
    - Programmatic display ads delivered **23 clicks last week at $9 per click**, slightly down but still contributing to brand awareness.  
    - Josh Reinhard shared progress with a large multi-location client, emphasizing the value of financial services engagements as tougher but high impact.  
    - Colin noted the importance of expanding audiences carefully to maintain cost efficiency while increasing reach.  

## **Website Content and User Experience Updates**

The team is prioritizing a comprehensive website overhaul focused on clarity, education, and lead conversion across key pages.  

- **A project plan is in place to update core pages including homepage, pricing, industry-specific pages, HR leader persona, and employee portals** to improve SEO, content clarity, and user experience (21:50)  
    - Content will emphasize features like no setup cost, pay-for-active-users pricing, and seamless integrations to reduce friction and highlight value.  
    - Colin Costigan will draft initial copy for review by Sam Lieberman and Josh Reinhard, integrating industry insights and personas from the benchmark report.  
    - The employee page will reduce demo form usage by providing relevant information directly, helping existing clients onboard more easily.  
    - Josh raised concerns about engineering needs and historic reasons why these updates hadn’t been made earlier, prompting a review of technical feasibility.  

- **Improvements will include adding testimonials, demo videos, and cross-linking to increase engagement and lower bounce rates** (24:00)  
    - Colin plans to add detailed integration lists and clarify which third-party tools are supported, working with the team to confirm accuracy.  
    - Josh advised caution about naming integrations like Workday due to lack of formal partnership agreements, suggesting a risk-tolerant approach pending legal input from Rob Whalen.  
    - The team agreed to proceed with listing integrations until told otherwise, balancing marketing impact with potential legal risks.  

## **Sales and CRM Process Enhancements**

The meeting surfaced key improvements for tracking sales activity and lead data management to align outreach efforts and measure results.  

- **HubSpot contact lists for active customers need review and cleanup before the upcoming November email campaigns** to ensure accurate targeting and avoid gaps (13:00)  
    - Josh Reinhard requested Steve begin creating and verifying lists, as Daniela’s absence has left uncertainty around current tagging and contact associations.  
    - Sam offered to pull associated contacts first, then hand off to Steve for refinement, highlighting the urgency given campaign timelines.  
    - The first email is planned for the week of **November 17th**, timed to avoid conflict with open enrollment and holiday distractions, followed by two more emails spaced every two weeks (12:00).  

- **Sales leadership emphasized the need for transparency on LinkedIn prospect engagement within HubSpot to track follow-up and progress on leads** (31:00)  
    - Manual notes are currently used to record LinkedIn conversations, but an API integration with HeyReach will automate this and provide real-time visibility into lead status.  
    - Colin committed to building this integration to improve accountability and coordination between LinkedIn outreach and email nurture campaigns.  
    - The Slack channel for LinkedIn responses will serve as a real-time alert system for sales directors to act promptly and avoid duplicate outreach.  

- **Points-based billing for website updates will be flexible, allowing the team to “eat ahead” on points to prioritize lead generation over strict allocation concerns** (26:30)  
    - Colin reassured that contract updates allow flexibility, so the team can focus on impact rather than immediate point exhaustion.  
    - Josh welcomed this approach, seeing it as necessary to address recent drops in web traffic and form fills.  

## **Operational and Technical Integration Planning**

The team is aligning on automation, system integration, and process workflows to support scalable marketing and sales execution.  

- **Automation rules will remove prospects from email sequences only after active LinkedIn conversation responses, preserving engagement while avoiding contact overlap** (17:00)  
    - Colin explained current automation limitations prevent fully automatic removal without human input, so Slack notifications will trigger manual updates.  
    - Josh and Sam agreed this hybrid approach balances automation benefits with necessary sales judgment.  

- **HeyReach and HubSpot will be integrated using an API/webhook to sync LinkedIn activities directly into CRM records** for more accurate tracking and faster follow-up (20:00)  
    - Colin will manage API creation and coordinate with Sam and Josh to test and optimize data flows.  
    - This integration aims to eliminate manual note-taking and improve visibility of warm leads across platforms.  

- **HubSpot landing page templates and forms require technical review and redesign to fix spacing, text formatting, and editing constraints caused by back-end code** (10:30)  
    - Colin identified HubSpot’s Hubble coding and style sheets as factors limiting text edits, committing to investigate and improve template flexibility.  
    - This will enable faster updates and better UX for promotional pages tied to webinars and demos.  

- **The team discussed careful handling of integrations listed on the website to avoid legal issues due to lack of formal partnerships** (24:30)  
    - Josh recommended involving Rob Whalen before finalizing integration lists to manage risk.  
    - The group agreed to proceed with displaying integrations cautiously and ready to remove if challenged.  

## **Client and Team Coordination**

Improved communication and role clarity are emphasized to ensure smooth campaign execution and client engagement.  

- **Josh Reinhard will invite Dan into the LinkedIn Slack notification channel to ensure all sales directors have visibility on inbound leads** (14:30)  
    - This will help coordinate outreach efforts and avoid missed responses or duplicated contacts.  

- **Sam Lieberman and Josh Reinhard stressed the importance of tracking and verifying follow-up activity on leads generated via LinkedIn and other channels** (31:00)  
    - The API integration with HeyReach will support this by logging conversations and responses in HubSpot automatically.  
    - Manual oversight remains important until the integration is fully operational.  

- **Nina was introduced as a new team member supporting Colin on PTO Exchange projects and will join future calls** to enhance collaboration and oversight (04:20).  

- **Colin will share screenshots and updates regarding specific lead responses, such as Banner Health directing outreach to corporate contacts, ensuring sales follow-ups are appropriately routed** (31:30).',
  '2025-11-06 18:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Add Nina Belina to future calls and coordinate her onboarding (04:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Duplicate existing landing page template for quick webinar campaign updates; improve form design and integration with GoToWebinar (09:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Create API key and build HubSpot integration to sync LinkedIn conversations and lead data from HeyReach (20:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Develop website content documents for homepage, pricing, industries, HR, employee pages for review by PTO Exchange (21:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Add points tracking column to project plans and manage scope within contract constraints (26:08)","completed":false},{"text":"Share links and screenshots of LinkedIn leads and responses, including Banner Health communication, with Josh and Sam (30:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback on landing page forms and copy improvements, focusing on form shortening and user experience (09:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Pull list of active customer contacts associated with deals in HubSpot and provide to Steve for validation and refinement (13:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Work with Colin on defining integration partners authorized for website mentions, consulting legal experts like Rob Whalen (24:17)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor HubSpot entries for LinkedIn lead follow-ups and ensure sales director activity is documented (31:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Invite Dan to LinkedIn outreach Slack channel for real-time notifications and coordination (14:33)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Steve to confirm HubSpot contact tagging accuracy and clarify lists for campaign emails (13:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Support sending survey emails according to agreed schedule starting week of Nov 17, avoiding Thanksgiving (12:09)","completed":false},{"text":"Ensure sales directors are logging LinkedIn lead follow-up activity into HubSpot manually if necessary (31:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare and validate HubSpot contact list of active customers linked to deals for campaign targeting (13:38)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Review Lead Source Bucket / Lead Source Specific (2025-11-07 13:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '75b32155-1255-4d17-b437-152e300521a0',
    '2025-11-07 13:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9A8S0FHQDS3Q5QB7RH7698R',
    'Review Lead Source Bucket / Lead Source Specific',
    '{"Greg Smith","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    2014,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81919787892?pwd=Yx7JqOfi7mNLOfcnEZ36peMsfBA8yw.1',
    '{"id":"01K9A8S0FHQDS3Q5QB7RH7698R","title":"Review Lead Source Bucket / Lead Source Specific","summary":{"notes":"## **Board Meeting Preparation and Communication Cadence**\n\nThe team decided to establish a structured update process for board meetings, focusing on clear communication and marketing visibility. (05:41)\n\n- **Greg Smith** outlined that board meetings occur about every **two months**, with a small, involved VC board that values regular updates, but marketing has had little visibility so far.\n- Greg plans to create a **recap deck updated every two months**, blending visual highlights with supporting numbers to improve board understanding by the next meeting in **January**.\n- This approach aims to provide clearer marketing context and foster better stakeholder alignment, addressing current gaps where board members lack sufficient info.\n- The cadence and presentation style will evolve to better position marketing achievements and data ahead of meetings, improving confidence and strategic input.\n\n## **Lead Source Data Integration and Management**\n\nThe team agreed on refining lead source tracking between Salesforce and HubSpot to improve marketing attribution and sales engagement. (09:05)\n\n- **Colin Costigan** connected the Salesforce **Lead Source Specific** field to HubSpot, enabling syncing of detailed lead origin data to better track marketing channels and campaigns.\n- Greg emphasized the need for a **two-field system** capturing both **first touch (original source)** and **last touch (latest source)** to balance attribution insights with real-time sales engagement context.\n- The system must support multiple lead source buckets like LinkedIn ads, website forms, webinars, trade shows, and organic social/search, with clear mappings from form completions to lead source categories.\n- They will maintain a **catch-all \"Other\" category** to capture uncategorized leads and ensure no data gaps, with ongoing refinement as new forms and channels are added.\n\n## **Lead Source Classification and Granularity**\n\nThe team worked through detailed classification to enable better campaign performance analysis and resource allocation. (22:25)\n\n- Greg prioritized distinguishing **paid vs. organic channels**, recommending granular lead source categories such as **LinkedIn Ads**, **PPC Paid**, **Organic Search**, and **Organic Social** for precise tracking.\n- They agreed on splitting event leads into **event sponsor** and **event host** categories, reflecting different ROI and marketing strategies for planned activities like **four US roundtables** and **five European fraud summits** in the next year.\n- The lead source framework will include multiple layers: a broad source (e.g., webinar, trade show, LinkedIn) and more specific descriptors (e.g., campaign name, form type).\n- This structure supports clearer marketing ROI measurement and helps avoid overstating success from certain channels, especially events.\n\n## **Operational Improvements in Lead Data and Forms**\n\nThe team addressed integration issues and form functionality to ensure data quality and user experience. (11:44)\n\n- Greg identified a **ZoomInfo import of about 205 contacts** lacking associated company records in Salesforce, indicating a sales process disconnect rather than a system error.\n- Colin added additional columns in HubSpot to surface the **latest traffic source** and record source details, enhancing lead context for sales follow-up.\n- A workflow was created (but not yet activated) to automatically set **Lead Source Specific** based on form completions, tagging leads by source bucket for consistent attribution.\n- Greg noted the **contact form message field had dropped out** but Colin quickly restored it, ensuring vital lead information is captured without disruption.\n\n## **Strategic Use of HubSpot Fields for Attribution**\n\nThe team opted to leverage existing HubSpot fields and workflows to improve lead tracking without overcomplicating Salesforce. (20:25)\n\n- They will use HubSpot’s **standard fields** for original and latest record sources to manage first and last touch attribution cleanly.\n- Greg emphasized that sales care most about the **most recent touchpoint** to guide outreach, reducing the need to duplicate first touch data in Salesforce.\n- Colin’s proposed workflow will assign detailed lead source specifics (e.g., exact white paper downloaded or campaign) to improve sales context and marketing measurement.\n- The approach balances comprehensive tracking with practical data use, supporting sales with timely insights while enabling marketing to analyze lead journeys.\n\n## **Next Steps and Accountability**\n\nBoth Greg and Colin agreed on clear ownership and timelines to finalize the lead source framework and resolve outstanding data issues. (33:14)\n\n- Colin will finalize the **lead source list** based on their discussion and share it with Greg for review.\n- Greg will create the necessary **picklist fields in Salesforce** and address the ZoomInfo import issues to ensure clean data.\n- Once Salesforce fields are ready, Colin will complete the HubSpot setup and activate workflows to automate lead source tagging.\n- This coordinated effort aims to have the system operational soon, enabling better attribution and sales engagement tracking without disrupting current processes.","outline":null,"keywords":["Lead Source","HubSpot","Salesforce Integration","Marketing Attribution","Lead Workflow","ZoomInfo Import"],"overview":"- **Board Meeting Updates:** Establish structured updates for board meetings every two months to improve marketing visibility and stakeholder alignment.  \n- **Lead Source Integration:** Connect Salesforce and HubSpot for better tracking of lead origins and marketing efficiency.  \n- **Granular Classification:** Focus on distinguishing paid vs. organic channels and categorize event leads for accurate ROI measurement.  \n- **Data Quality Checks:** Address integration issues in lead data and forms to ensure a seamless user experience and data accuracy.  \n- **HubSpot for Attribution:** Utilize existing HubSpot fields for effective tracking of first and last touchpoints without complicating Salesforce.  \n- **Clear Accountability:** Colin and Greg will finalize the lead source framework and data issues to enhance attribution and sales tracking.","action_items":"\n**Greg Smith**\nInvestigate ZoomInfo import issue and missing company records in Salesforce (12:20)\nAdd necessary lead source picklist values in Salesforce and deactivate outdated ones after final list approval (27:51)\nConfirm message field on contact form is restored and functioning (30:43)\nReview and provide feedback on detailed lead source bucket list from Colin (32:55)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nBuild and share detailed lead source bucket list and form workflow based on meeting discussion (27:51)\nContinue development of HubSpot workflows to assign lead source specific fields on form submissions (15:15)\nFix and maintain HubSpot contact form message field and ensure correct syncing (30:43)\nWork with Greg to finalize HubSpot and Salesforce sync parameters for first and latest lead source fields (18:06)\n"},"duration":33.56999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Greg Smith"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Colin, how we doing?","index":0,"end_time":322.399,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":322.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.399,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not bad.","index":2,"end_time":325.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Happy Friday.","index":3,"end_time":326.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Happy Friday.","index":4,"end_time":327.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This week was a long one.","index":5,"end_time":329.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Feel like we''re saying that every week now.","index":6,"end_time":333,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, kind of feels like it, huh?","index":7,"end_time":335.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Any.","index":8,"end_time":337.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any exciting plans for the weekend?","index":9,"end_time":339.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a board meeting next week, so stressing about that.","index":10,"end_time":346.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Anything we can provide that would help?","index":11,"end_time":351.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not for this one, I don''t think.","index":12,"end_time":355.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But I actually do think next time.","index":13,"end_time":358.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I want to get a little more markety about it.","index":14,"end_time":365.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I''m still trying to figure out, like, what the cadence is, who''s who in the zoo, all that kind of stuff.","index":15,"end_time":373.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We.","index":16,"end_time":374.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.18,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It appears that we do them about every two months.","index":17,"end_time":377.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":18,"end_time":378.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":380.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is an interesting interval.","index":20,"end_time":381.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":21,"end_time":382.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I think, I think part of it is so like, were vc, not pe, so they tend to be a little bit more involved and it makes it.","index":22,"end_time":396.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And it''s a small board.","index":23,"end_time":397.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s not.","index":24,"end_time":398.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s not that big, which helps.","index":25,"end_time":400.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And so they, I think, appreciate the regular cadence.","index":26,"end_time":405.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But like, there was, my perception is very little about marketing in the board conversation.","index":27,"end_time":414.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then there was a little bit about marketing in the board conversation that was, you know, Michal put forward.","index":28,"end_time":422.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And last time the board was like, yeah, we want to talk to Greg, which is the right thing to do.","index":29,"end_time":432.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":30,"end_time":433.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this next one, I was like, hey, do you want me to come?","index":31,"end_time":441.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And he looked at my slides.","index":32,"end_time":442.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"He''s like, yeah, it''s like, yeah, you have no idea what''s going on at that level.","index":33,"end_time":447.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So next time for good reason.","index":34,"end_time":451.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right?","index":35,"end_time":451.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":451.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s why you have a role.","index":37,"end_time":453.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He shouldn''t like, like, it''s not, like, it''s not a knock on anyone.","index":38,"end_time":457.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s like, no, that''s.","index":39,"end_time":458.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.63,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s if he had enough information on his own to walk in there, that would mean there''s issues going on.","index":40,"end_time":464.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":41,"end_time":465.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So anywho, next time though, I want to be a little bit more thoughtful in terms of how everything gets put together because I was not expecting a November conversation.","index":42,"end_time":480.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I was expecting a January conversation.","index":43,"end_time":482.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And so I''m like, oh, okay.","index":44,"end_time":484,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So now I''m still expecting a January conversation.","index":45,"end_time":488.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I want to make sure that, you know, we.","index":46,"end_time":491.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.04,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We have a nice, nice setup for that.","index":47,"end_time":493.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So, yeah.","index":48,"end_time":494.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Long wind.","index":49,"end_time":495.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Long winded way of saying, I think at the end of the year it probably makes sense for us to like, put together a recap deck and maybe we do it in like two month intervals.","index":50,"end_time":509.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Which.","index":51,"end_time":509.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":510.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just like start every two months updating it on a regular basis and like, not from a numbers or stats perspective, but more from like A pretty pictures perspective.","index":53,"end_time":520.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":521.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wins.","index":55,"end_time":522.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":56,"end_time":523.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.45,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That kind of stuff.","index":57,"end_time":524.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then I. I''ll have the numbers and stats and all that good stuff to accompany it, but.","index":58,"end_time":529.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.81,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":59,"end_time":530.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you definitely work on that.","index":60,"end_time":531.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let''s hop into Lead Source and Lead Source specific.","index":61,"end_time":536.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":62,"end_time":538.249,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.769,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in HubSpot, I pulled over your field from Salesforce.","index":63,"end_time":545.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":539.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":64,"end_time":546.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.45,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that is now syncing.","index":65,"end_time":547.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":66,"end_time":548.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.18,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s see how did you.","index":67,"end_time":549.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, so here I''ll restart.","index":68,"end_time":553.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So to set that up, I just went into settings, connected apps, Salesforce, and then once you go to Contacts, then custom like or contact property mapping pops up here.","index":69,"end_time":564.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I just searched because I was checking in Salesforce and I saw Lead source specific.","index":70,"end_time":569.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s coming over right here.","index":71,"end_time":571.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I just created a field with the same name in HubSpot.","index":72,"end_time":574.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":73,"end_time":576.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.75,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then who has precedence on that?","index":74,"end_time":578.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":576.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that''s what we.","index":75,"end_time":579.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":578.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to check with you here.","index":76,"end_time":580.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I had prefer Salesforce and less blank, but there are all these options.","index":77,"end_time":585.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":78,"end_time":586.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I think it''s two way.","index":79,"end_time":592.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":80,"end_time":593.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is the answer on this one?","index":81,"end_time":595.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because this is where we ran into issues before with always Salesforce overriding stuff.","index":82,"end_time":601.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":602.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The idea is that we will.","index":84,"end_time":604.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I want to be able to use this.","index":85,"end_time":611.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":609.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Oh, actually hold on, let me dial back for a second.","index":86,"end_time":614.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Maybe there''s two fields that we need.","index":87,"end_time":617.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.51,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Crap.","index":88,"end_time":618.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.91,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, let''s.","index":89,"end_time":621.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s put our thinking caps on for just a moment here so I know where you''re going.","index":90,"end_time":626.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":91,"end_time":626.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s two problems we need to solve.","index":92,"end_time":627.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s the where did it come from first touch problem.","index":93,"end_time":631.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s the what do they do last problem.","index":94,"end_time":635.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that might require a second field in Salesforce to capture that.","index":95,"end_time":640.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":635.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Now is there a field in HubSpot that would mirror that?","index":96,"end_time":648.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because don''t they have a first source?","index":97,"end_time":651.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.81,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, so they have original.","index":98,"end_time":655.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":653.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":99,"end_time":656.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And they have latest.","index":100,"end_time":657.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":101,"end_time":660.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And so latest.","index":102,"end_time":662.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s a lot of context in here.","index":103,"end_time":668.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From.","index":104,"end_time":668.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there like a Salesforce?","index":105,"end_time":669.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you guys do an import into Salesforce?","index":106,"end_time":671.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":672.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.62,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So if you.","index":108,"end_time":675.139,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So the cutover was the 5th of September.","index":109,"end_time":678.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":675.62,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So if you set create date to like 9-6- Forward, you''ll get a much easier list to deal with usually.","index":110,"end_time":687.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Oh, this?","index":111,"end_time":689.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like a bunch happened yesterday.","index":112,"end_time":690.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":689.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Zoom Info.","index":113,"end_time":692.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, from Zoom Info.","index":114,"end_time":694.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"What are you seeing?","index":115,"end_time":695.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Oh, for sake.","index":116,"end_time":704.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s like a few hundred of these.","index":117,"end_time":707.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you scroll left on that?","index":118,"end_time":712.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":713.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Amy.","index":120,"end_time":718.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''S about 205 of them that were imported from Zoom Info yesterday.","index":121,"end_time":729.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":122,"end_time":730.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.51,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Can you just grab one of those?","index":123,"end_time":732.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.03,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I want to see if it''s a contact or lead in Salesforce.","index":124,"end_time":735.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Crystal Myers.","index":125,"end_time":740.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we look at marketing lead status, engaged non marketing contact.","index":126,"end_time":749.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":740.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s correct.","index":127,"end_time":750.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Zero lead score.","index":128,"end_time":754.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s correct.","index":129,"end_time":756.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.04,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Source, zoom info, all that''s fine.","index":130,"end_time":759.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let me.","index":131,"end_time":763.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.81,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So who.","index":132,"end_time":766.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s Crystal Meyer.","index":133,"end_time":767.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":134,"end_time":768.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Crystal Myers.","index":135,"end_time":769.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":768.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s weird.","index":136,"end_time":772.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like a company didn''t.","index":137,"end_time":773.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":772.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There was no company created when she was pushed over.","index":138,"end_time":777.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It has her company name in here, but there''s no like actual company record that was created for Heritage Community Bank.","index":139,"end_time":785.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wonder if there''s no account for it.","index":140,"end_time":787.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.53,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You''re in Salesforce.","index":141,"end_time":790.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You are a.","index":142,"end_time":791.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You''re a lead.","index":143,"end_time":792.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"God damn.","index":144,"end_time":793.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It.","index":145,"end_time":794.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Feels like we''re still dealing with hyperscale repercussions.","index":146,"end_time":802.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This isn''t necessarily hyperscale.","index":147,"end_time":804.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"This is.","index":148,"end_time":805.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Nobody in our sales field listens and they just like follow their own process.","index":149,"end_time":813.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The age old battle.","index":150,"end_time":816.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":814.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":151,"end_time":816.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Sales and marketing should work hand in hand and it''s always.","index":152,"end_time":819.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, something did.","index":153,"end_time":825.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"See, I think it was a lead from TD Bank.","index":154,"end_time":827.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":155,"end_time":828.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":156,"end_time":829.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But that was awesome.","index":157,"end_time":830.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was a good one.","index":158,"end_time":831.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That one''s getting worked.","index":159,"end_time":832.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, this is a different issue.","index":160,"end_time":838.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I will address this.","index":161,"end_time":839.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s carry on.","index":162,"end_time":841.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":840.45,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let me know what we can do from our end.","index":163,"end_time":843.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, this is a.","index":164,"end_time":844.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"This isn''t us problem.","index":165,"end_time":845.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Fully on that.","index":166,"end_time":847.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":167,"end_time":849.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":848.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just.","index":168,"end_time":849.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Contacts, not leads.","index":169,"end_time":851.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":849.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like that was the whole point.","index":170,"end_time":852.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.05,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":171,"end_time":853.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just added in extra columns into the all contacts view so it''ll show latest traffic source.","index":172,"end_time":858.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":853.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are weird because it''s Salesforce and zoom info.","index":173,"end_time":861.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":858.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if I for example, set the record source to be forms.","index":174,"end_time":873.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There we go.","index":175,"end_time":881.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":880.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Then we can see like they went to the resources page and downloaded the scan proofing white paper.","index":176,"end_time":887.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know why a tag assistant is coming in here.","index":177,"end_time":891.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, because it was us testing through tags LinkedIn funnels here campaigns.","index":178,"end_time":900.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have these being measured.","index":179,"end_time":901.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can definitely get more descriptive if you like.","index":180,"end_time":905.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also have like record Source detail over here.","index":181,"end_time":908.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":905.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a little cleaner.","index":182,"end_time":909.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":183,"end_time":911.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then this is.","index":184,"end_time":916.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":915.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is what I want to go over right now.","index":185,"end_time":919.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I went ahead and set up a workflow.","index":186,"end_time":921.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have not turned it on.","index":187,"end_time":922.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":921.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What this workflow does is if you saw that Record Source detail I go back here was actually like the exact name of the white paper or anything they were downloading.","index":188,"end_time":937.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Set that.","index":189,"end_time":940.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So record source detail 1.","index":190,"end_time":955.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":951.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s the exact like form or whatever they''re filling out.","index":191,"end_time":959.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is pretty much what I imagined you would want Lead Source specific to be.","index":192,"end_time":964.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I have.","index":193,"end_time":966.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":965.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any time a form is completed, we set lead source specific to match RECORD SOURCE Detail 1.","index":194,"end_time":973.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":967.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then after that it checks which form was completed.","index":195,"end_time":978.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so it''s a bucket of all of the LinkedIn ads leads, the contact form, a Q2 landing page, and we can continue to add any form to this.","index":196,"end_time":986.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":978.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it would set a lead source to whatever the buckets we want are.","index":197,"end_time":991.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they submit the contact form, website, contact Prospect, if they submit a LinkedIn lead gen form, ABM, LinkedIn ADS Q2, we could set Q2, we could develop however many buckets we want here.","index":198,"end_time":1004.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so this is for the dropdown field lead source to start categorizing them basically.","index":199,"end_time":1011.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":200,"end_time":1012.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1012.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s what''s connected to Salesforce already.","index":201,"end_time":1015.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1012.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":202,"end_time":1016.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, so that makes sense to me.","index":203,"end_time":1021.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1016.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We will need to go through and refine that list.","index":204,"end_time":1027.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But that makes sense to me.","index":205,"end_time":1030.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1028.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And it''s.","index":206,"end_time":1034.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That just means that every time we add a new form, we need to make sure that we update the workflow to represent the, the forms that we have.","index":207,"end_time":1043.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So like, is, is that the right path or like should we go through and, and say no, there''s no way on the form to take that action?","index":208,"end_time":1057.939,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.25,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right now the toughest part is the LinkedIn side.","index":209,"end_time":1061.299,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.019,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It doesn''t come through the API.","index":210,"end_time":1062.659,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.299,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like the exact form name.","index":211,"end_time":1063.859,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.659,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":212,"end_time":1065.139,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1064.099,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s why I went with this route.","index":213,"end_time":1067.059,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1065.619,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":214,"end_time":1067.579,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.139,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, so that makes good sense.","index":215,"end_time":1068.859,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.579,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we just need, we need the categories and the like a catch all category of if it''s not like, like if we forget to add it, like have it be other or whatever.","index":216,"end_time":1085.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1068.859,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":217,"end_time":1086.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that we can catch it.","index":218,"end_time":1087.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1086.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But.","index":219,"end_time":1088.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1087.81,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then we can trim back that list of what''s available and then for the specific, I, going back to our original question, do we need first touch and last touch in there?","index":220,"end_time":1106.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1089.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You know, I, you might be able to convince me very easily that I don''t need first touch in Salesforce because if I''m doing attribution analysis, that comes out of HubSpot.","index":221,"end_time":1119.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1107.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":222,"end_time":1121.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s the great thing about HubSpot, right.","index":223,"end_time":1123.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1121.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it has activity tracker.","index":224,"end_time":1125.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1123.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So whether it depends on does the sales team want to see where they first converted or the journey that they''ve taken.","index":225,"end_time":1133.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1125.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Completely.","index":226,"end_time":1133.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they don''t care about where they first converted.","index":227,"end_time":1136.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1133.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They want to know something happened, what was it?","index":228,"end_time":1138.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.04,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":229,"end_time":1139.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Such that they can reach out and say, hey, I saw you downloaded this white paper.","index":230,"end_time":1143.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1140.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Would you like to talk that that is the use case that I think we''re trying to solve for, which to me says don''t worry about first touch, you just want most recent touch.","index":231,"end_time":1157.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And based on that, is there an activity field that is already a standard field in HubSpot that we can just map to.","index":232,"end_time":1168.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.18,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":233,"end_time":1169.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1168.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll be able to tap into these latest source traffic drill downs.","index":234,"end_time":1173.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can reformat the names that are coming through on these.","index":235,"end_time":1177.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this is like what''s kind of being tracked right now.","index":236,"end_time":1180.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Help me understand.","index":237,"end_time":1181.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1180.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Drill down one, drill down two.","index":238,"end_time":1183.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like, what''s the.","index":239,"end_time":1184.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"What''s the hierarchy there?","index":240,"end_time":1186.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1185.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"What are we looking at?","index":241,"end_time":1187.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":242,"end_time":1188.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So drill down two.","index":243,"end_time":1191.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So drill down one is typically either like a platform or URL.","index":244,"end_time":1197.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, got it.","index":245,"end_time":1198.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.04,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":246,"end_time":1199.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then drill down to.","index":247,"end_time":1200.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1199.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it was like LinkedIn as the platform, then it''s the name of the campaign.","index":248,"end_time":1204.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":249,"end_time":1205.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1205.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"What.","index":250,"end_time":1210.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Honestly, what I would say is I think we should have like a lead source specific original and the lead source specific latest.","index":251,"end_time":1217.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t see any harm in that.","index":252,"end_time":1220.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":253,"end_time":1222.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1221.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m all for just like a lot of tracking.","index":254,"end_time":1224.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1222.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":255,"end_time":1225.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I mean.","index":256,"end_time":1225.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":257,"end_time":1227.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1227.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like it doesn''t cost anything and.","index":258,"end_time":1230.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1227.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And more data is better.","index":259,"end_time":1232.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think my only question here becomes like, the.","index":260,"end_time":1240.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The PDF download is not sufficient, but we do we actually really more or less need the form.","index":261,"end_time":1246.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1240.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":262,"end_time":1257.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s too large of a bucket.","index":263,"end_time":1259.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s too high.","index":264,"end_time":1260.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":265,"end_time":1260.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":266,"end_time":1261.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1260.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what we can do is utilize like this information that''s passing through.","index":267,"end_time":1265.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1261.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":268,"end_time":1267.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1266.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Record source detail.","index":269,"end_time":1268.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1267.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":270,"end_time":1269,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can set like an original and a latest up.","index":271,"end_time":1271.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1269,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you.","index":272,"end_time":1279.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Are we pop.","index":273,"end_time":1280.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1279.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is that an.","index":274,"end_time":1280.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1280.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is that a custom field or is that a.","index":275,"end_time":1284.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1280.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"No, this is a HubSpot standard field.","index":276,"end_time":1286.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":277,"end_time":1287.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, so it''s a standard field.","index":278,"end_time":1288.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1287.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":279,"end_time":1293.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because like, that''s what we want.","index":280,"end_time":1294.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.74,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I. I think the question is if I, as a contact, get the scan proofing white paper and then I go and I fill out the scan flag form, does it change?","index":281,"end_time":1305.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1296.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what we can set up.","index":282,"end_time":1308.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1306.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This would not change.","index":283,"end_time":1309.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the record source.","index":284,"end_time":1311,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1309.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is the original right now.","index":285,"end_time":1312.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":286,"end_time":1313.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So then we would create a new field that would be the record source latest.","index":287,"end_time":1319.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":288,"end_time":1320.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1320.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s what we would.","index":289,"end_time":1324.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1323.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s what we would use.","index":290,"end_time":1327.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1326,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":291,"end_time":1327.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I think mimicking that is exactly what we''re after.","index":292,"end_time":1331.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":293,"end_time":1332.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s what I was building that workflow based off of.","index":294,"end_time":1334.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what would be helpful is if we could just land on.","index":295,"end_time":1337.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1334.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just open this up just as a test.","index":296,"end_time":1341.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1339.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":297,"end_time":1342.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We just need to set like what these buckets are.","index":298,"end_time":1347.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1345.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we want like LinkedIn and it''s, you know, AI versus fraud.","index":299,"end_time":1353.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1347.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":300,"end_time":1353.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like white paper, etc.","index":301,"end_time":1356.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1353.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then do we just want like a contact form prospect or do we want contact form and then we have Prospect and partner.","index":302,"end_time":1369.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1356.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a few different, like mindsets we can go down for this.","index":303,"end_time":1373.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1371.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":304,"end_time":1374.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think we want, we want the contact form variants at the lead source level there.","index":305,"end_time":1385.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that way it''s a bit easier to.","index":306,"end_time":1390.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think that''s contact form, prospect, but then in column B it''s Q2, it''s, you know, main contact, it''s scan flag.","index":307,"end_time":1407.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1394.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":308,"end_time":1411.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then do we want like LinkedIn as a bucket for these?","index":309,"end_time":1432.379,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1428.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we also have these listed on the website where some people download the white paper sometimes.","index":310,"end_time":1436.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.379,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we want that as a separate lead source.","index":311,"end_time":1438.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, this is where we get into mixed mediums, right?","index":312,"end_time":1445.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1445.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1445.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":314,"end_time":1455.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1455.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I want to be able to look at it and go, this came from LinkedIn paid.","index":315,"end_time":1462.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1455.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So maybe that''s like LinkedIn ads to be a little bit more specific versus this is something that came in through the website.","index":316,"end_time":1475.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1466.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So then I think if you''re saying, okay, let''s look at the white papers and contacts and stuff through the website, like that''s a separate exercise but basically like, is it organic, is it paid?","index":317,"end_time":1497.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1476.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like the, the.","index":318,"end_time":1498.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1497.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s a webinar one.","index":319,"end_time":1499.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There will be a webinar one trade show.","index":320,"end_time":1503.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like we got to get those.","index":321,"end_time":1505.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1503.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And like, maybe, maybe LinkedIn actually doesn''t belong in the lead source.","index":322,"end_time":1516.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.51,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Maybe it''s PPC paid and then the specific source becomes LinkedIn Dash thing.","index":323,"end_time":1533.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1516.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I''m looking at efficacy of LinkedIn, I''m looking at, at that in the context of LinkedIn, probably.","index":324,"end_time":1541.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So, like that.","index":325,"end_time":1545.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1545.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":326,"end_time":1547.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1547.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so why don''t I build out just what I think where we could land from our conversation and then if you want to tweak it, then we can build that out.","index":327,"end_time":1563.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":328,"end_time":1564.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.05,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I do think for the events, let''s distinguish webinar at the lead source level.","index":329,"end_time":1572.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s, let''s.","index":330,"end_time":1573.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1572.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because in the specific, I want it to be like the web webinar, the trade show that we went to here.","index":331,"end_time":1581.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1574.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I think it''s.","index":332,"end_time":1582.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1581.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":333,"end_time":1587.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1586.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then for events, let''s have two flavors.","index":334,"end_time":1600.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1597.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Sponsorships and hosted at the lead source level.","index":335,"end_time":1612.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1604.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because I don''t want, I don''t want success at a trade show to make it look like our banking fraud summits are the best thing on the face of the planet.","index":336,"end_time":1620.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1612.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Event sponsor and event host.","index":337,"end_time":1624.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1622.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, because we''re going to do.","index":338,"end_time":1634.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1625.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we''re going to do like four round tables in the US next year.","index":339,"end_time":1640.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1635.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re going to do five fraud summits in Europe next year.","index":340,"end_time":1645.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1640.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And in.","index":341,"end_time":1646.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I want those distinctly separate.","index":342,"end_time":1649.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1646.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":343,"end_time":1652.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1650.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":344,"end_time":1653.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1652.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":345,"end_time":1654.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think these are going to be.","index":346,"end_time":1658.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1656.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think this is pretty much all of the lead sources, so I can just expand the list of what we have in lead source specific.","index":347,"end_time":1666.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1659.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, right now I can''t think of anything else that would go into here.","index":348,"end_time":1670.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ll probably so don''t organic.","index":349,"end_time":1674.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1671.22,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Don''t make any changes in Salesforce because I''m trying to get mad at other people for making changes without telling me.","index":350,"end_time":1683.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1675.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I can''t.","index":351,"end_time":1684.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1683.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I need to eat my own dog food here a little bit.","index":352,"end_time":1687.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Once you feel like you have that list, I can go and add.","index":353,"end_time":1691.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1688.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"For.","index":354,"end_time":1694.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1693.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The lead source, which is a pick list.","index":355,"end_time":1695.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1694.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":356,"end_time":1696.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1695.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Populate it with the values that are necessary and then set all the other 35,000 values that are in there to an active.","index":357,"end_time":1703.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1697.03,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":358,"end_time":1704.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1704.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then do we want like organic as a lead source and then web and social as the specific.","index":359,"end_time":1709.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1705.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or let''s do organic search and organic social and then like I get organic search is going to be.","index":360,"end_time":1731.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1709.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Well, I saw something show up the other day that was GPT referral.","index":361,"end_time":1738.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1733.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":362,"end_time":1739.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1738.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like it could be like Google.","index":363,"end_time":1742.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1740.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It could be Chat GPT, Claude, whatever.","index":364,"end_time":1744.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then social obviously will be, you know, LinkedIn X, Facebook, YouTube.","index":365,"end_time":1749.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1744.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we''re putting ChatGPT in organic search instead of referral.","index":366,"end_time":1755.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1752.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":367,"end_time":1757.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1756.73,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":368,"end_time":1758.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1757.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s, I''ve been thinking a lot about that too.","index":369,"end_time":1762.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1759.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s where things are going to trend.","index":370,"end_time":1764.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1762.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I, I.","index":371,"end_time":1766.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1765.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":372,"end_time":1767.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1766.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Especially with, I don''t know if you played around with the atlas at all the chat GPT''s new browser.","index":373,"end_time":1773.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t, I''m like super scared to.","index":374,"end_time":1775.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1773.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because it''s not great.","index":375,"end_time":1776.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1775.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, good, good.","index":376,"end_time":1778.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1777.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That makes me happy because, like the last thing I want to do is be like, I want to use this browser, but I also don''t want to give over all my data to the machine, which I am anyway.","index":377,"end_time":1791.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1778.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But I have control.","index":378,"end_time":1793.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1791.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":379,"end_time":1794.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1793.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":380,"end_time":1797.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1797.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll continue to build all this out and then I''ll share it with you.","index":381,"end_time":1801.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1799.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if we''re on the same page about everything, then we can start if you create the fields in Salesforce and then we can build them all in HubSpot.","index":382,"end_time":1808.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1801.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":383,"end_time":1808.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1808.46,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":384,"end_time":1809.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1808.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''ll chase down what happened with the Zoom info import.","index":385,"end_time":1813.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1810.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ll try to figure that out.","index":386,"end_time":1815.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1813.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then there''s one other mini thing.","index":387,"end_time":1818.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1816.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I noticed our contact form no longer has the message field on it.","index":388,"end_time":1823.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1818.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Get that added.","index":389,"end_time":1843.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1843.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now that dropped out.","index":390,"end_time":1847.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re back.","index":391,"end_time":1868.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1867.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":392,"end_time":1869.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1869.46,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I figured it was as simple as that.","index":393,"end_time":1872.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, Yeah, I suspect that dropped out.","index":394,"end_time":1877.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Looks like this got swapped.","index":395,"end_time":1880.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1878.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know what happened because this was a different field.","index":396,"end_time":1882.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1880.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we were doing the comp.","index":397,"end_time":1885.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1884.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The country stuff maybe.","index":398,"end_time":1887.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1885.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, it, it''s a great thing about HubSpot forms is you just have to fix it here and then it reflects anywhere that that form is.","index":399,"end_time":1946.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1888.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, like I.","index":400,"end_time":1948.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1947.05,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There we go.","index":401,"end_time":1958.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1957.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I am a big fan.","index":402,"end_time":1967.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1961.13,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right, that''s all updated.","index":403,"end_time":1973.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1972.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Remember the days of inline HTML editing forms all over the place.","index":404,"end_time":1980.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1975.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":405,"end_time":1981.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1981.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Contact form seven.","index":406,"end_time":1983.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1981.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly, exactly.","index":407,"end_time":1985.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1983.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So big, big fan.","index":408,"end_time":1986.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1985.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Big fan.","index":409,"end_time":1987.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1986.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":410,"end_time":1991.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1991.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, well thank you for your time Greg.","index":411,"end_time":1994.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1992.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''re good.","index":412,"end_time":1995.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Shoot me a note when you, you feel like you got the list.","index":413,"end_time":1998.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1996.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''ll give it a run through but then also make the right fields in Salesforce and we''ll be off to the races.","index":414,"end_time":2003.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1998.63,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":415,"end_time":2004.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2004.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thank you very much.","index":416,"end_time":2006.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2004.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":417,"end_time":2007.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2006.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Take care.","index":418,"end_time":2007.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2007.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":419,"end_time":2007.752,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2007.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a.","index":420,"end_time":2007.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2007.752,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-11-07T13:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81919787892?pwd=Yx7JqOfi7mNLOfcnEZ36peMsfBA8yw.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com","gregory.smith@threatmark.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9A8S0FHQDS3Q5QB7RH7698R","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.87,"bullets":["Defined plan to track lead source with new ''original'' and ''latest'' fields in HubSpot.","Aligned on syncing HubSpot and Salesforce without overwriting key contact data.","Agreed to categorize events into ''sponsorships'' and ''hosted'' to clarify lead attribution.","Colin to build out lead source mapping and Greg to create matching Salesforce fields.","Resolved contact form issue by restoring missing ''message'' field across impacted forms."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We just need the categories and the like a catch all category of if it''s not...","speaker":"Greg Smith"},{"quote":"I think mimicking that is exactly what we''re after.","speaker":"Greg Smith"},{"quote":"I''ll continue to build all this out and then I''ll share it with you.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["delivery","lead attribution","crm integration"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-11T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Board Meeting Preparation and Communication Cadence**\n\nThe team decided to establish a structured update process for board meetings, focusing on clear communication and marketing visibility. (05:41)\n\n- **Greg Smith** outlined that board meetings occur about every **two months**, with a small, involved VC board that values regular updates, but marketing has had little visibility so far.\n- Greg plans to create a **recap deck updated every two months**, blending visual highlights with supporting numbers to improve board understanding by the next meeting in **January**.\n- This approach aims to provide clearer marketing context and foster better stakeholder alignment, addressing current gaps where board members lack sufficient info.\n- The cadence and presentation style will evolve to better position marketing achievements and data ahead of meetings, improving confidence and strategic input.\n\n## **Lead Source Data Integration and Management**\n\nThe team agreed on refining lead source tracking between Salesforce and HubSpot to improve marketing attribution and sales engagement. (09:05)\n\n- **Colin Costigan** connected the Salesforce **Lead Source Specific** field to HubSpot, enabling syncing of detailed lead origin data to better track marketing channels and campaigns.\n- Greg emphasized the need for a **two-field system** capturing both **first touch (original source)** and **last touch (latest source)** to balance attribution insights with real-time sales engagement context.\n- The system must support multiple lead source buckets like LinkedIn ads, website forms, webinars, trade shows, and organic social/search, with clear mappings from form completions to lead source categories.\n- They will maintain a **catch-all \"Other\" category** to capture uncategorized leads and ensure no data gaps, with ongoing refinement as new forms and channels are added.\n\n## **Lead Source Classification and Granularity**\n\nThe team worked through detailed classification to enable better campaign performance analysis and resource allocation. (22:25)\n\n- Greg prioritized distinguishing **paid vs. organic channels**, recommending granular lead source categories such as **LinkedIn Ads**, **PPC Paid**, **Organic Search**, and **Organic Social** for precise tracking.\n- They agreed on splitting event leads into **event sponsor** and **event host** categories, reflecting different ROI and marketing strategies for planned activities like **four US roundtables** and **five European fraud summits** in the next year.\n- The lead source framework will include multiple layers: a broad source (e.g., webinar, trade show, LinkedIn) and more specific descriptors (e.g., campaign name, form type).\n- This structure supports clearer marketing ROI measurement and helps avoid overstating success from certain channels, especially events.\n\n## **Operational Improvements in Lead Data and Forms**\n\nThe team addressed integration issues and form functionality to ensure data quality and user experience. (11:44)\n\n- Greg identified a **ZoomInfo import of about 205 contacts** lacking associated company records in Salesforce, indicating a sales process disconnect rather than a system error.\n- Colin added additional columns in HubSpot to surface the **latest traffic source** and record source details, enhancing lead context for sales follow-up.\n- A workflow was created (but not yet activated) to automatically set **Lead Source Specific** based on form completions, tagging leads by source bucket for consistent attribution.\n- Greg noted the **contact form message field had dropped out** but Colin quickly restored it, ensuring vital lead information is captured without disruption.\n\n## **Strategic Use of HubSpot Fields for Attribution**\n\nThe team opted to leverage existing HubSpot fields and workflows to improve lead tracking without overcomplicating Salesforce. (20:25)\n\n- They will use HubSpot’s **standard fields** for original and latest record sources to manage first and last touch attribution cleanly.\n- Greg emphasized that sales care most about the **most recent touchpoint** to guide outreach, reducing the need to duplicate first touch data in Salesforce.\n- Colin’s proposed workflow will assign detailed lead source specifics (e.g., exact white paper downloaded or campaign) to improve sales context and marketing measurement.\n- The approach balances comprehensive tracking with practical data use, supporting sales with timely insights while enabling marketing to analyze lead journeys.\n\n## **Next Steps and Accountability**\n\nBoth Greg and Colin agreed on clear ownership and timelines to finalize the lead source framework and resolve outstanding data issues. (33:14)\n\n- Colin will finalize the **lead source list** based on their discussion and share it with Greg for review.\n- Greg will create the necessary **picklist fields in Salesforce** and address the ZoomInfo import issues to ensure clean data.\n- Once Salesforce fields are ready, Colin will complete the HubSpot setup and activate workflows to automate lead source tagging.\n- This coordinated effort aims to have the system operational soon, enabling better attribution and sales engagement tracking without disrupting current processes.","outline":null,"keywords":["Lead Source","HubSpot","Salesforce Integration","Marketing Attribution","Lead Workflow","ZoomInfo Import"],"overview":"- **Board Meeting Updates:** Establish structured updates for board meetings every two months to improve marketing visibility and stakeholder alignment.  \n- **Lead Source Integration:** Connect Salesforce and HubSpot for better tracking of lead origins and marketing efficiency.  \n- **Granular Classification:** Focus on distinguishing paid vs. organic channels and categorize event leads for accurate ROI measurement.  \n- **Data Quality Checks:** Address integration issues in lead data and forms to ensure a seamless user experience and data accuracy.  \n- **HubSpot for Attribution:** Utilize existing HubSpot fields for effective tracking of first and last touchpoints without complicating Salesforce.  \n- **Clear Accountability:** Colin and Greg will finalize the lead source framework and data issues to enhance attribution and sales tracking.","action_items":"\n**Greg Smith**\nInvestigate ZoomInfo import issue and missing company records in Salesforce (12:20)\nAdd necessary lead source picklist values in Salesforce and deactivate outdated ones after final list approval (27:51)\nConfirm message field on contact form is restored and functioning (30:43)\nReview and provide feedback on detailed lead source bucket list from Colin (32:55)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nBuild and share detailed lead source bucket list and form workflow based on meeting discussion (27:51)\nContinue development of HubSpot workflows to assign lead source specific fields on form submissions (15:15)\nFix and maintain HubSpot contact form message field and ensure correct syncing (30:43)\nWork with Greg to finalize HubSpot and Salesforce sync parameters for first and latest lead source fields (18:06)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"667e13dc-6d78-4f45-bd9b-fc660c35e79c","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
