    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1',
    '{"id":"01K8X8X8TEX0EHDPPASG1WCV3R","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Video Content and Script Development**\n\nThe team agreed on refining the video series script to better highlight client pain points and showcase the product’s benefits through storytelling (08:15).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** confirmed the animation improves script clarity by breaking up long sentences, which otherwise sound like one continuous statement without pauses (08:15)  \n    - The video format makes the message easier to follow than audio-only versions  \n    - The team will consider adding shorter intro/outro options for different video lengths  \n    - Eli Bebinger suggested structuring episodes around a single main pain point per firm to create focused narratives  \n    - This approach supports client confidentiality by framing stories as journeys rather than comprehensive pain disclosures\n\n- **David** is confirmed as the primary interviewee and potential host, leveraging his deep experience in global resource management (11:12)  \n    - Axel Völker highlighted David’s expertise as a strong asset for hosting and interviewing  \n    - Colin will provide a framework for an episode featuring David and Eli to ensure targeted questions and flow (12:44)  \n    - The first episode concept centers on global rollout challenges in resource management, aligned with Desi Dalo’s strengths  \n    - Recording setup will use Riverside platform, simplifying remote interviews and enabling easy content capture\n\n- The team plans to rewrite the video script using materials from the product overview PDF and positioning documents to create a broader, clearer story of Desi Dalo’s value (34:05)  \n    - Colin will incorporate more resource management aspects and AI agent features into the new scripts (27:07)  \n    - The revised scripts aim to balance detailed product info with engaging storytelling for marketing effectiveness  \n    - Delivery of updated scripts and episode frameworks is expected soon after resolving access issues to shared files\n\n## **Advertising and Lead Generation Performance**\n\nCurrent ad campaigns on LinkedIn and retargeting platforms are under review with plans for creative refresh and offer adjustments to improve engagement and lead quality (14:12).\n\n- After **three weeks** of LinkedIn ads, the team recorded a **click-through rate (CTR) of 0.44%**, matching industry standards for IT services but reflecting high costs per click (14:31)  \n    - The most engaging ad promotes “stop losing proposals to resume bottlenecks,” which will remain in rotation  \n    - Ads with lowest CTR will be replaced every two to three weeks to optimize performance  \n    - Axel suggested testing calls to action like “register now” or “try for free” to increase appeal and conversion rates (15:18)  \n    - Colin confirmed early leads converted through free trial registration, supporting this approach (15:38)\n\n- The retargeting campaign via **AdRoll** was launched recently and is focused on brand awareness with expected low direct conversions initially (35:16)  \n    - Metrics on clicks and engagement will be shared once data matures  \n    - This complements LinkedIn efforts by broadening audience touchpoints\n\n- Email outreach has sent **822 emails** with about **290 opens**, but limited engagement so far (20:16)  \n    - Volume was recently increased to accelerate outreach  \n    - Colin noted email acts more as a supportive channel compared to LinkedIn’s higher conversion focus (36:11)  \n    - Eli questioned whether the email sender’s identity influences response rates; Colin clarified names and addresses used include Eli’s to personalize messages (36:35)  \n    - The team agreed to test messaging emphasizing free tool registration to lower barriers and attract more responses (21:11)\n\n## **Outreach and Engagement Strategy**\n\nThe team is actively refining outreach tactics to improve connection acceptance and follow-up quality, integrating video sharing and personalized messaging (16:03).\n\n- On LinkedIn, **284 connection requests** were sent with a **16.5% acceptance rate**, yielding **eight replies from 46 messages** sent (16:03)  \n    - Eli is managing messaging and will start sharing the product video link via YouTube to nurture interest (20:13)  \n    - Axel recommended sharing video content with recipients who have shown some interest to deepen engagement (16:23)  \n    - LinkedIn’s product video hosting lacks direct shareable links, so YouTube is preferred for distribution (18:48)  \n    - Colin supported video sharing as a complement while the new scripted video is still in progress (17:32)\n\n- The team discussed improving LinkedIn company page product video accessibility to aid prospect viewing and sharing (18:21)  \n    - Technical limitations prevent clickable video links directly on LinkedIn product tabs, requiring workarounds  \n    - Using familiar platforms like YouTube reduces friction for recipients clicking on demos\n\n## **Product Positioning and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe group is aligning on a broader, clearer product story to better communicate Desi Dalo’s unique value in workforce and resource management (27:33).\n\n- Axel shared updated positioning materials emphasizing three pillars: **skills, projects, and utilization** for IT consulting firms sized **500 to 3,000 employees** (29:00)  \n    - The product is framed as an **all-in-one skill and resource management solution** designed to unify sales and delivery workflows globally  \n    - Unlike traditional PSA tools, Desi Dalo offers **AI-native features** and a planned AI agent to automate resource manager tasks (32:02)  \n    - The team discussed using “workforce management” as the primary descriptor to differentiate from PSA tools and clarify market positioning (32:23)  \n    - Large enterprise clients like **Fujitsu and T Systems** value the platform’s global staffing workflows and skill-based resource allocation (32:47)  \n\n- Colin agreed to incorporate this broader positioning into rewritten video scripts and marketing materials once access to files is resolved (34:05)  \n    - The planned messaging will focus on **end-to-end process coverage, AI innovation, and global resource management strength**  \n    - Long-term vision includes replacing manual resource management with AI agents for firms with **250+ employees** (33:34)  \n    - The positioning work remains iterative, with options for taglines and use cases being brainstormed for future campaigns\n\n## **Technical and Operational Coordination**\n\nFile sharing, platform access, and communication tools are being troubleshooted to ensure smooth collaboration and content development (21:11).\n\n- Colin experienced access issues with the **New North SharePoint and Teams folders**, preventing retrieval of positioning and slide documents (21:24)  \n    - Axel moved files to more accessible folders and will continue troubleshooting login and permission conflicts (22:25)  \n    - The team suspects multiple email accounts and guest access configurations are causing inconsistencies (26:18)  \n    - Colin will work with internal IT to resolve these issues to avoid delays in script and content updates (26:59)  \n\n- The new recording platform **Riverside** was set up to facilitate remote podcast interviews with David and Eli (12:59)  \n    - Riverside mimics Zoom’s user experience, simplifying adoption for hosts and guests (13:03)  \n    - This technical setup supports the strategic push toward a professional, scalable video podcast series\n\n- Colin is managing creative rotation for LinkedIn ads every two to three weeks and updating email and message copy to push registrations for the free tool trial (37:27)  \n    - This continuous improvement process aligns with the goal of increasing lead volume and quality through multiple channels  \n    - Close monitoring of outreach metrics will guide ongoing adjustments and optimization efforts","outline":null,"keywords":["workforce management","LinkedIn ads","video script","AI agent","email outreach","global resource management"],"overview":"- **Video Content Refinement:** Focus on storytelling to highlight client pain points and product benefits in video scripts.  \n- **Script Development:** New scripts will incorporate resource management features and be clearer while maintaining engaging narratives.  \n- **Ad Campaign Performance:** LinkedIn ads achieved a 0.44% CTR; retargeting campaign aims to build brand awareness initially.  \n- **Outreach Metrics:** 284 LinkedIn connection requests sent; acceptance rate at 16.5% with eight replies from 46 messages.  \n- **Product Positioning Strategy:** Emphasizing skills, projects, and utilization as key pillars for clients with 500-3,000 employees.  \n- **Technical Coordination:** Access issues being resolved for SharePoint and Teams to prevent delays in content updates.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide Riverside platform login and training video for recording interviews with David and Eli (12:59)\nSend full package of animated and static video assets for review (13:00)\nDevelop and rotate new LinkedIn ad creatives, removing low-performing ones and promoting high-engagement messaging (15:00)\nCreate and test ads emphasizing ''register now'' or ''try for free'' offers (15:40)\nShare product video YouTube link for LinkedIn outreach; coordinate with Eli to send to prospects with open conversations (20:16)\nIncrease email outreach volume and test messaging incorporating free tool registration as a lower-barrier offer (20:12)\nTroubleshoot Teams/SharePoint access issues or request alternate document sharing from Axel (21:30)\nRewrite video script incorporating expanded positioning and overview from provided brochures and slides; submit for review (34:40)\nDraft episode framework for interview between David and Eli focused on global resource management challenges (34:45)\nProvide metrics for AdRoll retargeting campaign performance in next update (35:40)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nCoordinate sharing of positioning documents and slide decks with Colin; consider relocating files to ensure access (21:50)\nShare YouTube link of product video for LinkedIn outreach use (20:00)\nVerify member access and troubleshoot Teams/SharePoint issues, confirm email sender details and file visibility (24:30)\nProvide brochures and positioning documents to Colin for script rewriting (27:00)\n\n**Eli Bebinger**\nSend product video link to LinkedIn prospects who have replied or shown interest (20:16)\nContinue LinkedIn outreach messaging and monitor engagement metrics (16:00)\n"},"duration":38.06999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi.","index":0,"end_time":309.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":311.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good, good.","index":2,"end_time":313.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Happy Friday.","index":3,"end_time":315.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any exciting plans for the weekend?","index":4,"end_time":322.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not really.","index":5,"end_time":325.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Those are the most exciting plans.","index":6,"end_time":327.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do you have going on, Colin?","index":7,"end_time":331.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":329.73,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"We actually have like a break this weekend to just catch up on stuff around the house.","index":8,"end_time":336.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we had something every weekend last month and starting next weekend, we''re back to that type of schedule.","index":9,"end_time":344.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about you, Eli?","index":10,"end_time":352.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nothing really.","index":11,"end_time":356.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.58,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Probably go to the beach tomorrow and chilling.","index":12,"end_time":360.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":356.62,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Not sure.","index":13,"end_time":366.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":365.87,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, also some organizing, some cleaning, maybe a little painting.","index":14,"end_time":371.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.87,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"There you go.","index":15,"end_time":373.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":374.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.87,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Is your team joining?","index":17,"end_time":377.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know, I haven''t heard.","index":18,"end_time":382.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think we can just start.","index":19,"end_time":383.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hey, fireflies.","index":20,"end_time":384.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":383.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Just close.","index":21,"end_time":387.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":22,"end_time":395.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":23,"end_time":398.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to go through updates.","index":24,"end_time":400.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can ask me to summarize, create actionable tasks, bookmark important moments.","index":25,"end_time":406.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Eli triggered the fireflies.","index":26,"end_time":408.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So go through.","index":27,"end_time":411.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We developed the animations for the intro, but I know you had some feedback on the script, so I wanted you to see like how it came together.","index":28,"end_time":417.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if we do want to shorten the script, we can produce that no problem.","index":29,"end_time":420.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Go through LinkedIn ads, some outreach metrics, and then a bulk of our time spent on the video script feedback.","index":30,"end_time":427.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the video package, we have the animated video.","index":31,"end_time":434.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here.","index":32,"end_time":434.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me make sure that my sound is passing through for when I share.","index":33,"end_time":438.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Welcome to the Utilization Effect, the video series for resource managers and operations leaders at IT services and consulting firms, firms.","index":34,"end_time":468.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":461.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you''re dealing with poor skills, data, outdated consultant profiles, or friction between sales and delivery, or you''re simply curious how AI will transform skills and resource management, this series is for you.","index":35,"end_time":480.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":468.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Each episode explores how modern resource management, automation and data driven insight can help your team win faster, staff smarter and scale profitably.","index":36,"end_time":490.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":480.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s dive in.","index":37,"end_time":491.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":490.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":495.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''ve only heard the text without the video so far.","index":39,"end_time":499.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"With the video it''s a bit easier to understand and you''re not that much focused on the text.","index":40,"end_time":506.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you just hear the text without the video, it sounds pretty much like one long sentence without any period in it or any comma.","index":41,"end_time":519.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":42,"end_time":521.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And pre request, we had AI build that.","index":43,"end_time":523.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so like we had ellipses and all sorts of like EM dashes to do breaks, but then we sped it up so that it wasn''t a super long script as well.","index":44,"end_time":531.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it does play a lot better with the video actually being seen.","index":45,"end_time":535.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess with the video it''s probably okay.","index":46,"end_time":537.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Without the video it''s.","index":47,"end_time":538.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s really a bit hard to follow.","index":48,"end_time":541.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":542.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also, we have just like a logo intro with no voiceover that''s just like a nice clean so this is another option that we can just utilize as well.","index":50,"end_time":552.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the very short one.","index":51,"end_time":558.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know.","index":52,"end_time":559.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we typically use these for like the shorter, like 45 to one minute videos that we''ll produce.","index":53,"end_time":567.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that''s another option.","index":54,"end_time":569.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also have the outro here.","index":55,"end_time":570.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks for watching the utilization effect.","index":56,"end_time":576.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":573.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If manual resume prep you''d utilization gaps or slow proposal response times are holding your firm back.","index":57,"end_time":582.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":576.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Visit desidollo.com to explore how modern resource management and automation can help your team work smarter and scale faster.","index":58,"end_time":590.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":582.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess it was okay.","index":59,"end_time":595.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, it''s much better with.","index":60,"end_time":597.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"With the video for sure.","index":61,"end_time":599.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":62,"end_time":599.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was thinking we could kind of two put like a little bit of a theme to the episodes.","index":63,"end_time":604.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":600.61,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t know if I proposed that already, but like, if individual firms could have like one main pain point that we''re talking about.","index":64,"end_time":613.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.69,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":65,"end_time":616.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, that would typically be how we would like structure an episode.","index":66,"end_time":620.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would, you know, reach out to a guest and say, this is what we want to talk about.","index":67,"end_time":624.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":620.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our clients do that to a varying degree.","index":68,"end_time":627.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes it''s a less formal conversation.","index":69,"end_time":629.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":627.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes we almost write an entire script with like bullet point suggestions for what the guests can say.","index":70,"end_time":635.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s like a varying degree that we can choose how we want to utilize that.","index":71,"end_time":640.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":636.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I guess they don''t want all of their pain points necessarily being like public information.","index":72,"end_time":648.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640.26,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s better to tell like a journey, especially if they are current customers of, you know, what they were dealing with before, why they reached out to Desi Dalo and their experience after.","index":73,"end_time":658.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":74,"end_time":659.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.99,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I talked to David.","index":75,"end_time":660.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So he''s going to do that.","index":76,"end_time":662.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He just actually wanted to join today, but he had a conflicting meeting.","index":77,"end_time":665.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So the question is, who is the other person?","index":78,"end_time":669.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So David is the one we interview, I guess.","index":79,"end_time":672.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":673.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":672.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He could also be a good host, honestly.","index":81,"end_time":675.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":676.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And shows can have rotating hosts or it can be dedicated to one person.","index":83,"end_time":683.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know originally we had talked about Eli running these as well, and then we''d also talked about David running them.","index":84,"end_time":687.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":683.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be a conversation between David and Eli and David could still be positioned as the host, even though he would be having a lot of the conversation as well.","index":85,"end_time":699.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, David is the one.","index":86,"end_time":703.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":87,"end_time":704.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":88,"end_time":704.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For Eli, it''s probably a bit challenging because David has so much experience and you somehow need to, I guess, ask the right questions.","index":89,"end_time":713.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then we can do it to prep in a script though.","index":90,"end_time":718.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.58,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, we can try it maybe.","index":91,"end_time":722.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":92,"end_time":723.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":93,"end_time":727.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you would want to follow that structure of like when David was With Fujitsu.","index":94,"end_time":732.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":95,"end_time":732.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When he was with Fujitsu, like why he needed a solution, like Desi Dollo, how he discovered you, his experience afterwards.","index":96,"end_time":740.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, something like that.","index":97,"end_time":742.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The global rollout, basically.","index":98,"end_time":744.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think the challenges of global resource management.","index":99,"end_time":746.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think at one point early on we said around global resource management, the podcast, which can still be.","index":100,"end_time":754.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because I think that''s where we''re kind of strong and David is especially very experienced in challenges of global resource management.","index":101,"end_time":762.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.339,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be great.","index":102,"end_time":765.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":764.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I can put together a framework for that and share that with you.","index":103,"end_time":768.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":104,"end_time":769.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So yeah, maybe we should probably have a separate call with him or do you want to send over some like platform where we do the recording?","index":105,"end_time":779.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''re setting up Riverside today.","index":106,"end_time":781.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":107,"end_time":782.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":782.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that works like a zoom, essentially.","index":108,"end_time":785.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll give you a login and I''ll send you a video of how things are set up.","index":109,"end_time":789.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s pretty much just like hopping on a zoom call.","index":110,"end_time":794.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":111,"end_time":797.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so we have all these animated.","index":112,"end_time":799.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also have static versions of most of these as well, like the quote cards and lower thirds and things like that.","index":113,"end_time":805.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send over the full package for you to review.","index":114,"end_time":808.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But sounds like we''re good on the intro for LinkedIn ads.","index":115,"end_time":815.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve updated targeting based on that low quality lead that came in yesterday.","index":116,"end_time":818.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":815.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":820.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And regarding a question about seeing the lead gen form fill, I can''t remember the name of the person on your team that set up your business manager, but it would be more effective if basically we would either have to invite you to our business manager and just limit yourself to only view your account or the person on your team that set up your business manager can just give you access.","index":118,"end_time":841.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean it''s not.","index":119,"end_time":843.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":842.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If it''s just one lead every month is not a problem, I guess.","index":120,"end_time":847.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But yeah, well, we''re, we''re definitely hoping or looking to ramp that up.","index":121,"end_time":851.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the performance is not good or it''s actually pretty bad, I would say.","index":122,"end_time":855.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we''re, we''re about three weeks into running these ads, so we''re launching and developing new creative and copy to rotate in.","index":123,"end_time":867.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":857.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, is that above industry standard, the click?","index":124,"end_time":871.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, 0.44 is the average click through rate for industry standard.","index":125,"end_time":874.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":871.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For LinkedIn especially.","index":126,"end_time":876.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":127,"end_time":877.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":876.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that is LinkedIn.","index":128,"end_time":878.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Whoa.","index":129,"end_time":879.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That is.","index":130,"end_time":880.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":131,"end_time":881.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":880.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s a lot of money per click then.","index":132,"end_time":884.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":133,"end_time":886.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s a competitive and expensive space in LinkedIn IT services and consulting.","index":134,"end_time":891.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":135,"end_time":893.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":892.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But yeah, we''re developing new ad creative to rotate in, as I told you guys, every two to three Weeks.","index":136,"end_time":899.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like to rotate and select a new champion and a new test.","index":137,"end_time":902.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":899.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So far the one that''s been receiving the most engagement is stop losing proposals to resume bottlenecks, get profiles free.","index":138,"end_time":910.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to keep that one in the rotation and then just introduce getting rid of the one with the lowest click through rate.","index":139,"end_time":917.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So at some point we may need to reconsider like the whole package that we''re offering.","index":140,"end_time":923.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.329,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe it''s not compelling.","index":141,"end_time":925.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe we find something better.","index":142,"end_time":926.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":143,"end_time":928.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I thought maybe we should just try some with the like register now.","index":144,"end_time":936.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Try it for free or something.","index":145,"end_time":937.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, especially since the, you know, the early lead that we got from AMSUR went to the landing page and then clicked on the registration button to start that free account.","index":146,"end_time":946.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that is something I''ve been considering as well.","index":147,"end_time":949.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe that is actually working better.","index":148,"end_time":953.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can.","index":149,"end_time":953.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":150,"end_time":955.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe you can create some ads for that.","index":151,"end_time":957.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"See, like try it free now.","index":152,"end_time":958.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":957.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":153,"end_time":960.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":154,"end_time":962.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Diving into some outreach metrics.","index":155,"end_time":964.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we went over these in our meeting two days ago.","index":156,"end_time":967.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So far on LinkedIn, we''ve sent out 284 connection requests, 47 of which have been accepted.","index":157,"end_time":973.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Eli, you''re Okina to 16 and a half percent accepted rate there, which is strong.","index":158,"end_time":977.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve sent 46 messages and have received eight replies.","index":159,"end_time":981.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":978.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Eli, we added the video to LinkedIn.","index":160,"end_time":985.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":983.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think on video you can add product.","index":161,"end_time":986.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"On LinkedIn you can add product videos under this dollar product, but I think it''s actually hosted on YouTube.","index":162,"end_time":993.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure how it.","index":163,"end_time":994.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"When you.","index":164,"end_time":995.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you can send a link to the, to the LinkedIn video or which is a YouTube link, but I would probably send that to the people that have replied that where we still have kind of open discussion or that were somewhere interested or.","index":165,"end_time":1013.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Did you already do that?","index":166,"end_time":1014.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Send the video to people?","index":167,"end_time":1017.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.67,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I would do that.","index":168,"end_time":1019.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1017.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean if they.","index":169,"end_time":1020.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1019.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What nothing bad can happen.","index":170,"end_time":1022.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They haven''t replied back anyway, so.","index":171,"end_time":1024.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can''t get worse, I would say.","index":172,"end_time":1027.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1025.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yep.","index":173,"end_time":1029.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1029.19,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And you could check if you can you.","index":174,"end_time":1031.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1029.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think if you go to our LinkedIn page, company page, there''s a product.","index":175,"end_time":1035.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1031.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Let me just see if that is the LinkedIn link.","index":176,"end_time":1042.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1036.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":1044.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is your view on that, Colin?","index":178,"end_time":1047.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1045.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Should we just.","index":179,"end_time":1047.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1047.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, if we shared the video, it''s not really a marketing video, but I think it''s somehow better than.","index":180,"end_time":1052.069,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1047.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I think sharing the videos is great.","index":181,"end_time":1054.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1052.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially while we''re working on the script for the new video.","index":182,"end_time":1059.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":183,"end_time":1060.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":184,"end_time":1062.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1062.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":185,"end_time":1063.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1062.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Then let''s do that.","index":186,"end_time":1065.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1064.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Let''s check the.","index":187,"end_time":1066.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is LinkedIn the YouTube link products?","index":188,"end_time":1069.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1066.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s see if you go to products, there''s the video.","index":189,"end_time":1072.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":190,"end_time":1075.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not seeing.","index":191,"end_time":1078.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not clickable.","index":192,"end_time":1080,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You have to scroll down.","index":193,"end_time":1080.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1080,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s interesting.","index":194,"end_time":1081.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1080.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It looks different.","index":195,"end_time":1081.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1081.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völk