  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Video Content and Script Development**

The team agreed on refining the video series script to better highlight client pain points and showcase the product’s benefits through storytelling (08:15).

- **Colin Costigan** confirmed the animation improves script clarity by breaking up long sentences, which otherwise sound like one continuous statement without pauses (08:15)  
    - The video format makes the message easier to follow than audio-only versions  
    - The team will consider adding shorter intro/outro options for different video lengths  
    - Eli Bebinger suggested structuring episodes around a single main pain point per firm to create focused narratives  
    - This approach supports client confidentiality by framing stories as journeys rather than comprehensive pain disclosures

- **David** is confirmed as the primary interviewee and potential host, leveraging his deep experience in global resource management (11:12)  
    - Axel Völker highlighted David’s expertise as a strong asset for hosting and interviewing  
    - Colin will provide a framework for an episode featuring David and Eli to ensure targeted questions and flow (12:44)  
    - The first episode concept centers on global rollout challenges in resource management, aligned with Desi Dalo’s strengths  
    - Recording setup will use Riverside platform, simplifying remote interviews and enabling easy content capture

- The team plans to rewrite the video script using materials from the product overview PDF and positioning documents to create a broader, clearer story of Desi Dalo’s value (34:05)  
    - Colin will incorporate more resource management aspects and AI agent features into the new scripts (27:07)  
    - The revised scripts aim to balance detailed product info with engaging storytelling for marketing effectiveness  
    - Delivery of updated scripts and episode frameworks is expected soon after resolving access issues to shared files

## **Advertising and Lead Generation Performance**

Current ad campaigns on LinkedIn and retargeting platforms are under review with plans for creative refresh and offer adjustments to improve engagement and lead quality (14:12).

- After **three weeks** of LinkedIn ads, the team recorded a **click-through rate (CTR) of 0.44%**, matching industry standards for IT services but reflecting high costs per click (14:31)  
    - The most engaging ad promotes “stop losing proposals to resume bottlenecks,” which will remain in rotation  
    - Ads with lowest CTR will be replaced every two to three weeks to optimize performance  
    - Axel suggested testing calls to action like “register now” or “try for free” to increase appeal and conversion rates (15:18)  
    - Colin confirmed early leads converted through free trial registration, supporting this approach (15:38)

- The retargeting campaign via **AdRoll** was launched recently and is focused on brand awareness with expected low direct conversions initially (35:16)  
    - Metrics on clicks and engagement will be shared once data matures  
    - This complements LinkedIn efforts by broadening audience touchpoints

- Email outreach has sent **822 emails** with about **290 opens**, but limited engagement so far (20:16)  
    - Volume was recently increased to accelerate outreach  
    - Colin noted email acts more as a supportive channel compared to LinkedIn’s higher conversion focus (36:11)  
    - Eli questioned whether the email sender’s identity influences response rates; Colin clarified names and addresses used include Eli’s to personalize messages (36:35)  
    - The team agreed to test messaging emphasizing free tool registration to lower barriers and attract more responses (21:11)

## **Outreach and Engagement Strategy**

The team is actively refining outreach tactics to improve connection acceptance and follow-up quality, integrating video sharing and personalized messaging (16:03).

- On LinkedIn, **284 connection requests** were sent with a **16.5% acceptance rate**, yielding **eight replies from 46 messages** sent (16:03)  
    - Eli is managing messaging and will start sharing the product video link via YouTube to nurture interest (20:13)  
    - Axel recommended sharing video content with recipients who have shown some interest to deepen engagement (16:23)  
    - LinkedIn’s product video hosting lacks direct shareable links, so YouTube is preferred for distribution (18:48)  
    - Colin supported video sharing as a complement while the new scripted video is still in progress (17:32)

- The team discussed improving LinkedIn company page product video accessibility to aid prospect viewing and sharing (18:21)  
    - Technical limitations prevent clickable video links directly on LinkedIn product tabs, requiring workarounds  
    - Using familiar platforms like YouTube reduces friction for recipients clicking on demos

## **Product Positioning and Messaging Strategy**

The group is aligning on a broader, clearer product story to better communicate Desi Dalo’s unique value in workforce and resource management (27:33).

- Axel shared updated positioning materials emphasizing three pillars: **skills, projects, and utilization** for IT consulting firms sized **500 to 3,000 employees** (29:00)  
    - The product is framed as an **all-in-one skill and resource management solution** designed to unify sales and delivery workflows globally  
    - Unlike traditional PSA tools, Desi Dalo offers **AI-native features** and a planned AI agent to automate resource manager tasks (32:02)  
    - The team discussed using “workforce management” as the primary descriptor to differentiate from PSA tools and clarify market positioning (32:23)  
    - Large enterprise clients like **Fujitsu and T Systems** value the platform’s global staffing workflows and skill-based resource allocation (32:47)  

- Colin agreed to incorporate this broader positioning into rewritten video scripts and marketing materials once access to files is resolved (34:05)  
    - The planned messaging will focus on **end-to-end process coverage, AI innovation, and global resource management strength**  
    - Long-term vision includes replacing manual resource management with AI agents for firms with **250+ employees** (33:34)  
    - The positioning work remains iterative, with options for taglines and use cases being brainstormed for future campaigns

## **Technical and Operational Coordination**

File sharing, platform access, and communication tools are being troubleshooted to ensure smooth collaboration and content development (21:11).

- Colin experienced access issues with the **New North SharePoint and Teams folders**, preventing retrieval of positioning and slide documents (21:24)  
    - Axel moved files to more accessible folders and will continue troubleshooting login and permission conflicts (22:25)  
    - The team suspects multiple email accounts and guest access configurations are causing inconsistencies (26:18)  
    - Colin will work with internal IT to resolve these issues to avoid delays in script and content updates (26:59)  

- The new recording platform **Riverside** was set up to facilitate remote podcast interviews with David and Eli (12:59)  
    - Riverside mimics Zoom’s user experience, simplifying adoption for hosts and guests (13:03)  
    - This technical setup supports the strategic push toward a professional, scalable video podcast series

- Colin is managing creative rotation for LinkedIn ads every two to three weeks and updating email and message copy to push registrations for the free tool trial (37:27)  
    - This continuous improvement process aligns with the goal of increasing lead volume and quality through multiple channels  
    - Close monitoring of outreach metrics will guide ongoing adjustments and optimization efforts',
